INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu25190',377,'2019-02-20',5,'THE BEST RESTAURANT IN CHICAGO. Period. We love sushi and this is the only place that has ever gotten us to not order it and instead only get the special things on the menu. THATs how good it all is. The brothers have crafted the simplest, most delicious bites that its a waste to order anything else.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',170,'2017-10-15',5,'This is one of those spots that I dont want to hype up because its already hard enough to get a reservation, lol. But for real...its for good reason. Quite easily one of the top 10 restaurants Ive ever eaten at. So great that we went twice in one month.My one and only recommendation is to order the Omakase. Let the chef(s) take full control because I promise you, you wont regret it. My fiancÃ© who has become more of an adventurous eater over the years has zero complaints! That means nothing to you, but hes a total seafood scaredy-cat. The first time we came, I only ordered the Omakase and he ordered off of the menu. By the time the second dish was served, he was regretting his decision. The Omakase menu truly pushes you to try what might normally be outside of your comfort zone. For me, that was the quail egg. The perfect shooter with a mix of savory, citrusy, and spicy. Excuse me if I dont have an exactly refined palette, but thats what stood out to me and made it delicious. I was also very pleasantly surprised that they managed to make the textures not weird. With all the uniqueness offered, its priced VERY fairly - especially for Chicago at $80 & up per person. And when I say every single item is a favorite, I mean it. Im sitting here trying to point out the phenomenal angry crab, or the toro that just melts in your mouth, or even the fiesta maki but its just not fair to single any one item out! Go see for yourself.The second best part thats basically tied with the amazingly incredible food is the service. The staff has truly mastered their craft when it comes to timing of the food - especially when not everyone ordered the Omakase. Dont worry, my fiancÃ© only made that mistake once. Theyre also all very knowledgeable of the menu, and for me, that makes a huge difference. They do so well in their role, they sold us on anchovy ice cream. Yes, anchovies. It was the most unique and flavorful dessert weve all ever had. Its even preferred by the chocolate lovers at the table. Think smores!Long story short, come with an open mind and enjoy the quality and perfectly bite sized options on the Omakase menu. Trust the chef(s)! Theyre the pros for a reason.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',402,'2021-07-28',4,'Made a pretty last minute reservation for this place hoping that it would be good and it was!This place has quality sushi. It really isnt far off from the 150-200 dollar omakase places. The fish is just as fresh and the nigiri is just as good. The only difference may be a few pieces of more expensive seasonal fish at other omakases. But I was very happy with my dinner here and felt that the meal was very worth the price. We left feeling satisfied and full. This is a place I would come back to multiple times.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',1579,'2021-02-21',5,'Came here for the first time since Covid and Kai-Zan did not miss a step. My wife and I got Omakase to keep things simple. We just sat down by the bar area and let the chefs take care of our evening. Food was delicious as expected. I honestly cant remember the names of every dish but our fav is definitely the escolar (came out 3rd). The shooters were a bit too adventurous for me. I appreciated the different dimensions of flavors and texture that the chefs threw at us. By the time the sashimi came out, we were nearing stomach capacity. Portions were definitely enough. The entire dinner was an experience in itself. I highly recommend the Omakase! Really affordable too.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a83185',1034,'2021-07-22',5,'You wont be able to find this level of omakase for a better value anywhere in the city. The omakase menu is comprised of so many courses to fill you up. A handful of the courses even come with multiple items/bites. I was literally so stuffed that I could barely finish the sashimi selection towards the end. I was drawn here mainly because the chefs designed a menu with beautifully creative dishes intermixed with the more traditional nigiri pieces that you find in other omakases. The only thing missing for me was having the experience of watching the chef curate the dishes right in front of you. Getting omakase here doesnt guarantee a front row seat at the sushi bar, but I honestly cant complain because everything else was amazing!',50);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',1727,'2016-03-17',4,'Did the omakase which was great, especially for the affordable price (compared to some of the other omakase options in Chicago)We loved the first few courses - my favorite courses were the first two, the madai carpaccio and the maguro and escolar pearls. The quality of the fish was amazing and there were really unique flavors in each dish. Towards the end I started getting too full (and I can eat a lot, and was very hungry that day!) to really appreciate the last few courses - the last course is sashimi and its not small. Tips- We ordered an extra dish, a toro and uni special that you can make your own hand rolls with and it was really good, but if youre doing the omakase I would recommend not ordering anything extra to avoid the same mistake I made. - Some of the courses can also get pretty spicy with a good amount of wasabi - the fiesta maki especially was very spicy for me- The omakase is also pretty fast paced since its held strictly to the 90-minute limit so dont be late for your reservation!',32);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',415,'2020-02-14',5,'What a magnificent meal all around. I went in with an idea of what I wanted to get based on everything Ive read! We decided to opt out of doing omakase and basically form our own ten course meal from the a la carte menu!We were seated at the sushi bar and kitchen area and got to see them making everything in front of us. Its always exciting to see the action! They have booths on both sides of the restaurant as well depending on what kind of experience you want. We got the oyster shooters, dynamite mussels, polenta bites, flaming tuna maki, orange rush, char siu skewer, spicy toro maki, wagyu nigiri, otoro sashimi and lava cake. Everything was so so good! My favorites were the oyster shooter, the spicy toro maki and the otoro (Im a sucker for a some food fatty tuna). Every single plate was so jam packed with flavor and everything melded so well together. The fish was so fresh and melt in your mouth. The lava cake was the perfect finishing touch. It had a warm moist chocolate cake topped with black sesame ice cream (love love love black sesame ice cream) Overall my expectations were definitely exceeded. Definitely not super affordable sushi, but I would say its more affordable than many *good* sushi places. I would 100% recommend anyone to come here for a special occasion or if youre just looking to treat yourself!',51);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',1007,'2020-07-24',4,'If I ever am craving omakase, I would come here. The experience was very fluid and the ambiance was quite nice. The first couple dishes came out with a bang. Loved the sashimi and the nigiris well made and yummy. I didnt like the raw oyster or scallop shooters tho. If youre craving sushi, come here tho. They make it quite well. I was def all fished out after this meal. I actually came here for my birthday and was sad that they didnt offer anything or ask if we were celebrating anything since its such a nice place. But all in all, I would totally bring people here and come again.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',419,'2019-02-24',5,'Quick and easyWhats good1) Lobster Nigiri (The best thing youll ever taste, even as sushi guru - this is next level and for $10 per piece. Get all of them before they run out!) 2) The service and overall experience - Nice recommendations from the service and overall very accommodating in a nice interior! 3) Spicy tuna 5 pieces were also great!What to skip1) Shooters - too sour and they look and sound better than they actually taste. 2) Waygu need nigiri - too fatty and salty for our taste3) Toros and chu toros - it was good! But for the price weve had better ones4) the specialties with two prices each - skip the truffle ones. The salmon one was good! 5) zuke salmon was kind of disappointing Overall the lobster roll. The ok price for the quality and the service made it to 4 stars in our opinion! Wed come back for the lobster nigiri!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',1183,'2017-11-22',5,'By far, one of the best Japanese restaurants in the city. Reservation isnt easy to get here, you should plan ahead. Parking can be tricky but not any worse than other popular locations. I suggest finding a spot on Chicago ave. Food is to die for and service.. just average. Our waiter was more interested in jacking up the bill than taking care of us. For a restaurant like this, thats just too bad. Omakase is a great option, it includes a lot of their popular items. I suggest you try it at least once. For me, I didnt care for oyster/scallop shooter, tuna dashi, and sashimi. Heres what we absolutely loved and will repeat. Hamachi kama Spicy toro makiNigiri-Wagyu, Sea urchin, sweet shrimp, bbq eelChicken Karaage Charchu Angry crab*Madai carpaccio*Escolar and maguro pearls* Fiesta maki**=omakase item',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',198,'2018-01-31',5,'Fabulous bang for your buck. I left feeling the perfect amount of full. We each ordered a Omakase (there were four of us) that was 75 dollars each. I wish they provided me a copy of the menu with the names because honestly at this point, I am just guessing what the items were exactly.The space is a bit small so make sure you make reservations far in advance. I think we made ours about a month out and there werent many good options for times, so we settled for a 530 pm which is a bit rushed to get to if you work until 5 pm. I did like that our space felt very intimate. It was almost like its own small room for the four of us.My favorites were the nigiri and first dish, which I believe was hamachi. Would love to come back!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',1427,'2020-04-12',4,'TLDR; Flavorful and filling on a decently priced OmakasePrice$75 / person for Omakase. I dont think you will be able to find as affordable of an Omakase than at Kai Zan (but DM me if you know of a good one in Chicago). It doesnt have the traditional rice / soup numbers incorporated, and is all fish. VibeUnassuming location tucked away on the west side. The atmosphere was just right and what I was expecting - not as upscale as other Omakase experiences, but I like that about Kai Zan! We had a semi private seating area in the new extension of the restaurant. Semi secluded, and definitely felt safe dining here. Lets talk food. Highlights-Angry Crab generous amounts of crab and it was perfectly executed -Char Siu reminds me of how my parents like eating this (mmmmm drool). Tender, juicy, and flavorful -Sashimi 7 pieces, and this alone made the Omakase price fair.Meh -dynamite mussel is satiating, but the notes arent as delicate (probably because its a mussel) Fish are sourced from all over the globe, and it to have these flavors in Humboldt park is something else!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',49,'2016-09-23',4,'Outstanding. The chefs menu is an incredible value - SO much food. Â Sushi and sashimi are delicious but I also loved their cooked offerings suck as the pork belly sooo yummy.Beautiful restaurant with nice booths for larger parties. Great service. Do not recommend any of their wine but they have sake and beer I think.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',1245,'2020-12-04',5,'Glad to make it back here after a couple years! Omakase is still an amazing experience and value here. Desserts were also delicious.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum5724',1229,'2018-09-20',3,'9.5/10 - a high value, high variety omakase in a tasteful settingDollar for dollar, Kai Zan is hands down the best sushi that you will find in Chicago. This is compared to Roka Akor, Yuzu, Nobu, etc. The only better spots cost 3x as much as truthfully are nowhere near as flavorful.Their 10-course Omakase is a steal at $75. The staff is incredibly professional and the interior is a cozy date night spot. If you havent been, I highly encourage you try it!My absolute favorite are the Escolar/Maguro Pearls - they are perfect bite size gems with a wonderful char for extra flare.I have been 3 times and the quality is consistently excellent in all forms. I admire when an operation runs this smoothly over a long duration. Seriously impressive.Book well in advance and enjoy this gem.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',963,'2021-10-06',5,'Yummy sushi and cooked courses! I got the 10 course omakase at the sushi bar and it was so cool to see the chefs preparing food in front of us. This dining experience was a while ago so I dont remember everything but my favorite dish was the maguro pearls - they had a delicious smoky/char flavor. The rolls were also really good. I think Kai Zan especially excels with more flavor forward/sauce heavy dishes. The last dish was sashimi and it didnt wow me -- it felt like something I could get for a lot cheaper at any decent sushi restaurant.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin7639',976,'2016-08-19',5,'Where has this place been the whole time Ive been living in Chicago??? Clearly Ive been living under a rock. I got the omakase and it was an amazing deal for what it was - a combo of hot dishes and sashimi, as well as some fun shooters in between. With tea and dessert the bill came out to bed less than $100 which was insane. The service was amazing as well and the staff were so friendly. Will definitely be back!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quisque750',855,'2017-07-05',4,'Consistently the best sushi Ive had in Chicago and the most welcoming environment!! We just finished dinner and had the most memorable meal. We opted to do the a la carte as we tried the omakase last time and this visit was honestly even more amazing. Every single item was melt-in-your-mouth delicious and we had the kindest server, Kong, who made sure to walk us through everything and provide very thoughtful recommendations. I also cant stop thinking about the apple cake which was a great way to end the meal.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',107,'2016-01-07',5,'Top notch and just flat out fantastic! I have been here multiple times and tried just about everything on the menu. You can not go wrong with anything. Every bite is a burst of flavor no matter what you order! Only downside is how quickly the reservations fill up once they open the books, so book quickly!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',1046,'2021-04-30',5,'If price is no object I would say definitely give this place a try. While the food was really well done and fresh, I would say the value was on the spendy side. A lot of things you order are like 1 or two bites and range anywhere from 11-20 dollars. The fish was fresh and the flavors were good for the most part, some highlights were the Angry Crab bites and the Oyster shooters. The atmosphere was super cute and intimate, would be great for a date night but I wouldnt come here with a large group.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quisque750',1045,'2020-03-11',4,'WOW!!! The food here was phenomenal. Pictures do not capture their beauty and any words I put here cannot describe how delicious and fresh all the food was. The wait-staff was so kind, they asked for vaccine cards and the entire vibe was ON POINT. Perfect date night - be it friends or more.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yyy19',730,'2018-07-31',5,'Kai Zan- where have you been in my life? I tried Omakase $75 per person and also ordered Scallops skewer. We wanted to order Uni but it wasnt available on the day we dined. My Omakase meal was 10 courses and it was a-m-a-z-i-n-g. Now I see what the hype is about. It was a nice variety between sashimi, maki rolls, cold & hot dish. Surprisingly, these courses were fulfilling-- and I was full. My favorite was the Pearl rolls. I almost ordered another round, but thought Id save for my next return.',33);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1092,'2019-10-10',5,'Wonderful food at KaiZan! We ordered omakae and it was such a delightful experience! We liked everything and we were very satisfied and full at the end. Strongly recommend Madai Carparccio, Â Escolar & Maguro Pearls, Angry Crab, and Shooters.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',403,'2018-09-21',4,'The omakase is such a great deal with fantastic food quality. Food is slightly of fusion type but overall great for people craves for Omakase. The matcha crÃ¨me brÃ»lÃ©e is so good! The yuzu cheesecake is just ok.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',1505,'2021-07-27',5,'LITERALLY the best place EVER! The food was uhmazing! The atmosphere=Gorge! Our server, Danielle, was so knowledgeable and every single thing he recommended was better than he could even describe! Cant wait to go back!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo40189',92,'2019-08-28',5,'Best Japanese restaurant for the quality, value, and taste! Great sake selection as well.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',351,'2018-08-27',4,'My partner and I traveled to Chicago for the first time and I asked one of my local friends where he thought we needed to try. His first suggestion was this place and after going myself I understand why!I loved the atmosphere, it was so cozy and mellow. The way the seating is set up you have a sense of a little privacy. Also the service we received was amazing. I wish I could remember the name of our waiter, because he was great. He was so knowledgeable about the food and drink, knowing what paired well and where everything was sourced from. As for the food, please try the spicy toro maki! I will literally fly to Chicago again to be able to experience that sushi roll one more time. Every time I ate I piece I told my partner I was in heaven. All the flavors of the roll work so perfectly together, nothing was too overwhelming, just perfect.We also got a couple of nigiri pieces that were very tasty, the char siu skewer which was amazing, and the chocolate cake with sesame ice cream for dessert.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',200,'2019-03-18',5,'Never disappoints. The freshest sushi in chicago! Every single menu item is so perfectly curated and Ive never had anything below phenomenal. My personal favorite is to order the chef Omakase because you get to try all the most popular menu items.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla56102',1291,'2017-06-10',5,'Cool spot and decent food! For the same price range I had slightly better in NYC but this was still a very good place! Location A little bit out of the way since we were staying around magnificent mile and the drive was a bit but we thought this was a super cute spot! Tips Would recommend from their big menu than the sushi small menu since the items from the big menu was a lot more impressive. (Apps, skewers, special creations by chef) Must try  grilled scallop nigiri (wow!)Appetizer peral sushi (I forgot the name, see pic) Skewer ribSmoked fish special Angry crabYuzu cheese cake was nice too Just so so Ikaru (salmon roe) Botan ebi (sweet shrimp) -both could be a little more fresh. green monster roll (a little bit too loosely wrapped so it was falling apart) Shoutout to our sweet angel server Annabelle for food recommendations and lovely chat. Would be back if I visit Chicago again.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',503,'2016-04-21',4,'Amazing omakase experience. The brother chef duo really know what theyre doing. 10/10 would recommend.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',340,'2017-12-17',5,'My favorite sushi spot in Chicago! Great service and fantastic quality of fish. Some of the best nigiri bites and specialty dishes Ive had anywhere.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',45,'2019-12-14',5,'Easily the best sushi spot in Chicago!! They have the freshest fish in the city (some might argue thats not saying much, but they effortlessly rival coastal sushi restaurants!) and their unique presentation and flavor combinations will leave you in a state of nirvana. The sexy interior decor also sets the ideal backdrop for an intimate date or celebration.If its your first visit, definitely order the Omakase (chefs choice)-- the best bang for your buck and allows you to try various items. If youre looking at single plates, try the Tako Yaki & Madai Carpaccio--you wont be disappointed.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',191,'2019-01-23',2,'Not saying anything monumental here but Kai Zan is the best and freshest sushi in Chicago!! The service in here is impeccable, they have made amazing accommodations in compliance with COVID-19 safety. Not to mention the fact that the sushi is a great price for the quality-- Love picking up a platter deal to go!! So lucky to have such a great establishment in the neighborhood.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',390,'2019-08-29',4,'Perfect restaurant for a special day such as an anniversary or birthday. We ordered the chefs omakase and it was exquisite. I highly recommend the seasonal omakase as all the ingredients are fresh, delicious, and not too oily. The staff was friendly and took care of any dietary restrictions by allowing us to substitute pork belly for salmon. Highly recommend this place. The only downside is that they do not serve cocktails, only wine and sake. But that is mostly a personal preference.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',591,'2021-02-21',5,'We love to dine here whenever we visit our daughter in Chicago. Â  Its been a couple of years since we came here for dinner and we were excited to revisit recently. Â  We had a omakase and its menu has not changed much other than uni shooters werent available. Â However the scallop and oyster shooters were delicious. Â  In addition we had shishito peppers and strawberry mochi ice cream for dessert. Â The taste and freshness of foods were consistently great.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',1123,'2019-11-01',4,'This is the best sushi restaurant in Chicago. Â The flavor and presentation are both remarkable. Â Be sure to ask about off menu items as they are some of the best.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',1251,'2017-02-25',5,'This is probably my new favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago with Mirai and Dokku being my other favorites. The omakase is an excellent value (I left full) and delicious. Cozy ambiance.Favorites -PearlsAngry crabTako YakiMusselsPolenta bites (ridiculously good)Orange rushChar siu',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',182,'2020-10-25',2,'Quality, service and price, --- everything checks out at KAI ZAN. We ordered the Omakase and we received a great dining experience. We also added a few desserts and would not wanted to have missed those. Our service team was attentive, knowledgable and friendly. Every dish is prepared with amazing care for tase and optical appeal.Hard to resist making those Instagram pictures with every course of the meal.We paid a fair price and made already plans for the next visit. We drove 60 miles one way to eat at KAI ZAN and we will happily make the Trip again.Highly recommended for Sushi fans equally as for diners who want to experience Sushi the first time.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',1674,'2018-09-19',5,'Went on a date here and did the omakase menu (10 courses). It was delicious and I couldnt believe how much food they gave us! We both left stuffed.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',1729,'2020-11-26',4,'Just AMAZING!!! I am a picky eater but the whole experience was just perfect. Omakase was designed and delivered so so well. For high-end Japanese cuisine its also really large portions of food and with great value. Cant wait to come back.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tristique8035',1377,'2020-08-07',5,'Wow, was this good. Â Easily one of the best dining of experiences I have had, and THAT is saying a lot. Â This dinner vaulted into my all time Top Ten. Â My wife and I were in town with our daughter, who was running in the Chicago Marathon. Â Along with her boyfriend and two others, we had six people in the private booth. Â I ordered two bottles of Prosecco, which I learned years ago is the perfect counter point to sushi (go figure), then we proceeded to order round after round of recommended 6 pieces plates. Â A few merited the encore round, as in, hey Brian (our great waiter), bring another platter of whatever that was. Â Folks dont ask me to recommend anything, because its all a wonderful blur. Â Too bad, I dont live here, cause Id be back over and over and over again.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',20,'2018-08-29',5,'One of my favorite restaurants ever. A KA-POW of flavors in every single bite. If youre a foodie, skip Alinea and go here instead. Almost never a thing with sushi, but youll actually leave with a full belly when you order the omakase. The price point is beyond fair for what you get. Â Sitting at the bar is fun too. You get to watch the brothers in action making food art. A true delight.Oooof, so good!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',428,'2020-01-27',5,'I wish I can put zero stars. We made a reservation weeks in advance for friends from out of town and when we came to the restaurant they told us they cancelled our reservation. They wouldnt even admit it was their fault. We paid $60 Uber each way and we were left with no options for dinner on a Friday night.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in63197',335,'2020-12-23',4,'Kai Zan is wildly popular in Chicago and known for their Omakase. I first tried in 2012 when they first opened. I couldnt remember if I enjoyed so decided to try again. Ill start with the positives. The fish and other ingredients were very fresh. The restaurant is small, but service was a team effort. Everyone worked well together to ensure we were well taken care of.The less than positive. .. while each dish was made with fresh ingredients, I didnt find myself wanting more. Nothing was particularly flavorful. Again another dining experience were it wasnt bad enough to send dishes back or complain, but not good enough to seek out another visit. Clearly Im in the minority with my view. Ill try again if I happen to be in the area with sushi on my mind.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',103,'2021-02-07',4,'Best quality sushi Ive ever had. Great flavors and amazing nigiri. Can get over kaizan. Perfect there',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu1673',402,'2016-01-22',5,'Had the Omakase. Overall really solid, with some weaknessesScallops/Oyster Shooter - the ponzu sauce is overpowering, masks the subtle scallops/oyster too muchFiesta maki - similary the jalapeno is too overwhelming and blows out your palateEverything else was well-done. Favorites are the torched fish. At $75 you get a lot of high-quality food and will leave very full.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',428,'2021-05-24',3,'One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago! Ive been going there for years and just realized that I never reviewed them. Â The reservations arent as easy to get as they used to be but the food is definitely worth the wait. The omakase is a good value and a good way to sample the menu but once youve done it, its probably better to go a la carte and get what you want. MY favorites are grilled hamachi nirigi, maguro pearls, and anything with toro.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',1205,'2019-07-18',5,'Atmosphere! Food! Service! Cannot say enough about my Kai Zahn experience. Loved the food, everything was extremely fresh and tasty! You wont be disappointed!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',939,'2020-12-31',5,'No doubt this is a 5 star restaurant. I had no qualms bringing a friend for a special birthday celebration after seeing raves upon raves of Kai Zan, and several people telling me this was their favorite restaurant in Chicago. The title is well-deserved!We got the chefs choice omakase and the quality and execution of each course was top notch. Granted you arent paying hundreds of dollars for the meal so nothing was over-the-top decadent, but each dish used the freshest seafood. My favorite course was the seared orange rush (salmon-wrapped scallop), and my friends was the angry crab (tuna-wrapped crab) and the pork belly. Like many have mentioned, you will definitely leave feeling very full, but not full enough to leave out dessert! We tried the mango mochi ice cream thats made in-house, and it was definitely worth it.Service was so smooth and our dishes came out one after another with minimal wait. There were people waiting for our seats after our meal so it did feel a bit rushed at the end, but that really didnt detract from the meal. I really enjoyed sitting at the bar and watching the chefs make the food, but theres a variety of very cool and intimate booth seating here too.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',1085,'2017-04-25',4,'I was apprehensive to write a review prior to my 2nd visit based solely off of the fact that I believe takeout sushi is an oxymoron. However, this is the best damn sushi Ive ever had & its the flavors & quality are consistently good. Each visit I ordered the Kai zan bites set & the pearls set which are both amazing & warrant me ordering each item every time I visit. My first visit I got the wagyu rice which honestly I wasnt a fan of. It didnt have the extremely rich wagyu flavor Ive come to love. Thats however the only negative thing I have to say about this place. On my 2nd visit o ordered the flaming crab & angry crab maki set & this is truly solidified my opinion of best sushi in Chicago. Â Twas amazingly good. They have earned me as a loyal & although its expensive especially considering its take out, Ill be a repeat customer.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',1286,'2021-07-12',5,'Wow... I think I found my top sushi place in Chicago and top 3 around the US. My boyfriend took me here for my birthday dinner and our experience was phenomenal. Service was top notch - all the staff were so knowledgeable, attentive, and friendly. Its so hard to come across this type of amazing service in Chicago. The place is small, cozy, and intimate. We got seated at a booth, which was so perfect for our dinner date. We opted for the chef omakase, which is $70 for 10 courses I believe. You definitely will leave full. The dishes came out at a perfect pace. For each course, someone would come over and explain what the dish was along with the flavors in it. I drool every time I think of how amazing each course was, it was that good. Our favorite was the Madai carpaccio - freshest red snapper and olive oil gave it so much flavor and the toro (fatty tuna belly) just MELTS in your mouth! The escolar and maguro pearls was our absolute favorite - perfectly seared and that truffle is to die for. I cant even begin to explain how delicious all the flavors were. I will be coming back to try the premium omakase along with the uni. Make reservations a few weeks out. Credit card is required if its for more than a party of 2.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',1521,'2018-12-02',5,'Took my partner here for his Birthday. I made a reservation ahead of time. The food was prompt and came out very quickly. The staff was very attentive and kind. They did well at explaining the different options and the plates. The food was to die for. Ive never had omakase before and I will be having more in the future. The atmosphere was very small and intimate. This place made my partners day extra special.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',1720,'2017-11-25',4,'My favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago. The Omakase menu is one of the best deals in the city',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',170,'2019-12-23',5,'Open for carry-out during the pandemic! I was excited to see that they were offering some of the favorites from their omakase menu. I had the Kai Zan bites set. The maki rolls were actually my favorite. Fyi, the specialty sushi pieces were much smaller than usual. The food was good, regardless, and Im happy to support local businesses!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',265,'2020-04-30',5,'We made a reservation 1 month in advance cuz this place is extremely popular. As soon as we arrived, we were seated right away. The service here was up to par and our server was def prepared to answer our questions.We ordered their omakase (chefs choice which is $69 for 10 courses) and added $15 for two people to share. Since neither of us are big eaters, I would say this is more than enough for us to share. All courses are fusion style small dishes. Up untill tuna dashi, everything was delicious with their twists. The rest of dishes were the ones you can get at typical sushi restaurants in the Midwest. Our least favorite was the Main which were underwhelming. Overall, nice experience.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',299,'2016-03-30',4,'Completely amazing experience. I rather enjoyed sitting at the sushi bar and watching the magicians at work as they were preparing each dish.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',1627,'2016-06-04',5,'The omakase is great value and offers you a healthy variety of dishes to enjoy. Ive come here several times and have always left satisfied without breaking the bank. For a special occasion meal they prepared a surprise dessert for me which was delicious, Ive never had starfruit before!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',1491,'2017-05-17',5,'Come for the food, stay for the ambiance, and bring a friend. They will thank you for it.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',1725,'2019-03-21',5,'My first time trying out an omakaze! My mom told me she needed to make a reservation ahead of time and that making changes to the reservation cost money. So if you plan on eating here, plan properly and accordingly!The omakaze is charged per person and is 7 courses total. I am not am expert on omakazes so the roughly $60 per person for the omakaze may or may not break your bank (poor college student speaking here, I wouldnt have imagined coming here if it werent for my parents tbh lol).There were two menus to choose from for the omakaze. One allowed the sushi chefs to utilize their creativity to make a unique menu for you at a higher charge. The other is a pre-set menu that costs less.Each course of the omakaze were delicious, small bites of sushi or sashimi. The most interesting was the raw quail egg shot; not a huge fan but not terrible. The best was the fatty tuna nigiri in my opinion. The last course is a plate of sashimi for each person, and plates of rolls. Each party gets different rolls based on how many people are in your party. I thought that I wouldnt be full bt the meal but by the end I could barely finish and my stomach was so full.This was overall an enjoyable experience and would recommend (to those who could afford it).',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1056,'2017-07-27',5,'One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago! Kai Zan showcases a lot of tasty Japanese fusion-y morsels. Some of our favorites are the Escolar Pearls, Angry Crab, and the decadent Wagyu Fried Rice. The omakase (chefs choice, tasting menu) is a fantastic choice, as theres a lot of food at a price that doesnt break the bank. During COVID times, Kai Zan has not offered dine-in, but the pick up options (through Clover) has been great and the food travels well.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',240,'2018-10-22',4,'Its as other reviewers say. Youre getting a great omakase deal at 10 courses for $69. And the food is very flavorful and interesting. Most of the dishes are in small portions of course but youll most likely be satisfied at the end. The matcha creme brulee is not part of the regular omakase but I would recommend it as a strong finish to a fun meal. Service was solid. Polite and on top of replacing my dishes.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('enim3417',1201,'2019-12-04',5,'Beautiful food. Stunning presentation. Â Complex and thoughtful flavors. Make a reservation. Small space. Thoughtful staff. Legit vegetarian option. We WILL be back again.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',1023,'2017-03-31',5,'7 years industry experience here. Â The Restaurant made a fairly large error that negatively Â impacted the dinner Â and caused the party to leave. Â People are human and mistakes happen. However the manager did nothing to even try to resolve the issue. She Even responded with anger. Â It was just a bizarre experience.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1742,'2017-08-01',4,'Hands down my favorite sushi restaurant in the city! The omakase is the way to go, great for one or two people. The quality here is unlike any other sushi place Ive had in the city. Cant wait until they open back up for indoor dining!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',1182,'2018-03-10',5,'Kai Zan is absolutely delicious; if this is your first time going, I highly suggest getting the omakase. It is a perfect spot for special occasions and celebrations!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sodales69101',1606,'2019-07-28',5,'Interracial discrimination!!I used to LOVE this place, until my latest experience here. I came on a Friday night with my boyfriend. We sat on the same side of the booth and were approached by the manager and told that we were not allowed to sit next to each other due to Covid protocols. At the same time their bar was full of people sitting next to each other. The manager told us that we can leave if we dont like it I reluctantly stayed because my boyfriend really wanted the sushi. At the end of dinner I went to the bathroom while we were waiting for our Uber, when I came back I sat on my boyfriends lap. The waiter approached us and told us to keep it classy in a very condescending tone. I asked to speak to the manager who told me this was a family restaurant and we were being inappropriate. Now I would understand if we were being frisky or making out or whatever but I literally sat on his lap for 2 minutes!! I told the manager she had no right to treat us this way and we were not being inappropriate in any way. She told us to leave and not come back. Im honestly shocked!! I used to recommend this place to all my friends and family and am deeply disappointed at the Â discrimination and disrespect we faced yesterday. I definitely wont be returning.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis2682',672,'2020-04-30',4,'Best sushi in the city. Its the perfect post workout refuel after a strength session at The Garage Chicago gym down the block. Highly recommend just about everything here.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',276,'2017-12-11',5,'Chicagos hidden treasure. We sat in a private booth, and our server Brian was very nice and accommodating. Highly recommend pursuing Omakase route, you will not regret it. Its 10 courses of freshness, vibrant flavors, and creativity. Every dish, with ingredient listed, you can taste each individual contribution that the ingredient has in the dish, no flavors masked. Along with Omakase, we also ordered the two specials, which were so flavorful, well cooked, with many textures. The uni/tuna tartare and the wagyu lobster fried rice were sooooo good. I cant emphasize how amazing these dishes were. Im visiting the city for the weekend and thoroughly disappointed that I dont have access to this restaurant whenever I want it. Ambiance AFood A+++Service ADrinks A (byob, corking fee)Cost A',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',1654,'2016-11-04',5,'The chefs omakase is the way to go. 10 courses for $65? Hard to beat that price point in Chicago. We were seated at the sushi bar where we got to see the chefs live in action. They also have private booths that are more intimate, good for a date or larger groups.The food comes out extremely quick - like lightening speed fast. I barely had time to take a breath and the next dish is already in front of my face, which can be a good or bad thing depending on how you look at it. Personally I didnt notice it until my significant other pointed out that weve gone through 5 courses already within the span of 20 minutes. It bothered him a little that it seemed like they were trying to rush us through our dinner. I understand that turn over has to happen but I wish they gave us a little more time to enjoy the experience. So a downside would probably be the time limit of 90 minutes.However, everything was super fresh and delicious! They definitely save the best for last, which was the sashimi. The slices of raw fish just melts in your mouth. It would have been better if they put it earlier in the meal because by this time we were quite full and felt like we werent able to fully enjoy it like we would have wanted to. It was still incredible though! Besides the sashimi, my other favorites were the escolar & marguro pearls, shooters, and the orange rush. We were thoroughly impressed with the all the flavors and would love to come back and try their premium Omakase option.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla91184',1330,'2017-09-05',5,'Cant find the words to describe the experience we had at Kai Zan! Food was exceptional!! Service was top of the line, the ambience was incredible!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',1548,'2016-08-22',4,'Been here a couple times and I am SO excited and looking forward to going back! Kai Zan is the place where I first fell in love with escolar and hand rolls. We sat at the bar and ordered the New Omakase / Chefs choice. I had no idea what I was in for, but this was the freshest seafood I have ever had. The escolar feels like a cloud in your mouth and is the softest, most delicious fish. If youre adventurous and love seafood/sushi, this place is a must try! Even after I was done with the Omakase I placed another order of the Escolar Pearls. This was also my first time trying oyster and uni shooters and they were delicious. The chef prepared some very creative and unique dishes, and to be honest, I cannot remember the names of all of them, but I highly recommend everyone try the Omakase. It is on the slightly more expensive side (around $70), but it is a good amount of food (10 small courses) and so worth it. I dont usually like anchovies, but there one dish prepared with them that was amazing. Â The restaurant is small and cozy, but very popular, so I strongly recommend making a reservation as soon as you can. Nice ambiance. Service was great and the dishes were served in a prompt manner. Sitting at the bar, we got to see the chef prepare the dishes in front of us which was a cool experience. I actually prefer the bar seating over the wooden booth.Hands down some of the best sushi and seafood Ive had in Chicago. Highly recommend!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede20152',1437,'2017-12-22',5,'Wonderful experience getting carry out! Order was correct, fresh, and beautiful flavors as always -) Pick up was quick and well organized. So glad we can still enjoy fabulous sushi!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',753,'2021-02-05',5,'My all time favorite sushi place. We always loved coming here pre covid and now we get take out from here a LOT. Â Theyre so safe and we feel great about supporting one of our favorite restaurants.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam2176',1424,'2021-09-27',4,'Made reservations for a table over a month ago. Â  When we arrived, the hostess asked us to sit in a dark corner of the bar next to the dishwasher station. Â She was giving our table to someone with a back problem. Â Refused to give us another table. Â Space at the bar was tiny and already crowded. Â Definitely not appropriate during a pandemic. Â  We did not feel comfortable sitting in a cramped crowded corner and Â hostess refused to make any other accommodations. Â We had to leave. Â Before we even got to our car, we were charged $50 for a cancellation. Â Called the restaurant, owner refuses to refund the money even though restaurant did not have a comfortable and safe table for us. Â  Shame on you',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',917,'2017-03-25',5,'Our favorite restaurant in chicago. Great service, laid back atmosphere and out of this world omakase. 6 stars for the food and experience.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('potenti62109',776,'2017-07-08',5,'Oh my goodness. Â This is the second time Ive been here and this is hands down the best sushi Ive experienced in Chicago. Â Even though I dont live in Chi-town anymore, I did for 6 years and I eat sushi like a fiend. Â It is not cheap here but you have to pay to play and the raw fish will dance with you like youve never danced before.This combines the best of extremely fresh, elegant fish, with amazingly skilled chefs and creative fusion concepts. Â Live a little and go for the New Omakase. Trust me you wont regret it!Protip even though they serve liquor they are still BYO and at a $15 corkage for 2 bottles it is very reasonable for the caliber of the place. Â The liquor store across the street carries craft large bottle beers (e.g. Delirium or Unibroue) and a chilled sparkling Hitachino sake. Â That makes an awesome compliment for the awesome food.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit21153',1521,'2019-05-09',5,'Wow! This was my first time experiencing Omakase style sushi dinner. This was also my first time dining at Kai Zan. I was looking for a really good sushi restaurant to celebrate my birthday. At first I couldnt get a reservation but called the restaurant to add my name to the waiting list. They called me asking if I was still interested for a table or 5 for 715 pm. I was so excited and reserved the table with a credit card. Kai Zan will charge your card if you cancel. The service was excellent. The servers did a great job explaining the menu. Being that my party was new to Kai Zan our server recommended we do the Omakase at $65 per person for 10 courses. We agreed. They did a great job explaining the dishes. I really enjoyed all the courses. I enjoyed the Asian fusion flare added to the meal. I really dont know how to explain it but omakase is NOT the sushi dinner consisting of orders a spicy tuna roll, shrimp tempura roll and few salmon and tuna nigiri. We did order a salmon roll afterwards bc some of us were still hungry. We also ordered a bottle of champagne and I ordered sake. Cant remember the name of the sake but I really enjoyed it. We also ended the meal with in house made Ube Mochi, strawberry mochi, and mango mochi. Im very glad I got the chance to try Kai Zan and I highly recommend.The only disappointment I had was our server didnt acknowledge my birthday at all even though it was noted on our reservation. The hostess did greet us and said happy birthday but when we ordered dessert there was no candle or anything to wish me a happy birthday. Also the bathrooms were a bit dirty which was a disappointment. For those reasons I couldnt give 5 Stars',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',646,'2019-02-04',5,'Best sushi experience in the neighborhood! So delicious and Im dying to go back soon!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',1521,'2016-12-19',4,'They cancelled reservations without calling me. Wouldnt say sorry for there mistake.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus366',1522,'2020-10-13',5,'Always amazing, even during a pandemic. You can go with anything on the menu and walk away happy every time. That being said, dont miss out on the pearls, they are a must!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',390,'2018-03-11',5,'Looking for a new date spot? Tucked away in West Town, Kai Zan is my go-to place when my husband and I want a fancy date night. At a reasonable $65 per person, the omakase is impressive and includes 10 courses featuring the restaurants greatest hits. I was blown away by the creativity of the foods presentation - you can tell that the chef puts so much thought into every single detail of each dish, which makes the whole experience so exquisite.The food comes out very quickly here and the service is stellar, so youll be finished with your 10 courses in about an hour and a half. Kai Zan does serve alcohol, but we did see a couple run out and buy their own bottle of wine so I believe you can carry in booze as well. We ordered the Wandering Poet sake which we paired with an IPA.Favorite courses Oyster and scallop shooters with quail egg I was a bit hesitant to try but each bite is just packed with flavorOrange Rush a seared scallop wrapped in salmon on top of a purple seashellDynamite mussels mussels with a kickAngry crab spicy crab wrapped in tuna with a tempura crunchBecause the restaurant is rather small (which makes it intimate) and very popular, reservations are highly recommended. If you are looking to be absolutely blown away with amazing sushi in a hip environment, check out Kai Zan ASAP!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',159,'2019-08-15',4,'Truly the best sushi in Chicago... possibly the best Ive had in all my travels also. The staff is outstanding.. the service is wonderful and their timing runs like a well oiled machine. Perfect in every way! We each did the 10 course menu and for around $70 each an amazing way to sample the best of this business! We also ordered desert...the lava cake and green matcha tea creme brulee at the servers suggestion. Favorites included the angry crab, orange rush and escolar& maguro pearls. We substituted the shooters for chef choice rolls. One was blackened tuna... fabulous! Incredible dining experience.. we will be back! Byob with $10 corkage fee also.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hina115',33,'2021-11-26',5,'Took my parents here for their 30th anniversary. Everyone had a wonderful time ) Loved the interior and the private booths. Great service and enjoyed all the food we ordered, omakase and a la carte. Both of my parents commented praise for certain items throughout the meal. Highlights were uni toro tartare and escolar pearls. Mum also enjoyed the unagi; Dad enjoyed the akami tuna. And well always remember Kai Zan as the place where my dad, with a not-so-secret secret sweet tooth, said he didnt have much room for dessert, but dove in for a giant bite once he saw it arrive to the table lol.I also went here for our 5 year anniversary with an early dinner res. Unfortunately they didnt have the uni toro tartare and informed us of an uni limit on how much we could order, but friendly service and overall had a lovely meal )',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',1038,'2016-12-24',5,'We have been to Kai Zan twice already and its always worth to go back to. Â We did tasting menu on both times and enjoyed each course served. Â The service is phenomenal and the ambiance is great! Â We were seated on both times in small private room.Their omakase is highly recommended and the price is reasonable compared to other omakase in the city.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',1600,'2018-11-08',4,'Ive been here twice and immensely enjoyed both of these experiences. I love how great of a value this place is especially for $70 for 10 courses of omakase and amazing service. Definitely my go to in Chicago if I feel like treating myself and getting some good sushi. You definitely need to make reservations for this place at least 2 weeks in advance if you dont want an odd dinner time. I got the regular omakase both time I came here and I was so full by the end. You do have the option of getting omakase individually if the other people in your party just want to order off the menu. The servers were super attentive and explained each of the courses that we got in the omakase. I have sat both at the bar and in a closed booth, and the bar definitely feels more intimate since you get to see your food being made in front of you. My favorite courses - Madai Carpaccio just super fresh fish, amazing taste and the olive oil really stands out - Tuna dashi I didnt expect soup to be incorporated but its such a nice break from all the rice and raw fish. Makes you feel all nice and warm - Sashimi platter So much fish wow just a great value- Occassionally the chefs will create something new and let you try it out, and we had this amazing kale and tuna(?) dish that was probably my favorite dish of the night. Will be back soon to try out the premium omakase!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a22154',677,'2021-03-29',5,'My awesome girlfriend made a reservation weeks in advance so we got sat right when we got there. We got the omakase which was quite good, keep in mind it is fusion style so the flavor profile for certain dishes can be more complex than traditional sushi. For those looking to try more dishes, two people can share a omakase for $15 extra.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec37198',1057,'2021-09-26',5,'Weve been here for the classic omakase so we had to come back for the premium which changes based on the ingredients the chef has and uses highly quality products. This seemed like a complete opposite of their regular omakase as it had much more earthy tones (think like hamachi taste and lots of mushrooms) than traditional Japanese seafood (sushi/sashimi). I kind of wish there was a better mix of both, but overall Im glad we tried this and everything was still very high quality. The quality products given were more uni, wagyu, high cuts of sashimi like fatty tuna. What was really interesting about the sashimi was it paired with a variety of picked vegetables - Ive never had that before! Really interesting pairing. The donburi with quail egg yolk, uni and ikura and of course the wagyu were my favorite courses. Staff was great, explaining each dish and sitting at the bar was exciting to see the chefs at work. They would even stop and ask us how we were enjoying the meal which made it really personable.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit96122',680,'2021-02-11',5,'Best meal Ive had in a long time, quite possibly ever! Â Each dish was carefully prepared with an amazing array of flavors, to perfection. Â Its hard to know where to even start, the fish is the freshest Ive had in the Chicagoland area. Â There was also a nice balance of hot and cold dishes. Â My favorite has to be the escolar as it literally melted in my mouth. Â Cant wait to come back soon for another treat!!!!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin7639',1692,'2017-02-03',5,'This is now my favorite sushi spot in Chicago -- bye Katsu ( Personally i prefer ordering off the menu vs the omakase but thats bc im allergic to raw shellfish. My favorites are the ouster shooters, maguro and escolar pearls. But everything is pretty amazing. Its hard to get a reservation, so definitely plan in advance. The service is always good and the servers are always knowledgeable and provide good recommendations.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt318',429,'2021-08-08',5,'Ive been to a lot of sushi restaurants around the globe. What still surprises me is that one of the best sushi restaurants in the world is right in my backyard. Kai Zan has a humble outward appearance, but dont mistake that for how they deliver their end product. Carlo and Melvin consistently create an experience that you will remember. Each piece that they make is a carefully crafted work of art. If this is your first time, try the omakase menu. For a truly unforgettable meal, go for the chefs tasting. When you leave, Im confident that Kai Zan will be the sushi gold standard for you as it is for many that have stepped through its doors.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',471,'2017-08-22',4,'Oh gosh, whenever Im in Chicago, Kai Zan is a mandatory stop. I dream of Kai Zan everyday! We visited before COVID and had the most perfect omakase dining experience, and we have ordered to-go from them as well. To keep it nice and simple, Kai Zan does not disappoint.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',772,'2019-12-22',4,'Love this spot and the fact that it is so close! Im happy they are doing carry out because of Covid bc I really missed their sushi. Highly recommended! Definitely get the green monster.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',1366,'2021-08-30',5,'Went here for an early evening dinner. We got there 30 minutes before our reservation and they dont open the doors until 5pm on the dot. As we were seated, our waiter got us our refreshments and went to explain the omakase menu. He also asked us any dietary restriction, which Im glad because I usually forget to tell them (no pork, no alcohol).With every meal, the waiters would come and explain the dish and how they suggest eating it. At first, we thought that we would not be full by the end of the 10 course meal, but it was very filling. The ambiance, service and food were all amazing and would highly recommend going there!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',988,'2017-06-05',3,'Been wanting to come here for quite awhile and finally did on a Friday evening to treat ourselves. To note, this place books fast - I was looking close to two months prior and the earliest res I got for Friday was 845 pm. We arrived maybe 10 minutes earlier, and given their strict 1.5 hr allotments, we were seated close to our scheduled time. It is a little intense having to scarf down your omakase in that amount of time, often with dishes coming out on top of one another, if not at the same time, but to be fair, they at least are transparent about the timing at the forefront, so I guess that should be expected. I personally didnt mind as much, as it was an efficient use of my time.I really enjoyed the space - on the small side, but not too much. There were nice nooks of seating. We were seated at the chefs bar, which I enjoy, but the separate booths certainly are more intimate.Boo and I opted for a regular and premium omakase. Service overall was fantastic. We were regularly checked on and given a run down prior to each dish. All the staff were very friendly, waters were refilled and plates were consistently cleared. It was fun seeing the chefs in actions, and they certainly were very well organized and devoted to their work. It was nice that one of the brothers even asked how we were doing at one point.I thoroughly enjoyed both omakases. I do have to say while the premium is more creative with higher quality ingredients (A5 wagyu and the fattier cuts of fish), the overall value wasnt quite there and was only marginally better for me. The dishes could have been more memorable. I found for both, that similar notes were often used for various dishes - e.g. I thought the basil lemon microgreens enhanced one dish while not the other and I dont know if the consistent use of edible flowers were necessary, except for a nice IG shot. There was a deep fried prawn, noted to be completely edible with the shell, except that I found it not as easy to go down as the more common, soft shell crab. Nonetheless, I still enjoyed the dishes, as they were tasty. We had two soups, and both the broths were clean and tasty. I also enjoyed the scallop dish and all the quality sashimi. Overall, I definitely enjoyed Kai Zan and would come back. Dont expect an authentic experience, as yes, you are on a time limit and the omakase is essentially pre-set (although they will cater to your needs). You def can be relieved that you at least wont have slow service here. Also, the chefs do fuse modern and traditional flavors here, so expect that and overall, good quality food. The chefs choice omakase certainly is a good value and the premium is nice to mix things up.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',1529,'2019-06-30',5,'If youre interested in an affordable Omakase dinner that will leave your stomach full and your heart happy look no further than Kai Zan! They offer a 10 course meal for $69 a person. Each dish was delicately created and intricately designed. No surprise that they gained a Michelin star in previous years. Courses were made fresh in front of us as at the bar seats. Every dish contained fish so arrive with a sea appetite! Wait staff were incredibly attentive. One of my chopsticks slipped off the table onto the floor and it was replaced within seconds. I recommend reserving asap if youre looking to dine in soon. We made a reservation three weeks prior for a Thursday evening.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',1625,'2018-05-01',5,'The omakase experience here is great! It was more than i could eat, and I can eat. Come with a group, order some sake, and settle in for a great meal!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quisque750',543,'2021-01-21',4,'Best Omakase! We tried the 10 course omakase and it was just great. Not only the food but the service! Would def recommend!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nam3954',1454,'2021-12-20',5,'One of the best sushi I have ever tasted! Â Its a small but quaint restaurant. Â Service is very accommodating and friendly. Â I ordered the Premium Omakase for $120 (but prices range on what they are serving that day). Â They were also offering a regular Omakase for $65 with some alternative options to share. Â But I must say, the Premium Omakase was impecable. Â My favorite was the sashimi and nghiri platter. Â The fish was so fresh and flavorful. Â You can taste the quality and detail put into each dish. Â Also, their uni was on point and also delicious! Â Overall Â Amazing sushi and a wonderful dining experience!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',690,'2017-03-03',5,'Really enjoyed the experience at Kai Zan.I was pleasantly surprised by each dish in the Omakase. Service was also pleasant and professional.Three stars because everyone in the group wanted the Omakase, but could not order it. That was the groups specific goal of visiting the restaurant.I would like to visit again, but dont want to risk the same disappointment of not being able to order the very dish we came for.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed7891',332,'2018-03-09',4,'Ive been meaning to try the Omakase for sometime now and Im so glad I did. I made a reservation a week in advance for a table of 4 at 5pm (not many times were available a week in advance). Its a 2 hour time limit for a table of 4. The restaurant is pretty small but has an intimate ambiance. My group was seated in a very cozy private booth. We started the night with 2 bottles of our own sake. Their BYOB policy is a 2 bottle limit and a $15 corkage fee. We all ordered the standard Omakase $65 and upgraded with a $5 uni topper. Madai Carpaccio This carpaccio melted in your mouth and had so much flavor. Dont ignore the micro greens, they add a unique but fresh flavor. Escolar & Magura Pearls The escolar beat the tuna in this dish. Angry Crab The Angry Crab was our first dish with the additional uni. The uni was so sweet, I wish we had more! Shooters 2nd dish with the uni topper. The shooters were my favorite! Full of texture. Orange Rush Honestly, cant remember much about this dish? I guess it wasnt memorable. Tuna Dashi Soup break! Main My favorite cooked dish was the shrimp and the mushroom. The mushroom was plump and had a plesant grill taste. Fiesta Maki The fiesta maki was overpowered by clinatro. The chefs were nice enough to include an additional roll, the Flaming Tuna. I liked it a lot more than the Fiesta Maki. Dynamite Mussels Nothing too special about the mussel but they were damn good. The scallion mayo really brought it together. Sashimi I was struggling at this point, so much food! The very final dish -- Matcha Creme Brulee (not included) Overall this was a fun and enjoyable experience. The staff was super quick and knowledgeable. We will definitely come back for the Premium Omakase!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',212,'2021-04-14',5,'Ive been the Kai Zan twice and highly recommend it. This was my first omakase experience. We selected the chefs choice which was $65/person and opted for the uni upgrade for an additional $5/person. We also ordered the toro and uni appetizer $28 which was my favorite. The service was great. They gave us hot towels to wipe our hands before our meal. The waiter/waistress explain each dish as they serve them and it came pretty fast. I was a bit hesitant on whether well get full off of the 10 course meal but surprisingly we were. We even had leftovers to bring home because we couldnt finish it all. The food and presentation were top notch. I enjoyed every course except for the fiesta maki roll. Each course was very different. My top favorites were the madai carpaccio and escolar & maguro pearls.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',1543,'2020-11-17',5,'My favorite sushi place in Chicago! The sushi is so fresh and the dishes are very unique. My personal go-tos are the polenta bites, the maguro pearls and the angry crab. However, ive had almost all of their bites and they are all great! You can also ask for their sushi menu, which has your more basic rolls (i.e. tuna avocado, spicy salmon, sashimi, etc.) for extremely reasonable prices.Because this sushi restaurant is highly sought out, they limit your reservation time to 1.5 hours for 2 people or 2 hours for 3 or more. They also require a credit card to hold the reservation for more then 2 people. However, it is extremely worth going here if you are even able to get in!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',1505,'2016-11-21',4,'Kaiz Zan has been at the top of my Chicago sushi list for a while, and it turned out to be as great as my expectations and more.I recommend making a reservation in advance to secure a spot.My friend and I got there a bit before our reservation, and while we were waiting, for the heck of it, we tried the white Domaine Sigalas Assyrtiko wine which only comes as a bottle rather than by the glass, but it was delicious. It was on a dry side but had a mild flavor that wasnt too sweet that ended up pairing very well with our dinner. Between my friend and I, we shared the classic and premium omakase.I can agree with a lot of what the other reviews said about the classic omakase being the tastier omakase option. Each dish from that menu was impeccable. I enjoyed how the premium omakase had some more adventurous flavors and risks, but it just wasnt as refined overall. The quality of the fish was amazing, and was convinced a few dishes into the meal that Kai Zan was my new favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',796,'2020-08-13',5,'This establishment has been around for about 6 years, recently expanded the property by occupying the space next door. It is has a very fun and intimate setting. A bar that sits about 6-8 guest comfortably, a few tables, and on the other side, private intimate tables that sit about 6 guests comfortably, probably up to 8 if necessary. The food here is good, but Id like to say that the experience I had here, was much more like a Kaiseki meal rather than omakase sushi, in which they choose to call it. Kaiseki is traditional multi-course Japanese dinner, and this is more like that than sushi. A variety of appetizers and fish dishes. They did offer soy sauce, which we declined. There are two levels of the meal, although we originally booked for the higher one, after seeing the menu, we determined it was way too much food for us to consume.First Dish Madai Carpaccio- Japanese red snapper with toro, tobiko, dressed with olive oil and basil. Very delicious, I almost asked for extra, but I needed to be patient respectful of our meal. Second Dish Escolar Maguro Pearls -Seared tuna and escolar dressed with scallions, truffle oil, and spicy mayo. Cute bite, alot of rich flavors going onThird Dish Angry Crab- Spicy crab rapped in tuna, topped with tuna and spicy mayo. I wasnt a big fan of this one, I wanted to see fresh crab meatFourth Dish Shooters- two shooters with oysters, scallpops quail egg and tobiko. Cold and refreshing. Fiance loved, and he usually does not like shooters Fifth Dish Orange Rush- Seared scallop, seared salmon with a dressing (orange?). This was delightful. The scallop was sweet and yummy. Sixth Dish Tuna Dashi- Warm dashi broth with tuna, shiitake mushroom, little neck clams. Warm and delightfulSeventh Dish Main one!- Shrimp, Char Sui(like pork belly), Tako Yaki, Tako Wasabi. I did not like tako wasabi at all, but my fiance loved it, so we traded aha, the other dishes were unique 8th Dish Fiesta Maki -Salmon tuna avocado chili oil. This was like... a sushi roll. wasnt expecting that ...9th Dish Dynamite mussel- your usual (single) grilled dynamite mussel with masago and spicy mayo 10th Dish Sashimi- Assorted fishes, Tuna, Salmon, Yellowtail, Nothing japanese imported or that exquisite.He tossed in a few extra dishes on the house, but nothing highlighted to me.It was a decent dinner, quite full, but wouldnt return. I would say it is a wonderful establishment, great pricing, and good to try. But I have traveled and always seek for omakase OR Kaiseki. I think they should reconsider that they are implying if they are going to say that they are serving Omakase, I understand omakase means leave it up to the chef, but this menu was pretty pre-set. Omakase shouldnt be pulled from the menu or preset, should always be seasonal. Now this place is good, indeed. But when it comes to omakase, I would like the food to seem exceptional.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin7639',1130,'2019-10-08',5,'Visiting family in Chicago, this was a highlight dining experience. Four of us sat in a quiet booth and the waiter, more of a guide, explained the beautiful menu. Accommodations for preferences, assemblage etc. were offered and entertained. All diners chose something different and shared when opportunity arose. I had the Omikase tasting menu. Â Unbelievable!Others enjoyed various rolls, hot dishes, cooked items etc. Outstanding service, food, presentation!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',161,'2017-06-05',5,'Best sushi in Chicago!The quality of the seafood was amazing and it was so good that it will be hard to enjoy other sushi in the area. Everything was unique, creative, and had well balanced flavor. Despite the limited selection of maki the fiesta maki and flaming tuna maki were the two favorite things we got. They both had a ton of fish and such great flavor. I will definitely be going back and would recommend to any sushi lover.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',848,'2018-05-19',5,'Amazing time there. Ambiance was really classy and cozy. Service was stellar. You have to make a reservation beforehand because they are always very busy. Even at 845PM on a Wednesday. Which is the time that we came at. We got the Chefs Omakase that was priced at $65 per person, but for a small increase, I believe around $15-$20, they increase the portions a little so that its a sharing size for you and your friend/partner. This was more than enough for the two of us but you may choose to add side dishes if you need something to fill up.The place is BYOB but there is a corkage fee of $15. But it also seemed like they were serving in house drinks.The omakase was very tasty and the taro mochi ice cream ($5) was very authentic and aromatic. I will definitely be back to try out other menu items.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',1120,'2020-01-03',4,'One of the best sushi experiences Ive had! We sat at the sushi bar and enjoyed talking to the chefs and watching them prepare our meal. The restaurant is small and intimate with great service. The omakase is reasonably priced for the quality and amount of food you get. Everything was presented beautifully and each course was unique and delicious. The angry crab, orange rush, escolar and maguro pearls and shooters were extremely memorable - a must order if you opt for the a la carte menu. Looking forward to our next visit!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',1482,'2020-06-14',5,'This place really exceeded my expectations. So Im from California and exclusively went to one place to get sushi because it was the best. Since moving out here, Ive been trying to find my new go-to sushi spot. While Kai Zan wont be that new go-to spot because its price range is a little high for that, this place is AMAZING for a special occasion!Both my partner and I got their traditional Omakaze menu, and course after course they just knocked my socks off! The menu had the perfect flow of fresh to sweet to acidic, ending with a beautiful plate of sashimi. Even my partner, who isnt the biggest sushi lover, walked away enjoying 90% of his meal - which is pretty darn good. Everything was fresh and soft and delicate with explosive flavor!Some of my own favorites off the menu were the shooters (because I love squishy things with vinegar) and the orange crush which was salmon wrapped around a scallop.Like previous reviews have said, you do get a lot of food for the price. This is not a tiny bite per course for 10 courses, you do really eat your fill! We were full by course 8 but kept trucking because everything was so darn tasty. The service here was also stellar, they explained every course as it was brought and our waters and teas were always full.Thanks for an amazing meal Kai Zan, you made my birthday very special!!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',1542,'2020-06-27',5,'I cant even with this place... just go. I dont think I can come up with the correct words to describe this place, just go!If you are a first timer, I highly recommend the Chefs Omakase. You can go up from there. I am indifferent about how this place evolved from a neighborhood place to an upscale place but I am certainly happy that Kai Zan is doing well. I have to admit, I did enjoy how well the staff knows what they are serving and all... so no complaints about that.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',1460,'2020-11-27',4,'Last week was my 3rd time coming to Kai Zan for their omikase menu and once again, they did not disappoint. This is probably one of the best Japanese cuisines in Chicago. First, I cannot stress enough to make reservations. The restaurant is quite small so if you walk in, it may not be possible to get a table. When you do make a reservation, they only allow for your party to sit for 1.5 hours. This allows for them to turn the table over for the next guest. If you make a reservation with a larger party, they will likely take your credit card information.Now the food. You can order the omikase menu or you could choose to order off the regular menu. I definitely have to come back and order the normal menu. Do not fear the omikase. The chef/staff will work with you if there are certain things you dont like or have allergies. They were able to tailor the menu for me so that I didnt miss out on the goodness. Out of the 10 items, my favorite were the escolar pearls. They will render you speechless. They lightly torch the escolar and give it a smoky flavor. To top it off, the pearls are accompanied with an amazing truffle soy sauce. I could just order a plate of those. The crab wrapped in raw tuna, sushi, sashimi and hot dishes were also amazing. Some of the 10 dishes may be small, but dont let that fool you. I could not even finish my 10rh course!Needless to say, you dont have to twist my arm to come back here!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',584,'2019-03-01',5,'Considering I love nothing more than raw fish its a shame it took me so long to get here. Small restaurant + melt-in-your--mouth sushi = difficult to get a reservation. However, my friend put our names on a waitlist awhile ago and got a call the day before they had a table free up. And so we traded in our original Italian plans for for sushi. They had a perfect table waiting for us- our own little secluded area. It seems like most of the tables in the restaurant are this special with the exceptions of a few regular tables up front. Our group of 4 was quite comfortable in there, but 6 would have been fine as well. We ordered some much needed cold sake (long day with the little ones) and our very informative waiter told us about the specials. They all sounded good- the soft shell crab special at the top of the list. We decided to order the chefs choice (there was a fancier name for it) and there was some sort of deal where you could share as a couple. Fortunately, my husband shares my taste in sushi. We also added a few specials. Our 10+ course meal of small bites could not have been more delicious. By the end we wanted more, but mostly cause the food was so good. We added a sushi roll which was probably the most disappointing part of the meal but still good. And then of course dessert - green tea ice cream and creme brÃ»lÃ©e. Highly recommend booking a res (or at least putting yourself on their waitlist) soon!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',1441,'2021-06-27',5,'I cant even being to explain what a wonderful place this is! I will make sure to come back every time I am in Chicago. If you go to Chicago and not come here, you made a huge mistake. Setting- the restaurant is a cute warm oasis from the cold dreary streets of Chicago. It is decorated with rustic wood, candles, and warm colors. It is a small intimate place perfect for dates or close gathering with a few friends. It is the definition of cozy. Service- we had our waiter, but also a number of different people would clear or plates, or bring out new dishes. Every time they brought out a new dish they would explain it. We were constantly checked up on. The food came out in perfect time. Right when we were done they would clear our plates and the next dish was set forth. There is a large jug of water on the table and a pot of tea so we wouldnt have to ask for refills. Yet they constantly checked our pot of tea to make sure it was full. Our waiter was so calm and obviously knew the menu and food inside out. Food- We got the omakase meal which is a must. It includes all the best dishes on their menu. For only $65 it is a no brainer. Everything was delicious but my absolute favorites, I mean the ones I would have to rest my head on my hands because I couldnt take the deliciousness were orange rush, angry crab, escolar and maguro pearls. It was so filling and trust me my husband and I eat a lot, so if we say we were stuffed, you will be too. However, regardless of how full we save a special space for dessert. Dessert is not part of their set menu but you would be an idiot not to order it. We got the apple cake with yuzu. It was warm and perfection. This was the most perfect place. If I cant convince you to go here, then you are hopeless. Go go go! Make reservations!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nam3954',430,'2018-05-21',4,'This is a late review. We were there on 12/21/18 and 12/23/17 celebrating Christmas. Â We are big fans of chef curated omakases! Â We love Kai Zan and this was our 2nd time here getting the New Omakase which is ...Chef Melvin & Carlos premium Omakase menu focused on carefully selected non-traditional ingredients according to the website. Â Although the menu had somewhat changed from the previous year, this years new omakase did not disappoint! Â We made a reservation a few weeks back and were seated after a few minutes. Â We always get the New Omakase + several other plates including the Uni Toro special which is my FAVORITE! Â However, the server notified us as we were about to sit that the restaurant is running low on Uni that day (so the picture is from last year). Â I was very sad but made my husband vow to return sooner! ) Â Yes, the New Omakase is more expensive than the Chefs Choice but it is that way for a reason! Â Every piece/course that you get in New Omakase is unbelievable. Â I am person that is very sensitive to smell and I am honestly not a fan of sashimi or any sort of raw anything. But at Kai Zan, I eat every piece including raw mackerel (which is infamous for its fishiness if not prepared properly)! That truly says it all. The way they curate each piece is pure art! Whenever we book a reservation at Kai Zan, my husband and I are both so extremely happy from the moment we hit book on the website until we eat our last course of the omakase which is usually a top notch warm decadent dessert that concludes the best omakase you will have in Chicago! Â Cant wait to return! (the pictures are from both 2018 visit and 2017 visit! )',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',1107,'2020-05-10',5,'Great spot for wonderful sashimi with good service... Had the chefs choice omakase which was a really great value considering the quantity and quality of fish. Â All the courses were imaginative and /or beautifully presented, but in terms of flavor the first couple courses were definitely my favorites (madai carpaccio & escolar/maduro pearls). Â We also had the full dessert menu (hey it was a group, stop judging- even though the waiter totally did ). Â The mochi cake was the only one I didnt care for, the rest ranged from yum (chocolate cake) to interesting (matcha creme brÃ»lÃ©e)We had one of the private booths that was really roomy for a group of 4 and the service was efficient... Â Overall definitely plan to head back, perhaps try the premium omakase or other items off the menu...',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',1264,'2016-11-03',5,'Coming from the land of Uchi in Austin and Kata Robata in HTown, its been hard to find other establishments that truly elevate my sushi experience- one that is refreshingly creative, yet authentic, without all the overblown boutiquey sushi fusion jazz you run into nowadays. Every concoction was a work of art, both visually and delictably. Â This has easily become my favorite place and my default go-to place anytime Im back in Chicago.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',216,'2020-11-22',5,'Kai zan is probably my favorite sushi place in Chicago. The fish is always so fresh and everything here is delicious. I came here for the omakase before covid hit and it was one of the best meals that Ive ever had. Ive since ordered for takeout and everything was still amazing.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec5093',1250,'2018-05-20',4,'I would definitely give the omakase a try if this is your first time here. The two of us tried the chefs choice omakase $65 and the premium omakase $115 (both were 10 courses each). The menu didnt overlap at all and really gave us a well-rounded tour of what they had to offer. Next time, I would probably order a la carte now that we know what our favorites are!Id say the best part of the premium omakase was the plate of fatty belly sashimi towards the end - omgosh fatty tuna belly, fatty salmon belly, fatty sea bass belly. SO BUTTERY. Also, the fatty imported Japanese wagyu nigiri. See photos - really top notch! The Madai carpaccio with basil was also solid.The chefs choice omakase was printed on a menu, so it was much easier to remember what was what. Anyways, here are some of my favorites from the chef choice omakaseTuna and escolar pearls - the escolar pearls were better than the tuna onesScallop shooters - very fresh scallops and bright tasting!Orange rushFiesta Maki - lots of fresh fish crammed into the roll, very yummyWhat we would NOT getTako yaki - such a disappointment, the outside was not crispy and the inside was very chewy.Dynamite mussels - was ok but not great.Angry crab - bland, no taste, I couldnt even tell there was crab inside!Probably all of the skewers. The pork belly one was dry and meh.Overall, wed come back and order just our favorites and the uni! They didnt have any the night we went, so wed definitely order some uni shooters or handrolls.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',1132,'2017-07-06',5,'This is a somewhat unconventional review. Â We went here for our 5-year anniversary two weeks ago. Â Everything was great, until my wife started feeling terribly ill. Â She ended up passing out on the counter, and we left the restaurant about 6 courses into the Omasake.We still dont quite know what happened. She is not allergic to oysters or any of the other fish we had. Â The symptoms that followed for the next two weeks or so are consistent with ingesting bad shellfish, but we dont know for sure (especially given the super fast reaction) and I suppose will never know.The reason for this review, however, is that in retrospect, I am woefully disappointed at how the staff at the restaurant reacted to the whole ordeal. Â To their credit, they asked if we wanted to call an ambulance, but we had already called an Uber to go to urgent care. Â But this is where the support ended -- the chefs didnt react at all, we actually had to pay the bill in full, and in my state of concern we paid the entire thing plus tip. Â It irks me to this day that the staff thought it appropriate to charge and run the credit card for the full amount while we were desperate and figuring out what to do, halfway through the meal.I dont know if charging full price in this situation is fair or not - maybe it is. Â You can decide for yourself, but were not going back.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',682,'2018-01-30',5,'I love love love this place. My friend told me I should go try sushi here. I looked at her like fish in Chicago where the ocean doesnt exist?!? I trusted her since, she used to live here and she knows what good food is. So thank god I got a reservation here on time (made it two days prior) at 945PM on a Friday night. My boyfriend and I recently got into omakase, and when we saw the menu, we noticed they have omakase and premium omakase. At the time, the premium omakase was ~$120. This included items off the menu and is seasonal. We decided to opt for the premium since we were visiting Chicago and its not like we can just come back next week. NO REGRETS were made. Oh my god their omakase was amazing. Its not a traditional omakase, so everything was very modernized. The fish here were fresh. The uni, amazingly sweet and creamy and so plump. The server asked us if we wanted their last appetizer. It was the DIY uni toro hand roll. That appetizer was to die for. If I were put on deaths row, that would be one of my top two dish I would eat before I get outed. The omakase also came with wagyu sliders, which melts in your mouth when you bite. There was a dish where the fish was smoked, so when you open the lid, a bunch of smoke came out and the smoke flavored the fish. I can go on forever, but this place is a must. We also had a bottle of sake. They let us try a little bit of the sake before committing to the bottle, which I thought was super nice!I walked out so full, and so many happy dances were had. I would definitely come back!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',730,'2021-03-04',4,'Best Omakase in Chicago right on chicago ave, most affordable. Chefs are dynamite, course it perfectly for $60 bring 3 friends and youll all be full and happy and slurp shooters! Best time',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',219,'2021-01-23',5,'Had a delicious seasonal omakase dinner here in this beautiful restaurant. The selection was very fresh and flavorful. Some items were accompanied by too many other ingredients for my liking, but I loved the simple plate of sashimi (wagyu beef, tuna, salmon, yellowfin, and uni) served towards the end. Staff was super friendly but the attention tapered off towards the end of the night because it seemed to get busier closer to 9 on a Saturday night.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',286,'2019-11-01',5,'My dinner experience here has left me speechless. Everything was so amazing and it has definitely ruined sushi for me since Kai Zan is now my new standard. If you get the chance I HIGHLY recommend you make a reservation here and have dinner here at least once. Reservations fill up quick! My boyfriend and I ordered the Omakase. The regular Omakase is $65 for one person which is so affordable compared to omakases at other restaurants. One omakase is a lot of food! If you dont want to get 2 separate omakase, you can just order one and tell them that you want to share between 2 people for an extra $15 so that they can give you extra portions to share. This is what we did and this is what Id recommend you do as well if its your first time here! This gives you a chance to try out the omakase but also leave room to try out some other things on their menu if you want!I was a bit skeptical about the omakase because some of the items on the menu sounded a bit boring. But I was SO wrong. The flavors that they add to everything is amazing. My favorites was the ESCOLAR & MAGURO PEARLS. Both fish is lightly seared and the spicy mayo and truffle oil makes these so savory and so delicious.We also ordered some additional items* WAGYU BEEF NIGIRI - my first time trying wagyu beef and this was really good. it was seared and had such a strong beefy flavor but it had such a soft texture that it melted in your mouth* SEARED FATTY TUNA - I forget what kind of tuna cut it was but it was very fatty and melts in your mouth like butter! AMAZINGThe waiters did a good job at timing the dinner. They cleared out our plates when we finished, and within a few minutes, a new plate would come out.For Dessert we tried* LAVA CAKE w/ BLACK SESAME ICE CREAM - Like your typical lava cake but with black sesame ice cream. Great dessert but nothing out of the ordinary.* UBE MOCHI - get this!! This is not your typical mochi. They make this in house. The outer mochi shell has yuzu sauce infused into it to give this slighty tartiness to the ube ice cream. It is so good!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1615,'2017-08-08',5,'Heres the scoop. This place...AMAZING. Hidden gem in Chicago.Im almost reluctant to give my opinion because I dont want anyone else to come here and ruin it.Staff here treat you very well. Its cozy, has a lot of flavor, creative, and overall one of the best sushi places in the Chicago area. If youre looking for something comparable to NY sushi nakazawa or LA sushi Enya, look no further.In a few years, this place will be legendary.The owners, brothers, are slowly but surely making their marks. Ill be back, for more.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',1240,'2021-01-14',5,'Hidden in Ukrainian Village is a nifty little Japanese spot. Atmosphere was great but hard to maneuver between tables, its a little cramped. Service was great, FOH was very helpful at explaining each dish. Everything that was served tasted good, but the char siu really stood out. It was nicely season and and just extremely tender. If it was served right away, it would have melted as I bit into it. Orange rush was also impressive, it was light and fresh, a classic seafood citrus combo. The soups had a nice touch with the addition of shitake mushroom but besides that it was just a basic miso soup. Hamachi Kama was bigger than what you get at other restaurants but I wish it was served to me hot, as mine was not at the temperature I prefer. Flavor wise, it was good and very meaty.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',699,'2020-01-31',4,'It was incredible to have a great Omakase experinece only for $69 per person! It was really excellent than my expectation. It is not a traditional Omakase, but still perfect. Especially, the soy sauce served with Nigiri was incredibly delicious. Very impressive! I want to recommend this place to students for celebrating thier anniversaries. The price is not too high, and the restaurant atmosphere is pretty cute.I really wanted to give 5 stars for this restaurant, but the oysters in Shooters was so bad. It was too fishy. I think for improving its taste, they need to use small ices into this dish. It was too warm, so it could not catch the fishyness even though they used Tabasco and lemon juice. Also, the salmon and the tuna of Sashimi was not that fresh too. It was too visible to notice that the tuna was just defrozen, and the salmon was just okay. It was not fishy, but does not have salmons own special aroma. So, I guess the salmons quality was just soso. Except these two things, everything was really beautiful. Oh, and the Strawberry sorbet flavored Mochi Icecream was so good too. I will definitely have this again.Actually, I wanted to reservate Omakase Yume or Omakase Takeya for our White Valentines Day, but both were fully booked, so I booked here. But, it was really NICE choice. We are really satisfied with the Omakase experience. I will definitely come again to have the Chefs special Omakase for next time since I can trust heres chefs! Thank you for the great experience!!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',195,'2019-09-29',5,'Hands down the best sushi in Chicago. While its a bit more expensive then most places in the area its the highest quality of fish around. The menu changes a lot based on whats the freshest at the time. I ordered the nine-course meal (70USD) and it was outstanding! If youre looking for good sushi, Id recommend Butterfly. If you want a culinary experience this is your place. Tip ask for the private booth, very romantic.',83);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',877,'2017-12-29',5,'We went for the Omasake menu which was a 10-course tasting menu. The food was great but we felt a little rushed for the 90 minute dining limit. We couldnt finish the last course as we were still digesting... we were brought the next course while still having the previous one.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',1425,'2017-07-16',4,'My partner and I did a late anniversary dinner here and had the Omakase. We both generally liked about 75% of the menu. I couldve done without either one of the shooters and without the tuna dashi, which was kind of tough and definitely fishy. For $65 per person, I expected to like all of it, so I was slightly disappointed, but the rest of the dishes won me over. If I were to come here again, I would see if I could sub out those two courses as they just werent up to par with the rest. Other than the food, the ambience is great and the staff is very attentive. The place is cute and cozy, not too loud.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',667,'2020-07-02',5,'I came here to check out the omakase with a fellow foodie friend, and we were blown away by the incredible food. I was watching the Tokyo episode from Parts Unknown recently (RIP Tony) and was inspired to experience an omakase menu. After reading great reviews on Kai Zan, I booked a table for two on a Thursday evening (no need for credit card with booking unless for 3 or more guests, I believe). We were given a menu for the Chefs Choice and decided on this set (we added uni to some of our courses for $5 per person), rather than the premium set. There wasnt a specific menu for the premium choice, but the main seafood ingredients were listed on a chalkboard next to the kitchen. We started out with the Escolar and Meguro Pearls which were delicious. I also really enjoyed the Madai Carpaccio (delicious red snapper with basil miso), Angry Crab (crab wrapped in tuna (I know, its insane)), Dynamite Mussels, and Fiesta Maki. I wasnt a huge fan of the Scallop and Oysters shooters but appreciated the freshness of the ingredients. I also expected more from the main course but by the time that came out (course #6-7?), I was extremely full. The plate of sashimi came at the very end which was unfortunate because I had no more room in my stomach at this point. I managed to take a bite of each of the different pieces and as expected, everything was super fresh. The only downside to the experience was the time limit of 90 minutes. At times, I felt like we were being rushed and towards the end, our bill was sent to us before we even received our last course. I understand the turnover that has to happen but wished they gave us a little more time to relish in the flavors more. Overall, I was thoroughly impressed with the food and would love to come back to try the premium omakase.',43);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sodales69101',1507,'2016-05-20',5,'If I could give more than 5 Stars, I would. What a great birthday dinner experience from the service to every bite of food. My fiancÃ© and I both went with the $65 omakase. Blown away with the first bite and every bite following that and I got surprisingly full by the end of the meal! Youre able to add sashimi, nigiri a la carte so of course we had to get some fatty tuna ($7) added on. We were also able to sub a protein because my fiancÃ© is allergic to shrimp. Servers explained every dish as well. Ugh I could go on and on and rave about this place. Totally brought us back to our travels in Japan! If youre looking for amazeballs sushi, this is it and get the $65 omakase.',70);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit96122',210,'2017-06-22',4,'This is a small & cozy restaurant with delicious food! I made a reservation through Yelp and they called the day before to confirm. When we arrived, we waited about 5-10 minutes for our table. They served us alcohol while we waited. We ordered the $65 omakase. We didnt think it would be enough but the portion was huge and everything had such a unique flavor! It is definitely different from the omakase Im used to eating, but I had fun trying everything they brought out!The seasoning they use for their food is different from the traditional soy sauce. They have so many different flavors for everything and we thoroughly enjoyed it. The omakase had a wide variety of food as well- it was a nice mix between raw & cooked dishes. The nigiri was seared and seasoned, the oyster and scallop shooters were slightly spicy, sashimi was fresh, and everything was cooked perfectly. It didnt come with dessert but we ordered the matcha creme brÃ»lÃ©e and it was yummy! It had a strong matcha flavor, which I appreciate. The omakase menu is going to be different every time but I personally enjoyed my menu and recommend it! Our reservation time was 1.5 hours which was more than enough time since they bring out each dish very quickly.',80);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',680,'2016-07-31',5,'Small place, make sure to make a reservation and request a booth for the perfect date night. Go for the the Chefs Omakase for a little taste of everything. I especially loved the unique ingredient combinations (like polenta wrapped in escolar) and the beautiful plating.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',1285,'2016-01-31',5,'I tell EVERYONE who will listen the same thing all the time hands down, Kai Zan is the best sushi value in Chicago. A stellar omakase for only $65 per person? It truly doesnt get better for that price. My husbands first omakase experience was at Kai Zan four years ago, and he was very skeptical (not all too adventurous, especially with sushi). He was blown away and liked things that he never thought hed even try. We now make Kai Zan our anniversary dinner restaurant every year, which says a lot since we rarely make it back to too many places over and over (outside of our little neighborhood standbys) since the selection of restaurants and food in Chicago is so immense.Kai Zan is worth the repeat visits, though!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',1053,'2021-10-24',5,'I was in love with this restaurant when I was living in Indiana and was starved of decent sushi for months. Return visit had me come back down to earth.Unfortunately, they were out of our absolute favourite menu item with the eskimo clouds. The regular omakase is roughly the same. Not really an omakase, treat it more like a tasting menu.Its a lot of food at a reasonably high quality at a reasonable price. You cant go wrong with Kai Zan, but at the same time its lost its magic for me. Though, I was never a big fan of fusion sushi in the first place.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('volutpat2346',1059,'2017-03-09',4,'By far the best value for money for dining exceptional food. Both times I have been there for special occasions. Ordered the Omakase both times and was amazed both times. Surprised to get out very full and experience an exceptional service with great attention to details.My favorite sushi spot in the city by far!',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1039,'2017-08-14',5,'Delicious! If Yelp had this option, I would give Kai Zan 5 flaming stars!! A week prior to our trip to Chicago, we were trying to put our itinerary together and was totally scrambling to make reservations at all the places we wanted to try. Somehow (counting our lucky stars), Kai Zen had one last available spot on Saturday at 1000PM.When we arrived, the host had seated us by the bar and we were able to see the chefs in action which was really cool.The BF and I opted for the chefs choice omakase ($60 per person) + uni (additional $5), totally worth it. We also ordered an additional dish, DIY toro uni hand rolls ($28) which was AMAZING. My mouth just salivated a little bit thinking about it right now. If you are an uni lover, I highly recommend trying it.I wont get into every detail about each omakase dish. However, I will say every dish was simple yet complex in flavor, everything we didnt expect to our taste buds to experience.Overall, Kai Zan was a remarkable dining experience from great service, delicious food and affordable prices. Its a totally hidden gem in Chicago and needs to have more recognition. Lets just say, if we lived in Chicago, we would probably be here at least once a month. Trust me, its that good!',99);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',887,'2016-08-17',5,'The premium omakase at Kai zan is one of the best sushi meals Ive ever had. Very comparable to omakase yume and omakase kumiko. The dishes were very creative, especially compared to other high end sushi. They did a lot of dishes that were Japanese takes on Other classics so it was like a sushi version of steak and potatoes or Italian food. The plates were also all very cool, and the service was great. Would love to go back!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hina115',1403,'2021-06-22',4,'It took me way too long to get to Kai Zan, but it was worth the wait! My girlfriend and I went here on a Wednesday night (made reservations on Yelp a few weeks out) and were seated immediately at the bar. Yay! Loved watching the chefs prepare all the food. We both did the traditional Omakase for $69/pp, and it was SO GOOD. Apparently this omakase menu has never changed, which is kind of nice if you want to have the same experience over and over. They also offer an elevated omakase which is a little more that does change seasonally. Stand outs for me include the escolar and maguro pearls and the dynamite mussels. Both were so so so good and Id order dozens of those pearls if I could. Complimentary hot green tea was delicious and service was great!',59);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempus72169',520,'2017-12-06',5,'Wow. This place is fantastic. Great cozy vibe. The food was phenomenal! I loved their polenta bites (i think thats what it was called I can eat like a million of those. Hidden gem for sure. I will 1000% be coming back and i cant wait',71);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',497,'2021-12-03',5,'I love Kai Zan. Live right around the corner and wish I could go every day!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',926,'2017-08-08',5,'This was an excellent sushi experience- everything from the food, service, and presentation. We tried the omakase menu and it did not disappoint. The highlights were the angry crab, orange rush, pearls, and oyster shooters! For an omakase in Chicago, it was reasonably priced and delicious. We ended up sitting at the sushi bar and enjoyed being able to watch the chefs in action.',64);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',890,'2020-11-15',5,'Step 1. Call for reservations.Step 2. Order the Omakase.Step 3. Thank me later.You might skim through the specials and find there are a lot of good items. Â Trust me, just order the Omakase. Â You will most likely get those items anyway and get a better deal cost wise.Only downside Id say to ordering the Omakase is if you have a small stomach. You get a lot of dishes, so you better be ready for it.Service is really good with timing. They give just enough time in between dishes which makes the whole experience flow together really well. Â Location is definitely in a place you would never expect. It doesnt stand out and if you drove by you were never know it was even there. Â I have yet to order the premium Omakase, but I am excited to try it in the future.Love love love this place!',79);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',39,'2021-07-01',4,'Food 5 starsService 2.5We came here for a birthday and did the Omakase for two. Â The Omakase was absolutely delicious and relatively affordable. Â The reason why this was brought down was because the service was so rushed. Â Its a 10 course Omakase and they served us the first course before we even had a chance to order our drinks. Â They also kept putting the courses on the table before we were done with the previous one. Â I want to be able to savor such delicious food and enjoy every bite but we werent able to because of how rushed it was. Â My suspicion is that they wanted to get us out for closing. Â When youre splurging on a bottle of sake/getting Omakase/its a birthday dinner, the service should be much more relaxed but it felt like they didnt care and just wanted too get us out of there. Â The reservation was at 10pm on a Friday night - they shouldnt have reservations for Omakase at 10pm if theyre going to rush us like this. Â It was also a bday but they didnt comp the $5 mochi ice cream - its not a huge deal but given how bad the service was, it just added to the disappointment.',71);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',514,'2018-10-25',5,'I was here first in September 2018. My first experience blew me away. Back in town again I decided to come here a second time. Got the 69$ 10 course omakase just like i did the first time... but everything that I experienced the first time around just wasnt alive anymore. The fish was standard, really basic, and the explosive flavors I remember from my previous visit just werent there. I remember every single course from last time was super fresh. The fish melts in your mouth in a literal explosion of flavors that worked together so well. Not this time... the fish was honestly sub par, actually underwhelming. And the flavors that I was expecting from each course just continued to disappoint me. I added on the wagyu sashimi just like last time and there is no way that was wagyu. If it was, then it was trash, def not a5. For 11$ a piece its just a waste of money.... Overall, yes I was disappointed. Because nothing I ate blew me away for one. Second I spent 100$ and left unsatisfied. I felt bad for bringing 3 other people with me. Money better spent elsewhere. I will not be back.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',465,'2020-12-30',5,'We had fabulous time at Â Kai Zan. Wonderful food, excellent service, great decoration . Â Definitely a go place.',53);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',839,'2016-06-30',4,'Kai Zan is so good your brain will explode. Seriously. Im currently writing this from the grave... because my brain exploded. RIP, me. Love you Mom. The keys to the motorcycle are in the old helmet by the door. I ripped a photo off the wall of an Italian Restaurant in Ohio when I was 15. What a time it all was.',93);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('enim3417',621,'2019-08-21',5,'It only took 3.5 years of living in Chicago to finally come here, but totally worth the wait. We came here for a late Valentines day dinner, and while we anticipated a good meal, we did not expect to be as impressed as we were by dinners end. Had to go with the Chefs Choice Omakase, and from the Madai Carpaccio we started with to the Sashimi at the end, it was great. It is one of the few times during a tasting menu where we liked every single plate that came out. That said, we definitely had favorites, like the Escolar and Maguro Pearls, Orange Rush, and the tako wasabi and char siu. But even non-fish based dishes like their soup or their oyster and scallop shooters, ended having flavors that worked surprisingly well.Their Classic Chefs Omakase is the most common order here, and after having it, I can see why. $65 for 10 courses, but its surprisingly a lot of food. Its not so much like a classic Omakase where all the dishes are various sashimi/sushi, but a kaiseki/tasting menu, which I had no qualms with. We actually chose to split it, which ends up with a $15 surcharge because they double 3 of their single-bite dishes(Orange Rush, Dynamite Mussels, Angry Crab). $80 for two people, and we were both satisfyingly full afterwards. We sat at the bar so we got to see all the food being prepared, and the speed and technicality with which they prepared all their signature dishes was quite fun to watch. This place fills up quick, and its easy to see why. But if you have the time, call a table in for a nice occasion, and you likely wont regret it.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',650,'2017-07-18',5,'Update 7/13/20- Kai Zan, as our city reopens, I have you in mind. I cant wait to return and revisit all the delicious food!!!',42);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',1269,'2017-04-05',4,'Best sushi Ive had in Chicago, easily. Â The omakase menu is incredible - normally $90ish per person (with tip + tax) is a pretty abrasive starting point, but its worth every penny. Â Every dish was melt-in-your-mouth divinity and somehow the next dish bested the previous. Â Super cool intimate place and the wait staff is laser super focused on making your experience unforgettable. Â I didnt think you could get such fresh and robust tasting seafood in a city several hundred miles from the oceans but Im so happy to have been proven wrong. Â Cant recommend highly enough and cant wait to go back and bring some people I wanna show off my culinary swag to.',41);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',965,'2019-06-06',5,'truly stellar little neighborhood sushi spot.dethroned arami & ani(RIP) as my top sushi spot in Chicago.i know they are known for their omakase, but give the a la carte nigiri/sashimi menu a go.top picks hotate, sake, chutoro, ama ebithe uni here is the perfect balance of sweet and buttery, really excellent californian uni',75);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',865,'2017-04-29',5,'4.7 stars...You literally cannot get more bang for your buck with their omakase special! It was an affordable $65 for a tasty ten courses, and we did the uni upgrade (only a $5 up charge). I was concerned we would not get full depending on how each dish was served, but both my husband and I left with happy, satisfied bellies. Out of the ten courses, I only thought two items were so-so (the angry crab and tako yaki), but I would most definitely return to grub on the remaining scrumptious items listed on the omakase menu. Would also really love to venture out to try other dishes they offer outside of their omakase. The service here was on point as well!',65);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',1497,'2017-09-15',5,'Some really amazing sushi here. Great little personal seating rooms that can make for a romantic night. Very original. The Omakase 10 course dinner is to die for and an amazing choice. The timing on all of the courses was almost perfect. The fish served was over the top in quality and not a hint of fishy taste at all. My boyfriend had the wagu beef fried rice and I thought it may lick the bowl clean. He said he never had fried rice like that before. We came for a special night and it felt like a special night.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',1454,'2021-12-01',5,'I mean. There is nothing better than Kai Zan in Chicago. The Pearls are to die for and everything is always incredible. I dont think Ill eat sushi anywhere else in Chicago again',72);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',286,'2018-07-09',5,'Probably best sushi restaurant in Chicago! Worth it at a good price. Liked the hot items but sushi was better.',41);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',1594,'2018-06-05',4,'Tasty sushi but I feel like its for more first time sushi eaters. I recommend making reservations because this place fills up fast. We decided with the $65 omakase with the $5 uni toppings. I thought all the sushi and sashimi were amazing and loved everything from it. The shooters were the best part! The carpaccio was flavorful and bomb. The cooked stuff was just aight and nothing memorable. I also didnt like how fast our food was coming out for an omakase experience! The service was excellent and very attentive. For my next visit, Ill try the premium omakase!',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',879,'2017-11-07',4,'In one word, if you are a more of a traditional Japanese type of appetite, this place is definitely not for you. We went here for the Omakase, 69 dollars for 10 courses. Unfortunately none of the courses are real Omakase. Its all heavily americanlized Asian food. Some of the dishes are very salty, like the soup and the pork belly (pork belly is not even a Japanese food!), some others are just sauced too heavily. As a traditional Japanese appetite, the most unreasonable dish was the Kimbab, which is Korean, with cilantro and jalapaneo inside(?!!)If you like Asian fusion, or Americanlized Asian food, please ignore this review. But if you are like me, who is a crazy fan of traditional Japanese food, you might want to skip this place or find yourself quite disappointed.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',792,'2018-09-04',5,'Innovative, imaginative and exciting. Weve heard nothing but high praise for Kai Zan and can easily see why. To categorize this establishment as a sushi restaurant is a disservice. The chefs create masterful dishes using the highest of quality seafood and A5 wagyu that Ive not had anywhere before. Truly a special place.',85);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra2114',242,'2019-04-05',3,'Kai Zan went above and beyond to accommodate allergies while ordering takeout. We had a gluten and egg allergy in our order. We called ahead and they helped steer us towards dishes that would be right for us. They even followed up with a phone call to confirm, AND provided gf soy sauce (a first)! All takeout was then labeled with notes to ensure safety. During COVID, its been especially challenging to order takeout, but Kai Zan made the process seamless. Thank you to caring and dedicated staff for taking allergies seriously, and for working with us so that we could help support one of our favorite spots for fine dining.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc15',573,'2021-02-17',5,'Best sushi not only in Chicago, but that I have ever eaten. This is my absolute favorite restaurant. Cannot recommend enough.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',752,'2016-04-06',5,'I came here for a a celebration for getting a new job at the recommendation of a friend and it was a treat! We got the omakase and there was tons of variety, huge number of courses, and deliciousness. Pricey but worth it.',95);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum7621',1683,'2017-11-06',4,'Hands down my favorite Japanese place in town. Having been in Chicago for four years, somehow I have never been to Kai Zan, but this visit completely wowed me. We sat at the bar seats and got to see how the chefs prepared for each course. I would highly recommend getting the omakase (or the premium one if you have tried the original omakase but wanted more high end / sophisticated raw materials to start with). Food is served to you in a super organized structure, and you wont experience a long gap or need to wait between two courses for sure. My favorite dish would probably be the uni tartare thats off the omakase menu. The uni has a super rich, satisfying texture - wrapping the tartare in the crunchy seaweed adds another layer to it! Within the omakase menu, the first couple of appetizers are simply amazing. The last couple of main dishes could be a bit salty. Overall, great experience and Ill be back again! This restaurant is definitely on par with momotaro, if not better. Also, remember to get the lava cake!! I love Japanese desserts and the lava cake here paired with black sesame ice cream will wrap up your dinner pretty well, and send you home with a happy tummy. )',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus528',184,'2020-03-15',5,'This is one of those places I have yearned to try for a few years and I have either had plans canceled or was just plain lazy or could not find a reservation within the time frame I would like to eat. Well that has all come to an end now!!!!I got the chance to come by this past Tuesday with a 7pm reservation with my very good friend. Not the biggest place but very nice looking and a bit fancier than your normal sushi joint. We were lucky enough to get one of the booths which was awesome. Our server was pretty much on point and basically walked us through the best option which was about 10 courses for $65 each...done!!!! To try so much for $65 at this place is a helluva deal!Started out with the Madai Carpaccio (Japanese red snapper, basil, olive oil and black tobiko) and it was a nice starter and we both enjoyed.Next up was the escolar and maguro rolls with truffle oil which were very good..actually we were like wow we should stop here if it gets better than this. Angry Crab was next as its basically spicy crab wrapped in tuna Â with spicy mayo and tempura...pretty decent.The Shooters were pretty nice as they came in the form of a shot and they included oysters and scallops, quail egg, black tobiko, ponzu sauce, scallions and tobasco....woooo that was good. Probably the best 4 shots Ive ever taken.Orange Rush was next and it was seared scallops and salmon which was goodTuna Dashi was amazing and a break in the action. It was a broth with shitake mushrooms, little neck clams and tuna....It was very good and flavorful AFMain Dish was tako wasabi, shrimp and pork belly on a stick...good...the wasabi was nice!Fiesta Maki was good and had a bit of a spice to itDynamyte Mussels were definitely dynamite as they included scallion mayo, black tobiko and masago...very good flavor...probably the best mussels Ive had!Assorted Sashimi closed out the courses and it was very good.I washed it all down with a 2016 Summer Water rose...2 glasses did the trick. My buddy had a blanc and he said it was one of the best he has had. This place was well worth my 5 year wait to try it out and is now my favorite sushi place in the city! Multiple visits will probably be made within the next few months!',49);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',632,'2018-05-25',5,'Consistent quality and service, and one of the best omakase experiences around town. Tho its Japanese themed not run, so it only gets you so far to the real deal',94);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut97174',216,'2016-03-30',4,'Splendid experience, 100% recommend! We ordered the Chefs Choice Omakase & it is definitely the way to go!You will have a perfectly coursed out meal that is truly DELICIOUS, diverse & so, so fresh! The $65 price tag seems fair (and maybe even cheap) considering the quality of food & thought put into the creation of the meal!After every course, my husband and I had a new favorite dish! It got better and better as it went. While each dish is a smaller-bite sized portion, there are enough dishes & spaced out nicely that you really do leave satisfied. Pair your meal with some of the plentiful sake or wine options & you have the recipe for a great night out! I absolutely plan on coming back and trying out the Premium Omakase!',49);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo41119',1582,'2016-12-31',5,'This is hands down the BEST sushi restaurant in Chicago. I made a reservation through Yelp for a party of 2 at 645PM yesterday night. We arrived half an hour earlier and we were seated around 615/620PM. We had our order customized by Justin ) (Thank you! Youre the best!) Our server Allan was extremely accommodating and was able to help us out throughout the night! My friend and I were so excited to splurge last night and we have no regrets! The ambience is casual/trendy and its perfect for date nights with your friends or significant others. Heres what we ordered escolar pearls, polenta bites, orange rush, green monster, smoked zuke, 2 salmon, dynamite bites, toro gunkan, matcha crÃ¨me brulee, and strawberry mochi. We had another custom item but I forgot what it was called (all these fancy names... I cant keep up!) I fell in love with the toro gunkan - its a dish with fatty tuna that literally just MELTS in your mouth (MUST TRY!) Their truffle oil makes everything taste that much better - but my all time classic favorites are the escolar pearls, green monster, and the smoked zuke.I cant get enough of this place and I cant wait to go back for round 2 soon! ~)',56);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',386,'2017-03-06',5,'Kai Zan has been our favorite sushi spot since 2012! We miss dining in here with friends. They have cozy booths and we also love to sit at the sushi bar! Their take out sushi options are amazing. We have tried everything on their menu and I love every bite of food I have ever had. Definitely recommend the pearls as a must order and my favorite bite is the grilled hamachi. My husband likes the angry crab and the Danielle. Dont forget to ask for and try the pickled wasabi.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',130,'2016-12-23',4,'Holy moly wagyu! We did the premium Omakase here tonight and it was delightful! It was $120 per person for the premium Omakase and it was worth the price tag considering the quality of ingredients. My favorites definitely were the nigiri composed of the fatty tuna (otoro), smoked lobster with fish roe, hamachi and then the wagyu. Each piece progressively got better with each bite. I also enjoyed the salmon, tofu and truffles with the shiro miso and dashi stock poured over it. The sashimi platter was amazing, I couldnt figure out what piece I wanted to savor last! Overall it was a great experience. Im curious to see what the chefs choice Omakase entails since it seems like it was such a great value at only $65. I might have to come back for that one!',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat4359',152,'2018-11-26',5,'I came here when I was pregnant and they were completely helpful with all accommodations and very tasty. Amazing they had Filipino inspired desserts as well! If you live in west town/Ukrainian village/Humboldt you must try this beautiful restaurant.',48);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',965,'2016-11-09',5,'This is everything, literally everything. TheMost wonderful, the best ... we come here for EVERY big occasion! Bc its amazing',32);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',1010,'2019-01-02',5,'How have I not already written a review of Kai Zan!This is hands down my favorite sushi and fancy dining restaurant in Chicago.This is the Uchi of Chicago with its quality and artful dishes. A very intimate and personalized eating experience. You MUST get the omakase for $65 (one day, Ill splurge for the premium omakase!!) and treat yourself to the chefs delights. Ive even took the omakase menu home so I can occasionally reminisce on these tasteful bites. NOTE You have to make reservations which quickly fill up well in advance.My most recent experience at Kai Zan, my boyfriend and I were seated at the bar right in front of the chefs for dinner and a show! Service is very attentive, friendly and happy to answer questions, explain each dish in detail or make accomodations. Also offered is an uni upgrade to the shooters dishThe omakase included the Madai Carpaccio, Escolar & Maguro pearls, Angry Crab (sushi bite)Oyster and Scallop shooters (yum!), Orange Rush (scallop bite), Tuna Dashi (subtle but delicious soup), Main (bites of shrimp, char siu, tako yaki octupus ball, and tako wasabi salad), Fiesta Maki (sushi roll), Dynamyte Mussels, and a Sashimi assortment - my kind of dessert! Â Literally no complaints. Even as a repeat customer, Im consistently impressed with their creativity and commitment to the art of sushi. Perfect for special occasions for your loved ones.',96);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',524,'2022-01-16',5,'Heaven! The Omakase was the best selection Ive had in the US outside of NYC. The rice is also excellent - though definitely quite vinegary. I would definitely come back again next time Im in Chicago.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',310,'2019-11-19',4,'16!!! That is the number of times Ive enjoyed the Kai Zan experience. I am blown away that Ive never posted a review. It seriously makes no sense. From my very first visit, top notch, absolutely divine service and taste. After 16 visits, I can safely say Ive tasted everything offered on the regular Omakase and standard menu and nothing disappoints! That is not hyperbole, nothing here disappoints. The early bird (tues/wed) special is a great way to sample some of the standard Omakases highlights. For those in your party that dont LOVE sushi, there are a number of delectables on the menu. Think Karaage, Yakitori-style skewers (Yum mushroom!!!)Because the ingredients and menus change (especially the Premium Omakase) I have never once been bored, underwhelmed or felt like I could have passed on any given bite. Service One of my favorite servers/waiters is usually in the building, being dope. Seating Cozy and cute. Two to Three person booths to the right, large group booths (GORGEOUS) to the left. Extra fun sitting at the sushi bar watching the Chefs make magic. Gotta end this ramble to book Sweetest 17!',73);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',1037,'2021-08-19',5,'So. Good. Took my husband here for his birthday recently and had the chance to try their premium omakase--definitely worth it. And for the amount of (quality) food you get, the price point is really not bad at all! Take note that this is not a traditional/authentic omakase--felt more like a prix fixe menu centered around raw fish/meat (nothing to complain about here though). Every course was perfection and super unique. Our favorites were the wagyu & toro nigiri.',51);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',620,'2017-01-21',5,'The quality of the ingredients, the spectacular presentation of the dishes, and the relaxing atmosphere makes Kai Zan one of the best restaurants in Chicago. I went with a group of four and we were seated in one of their private booths. Â Our server was friendly and made some great recommendations. Â The 10 course Omakase is around $65 and is well worth it. Â Im personally new to seafood and didnt want to commit to my own Omakase so our server had suggested that I join my husbands for an additional $15. Â We shared most of the courses and the courses that were meant to be enjoyed as single bites (ex angry crab), they brought out an additional bite for me. Â  In addition to the Omakase we also ordered all three of the daily specials. Â If youre there and they have Wagyu, go for it! Â  It was $10 per piece but it was well worth it. Â  Their taro chip special was great too, it reminded me of ceviche. If you like seafood, I suggest the Omakase. Â If youre on the fence like me, skip the Omakase and order Ã  la carte. Â Although I enjoyed most of the courses, I couldnt stomach the oyster shooters and didnt enjoy the orange rush (sushi scallops wrapped in salmon). Â  Again, I didnt enjoy these dishes because I dont love seafood, not because they werent good. Â  If you only get one thing, let it be the Escolar pearls. Â Its quite easily one of my favorite dishes of all time! Tips Its BYOB (limit of 2 bottles) Â  Â  Â  Â  Its popular (make your reservations in advance) Â  Â  Â  Â  Go with a group (So you can be seated in a private booth)',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dolor4397',1158,'2019-03-12',4,'Fantastic price for very high quality sushi. Our Omikase tasting menu was $69 for 10 courses and we were more than satisfied and full. The dishes were creative, diverse and fresh. Wait staff was thorough and attentive. I tend to eat fast and they definitely kept pace which I always appreciate. I highly recommend this Japanese restaurant.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',1682,'2021-05-18',5,'Absolutely delicious, everything on the menu(s). 10/10 would go here again, 5 stars for both the food and service. Worth every penny. Fairly large selection of both sushi and non- sushi items. Definitely make a reservation.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',1596,'2019-09-01',5,'So I booked a trip to Chicago as a surprise for my wife on Mothers Day. The main purpose of our trip was to eat our way through chicago. Were both sushi snobs and have eaten omakase everywhere. Â So we arrived in Chicago from Houston today. And took out uber with our 9 month old son to the restaurant. On the way there, I called to tell them I was running 15 mins. They told me no problem and that the kitchen hood was messed up so they could only make cold items which was okay I guess. On our last trip to Chicago, we are here twice we liked it so much. So this time around, we were super excited and had our list ready to order. 2 blocks before we got to the restaurant, they called and said theyre closing the restaurant due to issues. Â I asked for a reschedule Sunday or Monday but unfortunately, theyre closed those days and we have to return to Houston on Monday. So my wife and I and our 9 month old son are kinda bitter and pissed. I showed up. We explained our whole situation. The owner and sushi chef came out and was super understanding and apologetic. We showed him our list on our phone of the items we wanted to order and he determined what he could and couldnt make. We waited and he came back with two bags of to go. He even comped it because we had to take. $25 uber there and $20 back. We felt better but were still not satisfied because we didnt get our full menu of everything we wanted. We tipped $20 and left. Were now back at the hotel and even to-go, this is the hands-down best sushi restaurant in the USA. Order these items below. The chef made us what he could have an it was to die for. My pictures dont do their sushi ANY justice. Try this place. We literally booked a trip from houston just to eat here because we love it that much. Maguro and escolar pearlsUni shooters, oyster scallop shooterDIY toro handrollsTuna bellyKing crab and uni cucumber rollAngry crabDark chocolate Vietnamese coffee MochiMadai carpaccioÂ Orange rushWagyu pearlLobster uni caviarHotate',69);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi5344',1059,'2016-12-13',4,'Just go here. You cannot go wrong. Top 3 sushi place for me in the city. Order everything. Do not forget the friend chicken, it is fantastic. Make sure to make a reservation, usually difficult to get in without.',99);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',1126,'2016-02-18',5,'Just five years ago, I didnt have the most refined palate.My sushi tastes consisted of shrimp tempura rolls, fancy rolls with a lot of aioli, or normal rolls doused in soy sauce. Raw fish topped with rice? Bleh.Sashimi? Double Bleh.I like to call these the dark days. Fast forward to now and me and the bf are looking for the best sushi in Chicago.A quick google search brought me to Kai Zan.I was trying to make a reservation for a Friday night on a Wednesday and the earliest that they had was 10PM. We took it and we were ready to go. Friday night, we found ourselves on a long drive out to West Town. We definitely drove past the restaurant and werent even convinced we had the address til we took a closer look at the place. But we walked in and the ambiance was very cozy. There were some private booths to the left, but we were immediately seated at the sushi bar in the room to the right.I knew that we had to get the Omakase. How were we going to find the best sushi in Chicago if we didnt try the best of the best?The waitress explained the regular Omakase was $65 and the Premium or Chefs Choice Omakase was $115 so we opted for the Premium.She came back a little while later to tell us that since it was already so late, they wouldnt be able to do the Premium for us, so then we downgraded to the regular. I was a little bummed, but she did give us the option to add on uni for just a $5 upcharge. Id never had uni before, so of course I said, Sure, why not.And you guys. This. Was. Amazing. I wish I had a list of everything we ate, but instead I took pictures because thats the type of person I am. We started with a bunch of raw dishes. One of my favorites was a quartet of fatty tuna that really just melted in my mouth. The plating was simple and thoughtful. Im not a huge fan of oyster shooters, but the oyster/uni/scallop shooters that they had at Kai Zan tasted great and had a good kick. We got a plate of their Fiesta Roll which was probably the most boring part of the meal, really. The warm dishes were good (though tbh, we were already enthralled by the sushi). And we finished off the Omakase with a plate of delicious, high-quality sashimi. Â Now 20 year old Kevin would be cringing at the whole ordeal. But 25 year old Kevin? Thoroughly impressed.We finished off the whole meal by ordering some Orange mochi and it was the perfect light way to end.Overall, if thats what $65 bought me, I cannot even imagine what $115 buys you. Sushi wrapped in gold leaf? You get to take home your own goldfish? Mermaid sushi?I just know that I HAVE to come back to have it. Do you like sushi?Go to Kai Zan. Get the Omakase.Do you not like sushi?Give it another five years, kid. Then go to Kai Zan. Get the Omakase.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',1731,'2016-11-07',5,'One of the best sushi places in Chicago. Hands down. We order service the Premium Omakase and was feasted with beautiful and fantastic food. I normally would enjoy more selection of fish in my omakase but this one (with less fish and more other stuff- beef, truffle, etc.) really blew me away. The restaurant is small and intimate. Atmosphere is not really very fancy but nice. We had our own little booth and the waiter is so fun explaining to us each course and very tentative.Will come back for the standard Omakase which I think focuses more on fish.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',1595,'2017-02-24',5,'Omakase menu. No more needs to be said.Server was great...attentive without being too much and certainly did us a solid with the sake recommendations. We were a party of 5 and had a private booth which was perfect for enjoying both the company and the food/beverages.',64);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non93107',1234,'2021-06-18',4,'I wish I had enough words to describe how amazing was the food! Me and my wife had the tasting menu and every single dish was great! It was much better than I accepted. Ill come back for sure.',63);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',1067,'2021-02-05',5,'Kai Zan was on my list for almost two years and finally got a chance tonight. First of all, make a reservation, at least 2 weeks in advance. This is not a big place, and full of people all the time. We planned to order both regular premium omakase to get a full experience, unfortunately they didnt have premium. So we got a regular omakase, uni wrap(special for that night), scallop and cha siu skewers, stir fried soba. Omakase a 10 course chef choice. A great way for those new to KaiZan to try their highlight dishes. Lots of food, so be prepared. Uni wrap $28 night special, uni+tuna+egg+nori= worth every penny! Skewers Both Hotate and ChaSiu are good. ChaSiu is a must try! I usually dont like fatty stuff, but the pork fat here tastes just like heaven. Stir fried soba The only dish I didnt enjoy. Taste bland and not in good presentation. The dish came out without edge being cleaned, it was really not a pleasant thing to see onions and sauces all over the plate. I understand it must be a busy, but people eat with eyes. Overall we had a great night in KaiZan, looking forward to try their premium omakase.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',576,'2020-12-03',5,'Amazing experience at Kai Zan for a birthday celebration! The service was top notch before we even set foot into the restaurant, with the hostesses being accommodating about our wanting to celebrate a birthday as well as reminding us to reserve a premium omakase set if we were interested. We shared one premium and one regular omakase, and it was a perfect way to try the many, many, many amazing things that Kai Zan had to offer. The flavors were excellent and ingredients were so fresh, with the fish and meats just oozing the perfect fatty flavors. The wagyu nigiri from the premium omakase was at the top of our favorites list, along with the chip and dips and the raw shooters. Thank you to the Kai Zan staff for a wonderful experience to taste the incredible flavors you guys have created!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt58127',1399,'2022-01-19',4,'One of the best sushi spots in Chicago. We both got the Chefs Choice Omakase and every dish was amazing. Â Cant remember them all but it was a nice variety and they even brought out a few extra plates on-the-house. Â For the quality of sushi you get here, I think the Omakase was a great bargain at $65 pp plus you can add-on extras (we opted for some uni which I recommend everyone do here).Chefs Choice Omakase 5/5',NULL);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',1264,'2019-04-19',5,'Omakase $65 worth. Came in at a 5 o clock reservation with my brother and his friend. They both knew they wanted omakase but I was hesitant. Â I had read up on a couple of things that many people raved about, so naturally I wanted to try those. Asked the waiter if those things were on the menu and he promptly brought out the omakase menu (this is a plus). I saw many things I wanted to try on the menu so I thought to myself, Â why not! Not to be some bougie ass stereotypical think-I-know-it-all-and-am-the-best girl from SoCal, but I know good sushi because Ive had a good amount and because my brother is some sort of sushi connoisseur. Ive had the good and the bad. Came into Kai Zan honestly not expecting that great, but l was pleasantly surprised. There were 10 courses and more than one course had more than one piece of sushi in it. The pearls came with two of each. The main had four different pieces, etc. My favorites were probably the Angry Crab, Orange Crush, and the oyster shooter. Â All full of flavor, creative, and pleasing to the eye. Wont say too much since its definitely something you have to experience for yourself. Known to be one of the best in Chicago it is WORTH (although it aint near a train stop, so youll likely have to hop on the 66 and head hella west and they open during traffic hour so hella people on the 66)!!The food was great, and so was the setting and service. The booths that they place you in are nice and private (not the bar). You get to pay attention tp the party youre in and dont have to shout at one another. Service is also absolutely wonderful - checking on you just enough, but not too much.',NULL);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',128,'2018-02-23',5,'Fabulous food, atmosphere, service. Great for small to mid size groups. Love that the portions are such that you can try many different things. The staff recommendations were all hits.',86);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',1448,'2019-03-14',5,'Quite the experience for a sushi lover! Â Every bite is delicious and super fresh. Â Try the polenta bites and the maguro bites for sure!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',1079,'2018-11-28',5,'Highly recommend the chefs choice omakase! Ive been back for the same thing, three times now, its truly worth every penny.When you make a reservation (& you HAVE to make a reservation!), they warn you that any seat requests can not be honored, but I tried it out anyway. I asked for a private booth, the day before Valentines day... the private booths are big enough for 6 people, so I didnt really expect them to seat 2 there, but they did! The bar is fun to sit at because you can watch the chefs do their thing. Its just kinda difficult, with big coats and bags. Even with the cramped quarters, this place still gets 5 stars.',73);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1654,'2016-10-01',4,'While I prefer eating at Yuzu down the street, the food quality at Kai Zan has the edge. Â We tried the shishito peppers, the beef tataki, the edamame, the agedashi tofu, the Angry Crab, the Flaming Tuna, and the yaki soba noodles with pork. Â I would get every dish again, and all of this came out to $65, the same price as the 10-course tasting meal, so you can pick your poison and do damage here to fill yourself up!The space here is great, and while I like the energy at Yuzu more, for a date night, Kai Zan is the better choice (although the soundtrack at Kai Zan was just weird to me...the mix of music and movie soundtrack stuff I heard last night was wacky, right up to the point when the James Bond score/theme started playing. Â WTF?).Prices are fair and they have a good list of beer, wine and sake choices. Â There is a corkage fee of $15 for two bottles if you bring your own.Excited for my next visit!',69);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',513,'2016-01-23',5,'This is actually the greatest sushi restaurant in Chicago. Its so fancy, and so worth it. Even the vegetarian rolls are INCREDIBLE. If youre a sushi lover, Kai Zan is a must try. Thank me later!!',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',867,'2021-08-10',5,'This has become my favorite sushi place in the city. You must do the omakase, which is truly an experience. Sit at the bar if you can, watch the chefs and talk to them about the food. At $65 a person, the quality and quantity of food cannot be surpassed. In fact, there was too much good food, if thats a thing. By the time the last sashimi plate came out, I was so stuffed and had a hard time savoring the beautiful fish on my plate. Next time, I think I may share an omakase and double up on all the courses that contain a single serving.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',886,'2018-07-17',4,'Came here for my husbands birthday and we werent disappointed. You HAVE to get the omakase, the $65 per person option is MORE than enough food. We were so stuffed at the end, and we can eat! You definitely get your moneys worth and more! A lot of the a la carte menu items are actually in the omakase, so you get to try a bit of everything and is the best bang for your buck.Service is very helpful and attentive to any allergies you may have. I have a shellfish allergy and the server and chefs expertly substituted any shellfish tastings with a non-shellfish version. When it got too cold for us in the booth (there was a vent directly above us), they even increased the temperature for us! Its great for a date, especially when you get your own private booth... it feels both romantic and intimate, like youre in your own personal sushi world.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('morbi7160',586,'2018-02-24',5,'Come here for the Omakase...& if youre an uni lover like me, then you will for sure love it!Also, if your order the omakase, just be prepared to eat a lot of food. By the end of it I actually couldnt even finish my sashimi because I was so full. Some of my favorites were the seared maguro & escolar, angry crab & shooters.Nice ambiance for a date night, & definitely recommend making reservations ahead of time.',83);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',339,'2021-08-01',5,'I was a little hesitant about this place seeing as I dont trust sushi that is so far away from...well...an ocean. But this place is an excellent ode to refrigerated transport.The hubs and I opted for the omikase/chefs tasting menu based on a trusted foodie friends rec. There is so much I can saw about how delicious and fresh every single course was, but I would end up writing a novel. Â As experiences go, this has the makings of Chicago Bucket List status. Our server was so in tuned with us, he was informative and helpful every step of the way. We sat at the sushi bar and I loved that the chefs were friendly and interactive. I would love to go back to Kai Zan and try some of their menu options the next time I am Chicago.',65);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',577,'2020-10-26',4,'This place is simply amazing. The service is top notch and the food is amazing. We did the 12 course omakase and already want to come back and get the upgraded omakase. This is a must try for any foodie.',45);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cc110',1231,'2019-12-14',5,'Great sushi, excellent service, cool spot to dine in. Amazing chefs. The quality of the food is superb. I will come here again and again for date nights with the hubs.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ullamcorper075',1500,'2016-08-23',5,'We finally made it to Kai Zan after years! We found out about the place on check plz and always wanted to try it. I got a reservation on 12/13 for my husband to surprise him for his birthday. Im glad we came but still wish I could give it a 5 star review. We came on a rainy Thursday night hitting lots of traffic. Fortunately, we made it in time for my husband to try the special omasake menu. It was very creative and good quality overall. You can see the pictures. However, we prefer a good balance between cooked and raw items. In our mind, Katsu is still by far the best sushi restaurant in Chicago. (Too bad its closed now)I ordered the agadashi tofu and spicy seafood soba (special of the day). The soba came with king crab, shrimp and scallops. The seafood was very fresh but a bit heavy and oily for me. Its a nice date place for couples and late night finds. I would come back if Im in the area, but probably not driving for an hour for it.',56);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',1624,'2019-02-12',4,'Outstanding service that was both friendly and never pushy. Place was very well decorated and thought out without being too posh or stuffy. T-shirt and jeans kinda casual. Highly recommend the omakase. Friend went with the classic, I opted for the new style. We were both thoroughly impressed and very much enjoyed the selections. The nigori sake, although a very short list for nigori, both were outstanding. Im a tourist in Chicago and already planning a trip back so I can make sure to enjoy dining here again.',95);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',1238,'2017-06-29',5,'I dont really do reviews unless its bad, and Im not a big sushi eater. But it all changed when we ate here. Everything was so good, melt in your mouth freshness. We went crazy with the orders,4 escolar pearls (truly life changing)3 polenta bites2 orange rush2 wagyu nigiri (another favorite)2 angry crabAnd Justin recommended a REALLY good Japanese craft beer - the Yuzu Salt Ale, didnt plan on drinking either, but it got me drinking 2 cans ;)',60);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',422,'2017-12-27',5,'It wasnt before long till I had to come back for the Omakase. It was as good as last time, if not better. The chefs also gave us a complimentary piece!One thing I would highly recommend - pay $5 to add uni to some of your dishes. In our case, it was the the scallop shooter, the angry crab, and the dynamyte mussel. The angry crab was sooo mindbogglingly delicious with the uni added on top. We were going to get the uni toro tartare appetizer, but ended up being too full by the time we moved to the dashi on the Omakase menu. We also did not mind eating at 430pm. We chose to sit at the sushi bar and had so much fun watching the chefs work their magic, especially when they were cracking 30 quail eggs into those shooters. It was such a great dining experience for an unbeatable price. I am already planning my next trip there.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',353,'2021-03-21',4,'This little sushi place is something. We couldnt get Â in but we took order to go Â and it was fantastic. I want to try go back.',85);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',1430,'2019-02-17',5,'The BEST sushi in Chicago!! great atmosphere, but very small dining room. Prices moderate but food spectacular. BYOB with corkage fee, but fabulous Saki list.Its one of our regular sushi places.',99);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',862,'2018-06-10',5,'Dinner with my boyfriend for my 2_th birthday! He did lots of research on all types of restaurants all over Chicago, and finally landed on Kai Zan. Im happy to report that his hard work paid off...this place was great! We got seated right away after checking in for our 7pm reservations, and knew what to order immediately. We each asked for the 10-course Omakase menu ($65) and added uni to select courses for an extra $5. 1. Madai Carpaccio Loved how delicate and fragrant this dish was. The red snapper melts in your mouth! Great way to open the meal.2. Escolar & Maguro Pearls The sear and truffle oil were very good, but not super unique. Very well executed though.3. Angry Crab Uni makes its first appearance here, and it was SO buttery and delicious.4. Shooters 1 Oyster shooter (with Uni) and 1 Scallop shooter, each with a quail egg, and topped with tobiko. Yum!5. Orange Rush Again, great sear on the scallop.6. Tuna Dashi Okay. The tuna was a touch overdone, but due to being submerged in the hot dashi.7. Main entree My least favorite - did not care for the char siu or tako wasabi, but thats just my preference.8. Fiesta Maki Tasty, but not super unique.9. Dynamite Mussels Same as Fiesta Maki.10. Sashimi Beautiful, fresh cuts of fish. However, I was too full at this point to completely enjoy this, so I handed most of this off to my boyfriend.*11. Mochi - complimentary birthday treat!If youre looking for a fresh, well-executed approach to sushi (and a wonderful Omakase menu), Kai Zan is the place to be. Ill definitely be back!TL;DR Stop what youre doing, make a reservation online, and order the Omakase menu as soon as you get seated. Dont forget to add on uni to select courses for an extra $5. You cant beat this deal for the amount of food and quality you receive!',32);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',569,'2017-12-24',5,'What can I say...after living a block away from here for years (sadly no longer) and having been here five times, I am not sure why it took me this long to write a review. Lets just say Kai Zan is top notch. The quality of the food is stellar, the atmosphere is intimate, and service has always been outstanding. I have heard people come in and complain they have to sit at the bar and it always baffles me 1.) it says on their reservations page this may occur 2.) they tell you this when they call to confirm your reservation, and 3.) it is actually pretty cool to watch the guys at work prepare your food.Some highlights from the menu for me include the Orange Rush (I could probably get 10 orders of just these and be very satisfied), the maguro pearls, and the Madai carpaccio (absolutely outstanding). We tried Potato Ohitashi this past visit for something different and it was SO good, plus a little more filling. For dessert, their green tea ice cream is very good (creamy, not very sweet) as are their mochis (love the Japanese pumpkin flavor they had during our most recent visit)My only complaint is the 1.5 hour time limit (we tend to make later reservations so we dont feel rushed), based on the space and the popularity, I understand why they do it; however, the one time we chose to do the Omakase I personally felt a bit rushed. That all said, I cant wait to get my next five visits on the books!!',89);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',693,'2018-07-28',4,'Best sushi experience in Chicago! Definitely get the omakase for $65. Add $5 more for uni if you are into that. I actually think you can share two omakase with three people. Pace yourself - The sashimi comes at the end and by then Im always so full! Make reservations ahead of time and enjoy!',81);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',556,'2020-07-21',5,'Anniversary. Birthday. Friends in town. Its where I go when I want to go to Kai Zan. Book in advance if you want to get in- weve done omakase twice but after ordering a few times we know what we want and will order 3 orders of escolar pearls and the orange crush. Â This is our favorite sushi in chi and one of our favorite restaurants.',95);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',475,'2021-12-10',5,'Ill admit its hard to please a food snob like me, but the dining experience here was spectacular, from service to atmosphere to food. The fish was buttery, soft, and fresh. The omakase courses were all timed perfectly. The staff attentive without being overbearing. The menu was creative and cleverly deviated from the norm without going too far.If its your first time, you must get the chefs choice omakase for $65. This is the tried and true omakase that highlights the best and greatest of Kai Zan. It included- madai carpaccio with tobiko and basil miso (basil flavor a tad strong, but refreshing dish)- escolar and maguro pearls (LOVE, wish i couldve had more of this. the fish was just so delish)- uni and scallop shooter with ponzu and quail egg (not my fav, but my bf liked it)- angry crab and grilled scallop (unique takes on some common fish)- misc hot foods such as shrimp, char siu, takoyaki (least favorite course, but it was nice to try the hot foods they offer here)- dynamite mussel with black tobiko and negi mayo (small course, but yum!)- fiesta maki (cant go wrong with sushi rolls esp if fish is as good as this)- sashimi comes with yellowtail, tuna, escolar, salmon (soft and buttery yassssss)We also HAD to get the uni toro tartare for $28 because it looked amazing. Youre supposed to mix together everything and make the roll yourself. It ends up looking not very appetizing, almost like a gushy, yolky, slob of rice but OH MAN WAS IT BOMB. Im especially picky about eating fresh uni and this place passed the test. Next time Im back, Im definitely getting 2 of these and no, Im not sharing.Cant recommend this place enough. Favorite restaurant in Chicago so far.',75);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci23113',628,'2021-03-18',4,'You know that a restaurant is good when you book a table almost as soon as you get home. Like a lot of people, we got the regular omakase, which is the $65 standard. (The premium is market priced, I believe.) Unlike a lot of tasting menus, which can be hit or miss depending on when you go, they brought out their greatest hits for theirs. The Maguro Pearl might be one of my favorite bites Ive ever had in a Chicago restaurant, and I loved how much variety you got. I was afraid that I was going to be a little hungry, but the boyfriend and I were both STUFFED after the meal. We cant wait to come back and order off the regular menu, now that weve gotten a little taste of everything.All in all, this is one of the best deals Ive seen. Run, dont walk, to Kai Zan!',56);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',1428,'2018-11-07',5,'I love this place! Its expensive, but so worth it. Each dish is unique and scrumptious. Its hard to get reservations since the place is quite small, but once you do... dont turn back! Definitely worth the wait, the time and money.',64);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',861,'2017-06-11',5,'Wow! Â I love sushi and most things Japanese (Hello Kitty...Im still not sure). Â Carlo, Melvin & crew create dishes that are edible poetry.In San Diego, there is Tanaka. Â In Vegas, Roku. Â San Francisco has Akiko. Â And finally, Chicago has a restaurant that competes and excels.Make reservations, and just go with the Omakase, if you are uncertain. Â But really, you cant go wrong. Â Its just magic for your eyes and in your mouth.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',1374,'2016-01-11',5,'Random date night here. Ambiance 5/5 We went on a weekday and early (around 6PM) and no wait. Normally youll need a reservation. Decor is beautiful and private if you dont sit by the bar. Though for Omakase I kinda wished we get to see the chef at work. Â Taste 4/5I had the basic Omakase and I believe it is very good value for $65. We had Omakase twice the price and yet Kai Zan is on par, to be honest. We especially enjoyed the nigiri. Price 4/5Like mentioned above, very good value and not out of the world. Cant beat the little sushi shops in LA-Little Tokyo for price-quality ratio but Ill take it for Chicago.Service 5/5Wait staff are all knowledgeable and friendly. 20% tips for sure!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',1222,'2017-03-01',5,'I had the pleasure to return to the exquisite Kai Zan. Last time I got the $100 Chefs Omakase and it was the best meal Ive ever experienced. This time we opted for the $60 since we had a bigger group. I havent sat in the booths before now and I really enjoyed it, cozy and cute. Would definitely recommend being in the other dining room so you can see the chef at work, bar preferably. We had to make a reservation a week or so ahead of time. The wait staff is always great and did great considering all of the plate changes for 5 people getting the omakase. If you arent sure if the extra $40 is worth it, trust me I was there too. Honestly, this is the most expensive meal Ive had but this splurge smacks your taste buds in the face! Im not a fan of Uni and the kitchen was also so nice by offering me a different choice or more of something else when Uni was called for. Our waitress recommended the 2012 Weissburgunder white wine, it had hints of butter and that isnt a bad thing! Our group enjoyed two bottles. We will definitely be back this year, I hope, to get the $100 meal again!We tried the dessert a couple times and just havent liked them too much, I had the chocolate sesame one and wont get it again. The $100 comes with a dessert but you probably wont have room anyway for dessert after the $60 Omakase either. Recommendations- This meal can be very filling so eat a smaller lunch if possible, a couple ladies in our group were getting pretty full about 70% into the meal.- Get seating in the main dining room, makes a huge difference being right there!- Reservations ahead of time.- Just go with it! I didnt know half of the things I was eating but I sure remember them every time I think of this place. - Even if you arent a sushi person, honestly I am not a huge one either, this place isnt just sashimi and rolls. They put so much into each of these dishes and has kind of ruined me for the rest of my life LOL....',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula35188',1456,'2016-09-19',4,'Went there with my dad for the Omakase (Chefs choice 10-course meal) $65 each. Considering this is in Chicago, what a great deal for the amount of food and quality you receive! Reservations were easy to place online (open table) and we had a private dining nook that looked like it could fit up to 6 people! We also got the wagyu beef which was partially seared with heart leaf, scallions, wasabi, spicy ponzu, black tobiko and jalapeÃ±o. Â This was by far my favorite. The 10-course meal definitely fills you up! Trust me, Im a girl who can EAT! The only thing I wish I suggested, was for the sashimi to come out first. By the end of the meal, the beautifully cut pieces of fish were served like an afterthought and my palate was saturated in all the other flavors by then. As a small restaurant in Chicagos Ukrainian Village, this is definitely somewhere that you need to try. Â Im definitely returning when I get the chance!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('morbi7160',153,'2016-10-27',5,'Kai Zan is it. Some of the most creative dishes Ive eaten. If you have around 4 or 5 people you can get seated in these cozy booths on the left hand side of the restaurant so I would recommend inviting friends. Regular omakase runs 65 dollars, chefs special omakase is more pricey (around 100-120 depending on ingredients) and both are great choices depending on your budget.Last time we visited our server recommended we do 1 order of omakase for 2 people, with a 15 dollar upcharge and this might be the way to go, because then you can go wild on other menu items or specials not included in the omakase. Sake and beer selections are on point. They have a salted ale, try it! Service has always been impeccable so its perfect for a special evening.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',970,'2022-02-06',5,'Im from Chicago and a big foodie and Ive heard tons of hype. And Im happy to say this place lives up to it!-modern and trendy, but still intimate atmosphere (definitely great for a date you want to look impressive on)-we sat at the bar which I think was best spot--could see all the action and got to talk to the two owners and get their recs!-sushi was absolutely delicious--Im salivating just thinking about it-lots of uni dishes--and it was fantastic and fresh uni -beautiful presentation--very artfully doneDefinitely have to go back soon!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('velit8725',257,'2019-08-02',4,'Kai Zan will forever change the way you view Sushi. This restaurant exceeds expectations in every way possible, from the time youre greeted by the host until you leave, everything is A+++.The staff is nothing short of amazing. While you are in the presence of the two most amazing Sushi Chefs (Melvin and Carlo) on earth, you also have the opportunity to meet a extremely friendly and personable line up of hosts and wait staff. Every single one of them ensures that your experience is unforgettable. Ive been coming here regularly for about 2 years now (at least once a week) and truly feel as if I am part of the Kai Zan family, its unlike any connection I have ever had with any other restaurant.Now lets get to the good stuff...aka what you MUST order. Just to start off, Ive virtually tried just about every single dish on the menu and can confidently say, its all amazing. Not only is every dish unique, well thought through and different from Â  other common sushi spots, but the QUALITY of the ingredients used is a huge difference maker. Melvin and Carlo will only serve you the highest quality of fish/seafood and if they are unable to source ingredients that meet their expectations, well then it wont be on the menu (specifically Uni).Personal favorites and must try listEscolar Pearls-I wish they offered a bottomless special of this dish, the first time I tried these I ordered them 3 times...stop judging me.Maguro Pearls-A close 2nd to the Escolar Pearls, absolutely incredible.Dynamite Mussels-Personally, I had a strong dislike of the texture of mussels my entire life, until the Chefs recommended I try them....theyre unlike any mussels youll ever have and an absolute must order-the flavor is mind blowing!Angry Crab-I recommend getting these as hand rolls (not on the menu), it is hands down the best hand roll you will ever eat in your entire life, dont take my word for it, try it and I guarantee you will order at least 2 during your meal.Uni Toro Tartare Special-If they have Uni, they will most likely offer this special. I recommend you order this because its unlike any dish you will ever eat anywhere else. You receive a beautifully presented dish with Uni, Toro, Pickled Wasabi and a Qual Egg on top (theres more in there...trust me) which you mix up and then create your own rolls of goodness with....this one is arguably my favorite dish all together, ever!Green Monster-This roll is presented beautifully, its a avocado wrapped roll that is second to none and extremely delicious!Polenta Bites-Another creation that is over the top. Its simple, but the flavor is HUGE!King Oyster Mushroom-Unlike any mushroom dish you will ever taste in your life. The consistency and flavor if this make it hard to believe youre eating a mushroom skewer!All of their shooters are amazing but the Uni Shooter is my favorite. The concept is actually not something I generally would enjoy but after having tried all of them I can now understand why they are so popular!I recommend always getting any and all specials they have, these are always the absolute BEST and AMAZING creations. You will never want to miss out on these. If you show your face often enough, you may even get lucky from time to time and have them re-created....only if youre lucky though!I recommend you sit at the Sushi Bar if you have the ability to, watching the Chefs in action adds to the experience. They are all very friendly, outgoing and are fun to watch as they create greatness!Thank you Kai Zan for coming into my life, I will forever be indebted to you for changing the way I look at not only Sushi, but dining experiences all together! It goes without saying, I am your biggest fan and look forward to many more evenings spent in your beautiful restaurant in the first two seats at the Sushi Bar (as always!). (If I had the ability to give this review 5 more stars, I would....)',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('morbi7160',1054,'2017-03-29',5,'What an unexpected find! I was visiting Chicago for the weekend and a friend recommended this as her absolute fave sushi spot. As a New Yorker and someone who eats sushi daily I took her up on it!The omakase was phenomenal- creative and tasty. Our group was 6 so they actually recommended we get 3 omakase to share (they increased each course to 6 pieces) and also ordered some popular items on the menu. To me the winners were the polenta bites (with fried kale!) and the Madai with olive oil. I didnt love the scallop shooters as much as I though I would. Service was on point and Im pretty sure we stayed beyond the allotted timeframe given we were a larger group.Would definitely return next time Im in Chicago',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',132,'2018-04-05',5,'Yup...the best sushi ever.Its all been said...just go.I loved the decor. Â The private booths are fantastic.The food was plenty and amazing!!!I loved everything about this place except its distance from my house.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',1052,'2016-04-22',4,'In my opinion Kai Zan is most authentic Japanese restaurant in Chicago - love that place! I do like their sushi options more then their cooked diners. Great sashimi and sushi appetizers. Fish always fresh and tasty. Wish they would open another location -down town Chicago. They get booked easily so if you planing on going - call ahead to make reservations. Service also top notch - great job kai zan !!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',1334,'2017-04-09',5,'Walked in tonight, no reservation, and was lucky enough to score two seats at sushi bar being that there was a cancellation. Note to self make reservations on weekends. Hostess was very sweet and sat us down quickly. Received great service as well. Totally hidden treasure with a cool intimate vibe. Great quality fish. Love the Maguro Pearls, dynamite mussels, and make sure to order their special fried rice. Delish!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',1093,'2020-01-18',5,'We were late 10 mins for our reservation due to the crazy traffic and they told us they can only serve one omakase for us. The food here all tastes the same. Adding some mayo, some soy sauce, thats it. The price is lower than normal omakase, but its disappointing in taste.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in63197',1086,'2020-05-03',5,'I took my fiancÃ© here for his graduation dinner and we both enjoyed the chefs choice premium omakase. The food tasted exceptional, however I got VIOLENTLY ILL from the food here. I reported it as food poisoning and they said that was not possible since my fiancÃ© ate the same thing and didnt get sick. There was little to no apology. I recently had an allergist appointment and asked them to test a few things specifically because I thought that may have caused my illness but all of the tests came back normal. Ive had food poisoning before and am still certain thats what it was, considering the timing, food, and reaction. Unfortunately they never contacted me again, and my $300 dinner was definitely not worth it. Such a disappointment.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',1680,'2016-01-31',5,'Kai Zan is what I love most about food in Chicago. You have an unassuming place off the beaten path with amazing food.We had the omakase (courses selected by the chef) which I highly recommend. With 10 courses, I was excited to see what the next course would be. Each dish was creative and thoughtful. I appreciate that they take the time to explain each dish as they serve it. Everything was exquisite! Â The service was also great which can be hard to find at sushi restaurants. This is hands down the best sushi I have had.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',414,'2021-11-13',5,'Oh man! Â What a phenomenal meal. We went for a birthday dinner and had the omakase. Both of them. The original one and the new one. We sat at the bar and watched Melvin and Carlo prepare not just our meal, but everyone elses as well. The precision and attention to detail of gear guys is fun to watch. Everything that came our way (19 courses in all) was creative, beautifully plated and delicious. The best Asian (not just Japanese) restaurant in Chicago. Period. Anchovy ice cream. Who thinks of that? Â These guys did. All you can say is ',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede20152',1220,'2020-03-22',4,'Probably one of the more fun, inventive restaurants in Chicago. I have literally never had one bad meal there.Get the tasting menu your first time, then order off the regular menu... they take uni especially serious here, and it shows.Highly recommend the pearls and the carpaccio!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',1512,'2016-12-10',5,'100 stars!! Â Hands down the best sushi we have ever had! We sat at the sushi bar and watched as the brothers worked - truly an awe inspiring and insanely delicious experience! We cannot wait to go back!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',1011,'2016-01-28',5,'I think Ive had the sushi once or twice here. Honestly I love their little side appetizers more than the sushi though! My most recent visit my wife & I had the wasabi tater tots. Oh merrr gosh!! They were soooo good. Definitely get here early because they get insanely packed instantly. I totally love this neighborhood gem!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',1505,'2019-04-01',4,'Literally had no idea where my boyfriend was taking me for our Valentines day and was pleasantly surprised to find out this really unassuming restaurant has the BEST sushi Ive had in my life! Very creative omakase options! I had the regular prepared menu omakase and he had the premium. Both were super awesome but the premium is definitely worth the extra $$. That dessert at the end with the smoked ice cream was out of this world! Thanks for a great night!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yyy19',1025,'2016-11-02',5,'I decided to go for solo dining on my birthday and went to Kai Zan and tried their famous Omakase. IT WAS FANTASTIC!Every course they served was a piece of art. A couple of them that tickled all my senses were the shooters (I can still taste and feel this one. Just amazing!) Â and the scallop wrapped with salmon (heaven in my mouth) I wish I know all of their names, but its best to leave the excitement for first timers. Their fish is fresh and very, very good. Definitely a must try!I sat at the bar, good choice to watch the chefs work their magic. Service was perfect, very comfortable. The place has a nice, quiet ambiance with the right amount of noise.For the price of their very delicious Omakase, its THE best deal. The place is not as fancy but they obviously put all their pride and excellence in their magnificent dishes.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',85,'2019-07-05',5,'After the raving review and recommendation of a friend, my wife and I tried this place out. The food didnt disappoint. We had the omakase and holy shit, we loved a few of those dishes so much. Wed go back for the Orange Rush and pork belly any day of the week. We also added some Wagyu, which was alright.. cooked a little too long.. and was a bit too thick, but still tasty. The only real knocks Id give is that a couple servers need to chill.. or unchill. Far too serious vibes.. whispery talking.. fake voice stuff. We would rather just have the food placed down and no awkward explanations, which we can read on the menu anyway. Also, we felt a bit rushed to eat. Give some time in between the meals. I felt like was choking my plate down just to have the next one placed in front of me.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',174,'2017-06-19',4,'I dont know where to start. The best sushi Ive had to this day. I was at a Michelin star sushi restaurant couple months before, but Kai Zan truly blew me away.Our server, Arlene, was phenomenal. Wonderful personality, knowledgeable and make great recommendations. We sat at the bar so that my husband could go with the omakase option. My husband cannot stop talking about the following oxtail soup, wagyu beef wrapped scallop, quail egg/scallop shooter and the quality/grade of the sushi in general. He said it was the best uni and mackeral hes ever had. They also had a wonderful selection of craft beers from Japan.We had THREE dessert dishes if you can believe it. Pumpkin ice cream crumble, Mochi ice cream and the refreshing green tea matcha ice cream.Please be sure to make a reservation and be on time so you have the full 90 minutes to enjoy your meal.Thank you for such a great experience and meal. We cant wait to return!!!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',904,'2020-05-19',5,'Best sushi hands down in Chicago. Any time we have visitors coming to town it is our first stop. The service is perfect as well as the sushi. We no longer even look at the menu and just ask the server to bring whatever he/she recommends. This place never disappoints the only thing I can say is it has ruined eating sushi anywhere else because it never compares to sushi at Kai Zan',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nam3954',107,'2020-03-06',5,'The best.We came here after my husbands coworker highly recommended it as the best sushi in Chicago. A casual Wednesday dinner we told ourselves. Hah.We didnt know much and decided we should try it tonight. When my husband tried to make reservations, he said open table didnt have much. I figured I could call later and try and see what we could get. Maybe its more walk-in?First interaction with the restaurant was exceptional. I didnt catch her name but the young lady who spoke to me was polite, patient and so so so helpful. For some reason when a hostess is like this at a busy place, Im happily surprised. But impressed. She informed me they were booked solid, but just in case someone cancelled she took down my name, number and time of choice. 30 minutes later she called me with a cancellation and offered me the spot. I took it. Then a torrential downpour hit and getting home from work was impossible, let alone to dinner. 50 minutes of driving later (river north to west loop to Kaizan) we rolled in a little wet and super hungry, 20 minutes late.Regardless of our delay, the same young lady checked in on us via phone while we parked and gently let us know they had reservations after us. We promised we would be out and completely understood. She was kind and patient with us as we walked in, slightly soaked. We were seated at the bar, and boy am I happy we were. This is no ordinary sushi spot. You are across from the action. Creative plates, focus, genius. I watched as twin chefs Melvin and Carlos plated each dish, more enticing than the next. It took all my will power to not sneakily chop stick pieces off the plates. Or steal some of Chef Ms white bottled sake (shhhhh).We had an attentive, warm, nice server - Brian. So genuinely into the food. The service is top notch, unpretentious and wonderful. Chef Carlos even gave us this polenta dish that was taste bud heaven. I love the people who work here.What did we eat? Edamame, shishito peppers, our first uni experience - nigiri style, white tuna (requested raw) pearls, hamachi nigiri (raw), beef skewer, sashimi trio of toro, salmon belly, an in season fish I cant recall but delicious, polenta gift fish (omg), angry crab, and a bottle of hot sake to compliment. I may have missed something but I couldve eaten more! Yum.I cant wait to go back. Im doing the omakase and requesting bar seating. Raw fish perfection. There is a reason on a night like tonight (flooding, winds, darkness) this place was booked solid. Its beyond. Go spoil yourself.Wow. Thank you.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mollis81165',259,'2016-06-01',5,'Kai Zan is one of the better places in the Chicago area where you can eat fresh sashimi. This is my second time eating here and I enjoyed my experience thoroughly. The service here is very fast, probably because you only have a set amount of time to dine. For two people, I believe it is around ninety minutes to finish your meal before you have to leave.I ordered omakase both times I came here and noticed that a few menu items had changed. I was excited to see that this time, the orange rush was incorporated into the omakase menu. This was one of my favorite dishes that I had ordered a la carte the first time, but it added a hefty $10 to my bill. Overall, I thought the omakase menu allowed you to get a nice taste of many different items, however, not all of the dishes wowed me. My favorites were the escolar pearls and orange rush. Some misses for me were the oyster/scallop shooters (Im not a fan of shooters) and char siu (which was a bit too tough for me to enjoy). I also ordered the uni hand-roll (not on the omakase menu) which looked spectacular, but for $28 I felt that it was a bit underwhelming. The uni was very fresh, however, and was a nice touch.Make sure you save room for dessert! I almost think that the house-made desserts are better than the fish...! The green tea ice cream had an extremely strong green tea flavor which I loved. It did not taste artificial at all like many other green tea ice creams. The chocolate lava cake was pretty good as well and was a nice contrast to the ice cream.If you just order omakase, the bill ends up being a bit over $80 per person which is certainly not cheap. I think it is a reasonable price for what you get and it is less expensive than what you would pay for a tasting menu at some other restaurants. Omakase was good, but some of the dishes were misses for me simply because I was not a fan of the ingredients. If I came back in the future, I would definitely order a la carte so that I can get foods that are more suited for my taste.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt58127',1431,'2021-04-29',5,'Excellent omakase. A lot of variety and creation, a lot of food as well (almost too much) for 65$ which is actually cheap considering the quality of the food and of the service. We also tried a creme brulee and it was delicious. Just be advised that most of the plates are spicy. Definitely would go back if I come back to Chicago )',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',69,'2017-01-22',5,'Love this place. Its one of the few places Id go and eat by myself. Because the food is so good that I think talking to a friend while eating is a waste of time. Service is awesome, great ambience. There are hundreds of Japanese restaurants in Chicago, Kai Zan is the only place that masters almost every dish on the menu, except their soup is a little bit salty. If its your first time visit, go with omakase, you can almost everything popular from the menu. The individual dish size appears small, however, with 5-6 dishes combined, its really filling.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',512,'2020-04-08',4,'Simply amazing!!! The food was spectacular. The flavor combinations and the freshness is unmatched. It took a long time to finally get better and Im sooo happy I had the opportunity. The service was great as well. Absolutely loved every dish (we did chefs choice for $69) except the soup course. It wasnt bad - could have used a little salt, but everything else was much better. It was a superb dining experience!!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',444,'2019-01-07',4,'Oh my! Oh my, oh my, oh my! So 5 friends & I had an Omakase (leaving your food selections for the evening up to the chef) experience here last night and it was other-worldly. The decor was simple, yet elegant, and I was loving the privacy of the reserved dining booths. Definitely make reservations WELL in advance for this glorious gem! We all (6 grown adults) found ourselves doing the happy, delicious, yummy food dance several times throughout the night here. Yep, imagine 6 30-*mer*-something year olds swaying & bouncing in their seats like theyre a pack of 6 year olds that have just successfully chased down the ice cream truck, with their first allowance, & theyve just had a taste of their very first Dreamsicle. Each succulent bite here packs more umami than the next! The sauces, the flavors, the quality of the sea fare & how it is prepared; all an expertly well-composed ballet of a uniquely palette-pleasing experience. Ok so you can continue to sit there reading about me gushing about this place....or you can go experience it for yourself.Well....what are you waiting for?',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',187,'2019-08-19',5,'The omakase is an absolute experience. Make sure you show up early as youll need 2 hours for all the courses',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',1136,'2019-11-12',3,'We had the omakase. The food was fantastic but too much. Â I was too full to even try the last couple of dishes. Â My husband couldnt either and he usually can eat very large amounts and always finishes what I cant. If the dishes were smaller this would be perfect. Â The place was pretty packed so obviously popular and we did like sitting at the counter. Â The sushi chefs were friendly and talkative. Â We will go back and try it again. Â The courses I was able to eat were inventive and tasty.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curabitur44172',1216,'2021-05-13',5,'3.5* The food was good, but dont expect any wild surprising ingredients.I went for the omakase and was seated at the sushi counter. The chefs are a bit too busy so they dont interact with you at all, which is fine but I wasnt expecting that. Â Each course was solid, but didnt seem to have a logical progression all the time (eg seared wagyu beef served nigiri style was followed by salmon/tuna sashimi).I also felt rushed by staff by the end of my meal although two thirds of the restaurant was still occupied by customers. They also forgot the dessert because they were trying to close down the kitchen.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',60,'2020-10-27',5,'Yes this place lives up to the hype. Make sure you make reservations. Everything about the dining experience is on point taste, presentation, service, ambiance etc. and the liquor side of the menu also impresses. Cant wait to go back.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',378,'2016-09-14',4,'Hands down this is one of the best sushi restaurants I have eaten at in Chicago. We had the premium omakase and the regular omakase for my birthday dinner. Everything was really fresh and nothing tasted off. In fact, this is the only sushi restaurant that has made me like uni and Ive had it twice before this restaurant. I think that the restaurant also does a good job at pairing various flavors since everything came together really well. Not only was the food good but the service was excellent. Everyone was super nice and helpful. We originally planned to go with the premium omakase with doubled up portions however within 15 minutes of the meal we decided that it might not be enough food. I was scared that we werent able to order another omakase seeing as the omakase is timed however the waiter was very accommodating and was able to put in the order for another omakase. Not only was the waitstaff very nice but one of the chefs at the end of the night had acknowledged and talked to us as well since we were sitting at the sushi bar.Unfortunately the only con I had about this place was that the cleanliness is questionable. At the end of the omakase I had eaten a piece of sashimi and it made my stomach hurt and cramp immediately. However, my boyfriend had the same thing and he was fine so I think that my stomach is just sensitive. With that said I would go back again to the restaurant and try the regular menu instead but I do recommend the premium omakase over the regular omakase if you were to choose between the two.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',130,'2019-09-08',5,'4.4Month June 2018Day and time Tuesday eveningFood 4-5 starsWe ordered escolar pearls, maguro pearls, oyster shooters, karaage (fried chicken), braised octopus, the mushroom medley, hamachi collar, and various nigiri. The oysters were refreshing and cleansed the mouth between the competing tastes of the other dishes. All of the fish nigiri were outstanding - the tuna and hamachi were smooth and silky, but the salmon belly rose above them both with its richness. I was a little disappointed with the wagyu beef, both when served on its own and as nigiri. The juices caramelized on the surface of the meat, providing a promising first bite, but the flavor held little longevity. The karaage was ordinary, despite the hope offered by the marinated chicken meat. The hamachi collar was the most popular dish among our table of four, though I preferred the salmon nigiri. It took little encouragement for the white fish to fall from its frame, and even less so for it to melt in the mouth. It was accompanied by a ponzu-scallion sauce and grated daikon radish which brought a welcome salty kick to the otherwise unassuming hamachi. The braised octopus - a special of the day - was lightly-charred and its toughness changed up the texture profile of the evening. We finished our meal with mango mochi, lava cake, and matcha creme brulee. Most dessert lovers could find satisfaction somewhere across the selection, and indeed this dessert skeptic enjoyed sampling all three.Setting & Atmosphere 4-5 starsWe were lucky enough to be seated at one of several large booths along the left wall of the restaurant. We had the utmost privacy - we neither saw nor were seen by other customers during our meal - but the chatter in the air reminded us there were plenty of other lucky souls enjoying their meals too.Drink 4 starsWe each took a beer, and were pleasantly surprised to find the Asahi offered was not the Super Dry but instead the Select amber lager.Service 5 starsI have nothing but compliments for our server, Brian. He knew the menu inside out, offering sensible alternatives where our first choices were unavailable. We ordered several off-menu items on his recommendation, including the show-stealing salmon belly nigiri. Service was attentive, comically so at one point when replacement chopsticks were provided within seconds of a pair falling to the floor.Value 4 starsThe a la carte menu varies in its value-for-money - the daily collar offers an entree-sized amount for cooked fish for ~$14, but you would need to spend 2-3X that on appetizers to feel full. You should go to Kai Zan expecting to spend well for some of the best raw fish in Chicago. With such an approach, the omakase at $65 a head looks outstanding value.Return YesI could return and eat exclusively fish, as the tuna, salmon, and hamachi were the freshest Ive tasted in Chicago. I would like to check out the chefs omakase too - while the chicken and beef play second fiddle to the fish here, they would still be upper quartile across Chicago restaurants.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('volutpat2346',1118,'2019-08-20',5,'Its bad for business fix your food it feels like somebody poisoned it and I never want to eat at this restaurant again',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',1526,'2020-04-02',4,'This was my 3rd dinner restaurant stop during a recent visit to Chicago. Â Its a relatively small restaurant so you must make a reservation and stick to your reserved time because most likely they cant fit you in earlier or too much later - be prompt! Â It is not a totally traditional Japanese restaurant but I do recommend the omakase to eat the best of the best here! Â I loved the mushroom soup, the oyster and uni shooters, the char sui bite and the sashimi (so fresh, love!!) the best. Â They spice up some of their dishes - lets just say the wasabe will clear your sinuses! Â Service was attentive and patiently explained the menu and dishes. Â And I love the decor of this place - you feel like you stepped into a home in a Japanese village. Â Have them call you a taxi if needed after your meal as taxis arent too frequent in this area.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('velit13144',1395,'2017-01-01',5,'Best Japanese restaurant in Chicago! It is innovative but also beautiful traditional sashimi cuts. The Omakase is phenomenal! It was a great experience! Server, host, busser and food runner were extremely well trained and the place is just beautiful. There is literally nothing I could say that they could have done better. Everything was wonderful and we had a great night!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1346,'2021-01-02',5,'Oh man... What an experience! My mouth is watering just thinking about our dinner! My husband and I both ordered Omakase I cant even tell you how impressive our experience was! They give you about 90 minutes to finish your meal, which might sound like not enough time, but the staff at Kai Zan works like a Swiss watch and there is little to no waiting time between the courses. We were seated at the bar and it was an additional bonus as we could watch the chef work his magic! Our server was a delight. I will not go into the details about our food as it was rather complex, layered, with a ton of colors, textures and flavors. Hands down one of the best dinners I had in my life. I think this dinning experience was better than the majority of Michelin rated restaurants that I have been to. I will most definitely be back and recommend this place to everyone! Keep up the good work guys!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',857,'2019-02-13',4,'Let me start by saying Ive been to japan twice, and have friends of japan that cook here in America. So I have a small amount of things to compare this place to.Though a small restaurant for American size, the decor is very nice. It had a Japanese feel, while still having an American feel since the staff is diverse. Music isnt loud, as a matter of fact, I dont know if I actually heard any music at all which is good.This place is amazing. Maybe because we ordered the chefs choice omakase may have something to do it with. Everything was so fresh, and the flavors blended and melded together perfectly. I could taste the layers of rich fat and beef in the wagyu, as well and the hint of wasabi that wasabi microgreens added to the wagyu nigiri we had as one of our sushi nigiri sets. The dashi was also had was flavorful, with just enough salt and the tiny tobiko that popped in my mouth was both fun and good. Lobster mashed potatoes... heaven.I loved every dish my husband and I had. Im not a mackerel eater but the horse-striped mackerel was sweet, tender, and clean tasting. Expensive yes. Worth it, YES. We plan on coming back again and again.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam9757',578,'2016-05-12',5,'I have had all kinds of sushi in all kinds of places. Â This is the best. Â The pre fixe menu is a steal. Â Might be the best meal for the price in the city. You can B your own B if you so choose. Â And everything I ate there was literally the best thing I ate. Â Stop reading. Â Go there now. Â But you might wanna call ahead. Â Getting a table it a bit of a pain.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',788,'2018-09-21',5,'I have so many wonderful things to say about Kai Zan. The food is awesome. One of our favorite places for Japanese weve discovered in Chicago so far. Also, very good value. We had the chefs tasting menu for $60 and that was 10 really generous courses. We were stuffed by the end of it. The service was great. Overall just loved the vibe, the fit-out, the whole experience. We literally left dinner and the next day booked our next dinner here.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',899,'2020-01-29',5,'These reviews dont lie.BEST. SUSHI. EVER.GO. NOW! (Okay theyre temporarily close, but GO as soon as they re-open!)Highly recommend the Chefs Choice/Omaske especially if you like to try a bit of a everything on the menu.What more can I say? Delicious!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem1829',238,'2017-11-30',5,'This was my actual Â first dinner restaurant here in Chicago, IL. My girlfriend and I were here on vacation and my gfs brother recommended this place. We have never been here, but it was a very pleasant and decadent evening. We tried the Premium Omasake, which is a 10 course meal. The last dish was a dessert. The inside of the restaurant is really nice, dimly lit with enough light to make it romantic but not too dark where it would be difficult to navigate around. Every decor matched the Japanese theme and presented itself as a fancy restaurant. My gf and I loved it.The waiter and waiteress were very knowledgeable about each meal because they introduced each dish like it was its own. They presented the dishes with a very good explanation of what we were eating. Even to the simplest thing as refilling our water, they were watching ti make sure we never go thirsty. Our group enjoyed it and we would recommend any tourist (like ourselves from California) to any locals.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',235,'2016-08-22',4,'This food is always the best. Grilled octopus charred and delicious. My husband doesnt eat a lot of meat and every time we go in we get offered a vegetable special for the evening. A little far downtown but a must!!!!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tristique8035',87,'2020-05-21',5,'The WORST restaurant experience I have had in a long time. Now service, as a whole, in Chicago restaurants has been lacking but this place takes the cake.After refusing to honor a reservation request for the reservation we made months prior, we were sat at the sushi bar and hurried into deciding on the omakase menu.Each dish was rushed from the start. After barely taking the last bite the next course was dropped in front of us. Food was fine, nothing you cant find at the million other sushi restaurants in town. Fish was fresh but they kept deciding to cover it with spicy mayo or even worse burning it with the Â torch that gives everything a bitter butane flavor. A couple dishes were so bad we didnt even finish them (defrosted New Zealand mussel course & squid salad - Im talking to you)Finally halfway through the final course we are brought our bill and told our time was up. Excuse me?! YOU set the omakase menu, YOU set the pace of the courses and then IM told I need to leave before Im finished?!Dont offer a 10 course tasting menu if YOU cant serve it in the 90 min. time limit YOU set.Kai Zan can get bent. Ill be taking my money elsewhere and never recommending this place to anyone.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',417,'2018-11-13',5,'I came here a few years ago and had the regular omakase. This time around I got the chefs special omakase- more expensive, but definitely worth it. Great food, service and atmosphere!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',1188,'2017-12-10',4,'This was our first omakase experience and oh boy, it lived up to the hype. Our server, Justin was incredible and made sure we were well taken care of. All of the items in the 10 course premium omakase menu we chose were phenomenal and we would order again.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rhoncus2633',1015,'2018-02-07',5,'Great, fresh seafood! Definitely the best sushi Ive ever had! We got the omakase for two people (add $20) and enjoyed it very much! The only complaint was that we got way too much food. We got to meet a chef as he was walking around after the sushi bar had closed and he was really nice and personable. Although we were not able to, definitely try to sit at the bar! The omakase is also really adaptable for certain tastes! The waiter saw that we didnt enjoy the shooters (not a big fan of raw eggs) so he gave us a complimentary replacement to make sure that we would enjoy all 10 courses to the omakase. Definitely must try restaurant with great service! Tip make sure to reserve early to get a good time to eat. We didnt reserve early enough so we had a late, 930 dinner.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',1693,'2022-02-22',5,'Shared one order of Omakase $65 with several add-on dishes )! Staffs are amazing, and foods are de-lio-cious!!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',351,'2016-07-30',4,'Shhhhh....Psst! Â I have a secret to tell you This is Da Bestest Sushi in Chicago! Â Truthfully, I am reluctant to share their GREAT review because it is already so hard to get reservations. Â  Â But its about my peeps! my fans! about YOU! Â not me ) . Â  So lets be real, there are many good to okay sushi places in Chicago. Â   Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â   Â  Â But often they are a forgettable experience. Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â   Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â PG-13 review warning  Â  Â Cmon now, were talking about raw fish; often not much to the flavor profile to distinguish itself from other places. Â  Â So often with sushi places is the D-Test (the question about raw fish), did I get sick afterwards (D test , as in Diarrhea ) or not?!!) . Â  Â  Â Obviously the bad places means bad fish ......Back to Kai Zan The creativity, the rice, the sauces, the taste, the combinations and the service. Â  Â Mmm, mmm GREAT. Â  Had the omakase prix fixed menu @ $65 each. Â  Reasonable. Yummy. Quickly served. Â  Â  Tues and Weds they have an early bird special for $35 each. Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â Be sure to note the address because signage is very hard to see. Â  But like some other top places (Alinea), poor signage doesnt matter because so many people go there already or look for it! Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  ................So remember this place is our little secret !',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dis16196',1124,'2017-11-15',5,'The omakase is a great deal. Â Regular is $60 for 10 of their best house dishes. Supreme omakase is $130 for 11 off the menu courses, extra course was a sushi roll the night we went. Â Every dish took a lot of care to put all the ingredients together and was perfectly plated. Â Hence the gazillion pic on yelp as any amateur can take a good pic of this food. Â It sells itself. Â Really enjoyed the Waygu beef and they boiled their lettuce in dashi broth, so tasty. Â  Thank you for doing such an excellent job in combining all the flavors and yet without having to resort to sweetness, something many restaurants overdo unnecessarily before dessert course. Â You get 90 min for your seating so be prepared to eat each course in 7 min, 8 tops if you are doing omakase. Â To keep the prices so reasonable, they have to serve multiple seatings nightly. Â Extensive sake menu and reasonably priced wine offering. Â Superb staff who knows their dishes well and are very courteous. Â Will definitely be back.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1685,'2020-04-25',5,'Best sushi in chicago. Get the pearls and the angry crab. Also get angry crab as a handroll. Best thing ever.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a22154',8,'2016-01-07',5,'I dont know what is the hype. The presentation is pretty but food quality is just so so.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',529,'2016-08-03',4,'Amazing service, fantastic and creativity by two wonderful sushi chefs.Great and very intimate. Was very impressed by the presentation and quality of the sushi, and would definitely come back again.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',387,'2019-01-07',5,'Such a unique experience. Definitely recommend doing the omakase. Its $60 and we added uni for $5 more (worth it). Make sure you make a reservation. I did feel like some of the courses came out too fast, wouldve liked a slower pace but overall deliciousness makes it worth it. $15 corkage fee is a nice too. We ordered a separate dessert. It was the charred squash or deconstructed pumpkin pie as they called it. It was the only thing that night that didnt knock our socks off. Would probably opt for dessert elsewhere after trying it. Overall some of the highest quality sushi available in Chicago and a fun dining experience if youre looking for a pri fixe dining option.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('morbi7160',363,'2021-03-15',5,'The bf and I came here for the $65 omakase. Man the chef really knows how to pair flavors together. Everything we had was amazing. From the first course to the last, everything was delicious and well worth it. Id have to admit, I thought I was going to leave hungry so I did eat a snack before going to Kai Zan and by the 3rd course, I was already feeling full. That was a bad idea to snack beforehand. I would definitely recommend this place and you cant beat that price!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',260,'2017-11-11',4,'Amazing sushi! Â Hands down get the OMAKASE! Â It has samples of their most popular sushi. Â You cant go wrong with the OMAKASE. Â My favs on the OMAKASE menu1). My mouth fell in love with the ESCOLAR & MAGURO PEARLS. Â Seriously the escolar was silky and buttery. Â The pan seared tuna was perfect. Â I couldnt stop smiling when I took the bite. Â The pearls are so tiny, and they pop when you bite on them . Â 2) Fiesta MAKI... Get this. Â The salmon and tuna all work well with the cilantro, masago, chili oil... Oh gosh I seriously want two rolls to myself. Â You definitely dont want to share this with anyone! Â Not even with Grandma!!!3). Orange Rush ... That citrus glaze is refreshing. Â I didnt think it would work with sushi, but it does . Â 4). Madai Caraccio... Light and refreshing. Â A taste of Italy ... It reminds me of a Caprese Salad. Â For drinks I tried the pear sake. Â It was good.Sooo DO THE OMAKASE already! Â You cant go wrong with it!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo41119',1741,'2018-09-27',5,'I CANT EVEN Was gonna go for Sepia but changed our mind last minute and was lucky enough to get reservation at 530 on a Saturday. I am sure Sepia is great and all but oh was this one of the best choices I have ever made in life. Definitely go with chefs choice. 10 courses meal for $60, you get to taste quite a few of the signature dishes on the Manu. It was very hard to pick my favorite but the pearls were impeccable. We ordered one tasting menu and a couple more dishes to share, we were both very full by the end of it. As a girl, I would have been overly stuffed if I ordered my own tasting course. Our server was great. Helpful and friendly but not overwhelming. Food comes out very fast, one after another so you dont need to worry about spending 3 hours there. Still an amazing amazing experience tho dont get me wrong. Everything is just perfect. The food is to die for and the service was just on point. I wouldnt have dreamed for a better anniversary dinner. Damn.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat4359',821,'2016-01-04',5,'My favorite restaurant ever. Best sushi in Chicago. Must get polenta bites, ami ebi sashimi, spicy tuna handrolls.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ultrices32193',1695,'2016-09-28',5,'Absolutely incredible food! I actually do not recommend the Omakase, instead go al a carte so you can pick the types of flavors you like (I tried both options). Favorite dishesThe escarole pearls Wagyu beef sushi - to die for Belly salmon Polenta bites Only down side is the place is super small and can be tough to get comfortable. But overall the service is good and they have the best sushi in Chicago!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',1267,'2019-11-13',5,'Not much to say here except that this was the best meal Ive had in a couple years! Â Just go there and get the Chefs Okakase, dont even look at the menu. Â Everything from presentation to quality to flavor is top notch.. I mean 5 star BID! Â Inside is definitely cool with some semi-private booths on the one side/ sushi bar on the other. Â Service was great and I like the fact that the waiters/ waitresses switch off.. so if you dont like the first waiter dont be discouraged! Â Definitely one the best sushi joints in Chicago.. talk later PS- Dont forget the chocolate lava cake with black sesame ice cream! Mind blowing',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',113,'2021-03-23',4,'My girlfriend and I went there to celebrate my birthday. We understood that we could sit at the bar even we made the reservation. But we were sitted at the bar with a frying pot in our face, so we were surrounded in oily smelly and felt like getting fried the whole night. This was the major down.We ordered omakase each of us. Food were good and delicately prepared. Escolar and salmon were to very high standard. Shooter is something you definitely have to try even you dont go with omakase. The downside of food is the variety of seafood you tasted with ~10 courses are quite limited. I felt the third to last dishes (some xxx maki with salmon and tuna) were served as nothing more than stomach fillers. I would be more satisfied if they replaced that one with 2 pieces of sahimi.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',374,'2019-05-25',5,'Hands down best sushi Ive ever had!! Thats coming from a girl who loves her sushi/has tried sushi from pretty much all over. I cant imagine sushi getting any better than this. The flavors were amazing. Every bite was perfect. And it takes literally 2 minutes for the first dish to come out (we did the chefs pre-coursed menu). Really just cant stress enough how great this place is.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',1451,'2020-04-15',5,'Hands down my favorite sushi restaurant yet!!!Ive been to Kai Zan a hand-full of times and each time I felt very well taken care both because the service was so great and because the sushi was Amazing!!!Twice Ive sat at the sushi bar, which was really fun because the chefs would surprise us with dishes they thought we must try along with our original order! Ive also had the omakase, which was incredible especially in a larger group because then you can see how everyone else experiences each dish!From the pearls to the orange rush to anything on the secret menu is to die for!!!And...while this isnt the cheapest meal...it is worth every penny!!!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',115,'2020-11-30',4,'This is my favorite treat yoself sushi places. The chefs do a beautiful job on presentation, creativity and taste with all their dishes.We went with a group of four and did two premium and two regular omakase (tasting menu). They were both amazing! The premium is expensive but its worth a try and/or to do it for a special occasion. I believe the regular omakase doesnt change too frequently (I remember some of the Â dishes from doing it before) but the premium was such a fun experience. We got to try a lot of different new ingredients and combinations. I have provided pictures to give you an idea of how beautiful the food is.The private seating is nice option to have when you go with a small group.The service was great! The chefs came to greet us and were very personable.The whole experience is one that I will not forget!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',1362,'2020-07-27',5,'I would absolutely recommend the chefs tasting! $65 for 10 delicious and creative courses! I was expecting maybe one or two bites per course, but they were actually pretty big and filling! We didnt even have room for dessert after. This is definitely the best deal in town! Worth every penny and we will be back! The place is very small and cramped, but we were comfortable! Make sure you make a reservation!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',134,'2020-01-01',5,'Im not a sushi lover and before Kai Zan, I could have gone the rest of my life and never eaten sushi again and I would have been A-okay with it. I will say now that I am a sushi lover and Kai Zan is drool worthy. Have I had sushi before? Plenty of times. Im half Japanese, Ive had it my whole life and it was always just whatever, it was good but I never cared if I had it and I certainly never craved it. Kai Zan makes me CRAVE sushi and their fish is out of this world, melt in your mouth delicious.....will I be back? Duh. Im pretty sure Ive tried almost everything on the menu and what I can say is that its flavorful and you dont need soy or hot sauce. Everything is executed to perfection and the flavors are explosively delicious. Holy crap, I need a napkin to wipe the drool from the corner of my mouth just thinking about my several experiences there. Go, go, go to Kai Zan. Favorites?Angry crab, orange rush, escolar pearls, otoro, seguro, their specials are always on point, anything with scallops....the grill seared tuna....I mean, you could literally pick menu items blindly and not be disappointed with anything (Except uni. I hate uni) but if you love it, Im sure theirs is the best you can get. If they can make me love everything else except uni, holy crap, job well done. This is the only place I will ever eat sushi from again as nothing else is comparable or even close. Bravo Kai Zan. Bravo.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',251,'2019-10-18',4,'No words to describe Just the best ! Really enjoy everything from great service to amazing food !Thank you for being here in CHITOWN!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae1580',895,'2018-03-22',5,'One of the best places for sushi in Chicago. You wont be disappointed. Â Trust the chef.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit22151',1294,'2020-10-19',5,'Hands down my favorite sushi place in Chicago. You need to go at least once if you have not. Its small and a casual vibe. But the food is phenomenal.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',1475,'2018-08-13',4,'Went here for my birthday dinner based on the awesome reviews and we were not as impressed. Â It was difficult to find the restaurant since the windows advertise tattoos. Â When I finally spotted it, parking was easy to find.We had a reservation and were seated immediately. Â However, I was disappointed we were seated at the bar. But, the restaurant is BYOB so we popped open a bottle and began to drink (after paying Â $5 corkage fee per bottle).We decided against the Chefs Choice meal. Â It sounded like too much food and there were some courses I did not like. Â So we ordered individual items. Â All of the food was delicious and fresh. Â I did not eat anything I did not like.I am still bitter that they crammed us into the bar when we had a reservation and it was my birthday. Â There were some cozy looking tables and I was envious.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1420,'2019-07-02',5,'This place serves american style sushi (not traditional Japanese sushi). However, for 10-courses omakase plus complimentary chef creation for the first course at the price of $60, I cant complain, thats why I give it a 4 star rating.My favorites are Madai Carpaccio and Shooters. The Tuna Dashi tastes like nothing more than salt water soup. The Fiesta Maki and Dynamite Mussels taste average (nothing special about them).The service was really fast, the server keep serving the next food without giving you time to enjoy your meal.Overall, it needs improvement, but still good.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',427,'2019-10-05',5,'I dont want to gush here but....oooommmmgggg. This place was So. Damn. Good. We tried the Omakase Menu which consisted of 10 chef selected courses. My experience at Kai Zan was a stellar mix of high quality ingredients, and the creativity of the outstanding chefs. Each course was unique, inventive and surprising. Between courses I found myself getting excited to see what was coming next. I honestly loved everything that I tried, but some of the standouts for me were the oyster and uni shooters with raw quail egg, the dynamite muscles and the extremely high quality sashimi. No question this is the best sushi experience I have had in Chicago. Â I will say that this experience is probably not for sushi beginners. But if you already have sushi in your heart, run dont walk to Kai Zan and order the Omakase Menu.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec5093',1116,'2016-01-07',4,'What a great find here! Came here for an early dinner with my husband and the restaurant became packed really fast so make sure to make a reservation. Its a cozy atmosphere. Service got a little wacky at times cuz our server would disappear or get held up at another table but no big deal because in the end the taste of the food trumped everything. Out of our drinks the yuzu salt beer was memorable. Refreshing and taste just like it says. My husband and ordered the premium omakase which was such a great experience. We got to first enjoy the food with our eyes cuz the food is so colorful and plated so nicely. But tasting the food was amazing. My husband got a couple extra dishes from the main menu which tasted fine but we highly recommend the premium omakase. The components of each dish went really well together and it never felt like they tried too hard or too much. Â It all just tasted perfect. We will miss this place when we go back to NYC.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',542,'2020-05-03',5,'Such a delightful experience. The sashimi was just buttery melt in your mouth luxe. I agree with an earlier review that the sashimi should come out earlier because by the time we got to it I was pretty full. Â We finished with the taro mochi which was also super tasty -- not too sweet, interesting flavor and a light citrus finish. We were seated at Â the bar so got to enjoy watch Carlo and Melvin do their magic. Ready to return.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',1644,'2021-10-16',5,'Best Omakase Ever! I dont know why I didnt listen to everyone else in Chicago and made the trek to Kai Zan sooner. Like seriously, Ive been missing out!!! I could write a book on how amazing it is, but please listen to the masses and come here pronto! Let me say that they have converted me to an uni lover. I have never really been a fan of uni and now I know its because Ive never had truly awesome uni. I love sushi and Ill even tolerate subpar sushi but really this is out of this world amazingly fresh and creatively composed sushi!!! I had their omakase with some food loving friends and now I feel like I can never go back and not get the omakase. Its worth every cent and the chef even added an extra course with an off the menu item that still makes my mouth water when I think about it. Service was amazing. They kept checking on us and explained every course that came out in detail. I have nothing bad to say. This is my new favorite for sushi!!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1671,'2019-11-21',5,'Unnoticeable at first sight, but bars should be like that. Â Its cosy chic, music was playing at a great level; not too loud where you have to shout across the table and not too a awkwardly quiet. Â Heard some Black Keys and Alt-J prior to having a glass of sake. Â Speaking of sake, how come it came in glass flutes instead of the sake cups? Â (sake was delicious nonetheless)Loved the angry crab, maguro pearls, and I think I had the flaming tuna. Â Everything was fresh and the presentation simplistic and beautiful. Â Ill definitely go back to try the rest of the menu and then some. Â Omakase!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',119,'2018-06-03',4,'From quality to presentation, this restaurant was phenomenal. We had the premium omakase and the regular omakase to compare, and the premium one was definitely higher quality. I loved how not only do the dishes taste good, their creativity really shined through as well. Service was great too, our server explained every dish in detail, and even the sushi chef would ask us from time to time how we liked everything. There are 10 dishes to each omakase and I listed the prices below. We would return in the future... Price Premium omakase is $120 Regular omakase is $65.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',1627,'2020-12-25',5,'THIS. PLACE.After eating sushi, seriously, from all over the world, I can assure you this is the highest level of sushi quality I have ever had. The sushi melts in your mouth and left my mother and I in a state of stupor of bliss. If you are reading this review, I recommend to get down to Kai Zan as soon as possible without hesitation. Also sitting at the bar and watching the twins work their undivided magic is a presentation in itself. Art in action and in your mouth.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',477,'2018-12-14',5,'Went here with a bunch of foodie babes and had a delicious blast! The chef had a special menu prepared for us and I just loved everything! I mean no questions asked, just tasted everything they put in front of me and I loved it all!What was my favorite you ask? Well any of the uni dishes of course!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',1551,'2020-11-13',4,'One of the best and most affordable omakase in the city. Comfortable setting, with a great combination of classical technique with modern surprises. My only complaint is that the menu hasnt really changed much over the years Ive been coming here - try new things, do new menus! That would take Kai Zan to the next level.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus31129',1466,'2016-05-01',5,'Best sushi in the city and outrageously well priced omakase.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem1829',862,'2020-03-19',5,'I can honestly say that this was the best meal Ive ever eaten.My boyfriend and I had made reservations to go to Kai Zan several months ago, but did not go due to the distance (& ended up paying a cancellation fee -- take note of this when making a reservation). We finally made the trek several weeks ago, and now wholeheartedly regret not going that first time. Kai Zan is small & unassuming. We sat at the sushi bar & were immediately greeted by the chef. After he learned that my boyfriend is a recent sushi convert, he gave us an amazing appetizer on the house. Throughout our entire meal, he continued to check in with us. It made for an awesome, intimate experience.My boyfriend and I both ordered the 10 piece omakase, featuring the greatest hits from the regular menu & several off the menu dishes. We started out with various sushi items, moved on to soup & hot dishes, and finished with the best maki & sashimi I have ever tasted. I was a bit hesitant when I noticed the final course was just sashimi -- I have always been a huge nigiri fan, but I hadnt quite mentally acquiesced to the idea of eating just pieces of raw fish at this point -- but I was absolutely blown away. The salmon/sake sashimi was probably the best thing Ive ever tasted & now Im completely hooked on (good) sashimi.Id 100% recommend the omakase. Youll leave full and dreaming of your next visit for only $60 + tip. Then again, the highlights for me were the pearls, the Angry Crab, the fiesta maki, & the dynamite mussels -- all of which are on the regular menu. Just go. Go now.Random notes I really hate wasabi. I didnt mention this, but only 1 item had too much wasabi for me -- a wasabi vegetable salad type deal that was part of the biggest plate in the meal. Didnt bother me. We arrived at our reservation a tad late & were reminded there is a 2 hour limit at the sushi bar. Again, didnt bother me. Finally, we had the DMZ rosÃ© with our dinner. It was great & I have now discovered it is available at the grocery store for $10.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus31129',1719,'2022-02-26',5,'Finally I got to try out this place for my birthday! Boy was it a treat!My suggestion is to ask what the chefs choice includes and if it floats your boat, go for it! That was exactly what I did. This way you are able to try out a little bit of everything on their menu. You wont regret the decision, I promise. There was so much food and it almost seemed endless. In addition to the tasting menu, we ordered the uni toro tartare and dessert in the end. One of my favorite dish of the night was the uni toro tartare! I love the DIY concept to this dish, and it almost seem endless. You just need to work for your food. Mix the tartare together really good and channel your inner sushi chef to make your own rolls. As much of a turn off the time limit is when you make the reservations, I did not feel at all pressured during the service. We did take a bit of time to make a decision, but our server was very patient with us. He walked us through the menu and elaborated on any questions I had along with making great suggestions. The pace was on point, however my ONLY critic is that from sitting at the bar and seeing how the kitchen flowed, what I noticed was the timing and preparation of the food. Some of the hot food was sitting there longer than I would have liked it because when I got my food expecting it to be hot, it was warm, if not almost cold. Of the hot food, only the soup and dynamite mussel were actually hot. Everything else minus the raw stuff were almost cold, which was a bit disappointing. The concept of clean and simple flavors is what I left with at this place. The tasting menu flowed from simple to variety and back to simple again. Nothing distracted your palette of the original flavors. As the tasting menu ends with a showcasing a selection of sashimi, I thought was genius because the menu took you on such an adventure, but made sure to remind you of the origin with the main ingredients of the night, fish. Just the concept of something as simple as fish can be created and paired with different things, but yet alone it can still be appreciated. To end this wonderful experience, we had a cup of green tea (FREE) and Cashew Panna Cotta. Not too sweet or heavy. Simple but yet so many textures and layers involved in just a little dessert. It was the perfect way to celebrate my birthday dinner! Cheers.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sodales69101',59,'2017-12-07',5,'I have always liked sushi, but I dont think I realized that there is a next level of sushi until I went to also Zan. Â Ive gone multiple times - including on my birthday this year - and it is truly the most satisfying meal Ive had anywhere, each time. Â The omakase menu is a good way to go. Â Its not an inexpensive meal but its always worth it.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in63197',912,'2017-06-16',4,'Just do the chef special... its top three meals in Chicago and I dont say that lightly',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien4153',650,'2018-02-18',5,'Amazing! Our favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago. We went with the Omakase (Chefs choice) and everything was great.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mollis81165',960,'2017-10-02',5,'Made a same week reservation and secured a 430pm dinner reservation for Saturday. I was a bit put off by the time we were given. I was thinking to myself is that considered dinner or a late lunch? But I really wanted to treat my bf to omakase for our 4 year anniversary so took it anyways. After all, its my fault to making the last minute reservation. We tried the chefs menu and premium menu. The chefs menu is $65 for 10 courses. The premium menu is double the price with the same number of courses, but not twice the quality. For some reason, they dont print out the premium menus either. I would stick to the chefs menu. Food was fresh and delicious; a great value for omakase style. Its easily one of the better Japanese restaurants in the city. My favorites were the escolar & maguro pearls (2nd) and fiesta maki (8th). On the premium menu, the most memorable items were the fresh wasabi where the wasabi is cut up in tiny chunks, and the dessert which was ice-cream with passion fruit pure and crumble. If Im paying $120 for a multi-course meal and stating the most memorable items being a condiment and ice-cream, I think its safe to conclude it just didnt blow me away. To sum up the experience, we were running 5 minutes late, and when I called to let them know, I was told we had 90 minutes to finish and we might not get seated if we dont get there soon. A friend of mine who went recently said she had 2 hours to eat, so its not the case everyday. Perhaps its just a Saturday thing since therere more diners so they have to be rigid in sticking to the schedule. The staff choreographed beautifully in bringing out the dishes and taking them away promptly, but we felt rushed. The bill was handed to us at 6pm sharp. They asked if I was celebrating a special occasion the day before when they called to confirm my reservation. I told them my anniversary. When dinner was done, we ordered a dessert (additional one outside of the omakase meals), but there was no effort put into decorating the dessert, and we ended up paying for it. Ill admit that Im used to restaurants now waving the cost of the dessert for special occasions or at lease decorating it, but either way, why ask me if Im celebrating anything if they dont plan on doing anything for the guests? We walked out a little after 6pm and it was still bright. It was the strangest feeling since thats normally when dinner starts. Warning make your reservations a month early for those coveted weekend dinner seats, or get stuck with a late lunch time like what I had.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',23,'2016-10-27',4,'Very cool place. Simply, the best sushi Ive ever had, and I love love love sushi. The omakase at around $70 is totally worth it. I was worried that it wasnt going to be filling enough and it ended up being plenty of food. The large booths were nice and very private. Makes you feel like a VIP. A couple of the highlights for me were the angry crab, the sashimi, and the shooters. All delicious. Make sure you check this place out.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',1343,'2021-03-29',5,'Japanese AlineaIf you blink driving down Chicago Avenue, you may miss this haven of culinary luxury, but once inside you will be transported to a restaurant that feels far away from the West Town neighborhood. Linda and I had the pleasure of dining at Kai Zan for the first time and enjoyed a spectacular meal that filled our tastebuds with repeated surprises from beautiful works of art created specifically for the mouth. If you are looking for special occasion place or seeking a fantastic dining experience, Kai Zan is by far the best choice. If youre lucky enough to have Justyn as your server, you will enjoy this delicious dining experience all the more.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit21153',752,'2020-11-24',5,'As many reviews already stated, Best sushi ever given the ingredients that we had it was the best quality ever. We ended up having both the premium and regular omakase. Both were amazing but wouldnt be something to be doing all the time. Both Omakase was a 10 course meal each and both had amazing ingredients. But each shined in its own perspective. Starting with the premium we had to reserve it ahead of time along with put reservation to ensure we get one. The ingredients were high scale and tasted amazing. This contained stuff such as wagyu beef, blue fin tuna, applewood smoked yellowtail, and etc. As for the regular one it was more tasteful since it contained more fish for half the price. Overall worth trying each one first.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',1191,'2019-09-16',4,'Great omakase for a good price. I was expecting bite sized portions but surprised to find that some courses we each got whole plates. Definitely no complaints for portion amounts. Besides that everything was delicious and Id definitely return again. Only complaint is that its kind of tight and crowded but its outshined by the food.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae1580',263,'2016-09-15',5,'This is literally the best sushi in Chicago! I recommend EVERYTHING! The sashimi is so fresh and sweet! The chef choice is definitely a must-have. If you love uni, this is the right place for you! The only thing that can be better is the restaurant is too small. People are very close to each other and tables are small.Tips try to arrive as early as possible. Their chef choice and uni sold out very soon!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',315,'2018-07-29',5,'Delicious and authentic Japanese food. Came alone based on highly recommended reviews from co-workers and yelp. Their sake selection was great. I had the Emperors well, a yamahai junmai ginjo from Niigata. It was medium dry, and paired well with my food choices. Their Fiesta roll of sushi Â ($10 six piece) was delicious, and the usage of chili oil negated the need for wasabi. I also had the yakitori glazed chicken thigh ($3) off of their grill, along with the Kara Age ($9 boneless fried chicken) and grilled shiitake mushrooms ($3). Everything was delicious and reasonably priced, combining to make one of the best Japanese dining experiences Ive taken part of. Justin was also a well informed and great server. One of the cooks even complimented me on my Attack on Titan hoodie haha. Made me feel very welcome. Will be back soon!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum5724',1407,'2018-11-05',5,'Everything you have read good about this place and then some is all true. Best sushi experience of my life. They arent any more expensive than the small town sushi places I go to at home but is so much better you will want to run up a bill getting more. I would give it 10 stars if I could.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum23143',1308,'2017-08-25',5,'After we heard that Kai Zan was on the top of multiple peoples lists, my wife and I decided to give it a try. Â Not sure of which tasting menu to choose, we went with the premium omakase meal. Â We really did not enjoy it. Â There was so much richness to the meal that we were overloaded halfway through. Â Everything was toro this or kobe beef fat that. Â By the time we got to the sushi and sashimi courses (which were amazing), we were so overwhelmed by the earlier courses that it was hard to enjoy. Â This might just be personal taste, but we were not fans. Â But the sushi and sashimi courses were good enough that I was curious about the other tasting menu. Â So a few months later, we ventured back and the cheaper omakase menu was INCREDIBLE. Â We enjoyed every course and we would recommend this place to anyone.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',258,'2021-11-17',5,'I really cannot find anything wrong with this place because not only was the service superb, but the food was also delicious. My friend and I both got the basic omakase for $65 and then we added the option of adding uni to two of the courses for an additional 5$, which was uh SO WORTH IT. MY FAVORITE COURSE OF THE EVENING was either the oyster and scallop shooters or the sashimi. The only reason I am taking off a star is because my friend and I both felt that the sashimi was so so so fresh that it should be set as one of the beginning courses and not dead last. We were so full by the time the sashimi came that we couldnt fully enjoy it like we wouldve wanted. Honestly, we would have rather they taken out the cooked the main course if that meant we were slightlier hungrier and could savor our raw fish completely. My last piece of advice if you are considering coming here is that this place is very very Americanized omakase. Coming from LA, and having extremely authentic sushi may have ruined me but if thats what you are also used to then I would be weary of coming here. It wont satisfy your raw fish nigiri style craving. But still incredibly yummy!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis14141',1521,'2018-03-12',4,'Kai Zan is definitely really good, but I dont think it totally lived up to our expectations. Â Our waiter was super quirky. Â He didnt seem like much of a people person, which makes being a server at a restaurant a weird fit. Â Anyways, we opted for the Omakase and were surprised that the price was lower, but for more courses than most restaurants ($65). They totally can squeeze more outta customers for the quality but maybe because its further out from the city its lower priced. Â I want to say there were 10 courses. Â All of the courses were great, unique and great flavor, but we were really really fished out by then end. And for me, that means there was a lot of fish because seafood is my favorite food (see all other reviews of mine... youll get it). The last dish was a ton of sashimi (and it was fantastic), but by the time we got to dish 10 it was almost hard to eat all of it, which was a shame. Â Every single dish was some sort of raw seafood, which is totally expected for a sushi restaurant. Â However, many Omakase dinners weve gotten in the city have some variation (king crab soup, seafood dumpling, ramen), which I think we like a little bit more. I think they could benefit from doing less courses and just giving you bigger portions as well. Â Overall the quality of the fish was stellar and everything tasted great, but just be prepared for a lot lot lot of raw fish. Â You will have a great meal here though.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',210,'2016-04-20',5,'Sooooooo amazing!!! The omakase is a must!! And you definitely get full. Fantastic service as well!!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1380,'2019-04-03',5,'This place has mastered it all. Hands down rockstar across the board. Â Still thinking about the food days after, service impeccable. Â Atmosphere very cool. Â  Did I say food!?! Â Escolar pearls. Â Pickled veggies. Â Seriously. Â Shame on me for wanting to visit for two years and just going this week. My loss!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',553,'2021-08-13',4,'This is really, really good. Â Its most similar to having an Uchi (Houston/Austin) smack dab in Chicago. Â Chicagoland is sorely missing good sushi omakases, and Kai Zan fits the mark. Â This is a fusion joint, but, and this is a big but, they pay a lot of attention to detail and source very high quality ingredients. Â For example, last evening I had a sushi omakase with Mitsu-san himself at Sushi Yasuda in NYC, and I noticed Kai Zan was using some of the same exact ingredients (I could tell by the Japanese writing).I did the premium omakase with a few additional dishes thrown in to placate my inner sushi cravings1) Seared salmon marinated in soy and mirin (4/5) - interesting, almost smoky flavor. Â Very good ginger. Â Pickled wasabi. - Note, a lot of their fish are fatty cuts, but often marinated. Â That is fine with me, as I imagine they might not get fish from Tokyo every day, and sushi is meant to be marinated )2) Raw wagyu beef with a touch of toro and caviar in a maitake mushroom sauce (4/5) - this was almost an amuse bouche, in that it was one bite, I thought it should have come before the salmon3) Pei wei served katsu style with sweet potato tempura (3/5) -- Pei wei (?) is a Brazilian fish, and it was fried with a curry flavor. Â Im not as big on fried dishes, so I knocked this a point, but many people would probably like it. Â The black plate was a bit severe4) Chawanmushi with rice chip, radishes and caviar (5/5) -- loved this. Â This is where I became very impressed. Â Very good egg custard, and the crispy rice was an interesting garnishment, which was meant to be broken into the soup almost like an oyster cracker5) Wagyu beef seared with crisp greens (5/5) -- extremely strong. Â They source their waygu from Japan and it was cooked perfectly. Â This is reason enough for the premium omakase. Â Im still salivating6) Toro, lobster with uni, and hotate with truffle oil nigiri (4.5/5) -- I liked the nigiri course at this juncture, because they went with big flavors. Â Almost everything was marinated except the uni. Â The toro was delicious, and the hotate with truffle oil melted in my mouth - The rice was very good with nice flavor, although a touch cold for me (should be room temperature or a bit above). Â They serve three pieces at a time, which isnt a crime, but doesnt necessarily shine (sorry for the rhyme)7) Ika plus asparagus (3/5) -- This was a little dry compared to some of the other luscious dishes, although the pairing had an interesting crunch which served as an effective contrast to the oily aspect of the previous course 8) Hamachi kama (4/5) -- I added this, as I was craving a classic dish. Â The hamachi kama was cooked perfectly and was very juicy. Â There was a very good ponzu sauce and pickled cabbage. Â I enjoyed the miso soup with which it came (heavy on the tofu and mushrooms)9) Marinated toro with pickled wasabi and sea salt (5/5) -- they go big on the toro here, and the pickled wasabi is a lot of fun. Â if youre a fan of Hayakawa down in Atlanta, youd appreciate it here, too10) Cold smoked marinated Hamachi with pickled wasabi and micro greens and caviar (4/5) -- another strong dish, and it reminded me a lot of Uchi due to the smoke effect Â (think Jar Jar Duck of Uchi fame)11) Â Sashimi plate - Hamachi belly, toro, madai served with pickled wasabi (5/5) -- loved this. Â Perfect cuts. Â All very delicious. Â I found it surprising to be served sashimi Â at the end, but the server made note of this that they like to mix it up, and since the flavors were so rich it held up nicely12) Cucumber, king crab, uni roll (5/5) -- the chef comped this for me, which I found very kind. Â It was a refreshing dish, and the uni was so sweet which paired nicely with the crisp cucumber and delicious, succulent crab. Â It was almost a palette cleanser13) Nigiri dessert course (3/5) - uni, tamago, unagi. Â The uni was delicious. Â Straight from Santa Barbara. Â The tamago was not layered as tightly as I would have expected and the searing was too dramatic, which took away from the lightness of the egg. Â The unagi was BBQd too aggressively. Â They were out of anagoService here is 5/5. Â Everyone is extremely pleasant and even jovial. Â The chefs are not Japanese, but clearly have mastered many aspects of the craft and I did not notice any diminution of knife skills. Â They are very talented. Â The space is cool, although the sushi bar is not large so make sure you get your spot. Â I have this place tied with Katsu in Chicagoland for sushi omakase. Â Katsu, of course, is where to go for more tradition nigiri, albeit with gold leaf, and Kai Zan is where to go for a great time and a lot of different tastes',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',1326,'2021-02-02',5,'My wife took me here for my birthday a few months ago and had a great experience. The set menu is definitely worth it. The courses were very creative and each plate was better than the one before. I would highly recommend giving this place a go.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',864,'2020-09-02',5,'Great omakase experience ! I will definitely be back to try their ala cart menu. This would be my regular sushi spot if it wasnt so far from where I live.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',226,'2021-04-08',4,'I wanted to love Kai Zan and will likely give it another chance. We did the Omasake which was nice to experience all different things, but next time will go for the rolls and sashimi. Server was a little too intense.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',1305,'2017-08-24',5,'Great service great food nice atmosphere - will be back! We tried the omakase and enjoyed majority of the courses! The server was very knowledgeable and accommodating of food allergies.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',154,'2017-11-27',5,'Best sushi l have ever had. Just go here. Do yourself a favor.We had the maguro pearls, angry crab, orange rush, and a few specials I cant remember. For dessert we had he flourless chocolate cake, Apple pie shit, and one of the mochis. Everything was amazing. I could have gone without the friend chicken dish we got. But who gets fried chicken at a sushi restaurant anyways?',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',616,'2020-08-31',5,'One of the best sushi restaurants Ive been to in AWHILE. Came here for a special date night, and it was an experience! The attention to detail at Kai Zan is phenomenal to say the least.YAY - Angry crab (2pc) and orange crush (2pc) is a must. Interesting flavors and it melts in your mouth.- ****Wagyu beef with quail egg (2pc) Perfectly seered edges. Melts in your mouth.- Fatty tuna (2pc), probably the best tuna of my life.- Escolar pearls (white tuna)- Excellent service. Our server Justin talked through the menu and described all of our orders with ease. - Interior is warm but modern, inviting, and relaxing. Youd never expect the inside to look as nice from just looking on the outside- Food presentation was continually satisfying and beautiful!- If you love mussels, get the dynamite mussels. Everything about it was perfect. NAY- not sure what it was called, but smoked salmon in a pot with fog. It smelled amazing and had dried ice to look cool, but it was actually cold cooked fish with a sour/vinagar-y flavor. Not my cup of tea.EXTRA - make reservations the best seat is the window seat!- best for groups of 2 because of food distribution and limited seating- ask the server for personal favorites that arent on the menu.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',1164,'2019-11-18',5,'Walked to Kai Zan one night with some friends to discover it is the most quaint sushi spot in town. Ended up doing the chefs special 10 courses and it was all fantastic. They took us on a journey of flavors and textures that paired with various drinks. The seating allows for a very private evening.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ultrices32193',1734,'2021-07-01',5,'Boo and I had an incredibly amazing and fabulous meal last night. We dont like to celebrate Valentines Day, but we still needed a reason to have a nice dinner date night, so we decided that this would be our Valentines dinner. Im sure we could have found any old reason to come here, though. Its the best sushi in Chicago!Ive already been here a couple times but it was his first time. I guess you could say that I popped his Kai Zan cherry *high fives all around*. He got the omakase and I got some a la carte dishes off the menu. It was THE perfect way that we could enjoy a variety of their best dishes. For those of you who dont know, the omakase is the chefs choice course meal of on-the-menu AND off-the-menu favorites, so you get the entire spectrum (literally, all different colors and textures) of dishes that they have to offer. And ever since they posted their new uni toro tartare dish on their FB page, Ive been dreaming of and totally drooling over it. So it worked out that I didnt get the omakase, because who can afford getting the omakase AND ordering this dish? Maybe all you big baller shot callers out there, but not me.Just a quick note about the service here our server was super friendly and informative. I wonder how long it took him to memorize every ingredient in the dishes he would bring out? Mad props. And the chef brothers are amazing with their culinary creations, which makes for a very legit omakase.My top 3Uni-Toro Tartare Holy mother of sea urchins, batman! I was definitely in UNI HEAVEN with this dish and I will definitely get it every single time I return. Because this #unilover just cant get enough! The uni and toro are served with quail eggs and some other delicious goodness that I cant seem to remember (wasabi and other stuff), all over a bed of rice. Its best to mix it all in together so that you end up getting all the flavors in one bite. Theres a side of several small sheets of nori that you can wrap the tartare in. DIY sushi FTW!Hamachi collar OMFG this was melt in your mouth food porn awesomeness! The meat was SO tender and buttery and paired well with the ponzu sauce that came on the side. Its a fairly medium sized collar with plenty of fish meat to pick off, so Im very glad that we got to try this. Its sold at market price, which was only about $14. Some places will charge more than that, so we were pretty happy that it wasnt incredibly expensive.Uni/Oyster Shooters First of all, the presentation is beautiful. The shooters come in a lovely martini shaped glass and you can see the uni (or oyster) in the ponzu sauce. And then on top, you see a gorgeous sprinkling of black tobiko (fish eggs), an egg porn worthy quail egg, and chopped scallions. Since the uni (or oyster) and quail egg is more on the slimy side as far as texture goes, its balanced out with the flavor pops of the black tobiko and the crunch of the scallions. And then of course, the lemony ponzu sauce ties it all together so that its not too heavy.It is no longer BYOB but they offer beer and wine.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc15',1008,'2016-04-10',4,'I love the food here. The best sushi in Chicago is very fresh and authentic. Â The chef came to our table to tell us that he had personally prepared the salmon skin himself. Â The deserts are so delicious too.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',648,'2016-02-16',4,'Voonswa or vooshi vooj?Good tasting. Not exceptionally creative or unique. Nothing was overly impressive, except for the booth area. Very well done booth area. The food seemed a bit too ordinary yet is trying to present itself otherwise. Overpriced, as most sushi restaurants are. Tasty. Not bad. Not great. Trendy. For the interested. Small portions for price. Acting like they serve you a fine dining or very rare to find fish yet is on the basic spectrum of fish types. Good tuna but maybe in Japan its a joke. Fresh tasting, good flavors but not buying into it... Probably wont return.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',201,'2017-05-25',5,'We order a regular and a premium omakasa. Nothing special but salty. I am surprised, their chiefs are not Japanese.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',413,'2019-02-28',3,'This restaurant is excellent. We had a party of five and we were seated in a cozy booth. Â Our server Kevin did a great job explaining the menu. We had the chefs choice 10 course meal. It was perfect. The husbands each had their own, and I shared with one other in our group - so an amazing meal!Each course was beautifully presented and delicious. We eat sushi quite often and Kai Zan has very fresh ingredients and a unique presentation and combination of tastes and textures. If you want great sushi. Eat here!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',1297,'2019-06-28',5,'I have been to Kai Zan over a dozen times now. And they never ever ever disappoint! I always order everything on their specials menu. Who doesnt want otoro or their lobster waygu fried rice. (Insert heart eyes emoji here). Also its always a treat when they have uni. I can have a whole meal of it. Uni toro tartare, uni shooters, uni nigiri. Ive been to many sushi restaurants in Chicago and Kai Zan is my absolute favorite, even beating high end Momotaro.I love the lowkey intimate vibes of Kai Zan and theyre not pretentious at all. The sushi chefs are so humble and seem to really enjoy what they do and they enjoy seeing their customers happy.Im a customer for life!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',1332,'2016-04-20',5,'My favorite sushi place in Chicago. The fish is fresh and delicious and the omakase is amazing. Lots of variety and unique flavors. Also nice that it is BYOB (with a corkage fee). Perfect for a slightly more special occasion. Should reserve well in advance for weekends.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec37198',905,'2020-03-02',4,'Be sure to make a reservation! Its a cozy place, and I brought my cousin here for his birthday. Even with our reservation, we had to wait a little bit (5-10 minutes) - we were able to order a bottle of saki. Unfortunately, a reservation doesnt guarantee a certain seating - if you dont want to sit at the sushi bar, you should probably call-in to check. My cousin and I didnt mind the sushi bar at all since we got front row seats to see how our dishes were prepared.We ordered Mushroom Medley, Karaage, Uni Shooters, Grilled Scallop Nigiri, King Oyster Mushroom & Hotate Skewers. My favorite was the Uni shooters! For a delicious and fairly healthy birthday dinner, it was appropriately priced!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',841,'2017-09-16',5,'One of the best sushi places youll find in Chicago. Its not a cheap place, but as far as omakase goes, pretty reasonable for the quantity and quality. Ive been there 3 times and have done the omakase twice. They have a great assortment of other small dishes and sake. Would recommend for a third date or night out with the friends (despite it being close to nothing else).',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',870,'2019-04-06',5,'This little hidden gem was recommended by a local. He said it was the best sushi he has ever had and he travels all over the world. We would have to agree! Splendid service, excellent presentation and the flavor was bursting with each bite. Highly recommend the tasting menu if you have never been there before! Its amazing!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis2682',634,'2021-02-18',4,'15 corkage fee?!? Â And a can of 200ML sake is $23 that probably costs $3 is purely a scam. I get markup of liquor being in the business but this was just a tad too steep in my eyes. The food is nothing more than great! Â 5 star worthy but Im rating the overall experience. Omakase, please!!!! Â The Madai carpaccio, Maduro pearls & orange rush were the top of the list. Â The grand slam was the last and final course. Beautifully plated fresh sashimi that just melts in your mouth like budda!!! Â Top 3 sashimi Ive ever eaten in my life. The food is worth bragging about but you just need to be sober to enjoy it. -)',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',611,'2016-05-05',5,'YES! YES! YES! I took my date her for a late dinner on Friday and it was great. I loved the atmosphere. Its very intimate, perfect for a date. The service was amazing, no wait, they answered our questions and made suggestions. As this was both of our first times, our waitress recommended we try the Chefs Choice. It was a ten course, small bite, meal. Of course with something like this there were things I loved, and others I could have lived with out. Overall I was very impressed. My date and I both loved our experience. If you are ever in the area looking for good sushi or just a great dinner experience, Id highly recommend Kai Zan. I know I will be coming back the next time Im in Chicago.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',1535,'2016-01-07',5,'Now I know why people are always raving about this place! We were finally able to snag a table here for my birthday dinner. The area is pretty quiet and from the outside at night its a bit hard to find. I was told its small and no joke it is.  Our reservation was on a Saturday night at 8pm. Got there on time and only had to wait 4 minutes four our table. The restaurant gives you an option to either buy drinks from them or bring your own bottle for 12 dollars corkage fee. We opted to drink the wine we brought. The hubs was a bit reluctant to do the omakase thinking it might be too much food. The omakase was 10 dishes so like 2 from each section of the menu. Either way, I was dead set on doing the tasting. Needless to say he realized his wife is right. We ordered the regular omakase instead of the premium one. I believe the premium has uni and foie gras. We noticed the omakase was a popular option. It doesnt hurt it only costs 65 bucks. Much cheaper than other places would charge. Each dish was delicious! If youre a slow eater like me beware since the dishes come out fast! We were impressed by their efficiency. I couldve done without the Angry Crab. It just didnt stand out. The sashimi was like butter in your mouth. The red snapper carpaccio was a dish I would order 20 times over. We really enjoyed the oyster shooter and how the flavors complimented each other. All of the dishes were great just minus the angry crab. The service was wonderful and on point. We were lucky to sit in front of the kitchen allowing us to watch each dish come together. We did order the chocolate lava cake as our dessert. The black sesame ice cream blew us away. The flavor of the ice cream was just a tad sweet but had a great berry flavor as well. Skip the cake and just get the ice cream instead. Overall, my high expectations for Kai Zan was met. We are already planning to come back for the premium omakase.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',1625,'2019-12-25',4,'If quality is your number one priority, then I highly recommend Kai Zan. I was a bit thrown off at the atmosphere of the restaurant. I imagined a very quiet place with some classical music playing in the background (stereotypical view of high-end restaurants?). However, it was lively and vibrant, which was great.I had the omakase, the two specials, which were wagyu beef nigiri and toro, mochi, and the matcha creme brulee. First, the presentation on all of these were amazing. Im not one to take photos of food, but I just had to because it was so beautiful. For the omakase, you can tell that each item on the list was placed purposefully, in terms of what does the chef want you to taste next? Its hard to pick a favorite because everything tasted incredible, but I would say that the shooter was definitely something unique and highly worth trying. I would also highly recommend the matcha creme brulee.But, I think what made the experience great for me was the waiter. The way he presented and communicated each dish to us was pure poetry, and the way he interacted with us was probably the best service I will receive in a while. Overall, highly recommend going. I am hoping to come again to try the premium omakase.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1505,'2016-10-16',5,'Delicious fusion Japanese omakase, very reasonably priced ($65), food comes out fast, and I felt full by end of meal.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra37167',962,'2019-06-27',5,'Amazing, delicious, belly-satisfying omakase meal that I am still dreaming about. Ever since the first course, I have been making a mental list of all the people I must bring and tell about Kai Zan. Not to mention, wondering when exactly is too-soon of a return for myself?! On this particular visit to Chicago, my boyfriend chose Kai Zan as our first kick-off meal (& bless his soul for finding it). The small, intimate setting of Kai Zan was the cherry on top. Not too loud, not too many people. We decided on the omakase 10-course meal and it was the best decision ever. Priced at $60/person, not only was it worth every penny but also a steal if you ask me. A few of my favorites were the Escolar Pearls (spicy seared escolar with soy & truffle oil) and the uni shooter (uni and scallop in ponzu sauce with raw quail egg). I also liked that they ended our meal with an assorted sashimi plate. It was a nice, clean way to end the 10-course meal. More toward the bottom of my list would be the Madai Carpaccio, only because I felt that the pesto overpowered the dish. But there wasnt a single item we had that I did not like. There are too many dishes to go through individually, but check out my pictures! Each dish was perfectly unique in its own way. This is not your typical omakase meal and although I was nervous for the whole fusion thing, each dish left me in awe. It was interesting that they incorporated traditional items along with cooked items -- like our 7th dish which they called a main dish. Without doubt, I would highly recommend the omakase ... although Im sure everything on the menu is worth trying. Counting down until we meet again, Kai Zan.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit21153',1466,'2017-11-21',5,'Personally, Not authentic Japanese sushi. We tried chefs omakase and premium omakase. Using too much seasoning and decoration and the taste of fish itself being covered. Sashimi is good but the sushi rice taste bad, like undercooked. Wagyu beef is good and cooked well. The variety of fishes is small, at least for my visit, only about tuna, yellowtail, salmon. The service is just fine. Some server are good but the others made me feel like being rushed to complete my course....I dont feel the money I spent worth it. Not a course makes me surprised.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',1294,'2020-05-23',5,'Who knew there is great sushi spot on Chicago avenue in Humboldt Park?! Actually, a lot of people knew and I am only finally in the know. We did the ten course Omakase Menu ($60/person) and added the two daily specials. Â The food was excellent. Â Some of the highlights include the sashimi platter, Â the tuna and escolar, the main course (octopus, a pork belly, shrimp and arrancini-like ball) and the mushroom soup. The scallop shooter had a bit too much heat for my taste, but I loved the oyster shooter. Â The fish was very fresh and there were different dishes than Ive had before. There was a great variety between the courses. Â With the two tasting menus and the extra specials, were were very full. Service was excellent. We walked in a few minutes early and had a small wait for our table. Â In the meantime, we ordered a bottle of wine and had a glass while we waited which was a nice touch. Our waiter was friendly and helpful. Â My only complaint is sometimes I wish the courses slowed down a little bit. However, I understand that for a table of 2 they have a 90 minute policy to turn tables over. It was great food and a great value. Our tab for two was about $200 with a bottle of wine and some sake. Â Im always a bit hesitant to give 5 stars on the first visit, but they earned it. I cant wait to go back!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',1497,'2020-03-04',4,'The food was terrific. However their slouchy long-haired waiter rubbed our entire party wrong with the lax attitude rubbed us entirely the wrong way. He had no opinion on any of the dishes, made us feel stupid for not knowing the portion sizes, and made no efforts to make first time visitors feel welcome. Also, their wait staff picked up two dishes which werent even completely finished. Hey! We still have ginger on the plate asshole! Michelin rated for the food, not the service. This food was AMAZING but find some new employees',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',392,'2020-04-12',5,'Love love love this place! Ive been about 3-4 times and love all the things On the menu. I also love that the chefs are accommodating with special orders. It might sound weird, but my favorite thing has got to be their tamago. So light and fluffy with some sweetness. Almost like a dessert!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',736,'2020-04-17',5,'Im a little disappointed for spending over $200 and being rushed out because someone is waiting for our table, we had three people approach us and we had to leave our drinks and pack our food so we can pay quickly and leave. I understand its good for their business but defeats the purpose of A good dining experience. Even though the food was great I would never return here for this reason.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',223,'2016-07-06',4,'Kai Zans food is a unique, fun experience--the five stars reflect the dining experience as well as the service, but I want to explain more about the service I received tonight that warranted an immediate review.I came in with my partner to celebrate his birthday, but unfortunately wasnt feeling well. We made it through much of the (delicious!!) omakase menu before we had to notify the waitstaff that we wouldnt be able to complete the final course.The waiter was extremely kind, discreet, and understanding, completely accommodating our request. I could not have asked for them to handle the situation better, and it absolutely improved our experience. As a final plus, there were two wait staff who still asked us if we wanted dessert to celebrate the birthday (which we did pass on), despite the situation--which was a funny and positive note to the end of the meal. Thank you to all the wait staff working this evening!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',744,'2016-10-20',5,'Food and service is amazing. I went with some friends and got the omakase course. All servers/food runners were very knowledgeable about every dish that came out. The flavors were all there and shocked your taste buds each time. I was informed that all their desserts are made in house also including their amazing green tea ice cream. Definitely will be returning soon.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',714,'2021-12-13',5,'I went after finals with friends and was excited for the regular omakase (10 courses) which was highly recommended online as the best price in Chicago. $65/person and we paid $5 for extra Uni in our shooters - best decision! The shooters were our favorite. Each dish was an exploding bite of flavor. One of my friends didnt like mushrooms, but that just meant more for me. After going through most of the courses we were still a bit hungry, but then they brought the sashimi platter that definitely filled us up.The server was very knowledgeable and friendly. The courses were brought one by one with a good pace, so you dont have to think about the 90min limit.The only downfall is parking is kind of hard to find - have to go into the alleys.Im already making plans to go back for my birthday to try the premium omakase.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',1664,'2018-07-25',4,'Insanely good food and service in a cozy and comfortable room. One of the few places that could be considered a great value.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',75,'2018-09-25',5,'Best sushi in Chicago for the price or not. Better than Momotoro or Roka Ankor. Dont waste your money at those places when you can go to Kai Zan. Hands down freshest fish and most creative omasake! But of course if you cant get a reservation here because it is small and cozy you can try for one of those other hip places ;)',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',790,'2019-06-03',5,'One of the best sushi restaurants in Chicago in my opinion. It is a small restaurant so I suggest making a reservation far in advance but it is totally worth it. The Maguro pearls and polenta bites are two of my favorites! The chocolate lava cake is also something not to miss. Service is always fast and attentive. Not a spot to be missed!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis34168',1320,'2019-09-23',5,'Japanese omakase is one of lifes greatest joys. Â It allows for maximum appreciation of what youre eating everything is beautifully presented, every morsel a universe of harmonious flavors. Ive had sushi omakase at Nakazawa and Gari, but Kai Zan is a totally different beast. The sheer variety and quantity were enough to justify the $60+ bill per person.Like Gari, they are quite experimental with their sushi. But they also serve tastings of other grilled and cooked items. Â For example, we had takoyaki (!) and pork belly and uni and oyster shots. Â Its a well planned and perfectly timed orchestration of courses. Â As for quantity, you get more than a bites worth per course. Â In fact, we each got two pieces of several dishes, which is terrific because sometimes you just want to savor the same piece all over again (and again and again).Because it was our friends birthday, we brought in a birthday cake, and they kindly provided the candles. Â The inside is cozy with a bar in one room and private enclaves for big parties. Â That Michelin bib gourmand win is well earned!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',299,'2020-01-15',4,'Was visiting Chicago from St. Louis, and some friends brought me here. Â Hands down the best sushi and Japanese plates Ive had (for being in the Midwest.)My mother is Japanese, so I can be a harsh critic.For 4 people our bill was about $300.00, so your bill can definitely add up, but we left full and completely satisfied. Â Even the waiters knowledge of the menu (and things you can order off the menu) were impressive. Â What a treat. Â  Oh, and be sure to make a reservation first!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',1073,'2018-11-20',5,'We did the chefs omakase. And it lived up to my expectations fully. Â What a fun tasting adventure. Â Each bite was unique and flavorful and full of fresh fish. Â Creative pairings of sauces and seafood and presentations. Â My mouth said wow all dinner. Â The finale was a plate a sashimi and all thr cuts were thick and yummy and Melt in your mouthy. Â Thr only thing that made me happier was the value. Â At $65 this is a great deal to have this experience.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('Ettu14',1348,'2020-09-14',5,'Do yourself a favor and order the chefs menu. You wont regret it! Great for a date-night or a girls night, if you can score a large reservation spot.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',1739,'2017-04-17',4,'Had an early reservation. Everything was great. Did the omakase as suggested by our server. Added the uni with the $5.00 addition. The meal did not disappoint. We left happy and satisfied. The only thing I can mention is that towards the middle of our meal, we felt they were rushing service as they obviously had a second seating after us. We were also seated by the bar which was awesome as we had the culinary view. It would have been nice if we could have lingered but I do understand that they have to flip Â tables.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',1101,'2021-08-07',5,'My favorite sushi place in the city. Its pricey but truly incredible and the service is the best Ive ever had. Truly, I have been here twice now and im blown away by the attentiveness of the servers and how passionate they are about their jobs. On my last visit there was one dish that my step mom had ordered that she wasnt totally in love with and our server pressed her, politely, to tell us what could be done to improve it. Not only did he agree with her, but said he would let the chefs know the input (which I fully believe he actually did). I honestly have never had a dish here that I didnt like, but there are a few that you cannot miss- angry crab - uni shooters- orange rush- there was a waygu beef special roll that we had that was amazing!- grilled hamachi nigiri- madai carpaccio (our tables favorite along with the angry crab)Do the omakase menu and youll actually save money as its only 60 dollars and youll be full by the end. You can ask them to include certain dishes on the menu that you are eyeing so you dont miss them for a slight up-charge as well (usually 10 dollars).I cant say enough about this place - every bite is heaven. Reservations are a must as the place is very small - but if you have to wait there is a cute store next door with great little gifts.Go here before you die you wont regret it!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc15',77,'2021-02-24',5,'Hands down BEST SUSHI IN CHICAGOThe food is outstanding, every roll was perfect. The fish to rice ratio in every role is on point. The freshness and quality is amaZing. Ive never had a better sushi meal ever. The pearls are great start. They have a secret menu so be sure to ask about it. The service is wonderful and the knowledge of the staff is great. I look forward to my next meal',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempus72169',641,'2018-05-07',5,'We ended up coming to Kai Zan sort of on a whim--we were downtown, had time to kill, and we were craving fresh food. Not only did we get fresh, we got straight up raw. Kai Zan was exactly how a Japanese restaurant should be, absent of cream cheese and creamy sauces and with a focus on delicious simplicity. Best Japanese restaurant Ive been to to date.Definitely getThe uni shooterThe red snapper collarIf they have it (it was a special on the night we went) the uni tartar which came topped with quail egg, rice, and more as well as little seaweed strips so you can make DIY sushi. Sake, per your waiters recommendationsMake sure to ask for the specials if your waiter doesnt offer the information. And, if you dont think youre into the whole raw egg thing, keep an open mind!!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',163,'2017-08-29',5,'Finally tried the Omakase, which was out of this world delicious and super filling. Â Hubby was able to snag an early Friday night dinner reservation last minute. Â I was a little worried about bringing baby girl, but everyone was so accommodating. Â The space is cozy and theres no room for a high chair, but they seated us in the corner front booth next to the front window, which was enough space for her to sit and also roam around a bit in a controlled space. Â Many of the staff came by to say hi to her and say how adorable she is (thanks guys!!).Its difficult to pick a favorite from the Omakase, but also because I was so full halfway through and uncomfortably full by the last two dishes. Â I like how it highlighted the offerings of the current menu so we could sample a little bit of everything. Â I remember the Escolar Maguro Pearls and Angry Crab from our last visit, so its good they kept the fan favorites. Â Each dish was beautifully presented. Â All the ingredients were fresh and of the highest quality. Â The timing between dishes was a little rushed a few times, but our server apologized and gave us more time to enjoy each entree and slow down the pace a bit. Â Im glad I tried the shooters, but it was probably my least favorite given the texture. Â I was pleasantly surprised with how much I liked the scallops in Orange Rush. Â The dishes got heavier as dinner progressed, but Im glad it ended with the fresh selection of sashimi. Â Although I was stuffed beyond comprehension, I really wanted to try a dessert and so happy we ordered the Green Tea Creme Brulee. Â It was so good we polished it off completely.Ill have to prepare for the next time by starving myself the entire day so I can really make room for all the Omakase components!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci23113',95,'2019-12-15',4,'its just, straight awesome. A must eat here. everything is exquisite, the multiple unexpected taste well worth it.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat89150',273,'2016-03-06',5,'Pearls are the best we have tried in the chefs course. Overall it is very artistic and delicious.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed7891',1538,'2019-04-21',5,'Been wanting to try this place and I finally got the chance! We got the omakase and it was phenomenal. I also thought it was well worth the price. I highly recommend and cannot wait to go back!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id3571',910,'2017-05-10',4,'One of the best tasting menus I had in Chicago. Loads of small things but you will get filled up by the end. Everything is delicious.the place is very very small. Staff are knowledgeable about each course. Some of the dishes are very creative. Highly recommend it if you love sushi and sashimi.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',981,'2019-07-17',5,'Phenomenal. Im not often impressed by sushi restaurants because there is little to set most places apart. Kai Zan exceeded all of my expectations. The wait staff is amazing and extremely attentive. Appetizers I highly recommend the dynamite mussels, which is part of their everyday menu. However, their off-menu uni toro tartare appetizer was hands down one of my favorite dishes of the evening. It is served with raw quail egg, wasabi, and rice, which you mix together and wrap with dried seaweed. Both appetizers were enough to share between two people. Great way to start the meal!The Chefs Choice omakase was worth every penny and very very filling. There were a total of eight courses, so definitely dress comfortably and be prepared to eat. Some of the omakase highlights Lightly grilled maguro and escolar (white tuna) with truffle infused dipping sauce - my favorite omakase course. The fish has a nice smokey quality to it without being cookedOyster and scallop shooter duo - served as a shot with quail egg, tobiko, and wonderfully tart ponzu sauce. Personally, I preferred the scallop, but both were delicious.Angry crab - crab wrapped with tuna and topped with spicy mayo and crunchy tempura. I could eat an entire plateful of these. Madai carpaccio - thinly sliced red snapper served with what tasted like balsamic vinegar, olive oil, tobiko, etc. Char sui - braised pork belly with black garlic sauce and greens. The pork belly was cooked to perfection.Lightly grilled tuna with fried polenta and seaweed - the different textures and contrast of hot/cold complimented each other very well.Although there were many other dishes served in the omakase, these were the ones that I would absolutely order again. The desserts left a little to be desired, but I was impressed with the meal as a whole. I thought it was reasonably priced considering the sheer quantity of food and I will definitely be recommending Kai Zan to everyone I know.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hina115',1168,'2016-09-16',5,'Im sold. This is probably the freshest sushi/sashimi place Ive been to in Chicago, and would highly recommend to anyone!!Ive tried both the popular omasake tasting menu ($60) and the premium omasake tasting menu ($130). Both were excellent.Favorites from their menus are the oyster shooters (both), the wagyu beef (premium) and the fatty tuna fish (premium). Ambiance is intimate and upscale modern without being pretentious. If you have 3 or more in your party, youll get their private booths, which I really enjoyed sitting at. Make reservations in advanced. Its not a large venue and seats go fast! Its popular for a reason.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',92,'2016-11-30',4,'I feel like everyone is going to hate me on this one but I think Kai Zan is over rated. Great service, I love the intimate private booths, but I just couldnt get over how unimpressed I was. I came here with a group of friends and we all ordered Omakase. Maybe I can give this place another shot and order off the regular menu. Some dishes were better than others.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',1164,'2016-09-13',5,'This is my first yelp review and I wanted to make sure it was for the favorite restaurant Â of my wife and I in Chicago. We have lived all over the world and have fortunately (or unfortunately) tasted some great sushi, so we are kind of sushi snobs as a result. We have lived in Chicago for four years now and struggled to find something on par with where we have lived previosuly until we discovered Kai Zan in November 2012. In many ways, this has been our baby. We have watched it grow from a 17 seater relatively easy place to get a reservation place to a restaurant highly recommended and regarded by lthe ocal food press. That said, the service and personal touch has not changed as the place has grown up.The wait staff are really good and welcoming. Each table is given a 2 hour allocation, but we find them very accomodating if the group is having a good time and you run over a little bit. The owners Carlo and Melvin are a real treat. They offer amuse bouches. That could be because we come in about every 6 weeks, but my guess is it is something they just like to do. They make an effort to come by the tables to interact with the guests. Both of them are incredibly humble and warm people. One can even get off menu items. The uni toro tartare is an example of this!My recommendation to first time diners is to either do the $60 or $90 tasting. If you can afford the $90, I would recommend doing this. This place is great for groups as they have booths that can seat 6 people and contain the noise of the group very nicely.I was slighly saddened to see them move away from BYOB even though I am not a big drinker until I saw that the drink menu is quite reasonable. The last time we were in there a bottle of nice white wine was only $21. This is a place that is also good to bring people who may not be the biggest fans of sushi as they have char-broil items that are delicious as well. They did a pop up ramen night, which my wife said was delicious. It would be great to see them do this more often or even incorporate into the menu, but I can understand if they want to keep the menu more focused on traditional cuisine.Carlos and Melvin well done, you have a great restaurant and a place we always take visitors to town. This place is one of only two places (the other being Hot Dougs) that we have actually had people fly to town solely for the purpose of dining here. We cannot say enough good things about this place.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed91175',1145,'2018-10-13',5,'WORTHS YOUR EVERY PENNY!!Kai Zan is one of the best Japanese restaurants I have been to in the US. Their dishes were so fresh, innovative, and unbelievably delicious. I highly recommend the Uni and Tuna DIY hand roll and the salmon press. I love this place so much!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('enim3417',89,'2020-09-12',4,'Im celebrating my ROTD with an updated review! Ive since been back a couple more times to try their omakase. Check out my titillating photos, courtesy of my favorite eating-partner-in-crime. (Forgive me that I didnt quite catch all the names of the dishes as I was too busy stuffing my face).Faves- Uni Toro DIY hand roll- Yellowtail Sashimi with Kai Zan sauce- Orange Crush (Scallop wrapped in Seared Salmon)- Escolar Pearls- Toro!!!Passes- FlatbreadOf the 20+ dishes Ive tried here, Id only pass on one of them. Cmon, thats pretty good odds. But Ill be honest. This isnt necessarily the best Japanese food Ive ever had. The prices are lower here for a reason. Â You probably wont get the quality here that you get at Arami. Youre also not paying what you pay at Arami. But what they do at Kai Zan, they do really, really nicely. This a gem of a Japanese place and a fine addition to this otherwise quiet neighborhood. Now to decide whether to share this place with my friends or keep it all to myself...',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',1077,'2020-09-29',5,'If youre like me and you hate making decisions, Kai Zans Chefs Choice Omakase is the way to go. Yeah it has a bit of a hefty price tag of $60, but its well worth it. You leave it up to the chef to pick out the best of the best and they deliver 10 courses to your table.My favorites were the Escolar and Maguro pearls (oh my gosh, so good), and the Angry Crab - wow. So delicious.I did not like the Uni and Oyster Shooters but that is a personal preference, you should give those a try.I have been to Kai Zan before and not included in the Chefs Choice was the Karaage, my friend loved it but I wasnt as much of a fan, I definitely prefer their fish over anything. We also had the Apple Pie Shot which is definitely worth ordering for dessert - really unique dessert that I dont mind bragging about.Also, even though its no longer BYOB the wine is a great price. We ordered the Domaine des Cantarelles Cabernet Sauvignon for $30 and it was a great addition to the meal.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',1564,'2020-01-31',5,'/TL;DRSuper accommodating with great service. Spectacular food. Best gem is when you ask the waitstaff for their recommendation, and they lock up because they have a hard time telling you which one they love most.Since we were in the loop, getting here required taking a bit of drive with Uber to get there. Well worth it though./ATMOSPHEREOne way to describe this place would be small. From the outside, it looks it. Inside, its perfectly cramped which creates a type of intimate surrounding. The booths near the sushi bar are private in a way since the walls are very high. The decor was quite warm and inviting./FOODWe went with the recommendation the waitstaff provided. It was on point. If you need an idea, go for the pearls. We couldnt decide between the escolar or maguro pearls so they split a single dish. Honestly, it was the best thing we ate there.I dont know though. I mean... char siu? Ridiculous. So damn good. We also had a selection of maki rolls. They were probably my least favorite but still definitely memorable./SERVICEExcellent. Attentive. Knowledgable. A little slow at times... but Kai Zan was packed out! They were gracious with accommodating our late arrival. Glad, too, since it turned out to be one of the best sushi meals Ive ever had.HOW TO READ MY REVIEWS1 Star - Does not approach edible. Enter at your own risk.2 Stars - If Im in the area, Id pick something else.3 Stars - I would stop by if I happen to be in the area.4 Stars - I would pick this place out of other places nearby.5 Stars - I would go out of my way to dine here.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',1058,'2016-10-16',4,'I came here last month with the boy. We were celebrating Christmas early since we were going to be separated by the ocean during the holidays.To treat ourselves, we headed to Kai Zan! I made reservations for a Tuesday night dinner. When we arrived, I knew it was going to be a small space. But dear lord, it really was TINY. I think it might be slightly larger than my garage. We opted to get the omakase and it started off pretty slowly. We had the peppers, followed by a jalapeno popper, uni shooters, and I forgot what else. To be honest, I was quite disappointed. Perhaps Ive been building up too much hype in my mind, but I thought that the offering was rather boring. I liked the shooters. Actually, I liked them a lot. But that was probably one of the few standout points of the meal. I started to really pay attention when we decided to order 2 additional dishes after we were done with the omakase just because we werent full. Both were nice pieces of fish belly. It was served simply and it really let the fish speak for itself.The service was alright. We came in knowing that we were going to order the omakase, but when the food came, the hostess/waitress didnt explain what we were eating. We had to flag someone down to explain what was in front of us. But other than that, the chefs were nice. I dont know which brother it was, but he kept on asking if we were enjoying ourselves.The boy liked the overall meal more than I did. I just expected more, whether it was mixing up textures or serving it in a different way. It felt like everything was either wrapped in escolar, an escolar roll, a slice of escolar belly, etc. Sweet Jesus, what happened to other fish?! Sorry, just not enough innovation for me.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec37198',166,'2019-11-11',5,'We made a reservation last week and everything was smooth. This was introduce by a friend and I loved this place ever since.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',1254,'2019-09-22',5,'This is the best sushi place in Chicago. I mean it. Justin was really helpful and made some really nice suggestions. I dont know anyone who wouldnt love this place like I do. I barely leave any reviews and this is the one I cant wait to comment on. Excellent food. A must try.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',484,'2016-02-13',5,'Wow this place is awesome! No wonder it takes weeks to make a reservation here. My boyfriend and I were celebrating our anniversary Saturday night and were seated at the sushi bar. Our sever was informative and attentive. He right away walked us through the menu since we were new. My boyfriend ordered the Chefs Omakase. It was pricey at $125 but each course blew us away. I ordered the fiesta roll and mushroom medley at our servers recommendation. Everything was fresh and prepared wonderfully. Our interaction with the chef behind the sushi bar was enjoyable and they even gave us a complimentary dish!I would absolutely go back and order everything we had again minus the mushroom medley (it was okay but not great.) The fiesta roll was one of the best rolls Ive ever had and the polenta bites are a must try. The Kobe beef slider on the tasting menu was heaven. They have a $15 corking fee so we ordered drinks off the menu. Great experience we will be back!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',1439,'2019-05-23',4,'My favorite place for sushi! Â Great place to go for a celebration. Â A range of traditional rolls/maki but also unique options that are beautiful to look at and taste delicious.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yccc14',1259,'2016-06-21',5,'Kai Zan is the perfect date spot. Â My husband brought me here for my birthday and it was an experience. Â I love sushi, but I never had an experience like this one. Â This was my first tasting table or Omasake....and it was awesome! Â The Omasake was perfect because I was able to try things on the menu that I would not normally try. Â My mouth still waters when thinking of the Escolar Pearls! Â When the first dish came out, I didnt think I would be full by the end of the 8th or 9th dish I didnt know if I could eat anymore. The restaurant was smaller, but cozy and romantic. The best part was the BYOB, we stopped somewhere on the way and picked up a bottle of wine. Â They brought us a ice bucket to chill our wine. This was the perfect date spot, with a perfect new experience to share.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',1023,'2017-04-25',5,'Love everything about this place !!!!!! Food is outstanding. One of best asian place in Chicago !!!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',593,'2019-07-27',4,'Magnificent! I came here with my boyfriend, sister, and brother-in-law. It was an early celebration for my sister, who happens to be a chef, so I was trying to choose the best meal in Chicago that wouldnt break the bank, and a place that we all havent been to yet. And what do you know, Kai Zan was just that spot!We all got the Omakase Chefs Choice 12-course tasting. This is basically a surprise tasting, where everything is left to the Chef. Of course if you have any restrictions or allergies, the Chef will adjust the menu accordingly. I have to say, without exaggerating at all, this was the best seafood experience I have ever had in Chicago. Every single course contained the freshest and highest quality fish. I am super picky about sushi and especially sashimi, but this literally melts in your mouth. Every course was full of surprises and full of bold flavors. I have attached all of the food from the courses to this review if you want to check it out. Its BYOB but the corkage fee is $15, which has gone up from when they first started. The Omakase 12-course menu is $60/person, which is very very reasonable for the amount of quality food you get. Although the neighborhood seems sketchy, its really not bad. Plus, parking is plentiful which makes it easier to get to.The one and only thing I would change is incorporating 1-2 dessert courses at the very end of the meal because after the main course there are more maki and sashimi courses.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nam3954',261,'2016-02-17',5,'A sushi joynt with Billecart-Salmon rosÃ© on the menu ... wow!The Omakase is the way to go. Â Everything was thoughtfully prepared and fresh. Â Definitely moves to the top of my fav sushi spots.Will definitely be back.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1573,'2021-10-18',5,'We had the regular omakase- it was so delicious and definitely filling without being too much. The shooters were are favorite plus we were able to add uni to the dish and it was so delish! The Wandering Poet saki was a great balance to the meal as well. We will be back for more!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',837,'2018-05-03',5,'Chicagos best sushi. Deserving of a Michelin star. Hype worthy. To start, the ambience is sleekly romantic. The cavernous booths for larger groups next to the bar near the entrance seem to offer a phenomenal experience. The smaller booths in the kitchen room are also authentic and tasteful. We had the pleasure of sitting directly in front of the twin (yup!) chefs and watch them hone their craft. These guys work like a manufacturing line; precise and efficient! We werent starving, so opted for a la carte instead of omekase; wise choice! Uni shooters awesome blast of flavor, the urchin is decadent, sauces add some saltiness, quail egg balances the texture. Escolar/Maduro pearls decadent, delicious, freshest fish Ive had in Chicago. Angry crab tiny portion, but delicious. While other sushi joints overpower mediocre fish with spice, this dish featured a subtle hit of spice which complemented the tuna perfectly!Hamachi carpaccio My favorite dish! Slight tweaking of flavors with a bit of oil, tobiko, and greens, but this is the way a fresh offshoot of sashimi is supposed to shine! Fiesta maki the freshness of the fish made this awesome. Looks like any other generic sushi roll, but the texture and flavor of the fish propel it above the competition. Cant wait to come back with a bigger appetite and try the omekase! Love that this is in my general vicinity.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla56102',1473,'2016-03-06',5,'Very good food. We had 65 dollar omakaze and 130 dollar omakaze i think 130 dollar oamakaze is better and it is worth to pay 130 for new omakaze. Â i will visit again soon.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',771,'2017-10-04',4,'The food was fantastic as usual. Very composed, great flavor combinations. We had a bottle of rose sparkling wine and most of the sushi bites on the menu. The polenta bite with kale and tuna was delicious and the uni was very fresh. All in all the good was great.The service was good until the waitress dropped off the check and came back 2 minutes later to rush us out. It felt like we stopped spending money so her attitude changed and she was like get the f out. We had a 715 res and the next one after us was for 915. This happened at 840. She actually said, if you could finish up your conversation else where there are other tables waiting. We had been talking for 2 minutes after she dropped the check off. It honestly ruined a great meal. So disappointing. We know the place has a reputation for rude service and we commented on how they must have changed, then that happened. Too bad.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',1680,'2016-11-22',5,'Very delicious food ! Coming back 4 sure. Will recommend to my friends. Decent prices !!!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',341,'2018-11-02',5,'Incredible Omakase with really good service. Their Uni shoot is one of my favorites.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4994',1686,'2018-08-31',4,'The food was amazing! The service was great and they were very accommodating to my food allergies. The server was extremely knowledgeable about the menu, the origin of the fish and had great recommendations. The atmosphere is very intimate but didnt feel crowded. We had the spicy tuna roll which was great. We had the wagu beef and lobster special rice dish which was great! All the sushi and sashimi was so fresh! We also a hot saki which was really good! Would def recommend for a nice dinner that wont break the bank with great food and service!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',311,'2019-06-29',5,'Best sushi in Chicago! Weve tried everywhere old and new and always come back to Kai Zan. Always make reservations ahead of time!Can share one omakase (which is enough food for two people in my opinion to taste different dishes) Service is always great too!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dolor4397',558,'2018-01-21',5,'If you are looking to drop a ton of cash for good sushi and leave the place hungry, this is the place.They also do not even have brown sugar for the tea.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae1580',695,'2016-07-23',4,'We were certainly treated incredibly well here. Â There was a mixup with the timing of our reservation, but the restaurant handled it cheerfully and efficiently. Â The private booth was lovely and calming, our waiter was friendly, informative, and slightly ironic, and the pacing of our food was prompt without feeling rushed. Â Unfortunately, I just cant say I liked the food particularly. Â A couple of the early sushi/etc. dishes were tasty, vibrant, and flavorful. Â But most of the others I found indifferent, occasionally mildly pleasant, occasionally mildly unpleasant. Â And I am fully willing to concede that this may be a matter of taste (except for the occasional unbalanced dressings, and unripe avocado), but given Kai Zans reputation I was quite surprised to be left with ok.I would be inclined to bump up the rating given how nice they are and how superb the hospitality is, but I also have to think about price. Â There are a lot of places in Chicago where you can have a mind-blowing evening for this kind of money. Â I feel honor-bound to tell you that I do not think this is one of them.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yccc14',707,'2020-12-13',5,'A cozy little Japanese restaurant in Logan Sq. Â The Omakase menu showcases the breadth of their menu so it is worth to try. Â For a few additional dollars they will upgrade the Omakase with Uni - definitely go for it! We sat by the bar fronting the kitchen so apart from the decadent array of delicious seafood, we get to watch Melvin & Carlo perform their craft. What a great experience overall!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',567,'2021-08-30',5,'Incredible! I surprised my husband with a midweek dinner and they did not disappoint. We enjoyed it immensely, everything was wonderful from start to finish. Staff was kind and took good care of us. Anyone that says they dont like sushi, needs to come here and taste how sushi should be!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',458,'2016-12-16',5,'Favorite sushi bar in the city/ suburbs. Just so happened to move across the street.... been there once a week since . Chefs special recommended.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',1454,'2017-06-14',5,'This is without a doubt the greatest restaurant in the city and Im pretty damn picky and critical. The food was beyond what I could have expected in both flavor and presentation. Â I generally try to avoid ogling and photo documenting my meals but I couldnt even believe how unreal these dishes looked and I wanted a momento! The service was very attentive and beautifully orchestrated. Â We were literally depressed when the last dish of our omakase was brought out but we will be back very very soon I hope.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus528',1664,'2020-09-27',5,'Really good. Impressive in fact.I suffer from something known as I think I am a foody and Im also half Japanese. Call it Halfu Foody Syndrome. So I have eternally low expectations of every sushi place I go to because its basically become Asian fast food.Kai Zan was great, the best sushi place Ive been to in years.We had the $60/ person 10 course dinner plus a drink. Basically the 10 courses hit everything on their menu so I dont need to type it out.The flavors were great. Some heat, nothing really over the top. Salty but nothing I would change.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean67124',690,'2018-08-05',4,'The omakase is the way to go. I had the standard omakase ($65) and my husband had the premium omakase ($120). Both meals were amazing and each dish was fresh and flavorful. We completed our dinner feeling it was just the right amount of food, without feeling stuffed or deprived. Service was fast and knowledgeable. Street parking was easy to find on Chicago ave.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',516,'2017-04-03',5,'Nice sushi place that has a $60 prix fix menu , and regular menus, but has 2 items that are well worth it. I think the snapper piece is a real good item but the name escapes me (its the second plate that comes out) and the blue crush of tuna is also good. Perhaps just order these and save money. And grab a burger after. My biggest dislike is the use of mayonnaise (aka Chipoltle sauce or spicy mayo) in almost every dish. I think the fish could stand without this crutch.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',976,'2016-04-24',5,'My buddy and I got late reservations here on a thursday night. We sat at the bar with the sushi chefs. I will only say this. Â If you have never been here before, and I hadnt before this trip, get the 9 course tasting menu for like 70 dollars per person. Â It changed my life. When my wife told me she was pregnant with our daughter I didnt cry. Â The second course of this tasting menu brought tears to my eyes. I never had anything like it. Â The shooters with the raw egg is crazy too!Great space, quaint. Awesome atmosphere. Not great for big groups. If you love food and this type of sushi experience, really, really , really great!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',492,'2016-12-23',4,'The waiter that took our order wasnt friendly. He looked like he was constantly despising other people and treated us like 2-year olds. But.... the food was great! So good that we could completely ignore the waiter as he ignored us. We ordered a $70 omakase ($60 if you dont want to share), 2 chutoro nigiris and a chicken teriyaki. I cant say I enjoyed all of them, and because there was no desert so it didnt feel like a complete omakase meal, but some of the dishes were AMAZINGLY Delicious.A lot of the things were not on the menu. But if you have sth you want in mind, you can always ask them to prepare it for you. (Heres our waiter trying to look like a pro I mean, if youre a sushi bar, you have to have those things.)',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',1630,'2016-06-02',5,'Arlene was our server... She was awesome and helped us through the menu.... The food was outstanding... Â everything she suggested was on point... I would eat there everyday if I could.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a83185',116,'2017-06-11',5,'Byob with cork fee. Creativish omakase menu, very diverse selection, otherwise, could go with a la carte which is fine too',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',145,'2019-02-16',4,'Always a good time! This is my favorite Japanese restaurant in Chicago  the sushi is fresh and delicious. The ambience is intimate and relaxing. You wont regret getting the premium omakase! Its worth the price. Outside of the premium omakase I love the uni/tuna hand roll (though you do have to make it yourself) and the dynamics mussels!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi5344',750,'2021-04-05',5,'The service is spectacular. Although we were designated with one server, multiple staffs check in with us and brought our food. Water was always filled. They had complementary green tea. It was amazing to sit in the bar because you will have the experience to watch the sushi chefs and cooks make the food for you. It was very enjoyable to watch. They take their time and are so careful with their food. I would suggest getting Â the omasake if its your first time. Its a sample of all their specialties for $60 which included about Â 9-10 courses of food. Personally, I thought the cooked food was alright. However, what was really delicious was the sushi and fish. I have never had fish this fresh. Its so fresh that it doesnt even taste like fish. Once you eat here, youll realize what you have been missing your whole life. I love this place and recommend everyone to try this place. You will not regret! Proceed with caution as you will get addicted.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',1257,'2017-07-18',5,'This is the best restaurant in Chicago by far. Including all those Achatz places. Just have the waitstaff (especially the chefs sister, if youre lucky enough to get her) bring whatever the chef likes. Youll be blown away.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc61133',1348,'2016-03-24',5,'I never liked sushi bEfore but Â I after trying this place! Oh Jesus Im in love with sushi. The way you guys have it is beyond perfect I would definitely recommend this place!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',479,'2019-05-19',5,'One of the best sushi places Ive been to!!! Â You must get the chefs tasting menu. A sampler of many things that were all super tasty. Â Fresh taste with perfect flavors mixed together.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',1171,'2016-06-21',5,'The Omakase here are sooo amazing! Went here for my husbands birthday, had the best seats in the house at the sushi bar so we could watch the magic happen. Had a great time talking with the head chefs, twin brothers, who were super interested in knowing which dishes we loved, just liked, etc. You could tell theyre constantly working to innovate and ensure the customers LOVE each dish they serve. You really get a TON of food for your money with their omakase too. We were completely stuffed and unbelievably satisfied. To be able to try the greatest number of dishes we did one of the market omakase ($110) and one of the original omakase ($65). Both were full of unique dishes, no monotony in these menus. Also the servers were FANTASTIC. They all worked together as a team so well and no matter who was delivering a dish to our table they spent time describing in detail the ingredients and dish in front of us. We will definitely be back here!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis14141',1036,'2018-06-26',4,'One of the best japanese restaurants in Chicago ... hands down... no question... actually it is the best ive had other than nobuki in hinsdale, but their target and menu style is completely different.Menu is creative and the presentation is even better. Food quality is superb and the staff is amazingly attentive. very small, need a reservation... so worth it.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',419,'2018-10-02',4,'This was one of the best, if not the best, sushi experiences Ive ever had. You wouldnt expect it from its location but Kai Zan is such a gold mine! I took my girlfriend for a celebration dinner and was not disappointed. We ordered two chefs choice omaske and it was more than filling with 10 courses each. Albeit pretty pricey, it was worth it for such a special occasion. I do not think Ive ever had such delicious combinations of sushi and it even got me to step out of my usual and try some unique courses. The sashimi was so fresh and quality, the angry crab appetizer was so good I almost ordered another. The oyster and scallop shooters were not something I would typically order but I still enjoyed it. I would highly recommend this place for anyone looking for a special date night. It really brings one out of Humble Park and feels more like dining in Manhattan or Santa Monica. I would hope to go back soon!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede4256',1357,'2018-07-03',5,'We have been here twice and are excited to return for a special occasion again sometime! Everything they serve is perfection. The only downside is the small space and reservations/ wait. But it is well worth the wait. The best sushi in Chicago for sure. Also the best sushi we have ever had. The wait staff is super kind and informative. They support local breweries. The Hi Kitty Kitty is yummy.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quisque750',1624,'2017-05-16',3,'The best sushi in the city, hands down. I cant say enough good things about the food, the service and the ambiance. Everything on the menu is fantastic, if you havent been, go.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede23147',1671,'2021-12-05',5,'The quintessential Chicago fine dining experience. Â Food is creative yet comforting. Perfectly executed but not pretensions. Cozy decor, bustling room. Ive taken my girlfriend to many gluten-free restaurants and this place by far went above and beyond expectations. Â All staff and chefs made it a point to let her know they were aware and accommodating to her requests.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl36148',454,'2019-03-16',5,'Had one of my favorite meals ever at Kai Zan and what a deal it was at $60 a person! Im someone who generally orders similar things over and over even though I want to be trying new things, so a tasting menu is ideal. Not one course in this 11-course tasting menu let me down. The sashimi was melt in your mouth good, the mussel was dreamy, the pearls were divine. Ooh my mouth is watering.See my picture for most of the courses and do yourself a favor and go here ASAP.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',402,'2017-01-08',4,'Hands down one of the best Omakase I had so far. My boyfriend and I are sushi fanatics so when we decided to travel to Chicago, we started searching for a great sushi place. Kai Zan stood out because of their uni toro tartare that I still DREAM about to this day. It was a perfect combination of cream and umami. A must try if you decide to come here. Now for the Omakase, each dish had a different flavoring which was really refreshing to your palette. The fish were either fantastically seared or extremely fresh. You will definitely feel super full after and the price was not bad at all if you compare it to the quality of the food. 10/10 would recommend. Thank you Kai Zan for making me leave a piece of my heart in Chicago.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci23113',328,'2018-07-31',5,'Overall food was great. We were seated at a small room, and service was good overall. Some of us did the tasting menu and it was plenty of food for each of us. I wish the sashimi course came out first so I can enjoy the fresh fish first before trying other heavily sauced courses.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',297,'2017-12-17',5,'Love it!!!! Â Amazing place!! Â Weve been going there 2-3 times a month. Best place ever.. wont go to any other sushi place.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',1199,'2016-12-18',4,'OMG! No words can describe how good this place is. We did the Omakase and am happy we did! We already made another reservation for next month!!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',403,'2017-03-29',5,'This spot is a favorite that we try to visit 2-3 times a year. The omakase never disappoints and the service is always great. Personally prefer sitting at the bar to watch the action. Â Good tempo to the courses and never leave hungry.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ac67183',745,'2016-07-06',5,'Honest review (best sushi in chicago be warned its expensive to make reservation u have to give them ur credit card number n will be charges if u dont show up ) been here three times i love sushi n all of the places in chicago this is by far the best. The ambiance is pretty perfect for date nights the service is top notch only had bad service one time. If ur looking for unique sushi that doesnt have imitation crab or cream cheese this is the place for you ps bring back the black bean ice cream plz!! N plz put those cute edible orchids in dishes like before i miss that. If u dont wanna get the chef tasting menu order this exactly for the best meal of ur life angry crab/orange rush/ calamari/ escolar pearls/flaming tuna roll duck on a stick/pork belly/collar of the day/ fried octopus/grilled scallop nigiri/ for dessert Charred kabocha chocolate mouse and get the specials!! Always get all of the specialsMiso soup i liked this better then the tuna dashi. It has alot of mushrooms which i love the soup is really hot perfect when its cold the mushrooms arent cooked there in the soup raw but the heat of the broth makes themSoft. Then theres tofu which is really interesting there so soft only complaint would be more depth of flavor its good but not to the point where id order againTuna dashi this was okay not my fav its interesting it tastes like ocean water u know when u go swim n the water goes in ur mouth on accident thats what it tastes like wouldnt order again fix the fishy tasteFried octopus this was really flavorful the sauce was divine really rich really enhances the dish the octopus is really tender however i wish there was a bigger piece inside the bonito flakes werent an odd texture thats what made it perfectGreen monster good but not enough filling in the middle bbq eel needs more filling Fiesta roll really delicious u could really taste the seafood then theres avocado nothings better then that in sushi. I didnt taste any jalepeno or the other mexican flavors though its not a bad roll just i was expecting jalepeno didnt get that Wagyu pearls omg food-gasim the beef is cooked to perfect to the point where it melts in ur mouth. Then theres truffle on it this is so rich to the point where ur mouth feels likeIts in heaven Fried chicken its perfectly crisp to the point of sounding like photochips it isnt greasy at all the chicken was really tender. The problem was it had no sauce and was really bland actually. Put a sauce on plz!!!! We asked for hot sauce n they gave us a mayo with chili oil that made it extra good with soy sauce added to for a much needed salt flavorOrange rush presentation so cute! This is one of my favorites i usually dont like acidic dishes because there to acidic but this isnt at all the orange flavor goes perfectly with the richness of the fish. The seafood is cooked perfectly Grilled scallop nigiri omg when scallops are cooked perfectly its like eating a cloud just melts in ur mouth the sauces went perfect with the fish to make it rich but not to overpowering a must order!!Tuna belly if u never tried tuna belly order it now its better then any other tuna sushi u ever had before. This is really high quality topshelf tuna. Its cooked perfectly so it melts in ur mouth ur tastebuds will love u if u order thisYaki soba i was a little skeptical but its delicious this is the only dish where they give u a big portion. The noodles are cooked perfectly seasoned beautifully theres alot of texture i recommend ordering it with a meat Char sui (pork belly) omg omg best pork belly ever!! Its so good i love pork belly this by far was my favorite rendition of it. Its cooked perfectly so the fatty parts melt in ur mouth its not tuff at all. The sauce is to die for and the kimchi is kinda mild which it was more spicier n vinegary the sauce is to die for ask for extra though theres only a lil bitFish collar (salmon) {warning bones alot to the point where its easy to choke} omg order this! fish collar is the equivalent of a seafood ribeye. Its so rich like it has such a great fish flavor cooked perfectly the sauce adds a much needed salty richness u wont regret ordering thisCharred kabocha (best dessert ever) picture like a pumpkin pie but a 100 times better it was amazin the pumpkin was cooked perfectly not hard seasoned just right to remind u of thanksgivin. The icecream perfect texture complimented the pumpkin beutifully the best part was the pecan streusal amaizin so crunchy ask for more streusal thoughChocolate mouse this was our second favorite dessert. Its really delicous the rice crispy is really cruncy tastes like a gormea cereal. The mouse is rich not bitter must orderMochi good homemade i only had this once so cant really comment on itApple pie shot i feel its just crumpled up apple pie in apple cider the apple pie part is great the liquid was a lil bland nobody liked it',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo40189',1318,'2017-04-25',4,'Our favorite sushi spot in Chicago. We always get the omakase and order the green monster. It is the freshest sushi Ive ever had. The servers are always very attentive and will give you suggestions as well. The best thing is they allow you to split the omakase for an additional fee. Its also BYOB so thats another huge plus! The only downside is that its hard to get into, you need reservations far in advance, but it is so worth the wait!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',1205,'2017-12-16',5,'It was hard to make a reservation. We made a reservation after 940pm at Sat. Had premium Omakase and regular Omakase. Both were really great! But the price of premium is double of regular one. I think it was not worth it that price. But overall it was really good experience at Chicago.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',222,'2020-02-11',5,'Absolutely amazing sushi and beautiful ambience. Highly recommend Kai Zan, love coming here!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',1228,'2020-04-06',5,'Completely blown away by my experience at this unassuming 46-seat eatery tucked away in Chicagos Humboldt Park neighborhood. The restaurant itself is very tiny with limited seating so making reservations in advance is highly recommended (almost required if youre in a large group). There are seats at the sushi bar as well as intimate cozy booths where we were seated (booths seat six people comfortably). After taking our seats, we were greeted by our server who gave each of us hot towels to clean our hands which I thought was a very lovely touch. He explained the concept of the restaurant and answered any questions we had regarding the menu. For those who havent been to Kai Zan, I recommend going with the chefs choice omakase which costs you $60, but you get to sample some of the most popular items on the menu and its so much food! This way, the next time you come (...and you will be back, trust me...), youll know exactly what to get. Below is what we had on the omakase menu on our visit to Kai Zan with some extra dishes.COURSE 1 - ESCOLAR and MAGURO PEARLSOur omakase experience off with a big flavorful bang. These pearls were an absolute treat. I contemplated ordering more after finishing my four pieces. Hell, I contemplated stealing my friends pearls while they werent looking. These little nuggets of deliciousness are topped with soy and truffle oil soaked scallions which take the incredibly fresh cuts of fish to another level.COURSE 2 - MADAI CARPACCIO Slices of red snapper topped with fatty toro, black tobiko that pops in your mouth and drizzled with olive oil and soy sauce. I enjoyed this dish, but to be honest, I was still thinking about those pearls lolCOURSE 3 - OYSTER AND SCALLOP SHOOTERSI have been looking forward to trying the shooters ever since we booked the reservation and they did not disappoint! Both shooters were served in a citrusy ponzu sauce with a rich quail egg and dash of spicy Tabasco sauce. The meaty scallop was so sweet and succulent, but my favorite was the briny oyster shooters. I couldve eaten another 5 or 10 - SO GOOD!COURSE 4 - ANGRY CRAB The angry crab was a tasty bite with spicy crab wrapped in fresh tuna and topped with crispy tempura flakes COURSE 5 - TUNATINI This course was a party in your mouth because there were so many different textures with each bite you took from the buttery tuna to the crispy polenta to the herbaceous shiso leaf to the salty black tobiko that popped in your mouth.COURSE 6 - DASHIThis piping hot cup of dashi broth was just what we needed on a cold rainy Chicago night loaded with mushrooms, tuna, clams and sesame seeds -- warmed and satisfied our tummies.COURSE 7 - SHRIMP. TAKOYAKI. PORK BELLY. OCTOPUS SALADSampling of four dishes shrimp was served with shiitake and garlic butter. The takoyaki was perfect -- crisp exterior and gooey center with octopus inside topped with wasabi mayo and bonito flakes. The pork belly was so unctuous, tender and juicy; it practically melted in my mouth. The octopus salad ways my least favorite out of the quartet of offerings -- too much wasabi that overwhelmed everything else in the dish.COURSE 8 - DYNAMITE MUSSELSThese are gigantic New Zealand mussels that are steamed with sake and topped with black tobiko and negi mayo. AMAZING -- I need the recipe because I could devour a platter all by myself.COURSE 9 - FLAMING TUNA. GREEN MONSTER. FIESTA MAKIMy favorite was the flaming tuna which is a shrimp tempura roll topped with seared tuna and truffle soaked scallions so basically the pearls on steroids haha. The fiesta maki has all my favorite things salmon, tuna, jalapeÃ±o, cilantro, avocado and masago. I enjoyed the green monster, but compared to the other rolls, it was my least favorite; the texture was too soft.COURSE 10 - ESCOLAR. SALMON. YELLOWTAIL. TUNAEach piece of sashimi I tasted was incredibly fresh; my favorites were the escolar and salmon - rich, buttery and fatty.DESSERTS - CHOCOLATE MOUSSE & KABOCHA My friends ended the meal on a sweet note with chocolate mousse with puffed rice and green tea sauce as well as charred kabocha squash which was served with ice cream. The mousse was good although there was an ingredient in it none of my friends could quite put our fingers on. I didnt try the squash, but everyone seemed to enjoy it.EXTRAS - TORO UNI TARTAREEven though I was already full, I haaad to order it! Fatty toro and buttery uni served over a bed of sushi rice with quail eggs, scallions and freshly grated wasabi. How bad could that be?! Served with nori so you can make diy rolls. Cant even put into words how good it was - truly exceptional and flavors were sublime! ORDER THIS!Everybody from the hostess to the servers was incredibly gracious, attentive and knowledgeable about everything on the menu. Service was paced beautifully where we never felt rushed to leave. Im counting down the days until I can return for another drool-worthy dinner experience!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit96122',876,'2019-10-28',5,'Some of the best sushi Ive had in Chicago! Their uni and toro appetizer is to die for, I literally dream about it! Their omakase dinners are amazing and very affordable for sushi. I also recommend ordering off the menu or sitting at the bar. The servers are always very nice and attentive. I still come back here when I am in town from LA because it is totally worth it so make sure you get a reso ahead of time!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',1195,'2021-07-11',4,'Probably the best sushi in town. Â Make reservations, not easy to walk in and dine. Â Everything on the menu is amazing. Worth the wait and $$$',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede4256',358,'2018-11-10',5,'Might be the best sushi Ive ever had. This was THE place that my friends wanted to take me during my most recent visit to Chicago. The restaurant itself is tiny, so if you miss your reservation, youre out of luck.We debated getting the omakase (chefs tasting menu) as one of my friends has had it before and there were a couple of items he would have swapped/werent our preferences. We ended up going the a la carte route but ordering some of what would have been on the omakase, plus getting some additional suggestions from our server (thanks Arlene!). This allowed us to taste some of the best that Kai Zan has to offer while catering to our personal tastes and was comparable price wise.For the benefit of you, my reader, I will share what we got - all of which were uh-may-zing. I was unsure if this would be enough for 3 people, but it was the perfect amount of food.Escolar PearlsUni Toro TartareAngry CrabTempura MadaiChar Siu KushiMadai CarpaccioBlue Fin MartiniFiesta RollSpecial of the day (dont remember)And for dessert - sweet potato mochi',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',396,'2017-11-11',5,'Kai zan, Kai zan... what can I say. You are my food crush for LIFE. Every foodies dream come true. You make me want to bring someone special here to experience you JUST to witness their reaction. Ive followed Melvin and Carlo from old Kyoto to this place. I remember one late night a couple years back reading about this new Japanese place opening up in Chicago Magazine. These two brothers who pretty much made Kyoto a hot spot in Chicago where opening their own place. I knew right away it was Melvin and Carlo. Theyve changed the sushi game. True perfectionists. The MJs of sushi. The number one sushi spot in Chicago is this place. Everything they make is amazing. Go for the chefs choice, you wont be disappointed. Ive tried both ordering off the menu and chefs choice before. Chefs choice is exhilarating because you never get the same thing twice and they create items they havent even named and probably made up on the fly. These two are geniuses and presentation is beautiful which leaves you with a lasting impression. One thing I crave daily is the Escolar pearls (Maguro pearls are great too) ..... Amazing!!! One night we ordered it 6 times. Im brought my toughest sushi critics here and converted them over without even trying. The food speaks for itself. Favorite sushi spot in Chicago is KaiZan.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',1449,'2019-02-24',4,'Unbelievable experience. From ambiance to the service to the delicious and fresh fish. We had such a great time here. The sushi presentation and array of flavors and textures were exactly on point. The best sushi we have ever had. Arlene was our server (who was adorable) and gave us a ton of info on each of the dishes and choices as well as a little background on the restaurant itself--beautifully done and would highly recommend this fantastic family owned restaurant!!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',1145,'2018-12-07',5,'I enjoyed my meal very much. Extremely well organized staff Â polite and efficient. Â  The non sushi entree was average. All of the sushi was fresh and I feel good the next day. Â  Interesting combinations. Â Nice finish with full size meal type sushi at the end. 4.5 stars had the tasting price fixed Â  Good green tea. Â Nice rapid fire service. Â  A little Tabasco was added at the right times. Interesting non commercialized neighboorhoood.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',1545,'2017-05-12',5,'This is probably my favorite sushi place in Chicago. Not only is the presentation amazing, but it it is delicious. The Â  Â Omakase menu doesnt seem to change often. Ive been there in 3 times in year (August 2017, September 2018, and August 2018) and only one or two things changed on the Premium Omakase and Omakase menu. This place is definitely worth trying.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempus72169',1597,'2020-12-05',4,'Amazing sushi experience - we did new omakase. True sushi experience, with very developed flavors. Not just your trendy flashy sushi. Felt like we were in New York. Only negative was the continuous reminders that we only had 90 minutes for our reservation. Was told while making reservation, confirming and being seated - overkill and a little off putting.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus0123',1460,'2021-09-28',5,'Waiter told me since he was a waiter, its none of his business for my logistics recommendations to the restaurant, when I suggested they should begin a valet service because of the impossible street parking nearby that left us no time to take the tasting menu. Oh and speaking of the menu, Im glad that I didnt take it because, as an Asian, Ive never seen anything like this in Asia, especially my favorite country Japan. I think there might have been a mistake - the restaurant is contemporary American, not Japanese. Just because you use raw fish doesnt make you Japanese.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',425,'2017-01-11',5,'Each of the stars above represents 2 stars, because this place deserves 10!!! Simply blown away by the omakase -- the variety, the balance of flavors, the sheer amount, the quality of the ingredients, and of course the price. Excellent marriage between traditional Japanese and Western influences. Service was top notch too, servers very knowledgeable about the dishes and very considerate. I almost want to keep this to myself so I can still get a reservation easily!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',1627,'2016-01-21',5,'Man!!! This hit me right on every level. I love Asian food. Kimchee, sushi, bibimbap, sashimi, etc. Â This place has it all. And they had amazing service. I went with the Chefs Choice. 10 amazing plates. I was stuffed. Tip get the pickled vegetables...they were electrifying.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum7621',1248,'2016-01-09',4,'Came back here yesterday and this place is my hands down favorite restaurant in the city but please dont share with too many people! Â I ordered their new omakase menu (12 course for $90) and it was amazing. Â They still are offering the old one as well because people love it. Â I will only share a few of my favorites dishes but one was the Eskimo cloud, the seared lobster and scallop nigiri, and the salmon skin (think of a chicharone) topped with toro tartar. Â I hope this review doesnt encourage anyone to go because I still want to be able to get a rezzy.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ullamcorper075',442,'2019-09-19',5,'The folks at Kai Zan are family...and they happen to be the best chefs in the city as far as were concerned. We are longtime lovers of everything Kai Zan has to offer. The classics remain consistently top notch. There are always new dishes to entice and keep us wanting more. It was our best kept secret, until the rest of the city caught on. We only extend a Kai Zan invite to our most deserving friends. Treat your palate to Kai Zan, or dont...in which case I have a better chance of getting a reservation for myself.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra74104',1366,'2016-07-21',5,'How many people have I brought here who have left with a new opinion of what sushi can be? Each time I bring someone new I think Maybe this will be the time that someone doesnt fall in love and moan when they try the escolar pearls; maybe they will have had sushi that compares, but no, fate has other plans.Get the escolar pearls (twice!), the dynamite bites, the palenta bites, the wagyu with quail egg, the lobster with uni, the smoked samon in the smokey pot thing, and after that just tell the waiter to surprise you--you will not be disappointed. Shout out to Allen and Arlene for always making dinner here special.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',599,'2021-01-15',4,'We went here for an early dinner on Saturday, and we were able to get a reservation for 430 at 345, which was very convenient. When we arrived we were seated right away and greeted with warm towels (always a nice touch). We were so hungry, we made the mistake of ordering a lot of appetizers the calamari, the beef skewer, octopus skewer, and pork belly skewer. Then we ALSO ordered four sushi rolls Green Monster, Flaming Tuna, Fiesta Roll, and Spicy Tuna roll. In retrospect, we would have only ordered the sushi because every roll was so delicious and fresh and unique. The skewers and the calamari were ok, but I wouldnt order them again. They are the reason Im giving Kai Zan 4 stars instead of 5. The calamari was tough to eat. The sushi on the other hand, was PHENOMENAL. The Fiesta roll was so fresh and full of fish, but it was so so so spicy. My favorite roll was the Green Monster, which is rolled in avocado. I cant imagine thats easy to do, but it was well worth the effort. When I return to Kai Zan itll be for sushi only. They also have a great list of wine and beer, including some Japanese imports.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',1361,'2021-09-20',5,'Sixty dollar omakase?! Yes, please! If youre not familiar with the term omakase, it basically means youre leaving it up to the chef to decide what youll be eating. Definitely not recommended if youre a picky eater, especially when it comes to seafood. The omakase special included at least 10 assorted dishes, all of which were delicious. Overall, Kai Zan exceeded my expectations. I didnt think the quality of the dishes would be good (the price is pretty cheap for the quality of seafood youre getting). I also didnt think I would leave full (again, the price is cheap for the quantity of food). I left the restaurant very pleased (and extremely full) and can honestly say this was one of the best sushi experiences Ive ever had. The restaurant is really nice and the staff were all friendly and attentive. I would definitely come back for the omakase.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',1416,'2021-10-22',5,'Worst place. Total rip off. White hostess tries to sell Asian food as fast as she can. They rush you and charge a lot more than I pay in San Francisco. Pls stay away unless you want to throw $$ away.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',1554,'2017-07-22',5,'This was one of the best sushi restaurants I have ever been to. Omakase was the spectacular. And amazing service. A neighborhood gem!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',425,'2018-12-24',5,'Kai Zan offers a unique take on sushi; the sushi is, by no means, traditional, but at the same time the flavors work quite well. The omakase is 15 courses and definitely enough for two people to share, especially if you double up on some of the items that come in one portion. My favorites were the madai carpaccio, escolar pearls, and the polenta bites (I think--this was on the house). While Im usually not a huge fan of anything that deviates from traditional sushi, I appreciated the creativity that went into the rolls--the flavors were unique and well thought out. The kale in the polenta bites, for instance, was crispy, and the slightly bitter flavors worked surprisingly well with the toro. We also got an order of the madai collar, which was also quite good and well priced for the portion size.The one thing I would stay away from would be the traditional sashimi; this may have been an off day, but the sashimi I had was not very fresh, especially the maguro, which was a very oxidized, dark color. Hence the fiesta maki I got that day was also not very good. Â Overall, this was more of a 3.5 rating because of the lack of fresh sashimi. The hits, though, were enough for me to give them the benefit of the doubt.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl36148',436,'2017-02-08',4,'Very very tasty.Cute placeMenu very limited Left spending a lot and was still hungry',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',917,'2021-01-08',5,'If I could afford to eat here every day I would. The menu is refined and the atmosphere is surprisingly relaxed. Ive been 3 times now and was never once disappointed with the service or the food. Im a big fan of sushi and can wholeheartedly say this is my favorite restaurant in all of Chicago. If youre going on a date or just taking a friend out and want to impress them this is the place to go.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yccc14',833,'2017-05-19',5,'Let me start by saying how amazing every experience has been!! Â You will not be disappointed!! Our favorite is the Escolar pearls but be sure that Chef Melvin and Carlo will surprise you with their talent!!!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',984,'2019-03-01',4,'Ive had the pleasure of coming here 3 separate times, and each time kept me convinced it was my favorite restaurant in the city of Chicago. Â I ordered the standard omakase each time, which is a series of mostly single bite items. Â Everything is described by staff in detail as its delivered to the table so customers arent kept guessing what has arrived (its not always obvious what youre eating).Every single course is like magic. Â Its unlike any sushi/sashimi spot Ive ever been to. Â The standard omakase never leaves me stuffed by the end, but always sufficiently satisfied.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',832,'2016-03-12',5,'Id give 4 or 5 stars for flavor of dishes. Â Went to 2 for the service. Waitress didnt know anything about the menu or ingredients in the food and didnt bother to ask the chef but just made up answers. Â She told us that we didnt need soy sauce after we asked for some and we had to ask for wasabi even though all our food was raw fish sushi and dishes didnt have wasabi in them. Hopefully she was just having a bad few moments. The other staff were attentive and accommodating.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',494,'2018-07-05',5,'Love it here.. The food, the people and ambience is beautiful. Definitely coming back.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum5724',5,'2019-06-22',4,'I love this place!! I go here about once a month and it never disappoints. A couple things that I recommend you orderUni, uni, and some more uniAngry crab= deliciosoEscolar Pearls if you live super white tuna this is a must!!Escolar wrapped oysters with ponzu foam Im not a fan of oysters but theses were good.Try I nab a seat at the sushi bar. The chefs are great and super friendly',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',1212,'2018-01-02',5,'You really cant go wrong here. Awesome service, byob, and amazing menu. My favorite was the angry crab. Save room for the mochi; its made in house, its so fresh and fruity, and its an amazing way to end the meal. Zero complaints. Definitely make a reservation!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat4359',1521,'2018-08-30',5,'Wow!!! Â  The quality of the ingredients is unreal. Â Every dish was fantastic.Highlights were dynamite mussels and angry crab. Â Really top notch sushi all around. Â The place is small and strict on times so dont expect a 2.5 hour dinner. Â If you want a great dinner in an hour or less, this place was perfect.Also, service was great. Â We had Justin and he gave us great recommendations and got us through a quick dinner that never felt rushed.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',576,'2018-08-09',4,'best experience of my life. eating sushi will never ever be the same anymore.i dont remember what we ordered, but every single dish that came out was outstanding.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',650,'2019-01-03',5,'The Omakase is incredibly innovative and reasonably priced. Â We were expecting something authentic but it was nevertheless a happy surprise. Also our waiter is super nice! The only unsatisfactory is that we arrived 5min early than our 430 pm reservation (yes its that hard to get a reservation on Sats). It was freezing and we asked the hostess if we can wait inside even though they are not open yet. The way she refused is somewhat condescending and left us unpleasant.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ac67183',752,'2019-04-24',5,'Its amazing. Every time. Â Try things you dont think youd normally like. Â Every thing is delicious, creative, and beautifully plated. Â The servers/kitchen staff are so fun!!!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',331,'2021-07-15',4,'Amazing sushi dinner! Beautiful presentation & everything tasted fresh and savory. Creative preparations of classics. The Omikase, 10 course chefs choice, is very impressive but you have to go with a big appetite! Must have additions wagyu nigiri and the wagyu fried rice (incredible!). Reserve one of their 4 private bamboo rooms- so special! Definitely coming back here for another special event!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',581,'2020-03-26',5,'Great food tempered by a somewhat mediocre overall experience.First, the food. Did the 10 course omakase with the optional uni addition. Angry crab, escolar pearls, and dynamite mussels were all stand outs. Presentation was gorgeous and food was consistently tasty.As others have mentioned, the time limit was probably the most grating part of the experience. Made sense when they were BYOB; downright off-putting now that they are a reasonably pricey, destination sushi spot. We were there celebrating an early Valentines Day and nothing destroys a celebration like being in a rush.Potentially more problematic is the impact of the time limit on the food. The 10 courses came out at rapid speed, sometimes on top of each other. We had zero time to discuss or consider or even really commit the food to memory before the next course arrived. Doesnt lend itself to a good restaurant experience.Tl;dr-- Fine for a casual evening where you want a pricey but tasty meal. Time limit means this is not a place for occasions or celebrations.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',1268,'2019-06-26',5,'I am an avid sushi lover and this place met and surpassed my expectations.I took my boyfriend here for his birthday dinner and we both ordered the omakase. Â It was a fabulous sampling of the favorites from the Kai Zan menu. Â The grand finale was a beautiful plate of fresh sashimi pieces, which were incredible.If you love sushi and have not been here yet, it is a MUST-DO.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit96122',95,'2021-09-04',5,'Really good place if you enjoy creative and tasteful Japanese dishes. We had the vday omasake and did not regret it at all. The place is fully booked so we just had 1 and a half hour to finish 10 courses, which was a bit too tight time wise.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede2192',1144,'2020-05-17',4,'If youre looking at this review, its because youre thinking about eating here. Just do it already!Ive been here three times, originally prompted by my friends telling me all about their experiences. The chefs tasting menu has fantastic value if youre not a picky eater. As for my boyfriend, he would rather select what he eats for himself which he was very happy with. One of the dishes was an entree item that was like noodles, sauce, veggies, and meat and it was so good and their other entrees were well priced so we will be back for that sooner than waiting for something special to happen for their sushi!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1579,'2017-10-14',5,'Amazing!!! Carlo and Melvin are phenomenal! Each piece is a work of art. Â Arlene was super helpful with suggestions and very attentive. I dont remember all the names of what we got but just trust the chefs recommendations!!! Also, save room for desert, they arent too large and worth trying!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',1478,'2018-07-25',5,'Everything was perfect and the service is fastFresh fish, great presentation, intimate and cozy, will recommend that place!But you have to be on time for your reservation The place is small and very busy',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',1010,'2019-09-30',4,'Hot damn, this is hands down the best sushi restaurant in Chicago. Â They do everything exceptionally well. Â I actually cant say I have been to a better sushi restaurant in the country, and I have been to quite a few. Â The only place that comes close is the original Nobu in NY, and id rather eat at Kai Zan any day of the week. I just wish it was easier to get reservations.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',1345,'2016-10-31',5,'Its amazing. Everything about the experience is fantastic. The only con is that the restaurant knows it and they treat you like a third grader in regards to when you need to be out of your table for the next seating. I know its to set expectations but its a little paternalistic and it sounds like Miss Price from the first grade whenever they tell you about it.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',1183,'2018-04-28',5,'I experienced their regular omakase which is a lovely sampling of their highlighted dishes. To say their service and food was amazing would be lacking. I have never had a more mind blowing and delicious meal in my life! I think Ive decided Ill make it a point to do this more than once a year! Â Your server offered a great sake to pair with the meals.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis34168',1228,'2021-05-27',5,'I absolutely loved it here! I did the omakase and for $65, its one of the better deals. Everything was so full of flavor. The portions are tiny but its that kind of place so if youre looking for a hearty meal, dont come unless you plan to order a lot and spend more. If you appreciate fine dining though, to have to come! Some of my favorites were the orange rush, the maguro and escolar pearls and the fiesta roll.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ultrices32193',747,'2019-06-04',5,'If youre going to splurge (still amazing value)and like traditional sushi, this is your spot. Â Service a+, fish fresh, great sake recommendation, and smaller restaurant which I like. Â Excellent spot!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis2682',302,'2019-02-01',4,'Must try uni tar tar, perfect for a first date.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',1562,'2019-10-09',5,'So Im the type of person who hates going to a restaurant more then once, I live in Chicago and there are so many places to try! But Kai Zan is one of the few exceptions to this. Â Its the best sushi in Chicago! The service is impeccable. Â Everyone Ive taken here is always impressed. Â The omakase is such a great price for the food you get. Â Also, whatever you do, dont leave without trying the grilled hamachi nigiri and Maguro pearls.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',1535,'2019-10-27',5,'Great food and service. Cozy venue. Parking in the area is tough. Prices are high. Will go back again sometime but not often.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',1362,'2020-12-15',4,'Hands down best meal Ive ever had. Im a huge fan of sushi and Japanese cuisine all together and this just as good as it gets. Service was great, the chefs were asking us if everything was good...The experience overall was just top notch. Im looking forward to the next time!!!!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',731,'2017-12-17',5,'My husband and I totally enjoyed our meal here. Â Its a cute, TINY restaurant and the staff is excellent and extremely helpful. Â We shared the 10 course Omakase and ordered a couple of other dishes. Â If its your first time here, its a great way to get a taste of many of their dishes. Â When we come back next time, we will probably get some of our favorites from the Omakase and some new dishes off the regular menu. Â What makes their sushi so good are the flavor profiles that you usually dont get at other sushi restaurants. Â Our favorites were the maguro pearls and the madai carpacio. Â Our least favorite was the fiesta maki. Â The biggest downside is that you have to be out in 90 mins. Â We didnt need the full 90 mins., but could have if we had drinks and dessert.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',1142,'2018-02-05',5,'Not to be a downer, but I am going to have to give an okay-only review for Kai Zan, which I know might be rare. My friend and I both did the Omakase and while we were happy with our dinner and had high praise for most of the courses, it did not leave us with a positively glowing experience in contrast with the general raving we have seen so far. The cooked course, which I believe is third to last, was underwhelming at best. The last sashimi course was far from mindblowing, with thin slices of salmon, lean tuna, super white tuna and yellowtail that were not very fresh and feel like I could pay elsewhere for. My slight disappointment may also have something to do with the fact that they have no uni that day, which we were very disappointed to learn, although we respected that the uni offerings then were not up to par and we were better off without. This has been very good bang for buck for Omakase and great quality food all in all. I will be happy to try the Premium Omakase next time, but have to say this has not been the phenomenal experience that I had hoped for.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',451,'2020-07-13',4,'This was my third time here and it was just as exceptional as the other two times. I have always done the Omakase which is unbelievably creative, fresh, and delicious. This is hands down the best and most unique sushi place I have been to in Chicago. The prices are super reasonable and the service is impeccable. I truly believe that you are missing out if you have never dined at this restaurant.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam2176',463,'2017-07-23',5,'We used to love Kai Zan (and recommended them to everyone!), but unfortunately a poor service experience will prevent me from coming back or ever recommending this place again. Im quite disappointed since service was previously one of the most amazing parts of the experience.I made a reservation for family coming into town saying You have to try this place - best sushi / fusion since I was in Japan! They were running late (just flew in), and were told that they couldnt order the omakase if late by more than 15 mins. FYI, each reservation slot is for 90 minutes, and in my previous 4 times dining there, I always finished within 55 minutes, well ahead of the reserved timeslot. I got a call at 548pm (screenshot to prove it!) to confirm a reservation for the next day (yes I made another reservation), and the lady noticed that I had one for today and that they were running late (res at 530pm). During this phonecall, my family showed up at the restaurant. Even though they were only 3 minutes past the 15 min deadline (548 vs. 5;45), she wouldnt let them order the omakase.This whole experience along with the attitude of the lady on the phone has left a real poor mark on Kai Zan. She was very passive aggressive and kept replying I appreciate it when I pleaded to allow my family who flew in from out of town to order the omakase. Appreciate what?!Yes, we were late by 3 minutes, so our fault. However, the way the restaurant and the lady on phone handled the situation is not customer friendly. I dont understand why a mere 3 minutes makes an actual difference, especially when based on my prior experiences its more than enough time.Feel free to msg me for more details.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',1122,'2016-07-04',5,'Whatever you thought sushi was...you havent tried sushi until you have been here. We were eagerly anticipating our reservations and all our expectations were exceeded and more. We ordered the omakase shared it and ordered a few other different things off the menu. It was an explosion of flavors in your mouth. Presentation was beautiful. Staff was attentive and knowledgeable. It was a nice change of pace than the usual makis and nigiris at your average sushi joints. It was such a euphoric experience that we went again the following weekend to try the rest of the menu. This has become our new favorite place.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',636,'2016-01-08',5,'Hands down delicious! A hidden gem in Ukrainian Village by two chefs - brothers...twins actually!!!! - Melvin & Carlo who you can find at the sushi bar 5 nights a week...Tues - Sat. They are sweet and personable. Heres what we had and I cant rate them in any order because everything was equally delicious esclolar pearls, madai carpaccio, polenta bites (was super pleasantly surprised by this!), angry crab, orange rush, green monster, uni tuna special, yellowtail and salmon nigiri and mochi ube sorbet. Highly recommend! Â We will definitely be back! Thank you, Chefs!!!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sodales69101',942,'2020-03-22',5,'Its a not restaurant. Its a place to enjoy the beauty of food. Every dish is design art. Color, shape, composition all are awesome. The price is worth it. Hope everyone can enjoy at least try.)',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',1214,'2021-08-27',5,'A friend referred us to Kai Zan and it did not disappoint! The service was spot on and the food delicious. My husband and I have this bet going of the best sushi in Chicago and this is up there! We had Wagyu Fried Rice that was so flavorful we should have ordered the entree portion. The sushi was fresh and beautiful to look at. We had scallops that were done right. Only downside was you have 90 mins to have your table but we would go back.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc15',744,'2016-11-21',4,'the presentation is one of the best in Chicago and the food is very freshuni toro tartare (off-menu) is a must try, so fresh and very unique idea of wrapping your own sushithe uni shooter is awesome too, with a fresh raw quail egg insidei would also recommendshishito (very spicy though)orange crush',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',1533,'2017-11-22',5,'Express yourself isnt just a song by Madonna; its attitude, individuality, creativity, innovation, and interpretation coming to a full-circle. Â We came to Kai Zan this evening to celebrate our five (5)-year anniversary. Â Five (5) years ago, I said yes to my best friend, my gold-digger (ok...that was a joke), my chef at home, and most importantly, my foodie companion! Â Of course, a reservation is highly recommended, if not, required since the spots do get filled up quickly, for its a small venue. Â We were lucky because we sat right in front of Chef Carlo and Chef Melvin, the dynamic duo. Â Japan and I have a special connection. Â I didnt grow up watching Disney movies and playing my little pony. Â I had an unusual passion for dorama (Japanese soap operas). Â Among 1000 plus dorama Ive seen in my 29-year-old life so far, one of my favorites was the one titled Bambino, starring Jun Matsumoto (from a Japanese musical group, Arashi). Â Bambino was a nickname for a young man, who came to work at a popular Italian restaurant in Tokyo. Â He came from feeling conceited and thought he was Mr. Know-it-all. Â Soon after he experienced a series of frustrations at his work place. Â Finally, his transformation led him to becoming a professional who has gained respect and recognitions among his peers and supervisors. Â When I observed the professionals who were working in the kitchen, the scenes from Bambino came live in my head. Â How cool! Â I got to watch all the actions happening while enjoying great food. Â I think its time to talk about the Omakase. Â We chose the basic Omakase featuring Chefs recommendations ($60/person) from the menu. Â 1) fatty tuna maki roll (on the house) the natural, rich fat from the tuna was unbelievably abundant, but it was melted immediately in my mouth. Â What a great start of the night! Â 2) madai carpaccio I felt that it was an Italian take-on on Japanese red snapper. Â That basil miso was soothing and wasnt overly sour. Â It was a very elegant, sophisticated dish. Â 3) escolar/maguro pearls each piece of fish was perfectly seared. Â This was a good transition to the following courses. Â 4) uni and oyster shooter there was absolutely nothing to be intimidated by! Â The ponzu sauce was really smooth, which harmonized and acted like a lubricant to bring the oyster, uni, and quail egg altogether.5) angry crab the tuna and the spicy crab werent angry to each other! Â I felt the tuna was more of the protagonist, and the spicy crab played the auxiliary role. In other words, I tasted more of the tuna, not much of the spicy crab itself. Â 6) char siu/beef tataki surprisingly, this meat dish was light because of the addition of yuzu. Â 7) shiitake mushroom soup it also featured a tiny piece of oyster on the bottom. Â I enjoyed the broth; it was flavorful yet simple.8) an assortment of entree dishes what a luxury way to present the takoyaki! Â Although the takoyaki wasnt my favorite, the octopus with wasabi sauce was a nice change-up for the palate! Â You could definitely experience umami with this chefs creative combo. Â 9) dynamite mussel the flavor of sake was soaked throughly into the mussel. Â Sprinkling some of the lemon juice was a must! Â Im now have a brand-new perspective on mussels. Â 10) fiesta maki how could you go wrong with avocado and fresh raw seafood? Â 11) an assortment of sashimi the presentation was impeccable! Â That was an awesome final chapter of the Omakase. Â The service was very attentive. Â Dining at Kai Zan was certainly an unforgettable experience. Â I have no doubt that we will be back for the premium Omakase! Â The street parking was fairly easy on Chicago Ave. Â Otherwise, the CTA 66 (Chicago) bus can take you there, and be sure that you get off at Rockwell/Chicago.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra74104',368,'2018-03-22',5,'we have a group of 6. Each of us ordered the chefs special. The 65 -dollar meal. Its amazing and definitely worthy the value. The food is kind of fine art ,so pretty and tasty and the service is so good. I have recommended my colleague this restaurant for his anniversary with his girlfriend. Lol I am sure they will love it.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et65112',152,'2020-07-22',4,'The food here has always been good. Ive been here three times now. The prices are reasonable for the quality. Its by no means cheap to eat here, but its definitely worth it for the quality you get. The servers are always friendly too. So, why just three stars? Well, its because of the time restriction. We had an early reservation at 515 pm on a Thursday. We had exactly 90 minutes to finish our meal. From the start of the reservation, the clock starts ticking. We took a little while to decide what to order, but our food came super fast once we ordered. Since we were seated at the bar, we had to eat super fast to make room for the next dish. We felt super rushed. I really like their food, but the time restraint really dampens the experience. When we left it was 648 pm, and the sun was still out. I understand that its a small place, but if your business is doing so well, then maybe its time to expand. Its better than losing your customers.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('scelerisque1179',51,'2020-01-05',5,'As a vegetarian, they had very limited selection so I couldnt rate this high from my point of view. I have heard amazing things from others, as the Yelp reviews indicate, for non-vegetarian selection. We had the agedashi tofu, a maki roll with some pickled vegetables, and a mushroom skewer. Request the booths - the ambiance there is quite cool. We were sat at the counter, so it was fun seeing the colorful preparations designed quite well.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',942,'2021-01-19',5,'Kai Zan sushi is one of the best I have tried in the city! Everyone is so friendly! I do admit that the menu is a bit expensive but the quality of the food is amazing and definitely worth it. Make sure to make reservations because Kai Zan books up quickly. I have been back several times and will continue to go back. Definitely recommend checking out Kai Zan!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',772,'2021-06-15',4,'First the food was amazing. The staff was excellent. So, why 3 stars? For spending $100 per person I felt like the meal was rushed. We arrived about 15 min early to our reservation so I am not sure if they pushed us into the 5pm rotation but we werent even done with out first dish when they would bring out our second. Or they would bring a dish out as soon as your done with the previous. No time to reflect and enjoy in between. Great food, but for the money I dont want to finish my 10 options in 35 min.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',646,'2017-04-07',5,'Amazing! We did the regular omakase, and all of the dishes were really inventive and delicious, and we were both pretty full by the end. I took my boyfriend for his birthday, so I requested a private booth and they were happy to accommodate us! Each course looked so good we completely forgot to take pictures. The sake was good too!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',1463,'2019-04-27',5,'Almost a year from my last visit, I came here to find that they have expanded next door to give ample room for bigger parties.Melvin and Carlo never disappoint and are constantly inventing new and creative flavors.Ive had omikase from these guys at least a half a dozen times throughout their career and each time is better than the last.This is not your traditional sushi joint. Â Its not for the purist. Â This is sushi with fusion. Â Fusion sushi. Fushi? Â Lots of flavors going on at the same time.Spoiler alert We ordered omikase and this is what we got from what I remember. Â I dont remember all the names of each dish so I made up some of them.Escolar PearlsRed Snapper Italian CarpaccioRainbow Trout CarpaccioOyster shooterUni shooterAngry CrabDIY Uni rollsQuartet Mushroom salad, Uni Jalapeno sticks, bacon wrapped enoki, octopus saladMushroom dashiDynamite MusselTunatini2 Maki rollsSashimi boat finale Super White Tuna, Salmon Belly (My personal favorite), and 2 other types of TunaAfter this epic meal, I left stuffed and elated.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',1325,'2017-09-16',5,'Love this place. Best uni and omakase tasting menu is fabulous. Worth it! 3 people were in our party. 2 of us had the premium omakase for $110 each and 1 had the $60 omakase tasting menu that combines Â items off the menu. Weve also eaten there ala carte. For a special occasion pre-order the premium. It was a ton of food but included wagyu beef dishes along with upgraded nigiri and sashimi like toro. Always had a great experience. Its BYOB but serves wine and sake too. We are going back this Tuesday.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',421,'2018-01-10',5,'Some of the best sushi I have had! Very inventive without being too saucy, fried etc. VERY fresh fish. Â BYOB!!  Logistics Â TS A VERY SMALL RESTURANT! Maybe 7 tables, but they are expanding. They sat me, my brother and his wife at a 2 person table. well that wasnt going to work. They kindly let us sit in the new room which wasnt quite finished, but it was SO much better. Great service.Food We opted for the $50 tasting menu. So much food for the price. It is a totally reasonable pre fixe. Favorites angry crab, pearls, shooters, tempura jalepeno, mussels',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec5093',66,'2018-10-12',5,'My favorite sushi in Chicago! The owners are very nice and service is great. Highly recommend the omakase here',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',683,'2020-04-10',4,'EXTERIOR 2.5/5INTERIOR 3.5/5 (odd-shaped, very small interior. TIGHT SEATING)CUSTOMER SERVICE 5/5 (the waiter was very attentive and honest, but it is very unusual to sit AT the sushi bar and not be able to speak with the sushi chef; the sneeze guard was enormous, and Kai Zan is run like a factory line; the person in front of the sushi bar area was a plater).CLEANLINESS 5/5QUALITY OF FOOD 3/5TASTE OF FOOD 2.5-3/5-------(**note I rate each eatery relative amongst its type/range in THAT city. Â So, no, Im not rating this restaurant compared to Alinea or some Michelin-star restaurant. Â I rate it and analyze its component qualities (above) from 1-5 compared to other eateries with similar food type, aura, and price range)(+) DISHES madai carpaccio, angry crab, orange rushok DISHES Â 4 uni shooters (uni quality was acceptable but not fantastic; seasoning is very American, using tabasco sauce, etc), 4 oyster shooters (I prefer my oysters to be very cold), kamo duck skewer (duck is hard to mess up; dish was unmemorable), 1 pair BBQ eel (eel is also hard to mess up)(-) DISHES tako skewer (rubbery), char siu pork belly skewer with kimchi (pork not seasoned traditionally in the Korean style, and kimchi was extremely bland), 2 pairs of torched salmon sashimiCOMPLIMENTARY dishes escolar pearls (I generally do not eat escolar, because of what it will do to your GI movement), maguro pearls (excellent), eskimo clouds, 2 apple pie shooters~~~~~We nearly ordered the entire menu and some things off the menu Â I will say this, Kai Zan was given a $$$$ rating on Yelp, but in fact, I found it extremely affordable for a sushi spot. Â It was more like $$, while Katsu (which we went to later in the week) was EXTREMELY expensive (and not worth it... its like Nobu prices for medium-quality sushi). Â For everything we ordered, I believe the bill was under $120?It should be noted that Kai Zan is not an authentic sushi restaurant in regards to their flavor profile and size of sushi. Â Some inauthentic places border on large or small portions; Kai Zan is on the very small end. Â Their makis are served in pieces of 4 that are square-sized. Â They are very bite-sized. Â However, they are very affordable (I believe ~$8-9 for the set of 4).I have been attempting to hunt down a fresh, amazing sushi spot in Chicago. Â So far, I have had no success. Â Kai Zans sashimi quality was not remarkable; it was neither good nor bad. Â However, I did not like how they prepared their sashimi. Â I felt that the chefs generally needed more training with fish and various dishes. Â For example, I asked for 2 pairs of torched salmon, and they did not know how to torch the salmon. Â Sushi chefs will typically select fatty salmon belly, sprinkle it with rock salt, and torch it half-way. Â However, where Kai Zan seems to excel is their customer service. Â The waiter was very attentive. Â In addition, while we were not able to speak with any of the sushi chefs, they realized we were ordering everything, and sent us a few complimentary dishes.In general, while I wasnt displeased with Kai Zan, I was surprised that it has a Michelin star. Â Overall, I would recommend everyone try Kai Zan once to form their own opinion. Â It wasnt a negative experience; the staff is very amenable, and the restaurant is fairly trendy right now.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',551,'2019-07-18',4,'Literally the best sushi ever. After eating here, I compare all sushi to this (which, lets face it, other sushi in Chicago does not compare). If I could give this more stars I would! Try the omakase and prepare to have your mind blown!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',1653,'2020-07-28',5,'Wow, another fabulus meal at Kaizan. The food is stunningly good. And the service was impeccable. One example is that the waiter noted that my date had a coughing fit and needed to step into the restroom. While she was in there he came over to ask me if there was anything he could get her, and then checked in with her as well once she came back out.Outstanding all around.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',485,'2017-06-27',3,'I walked in tonight with a weird request. Two dear friends were celebrating a big event and would it be possible for me to buy them their first round of drinks. Kai Zen didnt bat an eye. I was not only able to give my credit card info to them (which they already shredded) but they texted me the total to approve and delivered a card to help them celebrate. What an amazingly kind and wonderful spot.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',84,'2019-05-20',5,'Best sushi restaurant Ive ever been to. Â Amazing and unique creations and flavors. Â Excellent service and ambiance. Â Highly recommend!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',681,'2017-11-09',5,'My husband and I went here a few time, it has always been wonderful. This last visit a few weeks ago I was ever so slightly disappointed in a piece of sashimi we got, I mentioned it to my husband and as it turned out, the manager over heard me and brought us a new piece. I asked her why she did that and she told us how important it was that we got what we expected and that the experience was a good one. Â I was truly impressed by this actually... here is a place that always gets great reviews, is always busy, but still found so much value in making sure we were happy, even without us asking. Love this place!Vicki',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dis16196',1495,'2021-06-30',4,'Best sushi in Chicago hands down. Ive had the Omakase multiple times and each time was absolutely amazing. The pearls, orange crush, angry crab and the carpaccio course at the beginning were extremely memorable and delicious. There are some incredible flavor combinations. I always look forward to the sashimi course at the end as the cuts of fish are very fresh. Great atmosphere as well! If you are at the bar, you can watch the Vizconde brothers prepare and plate your meal and the booths are cozy and great for a date night or intimate meal. The service is outstanding as well. Every time Ive been I have never had anything to complain about and often the wait staff goes above and beyond to make sure my experience is perfect. I highly recommend the matcha creme brulee for dessert! This place is worth the $$. Next time I go back I plan on trying the Premium Omakase.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed91175',1093,'2020-06-22',5,'Wow. Not sure if this place is better than Seadog, but, very close. I HAVE TO GIVE 5 STARS THE FIRST VISIT IM SORRY IT WAS TOO GREAT. I broke my rule, I usually have to go twice to a place before I give out the big red, but man everything was perfect. I liked how many different people had tasks, water guy, sushi guy, waiter guy, beer lady, host girl and they were all psyched to be there. I was solo so I really got nice attentive service which actually was quite wonderful and didnt make me feel like I was eating alone. Which is the way I prefer to eat alone. Small intimate place though so I wouldnt come with my whole biker gang, probably just Rodney and Tito and maybe Purple Steve. Even the guy sitting next to me alone at the sushi bar was just the right amount of talkative. I wrote a haiku about Kai Zan I am a fan andIll go again in the endWe all become fish',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',175,'2022-02-19',5,'This was our first visit to Kai Zan. Â I would give it 4 1/2 stars if that were an option. Â We went for my husbands birthday and they were quite helpful in assisting me in pulling off a surprise for him ) I really appreciated that. Â It did bother me that knowing this dinner was for my husbands 30th birthday, they say us at the sushi bar instead of one of the booths. Â The restaurant seemed romantic, unless you are seated at the sushi bar -/We went specifically for the sushi. Â The special sushi roll options were very limited, however, they are able to make any traditional sushi roll you like. Â The price was a little on the pricey side, for the portions.The food they do have/ that we tried was pretty amazing. Â Cant complain about the quality of the food at all )My husband says its the best sushi hes had in Chicago, so far.The service was also fantastic.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',984,'2021-09-09',4,'One of our favorite fusion sushi in Chicago! Make reservations, love how everything is bite size. Always satisfied and walking out with the happiest belly and smile! Our Â favoritesOrange Rush Dynamite mussels is not like other dynamite mussles anywhere else!Uni toro tartarEscolar and Tuna Pearls Madai Capriccio Eskimo clouds Oyster and Uni shooters if you like ponzu and quail egg )Skewers and nigiri are great too but you should really order all the above because you wont get that anywhere else!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('platea7440',736,'2020-11-23',5,'GO HERE. Dont order rolls and such - get the omakase and theyll serve you a perfect meal. My husband and I got one omakase and one premium omakase and then shared a bottle of wine. It was a lot of food but we wanted to try everything! And we finished it all (FAT). Its a very small space so make sure you make a reservation if you want a guaranteed seat and they also will potentially run out of the omakases towards of the end of the night. Obviously pricey but absolutely worth it - perfect for special occasions. Itll be like no other meal youve had.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',197,'2020-03-28',5,'Cute, hidden place that I could not find until I followed the building numbers. Its tiny! With very limited seating. Good idea to make reservations, I got lucky and they were able to seat us. Cool things BYOB! With 5 dollar corkage fee. And every month they have a new list of chef specials.Yummy things Yep go for the Escolar pearls like everyone mentions. The Angry Crab roll was probably the best of the night... but it only comes in 2 pieces. It left me wanting more. Skip the Green Monster Roll. It was very mushy and avocado-y.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',822,'2021-12-05',4,'Best place to do sushi in the city. The standard tasting menu is very affordable, and then there is also a seasonal option. These tastings walk you through a wide range of dishes and flavors, so dont just think you are getting maki and sushimi. There is also a la carte which I really want to try. Just FYI, its a timed res, so not a place youll lounge about for hours, and some of the chairs are hit or miss re comfortability. Gotta go here!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',566,'2022-02-12',5,'A decent menu... Â if nothing else, its diverse. Â A little sushi, a little izakaya, a little yaki niku... Â none of it very authentic or cutting edge. Â For sushi purists, theres really only Katsu. Â If Katsus prices are a bit over the top for you, try Mirai (and just ignore the teriyaki and udon). Â For modern interpretations of sushi and izakaya, Momotaro and Momotaro Izakaya are far more interesting and delicious.But if you like your sushi seared, deep-fried or coated in some sort of kewpie-mayo or other over-powering sauce, you may like Kai Zan. Â Although it appears to be a neighborhood sushi bar, the menu isnt exactly drop-by-on-a-regular basis pricing. Â $8 for TWO small tako yaki?!We gave it our best college try, but we were underwhelmed...- tako yaki (fried octopus fritters) Â good, but again... $8 for two small fritters- age dashi tofu Â the tofu was over-fried and the kombu broth strangely bland- karaage Â although the chicken, itself, was well-seasoned, the batter was bland and tasted strongly of raw cornstarch- uni shooter Â over-powered by the tabasco... also, strangely, when we ordered the uni sushi, we were told that the quality was not up to the chefs standards. Â so why did they use it in the shooter?- beef tataki Â bland, over-cooked (instead of lightly seared) and lacked the usual ponzu sauce- seared scallops Â covered in a strange gloppy orange sauce- fiesta maki Â decent. Â and the only sushi roll not deep-fried or covered in some sort of sauce- toro Â no tuna taste at all, much less the unctuous goodness of fatty tuna- hamachi Â same comment as the toro',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',640,'2020-09-19',5,'The first time we tried to go to Kai Zan, we strolled in on a weekend night, but were told they were booked up with reservations all evening. Oh. Didnt realize that. We had dinner at a place across the street, and when I got home, I made reservations for a Saturday night at 7pm. We got there a few minutes early, so they offered us a seat to wait, and took a drink order. When I ordered my wine the bartender(?) told me it had a distinct taste, and offered to bring me a sample first. I tried it, liked it, and ordered a glass. A few minutes later, our seats at the sushi bar were ready. They warned me when they confirmed our reservation that that is where we might end up sitting, which is fine with us - its fun to watch the chefs, and also, its easier to have a conversation when sitting next to your dining companion instead of across the table. Everything we ordered came out promptly and was delicious. I had the green salad (I love ginger dressing), we shared the fried chicken (so tender), the calamari (it was good, I really liked the dipping sauce that came with it), the Char Siu (one of my husbands childhood favorites), the Fiesta Maki roll, the Green Monster roll (my favorite), and for dessert, the green tea ice cream, Lava Cake and Aebelskiver. Everything was delicious and the service was friendly and perfectly timed. And the prices were reasonable in my opinoin (for the quality of food and being in the city).',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rhoncus2633',1220,'2017-02-06',5,'Yelp needs to have an extra credit rating or something, because I cannot praise Kai Zan enough. Â We ended up here for my girlfriends birthday. Â She used to live over this way, and when we started dating and were comparing This is the best sushi place in the city stories, she mentioned Kai Zan and stuck to it. Â Every place I mentioned, she would just say, I want to take you to Kai Zan. Â I put her off long enough to make it part of her birthday evening, and I am kicking myself for waiting so long. Â This was the best sushi experience I have had in the city, period. Â We started off with some chutoro, then dove into the Omakase. Â The chutoro was delicious, better than the otoro I have had some places. Â I will not recount each and every course of the Omakase as that has been done ad nauseum, but I will point out some highlights. Â I would make a meal out of the escolar and maguro bites. Â Delectable. Â A close second in the eat this until Im full was the maguro stuffed with crab. Â The shooters course included one with oyster and one with uni and scallop. Â Both had quail egg. Â The uni/scallop shooter was the freshest, most oceanic thing I recall having ever tasted. Â The only courses I would not rave about were the roll and the sashimi plate. Â The roll was a good roll, but it was still just a roll that didnt really showcase the fish. Â The sashimi plate was excellent save for the maguro which inexplicably did not seem to be of the same quality as that which had been used in the other maguro courses. Â It was still better than what you get at most sushi restaurants, but by the time that course (the 10th) came, I was getting spoiled. Â The service was just fine. Â Very pleasant, described each dish well, answered all questions. Â Only complaint is that the meal was a bit rushed as compared to other Omakase dinners I have had. Â A few times the next dish was brought right as we were finishing a course, and once we had two on the table at the same time. Â And I am not a slow eater. Â I can be quite the pig, if I have to be honest, so I dont feel bad saying I felt rushed. Â I really cannot understand any of the reviewers who have expressed disappointment with the prices at Kai Zan. Â $60 for an Omakase of this quality is an absolute bargain. Â Try getting all of those same dishes at Arami, Katsu, Macku Signature, Momotaro, whatever your favorite sushi place is, and I feel safe saying its going to cost more by a decent amount, and there are not more than a handful of sushi restaurants in Chicago where the quality will be in the same ballpark. I have other daily drivers I will continue to go to, but Kai Zan just secured a position as the place I will go to when I really want to do it right.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',818,'2020-03-11',5,'Best Japanese in Chicago. Three tips for when you visit1. Get the omakase. Kai Zan chefs know what you want more than you do. Trust me on this.2. Make a reservation. You will never get in without one. And be prepared to get up and leave after 90 minutes; theyre strict here.3. If its not on the omakase menu, do yourself a favor and add on an order of the escolar pearls.Prepare to have your mind blown!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',1467,'2017-08-03',4,'I la la la la love this place!! We made reservations in advance for 2 at the bar at 8PM; however they took the michael jordan statute down so we end up being free early and wanted a table at 7PM instead; yeah right! Got here and this place was packed! We eventually walked down the street for a drink and came back at 8PM; we ordered the $60 omakase; man it was so much food!!!! I couldnt finish the last three course had to take it home and eat it after walking everything off. The omakase gives you a sample of everything on the menu; definitely worth it! I really really really recommend it. I was looking at the menu and the omakase really offered everything that I wanted to try. Just when I thought we were done more dishes came. The place itself is really cute; I would love to come back and next time probably sit at a nice quieter table since the chefs were way too busy to converse with.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',640,'2021-04-19',5,'We all had omakase and for $50, i think its a really good value! We got to taste almost everything from the March special menu and the couple daily special that the waiter mentioned when we first sat down...we were stuffed at the end of the tasting but we still managed to check out the dessert menu. They are all really good but we like the mango mousse the best The food and the quality of the ingredients were good and creative for $50...though we all thought the agedashi tofu wasnt that great. it was pretty firm, chewy and not crunchy at all. I wonder why they use the firm tofu vs the soft tofu like everywhere else...the place is really small...they literally only have a table each for 4 and 6 people..but to be honest, we were seated at the 6-ppl table coz we have a group of 5, but i honestly dont know how that table can comfortably fit 6 people?! we had 3 people sit on one side and 2 people sat on the other. one of my friends on the 3-people side were half out of the table.. =/i want to go back to order the nigiris because our neighbours looked pretty good and i was hoping one of the omakase courses would have the nigiris since i am not at all into rolls, fried stuff and mayo/cream cheese-in-everything...lol....i dont think rolls and these condiments were japanese invention....',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',800,'2017-11-19',5,'Hands down best sushi in west town and maybe the city. Omakase is literally the only thing you should order and prepare to have mind blown. Genius. Flavorful. And not too bad on the budget.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',1058,'2018-11-01',4,'Wow! First off. I love that parking here is so easy! Street and FREE parking available. Definitely make reservations weeks in advance to get a table otherwise its a long wait on the weekend.My husband and I came here to celebrate our one year wedding anniversary here. We were originally seated by the sushi bar with his reservation. We preferred a table, so my husband asked if we can get a table instead which we did after waiting for awhile. The hostess told us that for future reference we should make note of the occassion when making the reservation so she can get us a table. She was nice about it, so we will be sure to indicate what we are celebrating when making the reservation.We ordered a lot of sushi. They were all so fresh and good. We really like their special - the summer salad. We also ordered the tuna tini which we thought is okay. We ordered three rolls - spicy scallop which is REALLY good, tuna avocado which is good, and the fiesta roll which was ehhh.. We had two of their specialty - angry crab (MUST ORDER!!!!) and orange crush which was good! For the rest of the food we ordered sashimi of almost every kind. My favorite was the salmon. My husband really like the otoro and yellowtail. None of the sushi failed - it is one of the best sushi places in Chicago and it is not hard to find parking!! Definitely would come back. It is pretty expensive, but its really good. Our waiter was really nice, too. Cant complain at all!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dis16196',355,'2021-11-09',5,'Undeniably the best sushi in the city. Split the omasake menu with my boyfriend with a little bit of an up charge so they could increase portions and make it easy to share. Â Every single thing we tried was incredible. Definitely recommend going!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra37167',940,'2019-12-03',5,'Hands down the best Japanese restaurant in Chicago and probably in my top 5 of all time favorites. The omikase is a must try and is an incredible value. This is our go-to for special occasions. Michelin star rated and worthy of every 5 star review!!!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',714,'2021-01-16',4,'The Omakase is the only way to go. Â The Chefs know what theyre doing and when you enable their creativity you only stand to have your mind-blown. My Wife and I went this route and have no regrets, other than not finding this place sooner.The sushi is remarkable. Â The presentation of the dishes very creative. Â Atmosphere energetic but not too loud. Â The service from the hostess to the waitstaff was excellent.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',1010,'2018-09-10',5,'Hands down the BEST sushi I have had in Chicago, and trust me, Ive frequented most places here. Born and raised in Chicago, I took a few years off and headed to LA. Lucky for me, I worked at one of the best Sushi places in the area, and since my return, I have craved the quality and flavors that I had on the west coast... FINALLY, yes FINALLY I have found THE place.Make reservations. This hidden gem is small. If youre seated at the Sushi bar, enjoy the scenic view of watching the chefs at work- seriously amazing.Order a bottle of cold sake and make it a night to remember.I suggest going the Omakase route. If youre feeling fancy and want something truley unique - go premium! You will not be disappointed. Forget your normal midwest sushi ordering of going to the roll route, and let these chefs do what they do best. 10 courses of surprises... the best surprises to ever hit your taste buds.Some highlightsJapanese red snapper topped w/ black tobiko, basil miso, and micro greensEscolar and Maguro with truffle oil soaked scallionsUni and Oyster ShootersFried tako with yaki sauce, wasabi mayo and bonito flakesNew Zealand mussels topped w/ black tobiko, and negi mayoSeasonal Japanese pickled vegetableSpicy crab wrapped in fresh tuna, topped w/ tempura crunchI cant wait to go back. Im so pleased that this place exists.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',1739,'2016-09-25',5,'Wow, probably one of the best omakase dinners Ive ever had. Theres a $60 option or a $120 premium option. The $60 option offers a tasting of some of the more popular items on the menu. The $120 option offers off menu, premium items. Â I got the premium option obviously and it certainly did not disappoint. Literally everything I had was unique and delicious. Several of the items in the premium option include fatty tuna and uni, which are two of my favorites. A few of my friends got the $60 option and it also looked amazing. You really cant go wrong with either option. Â The service was also very, very good. The waitresses were very knowledgeable and nice. The pace at which the food came out was also perfect.We ate here during our trip to Chicago and of all the spots we went to (Girl and the Goat, Avec, etc.) this was our favorite. Just tasted really fresh and clean.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam9757',1647,'2019-03-01',5,'You hear that squeaking? Its the wheels on this hype wagon thats got me going along for the ride! I have a feeling that Kai Zan is entering THAT level of culinary hype status for snazzified sushi. Â  OMAKASE!!!Beautiful, light, tastefully prepared course by course. I cant think of anything else better than relinquishing your meal to the pros. For those looking for an adventure, it was an epic multicourse from uni, escolar pearls, mussels, scallops, an assortment of maritime goodies... Ill let the pictures speak for itself as everything was wonderfully drowned in flavors and garnishes. However, the pickled wasabi was a little too much for me to handle... Â a little does go a long way. I wasnt a big fan of the bacon-wrapped enoki or the fried popper. My mussel was gritty. After we reached our $50 level, we had been asked if we wanted to proceed. After trying one more, we ended the meal with the mango mousse. I LOVE mango and you know they used the real stuff... slightly stringy, oh-so-creamy. Every dish came out with an intro from our servers, an emphasis on the thoughtfulness behind each creation. Dinner was a super intimate experience, Im not sure how theyd be able to accommodate groups larger than 4. I almost feel your chances of nabbing seats prove increasingly difficult if youre bringing more than one other person. For the variety and value, I would say the omakases your best bet. After having the roller coaster tour of all things Kai Zan, I shall be back with an appetite, BYOB, and friends (hopefully in one of the only two larger tables in the place)!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',317,'2017-08-03',4,'Terrific food! I was expecting a typical Japanese sushi restaurant with a few standout items, but the menu is quite different and exciting. I had dinner on a cold Sunday night with my mom, and I was glad that we had a reservation, since the space is kind of small.We shared a variety of items, including a couple of charbroiled skewers (shiitake and shrimp), the escolar pearls, the orange rush, and the flaming tuna maki. All were very good, but my favourite was the orange rush -- scallops wrapped in fish with a citrus glaze. Delicious! The portions were all small, besides the maki (standard 8 pieces), but we left feeling content after ordering the blondie & ice cream dessert. The blondie was probably the only item that didnt blow us away, although the salted caramel ice cream was wonderful.Service was a little slow to start, but once we ordered, the food arrived pretty quickly. The space is also very cramped, with a narrow aisle between the sushi bar and the booths. Not distracting while we were eating, but it required some awkward choreography to get down the aisle when we were leaving.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede2192',1625,'2018-11-27',5,'After coming across Kai Zans Instagram months ago (check it out @kaizanchicago, their pictures are drool-worthy), my friend and I have been dying to come here and finally made it out for their Monday Dinner. 5 courses for $35 a person - tuna & escolar pearls, angry crab, tuna dashi, main (pork, tako, shrimp, daily wasabi ceviche), salmon maki & 2 pieces of nigiri. Some fantastic bites of food for such a great price! The fish was thick and fresh and all the flavors were an explosion in my mouth. The chef also sent us an extra bite of fatty tuna, which was the icing on the cake. My favorite dish had to be the tuna & escolar pearls hands down. Will definitely be back to try the omakase and all of their uni offerings!!!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mollis81165',1638,'2022-01-18',5,'Hands down my favorite restaurant in the world. Â The atmosphere is laid-back but cute. Â The twin brothers who own it are friendly, hospitable (one time they sent me a free dish because they saw me eyeing it from the sushi counter), and beyond good at what they do. Â They provide quality cuts of sushi presented in unique and tasty combinations for such a reasonable price in the city. Â Youd be doing yourself a disservice if you didnt order the chefs omakese...only $60 for 9 filling courses of the best sushi youve ever eaten! Â  The polenta bites are my favorite dish, so Id also recommend adding this to your omakese as they arent included. Â In addition, they are very accommodating to gluten free and pescatarian diets. Â Over the holidays they host a drawing to give away 2 $150 gift cards. Â My out of town friends always request Kai Zan when they visit. Â Make sure you make a reservation well in advance.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt318',1120,'2020-08-12',4,'Best sushi Ive had in Chicago! Â Amazing experience--the waitress was fantastic, the presentation was beautiful--and the food simply amazing!We did the tasting menu ($60pp) and so-so-so happy we did. Â We were stuffed, and got to try the best of the best. Â This is a MUST go!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tristique8035',1152,'2016-06-16',5,'Came here on a Friday night - best sushi I have ever had anywhere hands down. They dont even have soy sauce sitting on the table as this is already incorporated into the roll. Each bite was packed full of flavor but wasnt like your typical sushi where it is covered in too much sauce and cream cheese. They rely on actual good quality fish. Tuna Magura might have been my favorite. Try a couple of rolls as these are not huge rolls. They focus on quality taste each bite. Will be back.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',718,'2020-01-22',5,'Premium okase, that is all. Worth every penny. Im going to make more money just so I can be a regular here.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',959,'2018-04-18',5,'I love it. Good service. I went there 2 times the week I discovered this place. Japanese tho, is my favorite cuisine so Im a lil biased. but! I am also very picky and can definitely tell the difference btw crappy Japanese and quality. Kaizan was quality. I had theOrange Rush (must have)Calamari Fry (must have)Escolar Pearl (must have)Fiesta Roll Carmelized onion sauce on grilled scallop (must have)...to name a few..I have to tell u tho, this table across me had the chef special 5course menu thingy and damnnnn it looked delicious. Im definitely gonna do that next time. I believe its $50 a person for that. Overall, price wise, it was a bit of stretch for me..cant be doing the twice a week thing. But I really hope others will enjoy this place as much as my family and I did.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',600,'2020-06-02',5,'I waffled a bit on 3 or 4 stars. Â Why you ask? Â Oh you didnt? Â Well Ill tell you anyway. Â The food was good. Â CA caliber sushi? Â No, but getting closer. Â So Chi-town sushi-wise decidedly 4 stars.However, our experience was a little dampened because we felt rushed-- they told us we had to be done in an hour. Â Admittedly, this was our fault for being 20 minutes late for our reservation. Â Parking was a b*tch to find in the rain so keep that in mind. Â Luckily I yelped this gem before coming so I made sure to get the Uni Toro Special and the Escolar pearls. Â The Uni Toro was an inventive, delicious, and memorable offering. Â The added richness from the quail egg was superb.Escolar pearls were good, but didnt leave the same impression as the Uni Toro. Â My friend and I went a bit crazy with our ordering and they brought the food out so quickly that we ran out of counter space. Â Everything else was good, though nothing made quite as much of an impression as the Uni Toro. Â Im partial to uni, so I appreciated the plethora of uni choices. Â Next time, Ill make sure to be on time, and Ill try the omakase.Almost forgot to mention BYOB!!! Â So bring it. Â Dont forget it in the car like we did.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum5887',1656,'2020-12-31',4,'Im a huge fish and seafood snob because Im from the east coast and used to a level of freshness often difficult to find in the Midwest. This place is spectacular. Everything is so fresh, innovative, and remarkably underrated. Chicagos best kept sushi secret. Puts bigger named places downtown in River north to shame. Get the deluxe tasting menu. Worth every penny.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',1489,'2016-08-26',5,'2 days after eating one of the most spectacular dinners of 2015 yet Im still dreaming about every course served up at Kai Zan. I try to keep up with the foodie scene in Chicago even though I moved out to the east coast a year ago and stumbled upon Kai Zans instagram page about a month ago. Kai Zan isnt your mommas sushi restaurant so check your expectations.. and everything you know about sushi at the door. Now step in. The decor will quite literally set the tone for the rest of the night, its dark..moody...sexy... you may blush a little when you step in even. The staff is incredibly friendly though and youll feel at ease immediately. If youre lucky you might get seated at the bar so you can watch the magic happen, but the cozy booths lend themselves to a more intimate seating if youre there as a couple or a small group and want your privacy. While stalking Kai Zans instagram I basically had my heart set on trying out their Omakase menu ...but literally everything screams to be eaten and the choices are insane! how do you pick one over the other?? the Omakase is a 10 course hand selected menu by the chefs which really does introduce you to almost everything on the menu. Its special.. it truly is special. We started off with the Japanese Red Snapper wrapped around toro and topped with basil miso olive oil and tobiko... and ZOMG!!! I may have had a moment ... wink wink ....followed by more amazingness.. but my personal favorite had to be the Oyster and scallop shooters topped with ponzu sauce and fresh Uni.. how is this even real life? So glad we got 2 shooters each cuz theres no way I would have settled for just 1. I think the chef over heard me gushing about my love affair with Uni, cuz he ended up treating us to an extra course of hamachi with uni on the house.. over this amazing sweet mango sauce of some sort.. I stopped paying attention to every detail after some time.. youll see the pictures on my IG and know what Im talking about.  I just wanted to enjoy each bite and every moment. By the end of dinner we were sufficiently stuffed..split dessert between the two of us and had a couple drinks. Definitely made for a fun girls night out and you really do need to go here with someone who appreciates sashimi in its best form. Save this one for a special night... but make it happen soon!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl36148',1739,'2016-03-26',5,'Get the omakase!!! Its 10 courses of amazingness! Be willing to try new things and you will have a great experience!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',706,'2019-08-02',4,'I took my girlfriend here for a special occasion.This was our first time here.Our server Arlene was wonderful in how she recommended all her favorite dishes to us since we didnt go for the omakase (chefs tasting menu). In a way she was giving us her tasting menu and did not disappoint! By far the star of the night was the escolar pearls.This dish had four bite size escolar nigiri lightly seared with a side of special ponzu sauce. Very light and refreshing. Just amazing!Everything she recommended was spot on. We ordered the angry crab Â - spicy crab wrapped in fresh tuna, topped w/ tempura crunchWe each got one piece. The fatty tuna and spicy crab really go well together. Just divineorange rush - sushi scallops wrapped in salmon, lightly seared with a citrus glazeI would really recommend this too. Never knew salmon and scallops paired so well. Definitely you notice a theme where the dishes are great for one whole bite and the sushi is fresh and flavors really really go well togetherWe also got the following.Dynamite Mussels - better than the ones found in normal sushi restaurantsChar siu skewers - reminds me of the char siu found in ramen but so tenderhotate skewers - good scallopssalmon nigiri (super fresh) Â  Â At the end of the night she recommend this clam dashi that was not on the menu but definitely cleansed our palate. This officially became our favorite sushi restaurant!FYIMake sure to get reservations before coming because its a small cozy place.Also it is byob but there is a 15 dollar cork feeif you have a party of 4 you get to sit in a cozy Japanese style enclosed table.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',103,'2019-08-23',5,'The overall experience was good. The food was unique. I would say it was Japanese style food with a strong south American influence. Lots of dishes had tangy notes.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien72146',218,'2020-06-15',5,'My husband and I have been here four times. I would say this is the best Japanese restaurant in Chicago, truly authentic Japanese food.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',962,'2018-05-26',4,'We did the chefs menu here and its amazing! The fish is fresh, delicious and presented in such unique ways. This is not a typical sushi rolls place. The chefs menu also includes pork belly and cooked shrimp dishes. The service is really good. Its a very small place so a reservation is a good idea.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',847,'2016-11-08',5,'My boyfriend and I had very high expectations for this place and we were absolutely blown away by our entire dining experience. Â We each had the Omakase and every single course was FLAWLESS. Â It was the perfect amount of food and we were both a nice full by the end of it. Â We also had the matcha creme brulee which was a yummy way to end the night. Â Everything was very well priced for the unbeatable quality that they deliver. Â I will be recommending Kai Zan to everyone I know!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1345,'2020-01-23',5,'Best sushi in the country let alone Chicago. Do the omakase and just thank me later! Blows sugarsfish and whatever other trendy NYC/LA place you want to name out of the water, these guys are pros!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit22151',904,'2017-07-14',4,'Step 1 Make a reservation Step 2 Order the chefs special (60$)Step 3 Be amazed, full, and extremely happyWho knew you could find Sushi this good in Humboldt park.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',1113,'2019-11-10',5,'We each ordered the chefs Selection Omakase and afterward got the Flaming Tuna, Green monster, and a mochi dessert. The service was impeccable in all aspects and the food has me reconsidering all the five star reviews Ive given to sushi places in the past.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',923,'2021-07-23',5,'Very unique and different experience. Definitely a must try spot in Chicago. The fish was very fresh, and the preparation was splendid. We got the $35 early bird special and it was very much worth it. We came out full and very satisfied with the food. Definitely will be back to try the full omakase.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',1305,'2016-08-03',4,'LOVE this place. The omakase is unbelievable. Unique, beautifully-presented. Delicious and super fresh! Â LOTS OF FOOD! Save room for the sashimi course which is served toward the end! You will be full! Â Service is terrific - staff is very knowledgeable and friendly!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',850,'2021-06-17',5,'Amazing food. Visited Chicago twice and went there twice. Absolutely high quality food',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',724,'2019-07-26',5,'5 stars all the way.Been here a few times and every time has been perfect. Have done the a la carte option as well as the 10 course menu and neither disappoints. If its your first time, I suggest doing the Omakase. All the fish is so fresh and delicious. A few favorites below-orange rush-angry crab-either pearl-lobster sashimiI cant remember the name, but we had this sashimi that was served in a pot and coal-smoked. It was amazing. I suggest asking your server about it and, if they have it, order it.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',1119,'2016-01-25',5,'I am in complete awe of this amazing eatery west of Western where I would never in my life have expected such a unique and upscale Japanese menu.BYOB = awesomesauceGo for the omakase if its your first time - an exceptional value for all the delightful treasures this kitchen puts out.Finally tried uni for the first time in my life - the shooter was a zinger! As was the oyster one ..My favorite dish was a toss-up between the escolar/maguro pearls and the fighting kani (which we ordered seconds of).The rolls were delicious and one of the last few plates was a a sampler with a total high and low - high being the perfect octopus salad (which was so fitting after the Hawks clinched) and low being the jalapeno popper - just not my cup of tea.The mussel was gigantic with great flavor profile but mine was so gritty that I couldnt really enjoy it -(Sad that Im moving because this was the perfect place to experience so many new ingredients and dishes that I normally wouldnt order off the menu - well done Kai Zan and welcome to the west side!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit9598',1001,'2018-12-06',4,'Uni may be the key of Kai Zan, and everything looks fabulous.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',74,'2016-01-04',5,'The first thing you notice when walking in is the small but great atmosphere. The building can be hard to spot but that is all negative I can say about this place .We opted like many other people on here and went with the omakase and it will well worth it . The 10 course deliver some of the most amazing bites of food I have ever tasted. There were several times I had to stop and think to myself I was eating fish as the taste was nothing like any other sushi I have eaten . The staff was very friendly and brought the food out at the right times. We did have reservations, which I would recommend as even on Tuesday it was packed .Overall this was one of the best meals I have had and by far best sushi I have eaten . I will be back next time I am in Chicago .',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',246,'2016-03-16',5,'great service! the staff are kind. good sushi and good environment!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',1524,'2019-10-21',4,'Kai zan is so good, it made my friend Amanda cry tears of joy.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',635,'2017-04-29',5,'3 months ago I made reservations for two and asked my sister to join me for our first dining experience here. Â We came here and was seated within 5 minutes for our late reservation. Â I was really expecting the typical sushi restaurant with crazy speciality maki rolls that would include every condiment available to mankind plus the fish of their choosing. Â I browsed through their minimal menu and was surprised to find the limited options to choose from. Â However, to keep things simple we both order the $60 Omakase tasting menu. Â The drink of choice was the Irritated Koala - a black tea beer. Â Loved it.This specific menu will give you a taste of everything that they currently offer - from sushi, sashimi, soup, and cooked options. Â I wont go into details as Im sure other reviewers have already told you how great everything is. Â Do know this... their raw serving (sushi and sashimi) was freakin amazing. Â Served with the perfect pairing of flavors, and a perfect balance of soy to smokiness. Â Though their cooked food options still need some improvements, but the fact that they were able to WOW me with everything else made their 5-star rating well deserved.I do recommend anyone coming here for the first time to try the Omakase just so you can taste everything and decipher what food you like and dislike from their menu, so that your second experience can be much more enjoyable. Â Ive been to Kai Zan 3 more times since my initial visit 3 months ago. Â My second visit I ordered everything ala carte (specials, sushi, and sashimi) and it was even better than I remembered.After leaving our first visit, my sister and I both felt that it was quite possibly one of the best meals weve had in Chicago. Â How did we not find this place sooner?',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',163,'2018-09-16',5,'Went on a Sunday night without reservation. Was seated right away and decided to order the chefs choice omakase. Everything was absolutely delicious and we left pleasantly full. The service was great and the quality of the fish was impeccable. Would def. return.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',27,'2020-11-25',5,'We had reservations for a Saturday evening and were seated in a private booth. Â There is good privacy and not a lot of ambient noise. Â We decided to go a la carte instead of omakase as there were some dishes we didnt want on the 10-course menu. Â The nigiri is on point and very close to what you find in Japan. Â A dab of wasabi is tucked under each piece of fish and warm rice which is all you need to enjoy. Â You dont need soy sauce or wasabi on the side at Kai Zan. Â I want to point out the rice is warm and fresh. Clearly, the sushi chefs experienced Japan with the rice being light and airy, warmed in the hand and not cold, packed together like you find at other sushi restaurants. Â We ordered salmon, tuna (maguro and chu-toro), yellowtail (hamachi), and ebi (sweet shrimp). Â We also got two specials the uni (sea urchi) tartare seaweed handrolls and wagyu beef nigiri. Â The wagyu is slightly kissed by a torch and melts like butter in your mouth. Â It is one of the best pieces of beef Ive had. Â The ebi is also done right (not pink from being cooked). Â We ordered some sushi rolls and they were above average as well. Â If you want fresh nigiri, this is the place. Â A shoutout to our server, Brian, who was fantastic and able to get us salmon belly and yellowtail belly cuts.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean2690',68,'2016-07-09',5,'Hands down one of the best Japanese spots in Chicago! I thought Momtaro was the best Japanese spot in Chicago until I came to Kai Zan. They are equally amazing. The freshness of the food at Kai Zan is impressive. Love it and cant wait to come back!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',707,'2021-06-13',4,'This place is spectacular.I went on a Saturday night with my brother (I know, awkward) and we had an early reservation - 515 p.m. You will absolutely need a reservation on a weekend ... I made our reservation the Thursday before, and my options were 515 and 930. But honestly, I totally get why. The food was delicious, the service was super courteous, and the ambiance was so charming. We both ordered the chefs special for $60 per person. I am somewhat cheap, and I still thought this was so worth it. 10 courses/plates, and the selection was awesome. Every single plate was delicious and beautifully plated.Worth noting Come with a somewhat adventurous spirit. This isnt really a typical sushi place. But everything is soooo delicious. You will NOT miss the average Philly role. Also, they serve beer, wine, and saki now. They still do BYOB as far as I know, but I believe they charge a $15 corking fee. Boo. But I still loved it! Our waiter recommended an awesome saki and it made our dinner extra delicious.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',661,'2018-06-19',5,'Dont come for omakase. Defintely not worth it. Their food is not fresh. The mussel makes me wanna puke.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',790,'2020-05-24',5,'As I reflect on all the sushi Ive had in Chicago...Kai Zan takes my #1 spot for sushi! The boyfriend and I went here for an anniversary dinner a couple years ago, and to this day it was one of our top 3 meals in Chicago. If you go here, you MUST do omakase (the chef selects your dishes for you). We opted for the 12-course menu which was about $60/person. Every one of our courses was fresh and scrumptious, but Id say our favorite course was the oyster shooters (and I dont even like oysters, so thats saying something!). The ambiance is trendy and intimate, great for a dinner date or special occassion. So if you like sushi and/or have a special occassion coming up, get your bootie down here! It may become your favorite sushi spot in Chicago too. =)',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',219,'2019-07-06',4,'Tried this place for omakase and it did not disappoint! Â There are 2 options, regular and premium omakase. Â Favorite was probably the oyster/scallop shooter and their nigiri. Food looked and tasted amazing! Â Server was nice and explained each dish that was brought out to us. Â Overall, good experience.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',990,'2019-02-25',5,'Amazing sushi! Â We got the tasting menu! Â Very impressed with the quality of the seafood and the taste of the sushi without much of soy sauce over powering the freshness. Â Probably one of the best sushi Ive had in the US.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',24,'2018-10-25',5,'Had an amazing 10 course tasting menu last night at Kai Zan and I was blown away! It was my first time eating Uni and I couldnt get enough. Â My favorites were the Orange Rush (scallop wrapped in salmon with a citrus glaze) and Maguro and Escolar Pearls. Cant wait to come back!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',498,'2019-07-29',4,'What is there to say that hasnt been said already...one of the top 5 meals Ive had in Chicago! My biggest regret is not doing the $60 Omakase chefs experience.- Reservations - Get your reservation and get it a week early if you dont want to eat at 5 or 9. Please note, they are closed Wednesdays. The interior is intimate and casual, though unlike many small sushi restaurants who maximize space by decreasing your personal space, Kai Zan has booths lining the wall that feel spacious and personal thanks to trendy dividers. We sat at the sushi bar, which I worried would be crowded and uncomfortable but after the face I Â think it is probably the best seat in the house! It allows you a glimpse in to the care and dedication put in to each dish and is way more exciting than reading words off the menu. - The Kai Zan difference -Sushigasms await! I am one of those sushi connoisseurs Â who usually chooses the roll with the most cream cheese, avocado or spicy mayo. Kai Zan has for ever changed not only my sushi habits but my life. Theyre dishes are packed with fresh clean fish and flavors. Though if you are not a raw fish fan we saw them making up some of the entree offerings with noodles, seasonal vegetables and your choice of portion, they looked great and a really big portion. Our meal was $100 for 2 including, tip, appetizers, rolls, skewers, two desserts and the corkage fee! (prices are not online so off memory) + Appetizer-Maguro Pearls 4pc - Rice spheres topped with fresh tuna, spicy mayo, chili oil and creamy wasabi+ Kushi Lava Rock Char Broiled Skewers-Scallop - four bite sized scallops with caramelized onion sauce-Pork Belly - with kimchiAmazing smokey flavor and really cheap ($3-5), Id say try them all!!+ Sushi-Angry Crab ($9) 2 pieces - Fresh tuna, spicy crab with chefs tograshi.-Orange Rush ($10) 2 pieces - Salmon, scallop with citrus glaze.Both were out of this world in presentation and flavor, consisting of 95% fresh fish fillet these bites are hearty and satisfying. -Flaming Tuna Roll ($14) for 8 pieces -Shrimp tempura, spicy tuna and avocado with seared tuna. Great flavor and Â crunch. + Dessert - Homemade Cheesecake with seasonal berries - the texture is a bit more gelatinous than most but its delicious- Lava Cake with Sesame ice cream - The ice cream has a slight peanut butter flavor and it is out of this world! Free tipBYOB but it was a $15 corkage fee for 2, which I personally feel is outlandish, good thing their food is amazing!!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',1241,'2017-06-28',5,'From the outside it looks nondescript. Â  In fact, I thought I had the wrong place, because there is a sign that says Tattoos in the window.We ordered the Omikase tasting for the four of us. Â I cant even remember how many courses there were... but each course... each different delicacy was better and more imaginative than the last.The flavours and presentations were fabulous. Â The service was excellent, and the atmosphere was lovely and pleasant. Â I cant say enough nice things about this place. Â I will, indeed, be back.My favourite piece of sushi, during the entire tasting, was something called Angry Crab, which was topped with a piece of Uni.Yuuu-uuummm.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisi29157',1694,'2017-12-14',5,'Service was excellent, chefs tasting was creative many things were delicious, but certain sushi items had definitely gone just a touch past their prime; the chicken teriyaki was dry and hard.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',1549,'2017-07-30',5,'Not sure if I could like this place anymore.. I have been here twice and both times I was beyond blown away by the food, atmosphere and service. The first time I sampled various different items off the menu and the second time I did the Omasake tasting. Let me tell you that the Omasake tasting was by far the most amazing combination of things I have ever eaten. Everything is beyond fresh and you leave feeling very satisfied and full. My table of four chose to BYOB and for the four of us it was a flat fee of $30 for bringing our own wine. This may seem like a lot, but there was no limit on how many bottles we were allowed to bring so it made it worth while.If you have not tried this place, make your reservation now and prepare your taste buds to be in heaven!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lobortis43186',835,'2019-05-22',5,'We looked forward to trying Kai Zan for quite some time. Unfortunately we were disappointed with everything we tried. While service was great, everything felt off, from the under-fried tofu to the poorly wrapped fiesta rolls. We go to Arami at least twice a month so couldnt help compare our experiences...but Kai Zan just didnt compare.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula35188',790,'2022-02-26',5,'There are so many sushi places in Chicago and way too many mediocre ones. Â Kai Zan is definitely not one of those. It was impressive from beginning to end. Â Food, service, decor, prices- Amazing. Its a very small place as mentioned in earlier reviews. Â Theres only a few tables and 3 booths that seat couples so its probably not ideal for big groups but this is def a winning date spot. Â Sitting at the sushi bar is highly recommended. The sushi chefs (infamous twins per prior reviews) were very attentive and made suggestions that did not disappoint. Â It was fun watching them do their thing and peek at all the fresh ingredients. Food wise- Everything we had was light and palate pleasing, just as a good sushi meal should be. Dont leave without trying the ESCOLAR PEARLS. GET GET GET IT. So goooood. Id go back for those bite-sized pieces of heaven alone. Between the 3 of us little asian girls- 2 bottles of wine, 1 app, 1 (comped!) mushroom dish, Â 3 rolls & 1 order of shishito peppers left us stuffed with satisfaction and amazingly, with cash to spare! Kai Zan- Thank you for reminding me that good, fresh sushi does exist in this city. I will be back!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non93107',1109,'2017-04-28',4,'Fresh and delicious sushi. One of my favorite spots. The restaurant is chic and cozy. Make sure to make reservation though and they get booked up. They have you on a time limit since the space is rather small. This was only an issue once when a girlfriend and I ordered the Omakase and were chatting so much that our last few courses were rushed out.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',720,'2019-06-19',5,'So. Good. My husband and I came here for our anniversary and both ordered the omakase menu. This is actually the first time weve had omakase, so in fairness I dont have anything to compare it to, but the food was stellar and from what we understand, very fairly priced for omakase. Our favorites were the escolar and maguro pearls (I could have eaten 5 more orders of this alone, holy crap it was to die for), the angry crab (a toss up between this and the pearls for best dish of the night, I think), and the dynamite mussels. Everything else was fantastic as well, these 3 dishes just stood out as OMG. The only dish I was so-so on was the tuna dashi (bland compared to everything else on the omakase menu), but it was a good pallet cleanser in between everything else I suppose. They space everything out really well so although they have a time limit, we didnt feel rushed at all. Ill definitely be back again.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',350,'2020-11-15',5,'Amazing experience! Perfect for 2 or 4 people. Wait staff very knowledgeable and completely honest about their favorites and what is the best looking fish of the day. Green Monster was our favorite of the rolls for sure. Yellow fin tuna sashimi melted in our mouths!!!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',546,'2017-08-06',4,'On my list for a LONG time, Kai Zan was just okay. Maybe my expectations were too high. I had the chefs menu - a couple exceptional dishes/bites, but a few that were so-so. Worth a try for newbies. I highly recommend you study the menu before you go. Its on the smaller side and a bit confusing. I was intimidated by it Â - simply because it was so hard to dig into.Service was terrific.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',85,'2016-02-24',5,'This was trying too hard for me. Japanese food (even fusion style) should be simple flavors with a lot of depth whereas this was a confusing mix of shallow flavors. We did the Omakase. A couple of dishes were unpalatable -the dashi soup broth was beyond salty and the shooters with oysters and scallops were far too acidic in the ponzu. On the plus side, service was great, ambience wonderful, and you can bring your own bottle of wine.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',1707,'2017-08-21',5,'Best sushi in the city. Went here for Valntines Day and got the special which consisted of a 12 course small plate meal (very filling!) for $85 each. It gave us a good idea of what Kai Zan has to offer and was an awesome deal. The fish here is fresh a hell and the atmosphere is small and trendy. It gives you one of those feelings that you are in the know when it comes to Chicago sushi spots. Anyway, I enjoyed everything I tried (no lie) but my favs were ANGRY CRAB (this is a MUST), Orange Rush, and the Oyster Shooters. I know the angry crab is expensive when its not in the deal, but try it...It meltsss in your mouth. Ever since Vday I have been craving this place like no other. Kai Zan is my happy place and I will be back.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',1531,'2019-03-03',4,'Never. Again. Â They will rush you as fast as they can to turn the table. Â You can get as good or better sushi at other area restaurants at comparable price points, but where you will not be herded in and out like cattle. Â You can do much better than this place and you should.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',820,'2016-02-06',5,'Ive eaten at a Â variety of sushi restaurants throughout Chicago (and other major cities), but I will say without a doubt ... Kai Zan was THE BEST sushi Ive ever had. From the cut of the fish, to the way it was prepared, to the seasoning ... everything was absolutely perfect. There were some pieces that fell apart in your mouth with only a ginger or wasabi dressing that was so simple but all you needed to complete the flavor. I dont think we used soy sauce/wasabi once. We ordered the OMAKASE CHEFS CHOICE. The cost of the chef choice was $50 per person but we easily had $100-$150 worth of food each. The restaurant was extremely generous, and dish after dish kept coming out. Overall, I wish I could have given the place a 6. Reservations can be made online through their website. I would plan at least 2 to 3 weeks out for a weekend reservation. Absolutely worth a try for the sushi fan.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',577,'2017-07-14',5,'Best sushi in Chicago! I usually did my sushi in soy sauce but the sushi here is so fresh and tasty you dont need! Love this place!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1164,'2016-08-10',5,'On vacation from Florida, for my sushi night I wanted the best Chicago had to offer.Kai Zan did not disappoint.I chose Kai Zan because they were well known for their Omakase. (Chef chooses all dishes)My girlfriend got the special omakase ($120) and I got the regular ($60) and we shared everything.The best omakase Ive ever had. Impeccable serviceSushi Chefs were amazing! After 3 museums, a great comedy show and an amazing architecture tour- it was my experience at Kai Zan that I will remember the longest.Thanks!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',212,'2018-05-11',5,'Stop reading reviews and make a reservation. Theyre hard to come by as this place is both small and popular, but well worth it. Weve dined here 3-4 times. Service, food and drinks are always exceptional. You walk away satisfied with a pretty unique sushi experience.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',1134,'2020-07-16',5,'Friendly staff. Our waitress was exceptional. She was friendly, knowledgeable, and gave great recommendations (owners sister. I think her name is Arlene). We did the regular and special tasting menu (Omakase). The progression of flavors kept amazing us. Â Ingredients included lobster, mussels, king crab, tuna, red snapper, and scallops. Â Everything was very fresh and tasted amazing. Food was creative yet not far from the classics. Presentation was great. The diner was expensive but very worth it.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',1034,'2019-05-04',4,'This place is pure amazing ness. There is nothing else like it. I always do the Chefs tasting menu and am never disappointed.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',1127,'2019-03-01',4,'Fresh fish. Unorganized reservation staff/hostess, had to sit and wait to be seated even after making reservation. Excellent server - always attentive, knowledgeable and 2 steps ahead. Incredible sushi. Will take pics next visit. Im craving more!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',880,'2017-03-20',5,'If someone says sushi and the first thing that comes to your mind is California roll, I am not sure if I should tell you to run to Kai Zan or avoid it like the plague. There is a lot more to sushi/Japanese food than the Americanized cream cheese and/or mayonnaise concoctions. If you are open-minded, Kai Zan is the place for you. If not (or, just not so much), you can still find plenty to eat here, but I think youd be missing out. Â At the very least, I think everyone should come here and try at least one thing out of the box. You owe it to yourself.As such, I tried a few things outside my normal Japanese wheelhouse (wheelpagoda?), and was glad I did - not just in that I had some semblance of an adventurous spirit, but because it was all really good. For some normalcy, my DC and I had a flaming tuna roll, and eel/cucumber roll, tamago, shishito peppers, and mussels. Exploration involved hamachi collar, oyster and uni shooters (not entirely weird I know, but Id never had either, and these had quail eggs in them - definitely not your normal shooters), and seared tongue. Yeah, I ate a cows tongue. Never saw that one coming. DC told me it has the taste/texture of pot roast. DC was correct. Still...I cant believe what I put in my mouth. Thats what *she* said. Oh, how I miss Michael Scott. At least when The Office was funny.Remember - you owe it to yourself.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',1275,'2020-03-06',3,'I enjoyed the fast service from this place. Â I have to say that the fish is incredibly soft and good quality, which is why I almost put this at 5 stars. Â I thought they could have more rolls on the menu because they had a small selection. Â Also, I did have to ask for a nigiri/sashimi menu as they just gave me a menu with their specialities, because I enjoy the classic raw fish part about the sushi experience. Â The appetizers we ordered were out of this world. Â I do think that the MOMO skewer could be better if it was not the thigh part of the chicken. Â I will be coming again and just not ordering the MOMO skewer. Â Thank you for the best service I have ever had in Chicago!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',574,'2016-03-09',5,'I have been looking forward to eating here for a while and was seriously disappointed to the point that I have to write this review and cant even see myself giving the restaurant a second chance. Some of the food was delicious (seared hamachi, escolar pearls), some was good but way overpriced (beef skewer) and some was short of decent and still way overpriced (scallop skewer and mussels). The main problem is the abysmal service. Having been a server I am sensitive to basic server issues like a busy kitchen, a forgotten order or just a bad night. Words cannot describe just how much the awful service soured my experience at this restaurant. Our server seemed really put-upon to even be there, not to mention forgetting part of our order and not offering drinks. He really just made me feel icky for having spent $100 and feeling like I owed him something. The food is NOT worth the cost or service. Stay away.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1407,'2018-10-22',5,'If you want a pretentious location with terrible service, then this is your spot. I was really looking forward to this place. I made reservations weeks in advance since it had all these great reviews, and they kept calling me to confirm telling me that we may have to sit at the bar because the restaurant may be full. We got there and the place was empty. The entire time we were there, it never filled up. The fuzzy long haired guy who served us...(Hawk...I believe was his name) set a vibe so terrible I almost wanted to get up and walk out. I asked a question about the menu and he just gave the biggest attitude and immediately discouraged us from ordering the sushi...why? Because its cheaper?We ordered the SOS...we wanted one to try and he discouraged us again saying we couldnt share it, so we got two. Why do you have a bite sized anything on your menu that I cant share? We ordered two though and umm, I would have preferred to share that one. Once I got it, it was missing ingredients and the fried salmon skin was cold. Ok...no big deal until that rubberband mistake of nasty cold calamari came. Did I order rubberbands or food??? So upon returning that, the pork belly skewer came out. It was okay, but by no means stellar. The one thing I enjoyed was the Green Monster roll. It was really good but I can get that at any sushi place with much better food and service, and actually leave full. I have never been to a restaurant where my waitor was so rude! I will always tip, but not this guy. I looked for the bus boy to tip him but he was M.I.A. upon leaving....probably because he was doing his job. The busser literally served us the entire time while Mr. Rude sat in a corner and crawled past us...never asking if we needed anything, enjoyed the meal...nothing...just wanted to raise the bill for his tip. Ill save that tip for someone who actually has people skills...this is right down there with Yusho, but worse. At least Yusho has great servers... But you have to ask yourself with these small plates places... is it about the small plates or just about being pretentious?!? There are lots of great small plates out there for decent prices...this is NOT one of them. If you want great sushi, go to Enso. Great place, great food, priced right, delicious and the service is wonderful, AND they dont litter with cheap throw away chop sticks when charging good money for food!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',830,'2021-07-02',4,'If I could I would give 10 stars. We tried around 10 different plates (plates are very small portioned) and they were all amazingly tasteful. Special kudos for the spicy tuna belly. We tried a sweet plum sake as well that went well with all the dishes. Will definitely come back. Thank you!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',1311,'2017-05-28',5,'Bottom line Â If you love sushi. Â If youre a foodie. Â This place.Full story9.24.12I had read good things about this place. Â Turns out theyre all true. Â We sat at the bar, essentially table number six. Â I know this because whenever the chef called out Six! we got a plate of food. Â Also, there were only five tables. Â KZ is intimate and lovely. Â Total date place.As you will read (if you do any research), KZ doesnt Americanize the sushi with cream cheese and fries. Â And whether or not pearls (rice spheres) exist in Japan, my wife and I dug them. Â We got the escolar pearls because EVERYTHING I read said to try them - AWESOME. Â We also got the green monster and flaming tuna rolls - GREAT. Â And the enoki bacon from the kushi-lava rock char-boil - SO GOOD WE ORDERED ANOTHER ONE. Â The special sushi was white tuna belly which they made into pearls for us - MAGNIFICENT. Â All in all, it was a wonderful experience/meal, and I hesitate to write a review at all because Id rather everyone NOT know how great this place is, but credit where credits due. Â It was AWESOME.Next time well probably try the omakase menu, because I know there will be a next time...PS. Â Also, the service was great.* Addendum 10.20.12 Hmmm, next time didnt work out so well... Â Ive taken off a couple stars because when we went in for our 9pm reservation, they didnt have our reservation. Â Um, what? Â Im sure it was a simple error, but when its Saturday night at 9pm and youre starving and youve been waiting all day and youre excited to introduce your friends to a great new restaurant - its um, VERY disappointing to say the least. Â #uncool. Â Im sure we will try again and perhaps then I will put the stars back, but this last experience left a bad taste in my mouth. Â I advise confirming your confirmation.(KZ isnt set up for opentable.)* Addendum 7.24.14SO this was a meal long in the making... Â Long story less complicated (being that youve read this far), more than a year ago Kai Zan wrote to me after I yelped about the lost reservation. Â They apologized and offered me an omakase menu to make things right. Â I didnt see this until a month ago. Â I thanked them for reaching out. Â But heres the thing; they said the offer was still good. Â Whuh?! Â So I went last night with my wife.We had a nice table for two against the wall near the sushi bar. Â (Theyve expanded, there are now more than five tables.) Â We ordered a sake, and explained how my wife was allergic to scallops.Bring on the omakase...The omakase is the Chefs tasting menu; sorta like a sushi roller coaster mixed with a log ride of other culinary wonderment. In other words, I cannot tell you exactly what I ate, but it was an awesome ride. Â To start, it ALL looked like Top Chef. Â Everything was beautiful and meant to impress the judges. Â Some bites worked my palette more than others. Â There was one thing - maybe it was called Angry Crab - it was a total OMG bite. Â We had a shooter with an oyster, there was one with a quails egg. Â We had sashimi, sushi, rolls, soup. Â There was pork belly, shrimp, mushrooms, I dont even know what else. Â It was familiar, but unlike anything Ive ever had. Â The final tray was a selection of sashimis. Â Before I could say anything, the waiter asked if we wanted soy sauce - because up until then Im sure soy sauce would have been wrong; sorta like ordering a dry aged medium rare prime rib, receiving it au jus on a hot plate, and then asking for ketchup. Im not qualified to discuss or accurately describe the various flavor profiles that danced across my tongue. Â All I can tell you is that it was a delightful and delicious experience; the likes of which if you enjoy sushi or consider yourself a foodie - Kai Zan. Â It is everything youve read/heard.PS. Â The service was exceptional. Â There were so many courses, I think we were presented by each person working there. Â They were all able to walk us through the different dishes; the takeaway being that the restaurant worked together as a team.PPS. Â Yes, its a nice little story, but Kai Zan is a true treasure. Â Im very happy to add back the stars. Â Bonus Â To bring it all full circle, you can now make reservations for Kai Zan through Yelp.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1614,'2021-02-23',5,'This place is great. Small and intimate. Great service and great food. We sat at the sushi counter which was cool to see the food being prepared. We tried the chefs tasting menu for $65 a person. Honestly it was too much food. It was ten courses, so I expected it would be literally a taste for each course -- one piece of sashimi or one piece of sushi roll per course. For half the courses they were giving two or three servings. I was uncomfortably full by the time we were halfway done, and I didnt enjoy the second half of the tasting menu because of it. Several of the items on the tasting menu are on the regular menu so if so went back I would figure out what looks good from the tasting menu and then order a couple of those plates individually.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',1095,'2021-03-28',4,'Best sushi Ive ever had and I refuse to eat anywhere else for sushi. Â I wish I could keep this my little secret since this place is pretty popular. Â Reservations must be in advance. Â Dont be afraid to experiment and always order the specials. Â I cant wait to go back!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',116,'2017-08-05',5,'Best sushi Ive ever had in the city. Did the chefs tasting menu. Highly recommend it',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt318',164,'2018-03-25',5,'Yum yum! Best sushi place in Chicago! The restaurant is a little bit small, but the food is strongly recommended! I tried the fix menu and always wanna go back!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut97174',1200,'2019-01-23',4,'Incredible bargain for the price and general quality of the food! We got the omakase and did not regret it! The server was also great and very knowledgeable of the menu and ingredients!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',756,'2019-10-28',5,'This is in my Top 3 sushi restaurants in Chicago.Very fresh and delicious! Presentation is beautiful. Staff is efficient, though slightly stoic. Doesnt seem to be any more or less expensive than what typifies the genera.I was intrigued by the quail egg shooters.Word of caution this place is very small, even with the recent expansion. MAKE A RESERVATION, or dont complain about how long you wait -or how nonplussed the staff is about fitting you in.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',945,'2016-05-22',5,'Took my husband there to celebrate our anniversary because he loves Japanese food. He got the tasting menu and I got ala carte dishes. He loved a few dishes from the tasting menu and I loved the tofu in broth and the noodles. A nice cozy restaurant and excellent atmosphere for a date night. I took one star off because the server could not suggest good sake options.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',139,'2021-04-29',5,'Best sushi place in the city. Highly recommend the chefs menu. Great staff, and the best food.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',908,'2017-09-22',5,'Best sushi in Chicago, period. I went with a large group and we all had a fantastic experience! Most of us opted to do the Â $60 Omakase menu and it was a creative, fresh explosion of flavors. Â Parts of the meal may have been spent in silence as everyone was busy taking pictures(everything was so artfully arranged) and then dying from happiness with each bite. Im still dreaming about the Escolar and Maguro pearls. Yummmm.Just remember, its a marathon and not a sprint. Â Make sure you save room for the Nigiri platter, I was stuffed by course number 10 and was super sad when they brought out a platter of Nigiri. (Dont worry, I still ate more).Desserts were good but nothing special. Also, its BYOB with $5-6 dollar corking fee, woohoo!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem1829',1507,'2019-08-10',4,'Sushi enamored foodies..........your search for divine perfection is over. Â Kai Zan is here and it better be here to stay. Â Kai Zan is magnificent. Â Kai Zan is an addiction. Â You wont be able to stop yourself from wanting to go back. Â  Â  I was in love with this gem of a place before I even got there. Â I mostly got Claudia to thank plus the abundance of rousing yelp reviews. Â I had questions for the restaurant and wanted to see their drink menu which isnt posted. Â The restaurants phone system wasnt working so I contacted them via e-mail. Â Claudia answered all my questions promptly and sent me the drink menu. Â We originally had a 930 pm seating through Yelp SeatMe and I really wanted something a bit earlier. She was fabulous enough to email me and let me know a Â 815 pm reservation was available. Â Talk about top-notch service; it really makes all the difference.The restaurant is still tiny but I heard had expanded recently. Â We got one of those prime seats right next to the bar and cooking station where the sushi twins were hard at work. Â Best seats in the house!Two words - Omakase menu. Â This is a 12 course chefs tasting menu for $60/pp. Â If sushi is a meaningful aspect of your foodie life, whats the point in looking elsewhere? Â Well, maybe theres just one more option. Â Allan, our server says theres a brand new tasting menu that offers a higher level of sushi experience and costs $100/person for 11 courses. Â I decide to hold off on this until next time. Â Lets face it; there will be a next time. Â Plus, thats pretty pricey.My husband graciously accompanied me although he doesnt eat sushi. Â So, he stuck with the cooked portion of the menu. Â I will normally try everything he eats but I was so mesmerized with Omakase that I paid little attention to what he got. Â I know he got beef steak and really enjoyed it.The Omakase was spectacular. Â No words will truly do the menu justice. Â There was fish galore. Â There was carpaccio, maguro, tuna, oyster shooter with a zing that you slurp up, out of this world angry crab, more tuna, fish cloaked in avocado that literally melts in your mouth, salmon, scallops, octopus, shrimp tempura, roe toppings and an awesome soup. Â There was more but I dont remember it all. Â Last course was a platter of sashimi to die for. Â In all, truly a roller coaster ride. Â I was trying to jot down notes but couldnt keep up. Â The fish was so fresh, there were many different and unique flavors, some topped with mayo and accompanied by wasabi for the kick. Â Good sushi is never cheap and $60 is a great price for what you get. Â  Â  At one point my husband says - Thats a lot of fish. Â As in - Are you really going to eat all that? Â Oh heck yah it was a decent amount of fish and I ate every single last piece.They even serve the most wonderful version of soy sauce. Â Not sure quite whats in it but I made it my mission to find enough food to soak it in. Â I probably would have drank the left-over sauce if it came down to it.The restaurant started off as just BYO but they now serve wine and sake. Â They dont however advertise their drink menu as you cannot find it on their website. Â The BYO option is now $15/table. Â Im a firm believer that drinking anything but sake with sushi is a sin. Â Allans first recommendation was for us to try the wandering poet junmai ginjo and I couldnt agree more. Â This happened to be the first pouring by sommelier Jill Gubesch at our Topolo dinner and is an outstanding sake. Â Most of the sake is offered as 300 ml size options with around four offerings in the 720 ml size. Â Sake tends to have a higher alcohol content than wine; we therefore opted for the 300 ml option. Â About halfway through the meal, we went with bride of the fox; another junmai ginjo. Â Spectacular and once again an incredible smooth finish that was a flawless accompany to the food.We both wanted dessert and selected the homemade cheesecake and lava cake. Â Both were delicious; portions were small which was perfect. Â The lava cake was topped with sesame ice cream and was uniquely delectable, satisfying, without being extremely filling.Even the ambiance is sheer perfection. Â The restaurant is small and intimate. Â It works for couples that want to hang out or friends that want to get together. Â It works for date night. Â It works for girls night out. Â It seriously works for any occasion. Â The menu is a bit rushed but I do not hold this against the restaurant. Â My preference would have been to spend double the time I was there as I like time between courses. Â Their website states that parties of 2 are limited to 90 minutes of dining time as they are a small restaurant and there is high demand. Â Guess I can live with that. Hey Michelin, time to give a sushi place in Chi-Town a couple of nods.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',869,'2017-03-10',5,'One of the BEST restaurants out there!!! I have been there 3 times so far and cannot wait until I can go back next. Most recently was in October for my boyfriends birthday. I made reservations the day before and they accommodated me with the only time they had which was later at night around 9 but I did not care because we wanted to go so bad. They called me back twice to tell me that there were cancellations and we were able to get the dinner time up about 2 hours earlier that I originally had. We ordered the Omakase and it was PHENOMENAL!! These chefs know exactly what they are doing. Perfect courses came to our table one after the other and we enjoyed every single bite. I highly recommend ordering the omakase instead of just picking from the menu. Pretty much all of the best things from the menu were included in the Omakase. WORTH THE MONEY! We did bring our own bottle of wine (there is a corkage fee) but also ordered sake ) Ended the perfect meal with some mochi! Seriously, this place is worth every penny you spend. The most delicious sushi and amazing staff!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',525,'2016-11-29',5,'Everything we tried was amazing and flavorful from the shooters, sushi, sashimi, & down to dessert. Definitely going for the Premium Omakase next time around.Service was top notch.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',843,'2017-10-12',4,'Im not the biggest sushi fan. Dont get me wrong I like sushi, but typically I follow the model of - the more things added to the bite crunchy, saucy, chewy - the better. Â BUT this place WOW this place will make you a believer of both the very complex and the very simple. Â As most of the other reviewer have mentioned, order the omakase. Â Give yourself over the the chef and team at Kai Zan - you will not regret it and in return youll experience one of the best meals of your life (and not just in the sushi category). Â Its kind of ruined it for my former local fave.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',232,'2021-04-18',5,'I want to give 3 stars at first, the tuna and salmon sashimi is really bad,however, the Madai Carpaccio is soooo great! And recommend the escolar and Maguro pearls are nice too~',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ac67183',1506,'2018-05-07',5,'The food is good and the service is amazing. Â I am more of a traditional sushi gal and some of the dishes seemed so overpowered by the smoke flavor, mayo, etc. Â Maybe next time Ill just get the nigiri pieces in lieu of the omakase.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',299,'2017-04-18',4,'I thought that another restaurant was my fave sushi spot in town...its now a clear second! Everything about my experience at Kai Zan was great - the service, the decor and private booths, the sale recommendation, and of course the food itself. Every bite was delicious in a different way. Cant wait to try the omakase next time!Recommended wagyu special, that one with the basil oil, the polenta bites, and then pretty much everything else, on and off the menu.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',226,'2021-10-14',5,'This place is so good! We shared a standard omakase and ordered some singles dishes and dessert on the side. Let me tell you, each dish within the omakase menu is unique and special in its own way. The rolls/sashimi are not typically what you would find in a standard Japanese restaurant. Some were sweet, some were spicy. Some were warm, others were cold. Honestly, for less than $100, the two person omakase is truly a bargain for the experience.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum23143',609,'2022-02-04',5,'My boyfriend and I thought we would grab a table on Friday right after I arrived to Chicago for the weekend. They were all booked -- highly recommend making a reservation. We made a reservation for the following Sunday at 815PM. I was glad they seated us at the bar. I enjoyed watching the orders come in and watching Chef Carlo & Chef Melvin create each dish spectacularly. Â It felt like this was something they could do with their eyes closed, incredibly entertaining. We ordered the Chefs Choice ($60/person) and it was hands down the best sushi/sashimi experience that Ive ever had. Its 10 courses -- I began to feel myself slow down at 5. We finished all, save for the last dish which they boxed up and we took home. There were a few dishes, like the shooters with quail eggs and scallops, where I had to stop a prepare myself for something new. No worries though, the flavors were delicious and fresh. Its a small restaurant, but the atmosphere is intimate and comfortable. Â Our server was well-versed in each dish that came our way. The rest of the staff was very attentive. Our water glasses were never empty and our plates were cleared promptly. The chef slid an off-menu roll across the bar between the 7th and 8th course that was the most wonderful marriage of flavors and textures that I wish my boyfriend hadnt eaten his so that I could have another. 100% satisfied. I would recommend Kai Zan to everyone. I would love to go again. My advice is to try everything, take it slow, and arrive with an empty stomach.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',610,'2018-07-31',5,'The waitress was kind and personable, fish was fresh, presentation was good. However, they need to work more on sushi rice - the rice for nigiri and maki were cooked too hard, and pressed too much when it was formed to sushi. Sushi rice at the expensive restaurant has to gently fall apart in your mouth.Overall taste was salty side.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',797,'2018-12-27',4,'Generally not a fan of Asian fusion type places - especially when it comes to Japanese cuisine - but, I must say I really enjoyed the food and my experience at Kai Zan. Â The waitstaff was fantastic, very friendly and knowledgeable of every item - describing in detail what each dish consisted of down to each ingredient. Â Took my brother here for his birthday and we ordered the Omakase (Chefs choice) which, I think, is a great deal considering its a 10-course meal that allows you to try a variety of items. Â Considering there were only two of us, we did an up-charge that adds $10 to the price of the Omakase where there were a few select single items that they doubled to allow us each to try. Â My favorites Dynamite mussels, orange rush, and oyster shooters. Â The flavors and textures were amazing!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec37198',881,'2019-04-24',5,'Let me just start off by saying how amazing the hostess was! I couldnt make my 545pm reservation and called to cancel, as there were no open time slots until 9pm. Within 15 minutes, Maya called me back to inform me that they had a cancellation and she wanted to offer me that time slot!The fish.... was the freshest I had ever had in Chicago. I have tried so many sushi restaurants but this was beyond what I expected. Angry crab, fiesta maki, flaming tuna, grilled hamachi nigiri and ebi sushi were all amazing! I could have this ebi sushi 1000 times!I was so excited to try everything and ordered a ton of food... some of which I really shouldnt have... I would pass on the skewers and yaki soba but try as much sushi and sashimi as you can!',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',1450,'2021-08-08',5,'Hands down among the best sushi Ive ever had! Seriously melted in my mouth. Plus its BYOB. I dont think I saw another dinner or table in my visit! Totally nice change of pace giving an intimate feel. Again with a group, sampled the menu. Of all the things I loved the flaming tuna the most, oh and the angry crab, oh and fiesta maki, oh and the escolar pearls, oh and the mussels, oh and ... Too many tastey things to boast Ive lost track!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',241,'2018-01-02',4,'Hard to find but worth it. The focus is on the amazing ingredients in an understated ambiance. I tried two of their toros and they were outstanding. along with the normal powdered wasabi they supplied some fresh ground wasabi (and now Im ruined for life). Beyond their wide list of fish they offered a list of 20+ other fish (all sustainable) I had never tasted before. The least expensive but best meal we had on our long weekend in Chicago.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',835,'2019-01-22',5,'I tried the chef special! And the seasonal chef special. They both exceeded my expectations! I always leave this place in the best of moods! Thank you to the chefs and the staff! You continue to surprise me! I wish i would of taken pictures but it was too good! I was enjoying it so much that i didnt even think to grab my phone.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisi29157',54,'2019-05-29',5,'Great food! we went there to try their premium omakase and regular omakase,unfortunately premium omakase is not available but there are some off menu  we settle for their omakase over all it was great,presentation is amazing,taste is great.we also tried their yakisoba,kinda remind me of some noodle serve at some airline,its Â good too but my favorite is their flaming tuna and the uni wrap(off menu) .will definitely going back to try more in and off menu items and of course their premium omakase. Great service too! Chef Melvin is very accommodating!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempus72169',1054,'2018-01-22',5,'My friend recommended this place to me when I visiting so I came in at 5pm, 30mins after it opened not realizing how packed it already gets! Even though I didnt have a reservation, the hostess managed to fit me and my plus 1 in!The food was incredible! Tried their octopus, scallop, and salmon rolls along with their Suki Slamon special and this special beef from Japan (sorry forgot the name!) and everything was cooked perfectly. The meat and fish just melted in your mouth, and had so much flavorful without being overwhelming. Our server Daniel was also super knowledgeable and was so great and honest with all his recommendations.The place itself is a little small so it has this cozy, snug, intimate ambience. But they do have booths if you need to RSVP larger groups.Great food and terrific service! I will definitely be back.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',466,'2016-09-12',5,'Wow, this place is outstanding. We had the Omakase and every dish was beautifully presented and tasting. Its an experience not to be missed by sushi lovers!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',218,'2017-08-14',4,'Omkase is great! Its BYOB. Best to make reservations. Parking isnt that bad for street parking',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',925,'2021-02-02',5,'Beautiful meal!! We had the omakase a couple of months ago and it did not disappoint. The fish was so fresh and delicious but a couple of courses were a little too adventurous for me! (If you are into that sort of thing, definitely get the omakase but if you arent stick to the maki roll menu.)',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc61133',274,'2019-12-13',5,'Oh Lordy!! I was beyond excited to go here!! Heard awesome raves, but unfortunately the night did not live up to par. I made reservations a WEEK ahead for this place, got there on time and still had to wait 45 mins for my table. At that point I really didnt care what we ate as long as it was food. The server was rude and hurried us along, our meal time was shorter than the time we waited!!! I didnt feel welcomed or felt like they wanted me back!!! Horrible time.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',46,'2016-12-24',4,'Amazing !!!!!! My husband and I came here for our anniversary dinner which was highly recommended by friends and we were not disappointed !! We did the chiefs special which was $70 per person and its an 8 course meal . Everything was absolutely delicious and delectable - every detail was considered to awakens your taste buds . The staff was very friendly . Its a smaller space so I would recommend making reservations . I love that its BYOY. Overall , I cant wait to go back . Its pricey but 100% worth it .',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',1358,'2018-05-09',5,'This is the BEST sushi, and service in Chicago. Complex flavor profiles that explode in your mouth. EXTREMELY helpful, knowledgable staff! Food comes quick which I always appreciate. On the pricey side, BUT WORTH EVERY PENNY. Great for a special occasion or just being in the mode for phenomenal meal. We will continue to go back. Highly recommend!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',976,'2020-09-27',5,'Reservations only - the place is small, but the food is ...perfection.I got the chefs tasting menu. There wasnt one thing I didnt like. Just go.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat1120',150,'2017-03-08',4,'Are you kidding me?? This place is magic! If you have not eaten here, please do yourself a favor and go NOW! I took my best friend for his birthday and we were blown away! I have had sushi and chefs tasting menus before, but this is by far THE best!! Great ambience and great service!! All I can say is Thank you Thank you Thank you!!! Its a great place for an intimate meal. Get the chefs choice menu and you cant go wrong.',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',1662,'2019-08-19',5,'When we sat down, we began chatting with our server about all the rave reviews wed heard about this unsuspecting sushi spot. He said that some people had told him it was, the best sushi in the world.I dont know if Id go THAT far (we are landlocked after all and this IS humboldt park), but the sushi dinner two friends and I had here last night was one of the best Ive had. Yes, probably ever. The escolar and maguro pearls were amazing starters. So fresh you actually feel a fresh taste in your mouth - I kid you not. We had a number of other specialty rolls, and a few classics, and everything was top-notch quality and served at a perfect pace. We all commented afterward how it felt different than post meal at other sushi places - you feel refreshed and satisfied - and not bogged down by too much breading or preservatives. While it was tough to get a reso here, and the location is a bit of a trek depending on where you live, I highly recommend and would definitely go back! Its small, though, so plan on going 11 or with a 4 -person group at max.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu25190',85,'2017-04-29',5,'Ive had both the regular omakase and the more fulfilling new omakase, and enjoyed all the courses. I especially liked the uni shooter from the regular menu and the seaweed powered salmon from the new omakase.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',722,'2018-02-18',4,'Just like all the reviewers before me, I enjoyed my visit to Kai Zan. The fish is super fresh and their menu offers a broad range of choices. I highly recommend this gem of a restaurant. Grab your family and friends and treat yourself to some great sushi.Also, the waiters are very attentive and knowledgeable.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',716,'2019-09-05',5,'Chefs menu was amazing!!! Although I didnt appreciate being told by the hostess that there was Â another reservation after (curse of the 530 rez) and thus there was a time limit on our booth because it made me feel rushed as we went through the 10 courses of amazing fish. Other than that rather curt notification from the hostess the food was amazing and the service staff was knowledgable and attentive.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus0123',1238,'2017-09-07',5,'Making the reservation through yelp was easy. Went there with my boyfriend last night and we had a good time. Our server was very patient and polite and answered all our questions. The food was delicious too. The chef accommodated my request for sushi naruto style since Im avoiding carbs. The salmon collar was also very tasty and it was a good deal for $14! My boyfriend enjoyed his firecracker sushi and chicken teriyaki as well. All thumbs up',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt58127',628,'2019-05-07',4,'Great food and service. It is probably one of the best Japanese restaurants in Chicago. We come here for anniversary or birthday dinners since it is a bit pricey for us for a weekly dinner, but well worth the price for a special night out. You have to make reservations way in advance to get a good time. Usually if you wait till the week of, you will only get early slots (before 5pm) or late slots (10pm). This last time my husband had the omakase, which he loved. I had the Yaki Soba with shrimp, which I also enjoyed.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',613,'2022-01-13',5,'Kai zan has been on my list of places to try for a while. My expectations were really high considering all the great reviews. I was really excited for a great adventure so we ordered the omakase. Â The service was friendly and quick. I enjoyed the first two dishes of the ten the snapper carpaccio and escolar pearls. Both were well balanced dishes. As for the rest of the dishes, i wasnt that much of a fan. I am a bit bias toward more traditional nigri but the fish in the sashimi wasnt great quality. Roll was nothing more than a standard tuna and salmon roll with chilli (i hate when people add spice to cover fish quality). The escolar was a bit icy within the fish. Â Maybe on my next visit, i should try ordering a la carte sushi.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien72146',739,'2018-08-03',5,'OMG. Best sushi restaurant I have ever been to in my 62 years. Â We had the Chef Special Omakase. Â Unbelievable. Â It changes, but want you to read what we had. Â Zuke salmon, Lamp pop, Chawan Mush which was a soup, Otoro, Lobster & Scallop nigiri, Kani Tsunomono, Otoro Shira Koji with cubed heirloom tomatoes and edible flowers, Aji and Whole Fried Horse Mackerel with sashimi, Otoro, Sake belly, & Hamachi bely, LIVE green and yellow Scallops, Gunkan Maki avocado and corn, and last Kushiro Oyster with Ankimo. Every flavor was different and great.The service was impeccable. Â The explanations of the sushi items were very helpful. Â If you can go, save up, it is worth it.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec5093',1020,'2017-06-13',5,'Hidden gem on the west side of Chicago. We couldnt decide what to order so we opted for one chefs choice and one premium omakase in order to experience their current offerings. Overall we had a lovely evening. The dishes were thoughtfully prepared. They were visually beautiful and tasteful. Or as I like to say they had dining hat trick- TTV - taste, texture and visual. In addition to the food, the service was exceptional. We had a trio of waiters present our 19 dishes (omg) and the culinary knowledge shared between them was outstanding. Cant wait to go back.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',1602,'2018-03-02',4,'This deserves 10 stars!! Great quality of fish and the service was perfect. Me and my mom had the Chefs Choice and it was insanely good and also not too overpriced for what you are getting. Cant wait t go back!',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vulputate64142',578,'2021-01-18',5,'Came here to celebrate my husbands birthday and it was the perfect night. We ordered the tasting menu, which was adventurous for new sushi enthusiasts. Really enjoyed our meal here. It felt very special and the waitstaff were wonderful - describing each course as it came out and answering any questions we had. Looking forward to coming back soon!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean67124',1617,'2018-06-19',5,'This place is awesome, definitely not your average sushi experience! The Omakase tasting menu is a must here, and you definitely wont be disappointed. Its also very well priced. Interesting flavors and every dish is a surprise itself. We had such a great night at Kai Zan, I cant recommend it enough',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',1598,'2021-04-02',4,'While this was by no means a bad meal, it was disappointing in that expectations were quite lofty based on other reviews here as well as positive experiences friends passed on and even recommendations from a couple people in the industry. Having recently enjoyed the best sushi experience of my life at Kusakabe in San Francisco, my wife and I were hoping to find a venue to fall in love with in Chicago to frequent regularly. The first annoying aspect had to do with the time limit on ones reservation. Kai Zan used to be BYOB and is a smallish venue, so I can understand the concept of a time limit to prevent people from lingering after the food is gone to finish wine - costing the restaurant revenue and delaying reservations to follow. However now that Kai Zan has a liquor license and serves wine, sake and beer this seems unnecessary. And it was complete overkill to inform me of a 90 minute time limit (for two-tops) and 120 minute limit (four for tops) when reserving online, then again via voice mail when Kai Zan called to confirm the reservation, then a third time when I called them back (as requested) to confirm I received their confirmation. Before entering I actually half expected to see a stop watch on the table counting down my allotted time. That said the initial impression upon arrival was positive. We were dining with another couple and our friends arrived early and were immediately seated rather than made to wait for our arrival. Loved our placement as well; spacious, comfortable, aesthetically pleasing booth surrounded by three walls - almost like a mini private dining room. Our primary server, Brian, was rather friendly as well.At Kai Zan one has the option of a la carte, a ten course Chefs Choice Omakase ($60 per/person) that involves a progression of items from the a la carte menu (dessert is optional and additional) or a premium Omakase (price varies, was $130 the night we dined - this involves a sequence of courses generally not on the a la carte menu and it is recommended to be requested in advance due to limited availability). We opted for the $60 Omakase and had our server recommend some sakes by the glass to pair (he made some nice recommendations and often brought samples to try before committing to the glass which was much appreciated). The major disappointment involved the generally mediocre quality of the cuisine. While all but one course was fine, there were zero stand outs and lots of repetition (i.e. big eye tuna was featured in quite a few of the ten courses; a generic fish that you expect to find at an inexpensive all-you-can-eat sushi venue). There was a nice variety of presentations (i.e. rolls, sashimi, nigiri, shooters, soup, a fun course where you create a taco by wrapping tuna and seaweed into a shiso leaf etc.) but with rare exception they were no better quality wise (or just a small step up) from fare Ive received at unheralded run-of-the-mill sushi joints. Often truffle oil or citrus sauces overpowered the fish and the high quality experience we were expecting was just not there. In addition to an overabundance of big eye tuna, tobiko was present as a component in nearly every course. One dish, a mushroom soup was nearly inedible; unpleasantly salty broth and a smelly, extremely fishy tasting piece of cheap tuna. The sake was definitely the biggest hit of the evening at our table with the Bride of the Fox being the consensus favorite. In addition to the food being a let down, a couple other negatives (on top of the aforementioned annoyance regarding the time limit); at times beverage service was slow (at one point three courses came and went from the time my wife ordered a glass of sake to the time it arrived) and periodically the courses were brought in such rapid succession it resulted in feeling kind of rushed (i.e. twice new courses arrived before the previous course was consumed - and it was not attributable to us dawdling). When dropping over $100 per/person (including food/drink/tax/gratuity) I expect at least a somewhat leisurely dining experience. I do have to give credit to Kai Zan for value; even though the food only generally ranged from OK to pretty good, we did receive a lot of courses for $60 (often with more than one distinct component per course) and I left completely full (we also ordered one supplemental roll, a Japanese Wagyu roll with freshly shaved black truffle - but nothing else extra). That said I think Kai Zan needs to either up the price of the Chefs Choice Omakase and include better variety and quality of fish or have a middle tier option between the $130 Premium and $60 Chefs Choice where without breaking the bank one can receive a meal that is clearly elevated from what is available at nearly every sushi joint in town.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra80187',24,'2019-05-31',5,'The service was great, but the fish is not. The premium Omagase never compares to the one from another restaurant in town Katsu. You can tell the chef has put a lot of efforts into decorating the dish, but again sashimi is more about how fresh the fish is rather then how the dish looks like. I would recommend if you are looking for a great dining experience but NOT if you are looking for great sashimi.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus31129',299,'2020-07-05',5,'Was visiting Chicago and had read all these great reviews so made a reservation. Both my husband and I had the omakase menu. Both of us agree it was the best sushi we have ever had. The fish was so fresh and flavorful. The combination of flavors was perfect. The staff (especially Alan) was wonderful and very knowledgeable which made the experience just amazing.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',1555,'2016-06-15',5,'Went there for a dinner before Christmas holiday! First impressions, I would say that the place is as small as it gets for a restaurant, heard that they could only fit about 22 seats. You barely have space to walk around (that is if you ever need to). The place isnt decorated like your typical sushi bar, because it isnt one. Kai Zan is more of a fusion sushi place, I dont think people who hate fusion sushi places would be fond of this place much. Although, it is not the typical fusion sushi either, where all their dishes are carefully made with great ingredients that go well together that are not things like stupid cream cheese or spicy mayo.All I hear about this place is its Omakase. The fact that I was there the first time and didnt want to bother looking at the menu much or take time to think my order through because everything sounds delicious leaned me towards ordering the Omakase. This way, I would be able to taste the best of the menu that the Chef wants to offer his diners. Overall food was great, everything had great balance to it. Theres about 10 courses, so you dont really have to order anything else. I would say all their dishes are upscale fusion sushi, which is definitely what people who are a fan of sushi and want to explore somewhere else without leaving the traditional mindset.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',49,'2018-05-13',5,'Favorite sushi place in town! Always fresh, good ambiance for a date, girls night or client meeting. Friendly service and they take reservations!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',455,'2017-02-17',4,'Fantastic restaurant. The omakase is a great deal although it is light on sushi and far more tilted towards small Japanese bites that incorporate raw fish. Definitely worth it though.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cc110',254,'2019-09-20',5,'Uni shooter and the Orange rush - Â are the must have ! Everything was great )We will definitely come back again',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede2192',1202,'2021-07-08',5,'Best sushi in the city. Hands down. If youre actually a sushi eater - this is your spot. Im kind of over rolls after 10 years of eating sushi and kai zan is the best at small sashimi bites! It isnt BYOB anymore apparently, but they allowed us to bring in our wine and charged us a cork fee. I definitely recommend doing the omakse, it was such an awesome experience and I tried things I would normally never order.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',770,'2020-04-16',4,'I went there for my birthday and got the Omakase. I never had a tasting menu before at any restaurant so I was hesitant thinking it would either be too much food and too much flavors going on. Not the case here at Kai Zan. Each course was impeccably executed and complimented the previous and succeeding course without being overwhelming. The fish was fresh and the flavors melded together perfectly. Â My boyfriend got some rolls and robata a la carte and those were delicious as well. Â My favorites have to be the Angry Crab, Tako Yaki and the special of the day Blue Fin Tuna Roll. Â I will certainly be back! Thank you Kai Zan!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem1829',1606,'2021-02-10',5,'Id really love to give this place 5 stars but theres 2 things stopping me. First though, the food was incredible. We did the $60/person omakase and I was seriously blown away on flavor and presentation, and was even pushed to try things I wouldnt have eaten before(i.e. Raw quail egg). The atmosphere was laid back and romantic, timing was great, we didnt have to wait long between courses and we left full, which sometimes doesnt happen from chefs choice tastings at other places. I cant give it 5 stars because of the service. Our reservation was at 430 so we arrived at 420. Turns out they open at 430 so everything was locked. It was like 40 degrees and raining. I could literally see the hostesses and servers inside so I called and the girl who answered said shed send someone out to open the door for us. But no one came until 431. So our meal was eaten while wet, shivering and cold. While its not their fault it was raining, i dont understand Â how a place takes a reservation but then doesnt allow for people to arrive early. Lastly our server was...nice, but very unusual. You would think hed never spoken to another person before and was very jittery, didnt make eye contact, and crossed his arms with his hands under his armpits several times. Definitely didnt want him touching our plates but what can ya do',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',1540,'2021-10-26',5,'Exceptional sushi restaurant. Â I had the sampler. Â It was $65 and was plenty of food with a wide variety. Â The staff is beyond professional. Â The atmosphere is relaxing and pleasant. Â This organization is well run and executes the dining experience flawlessly.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',1604,'2019-12-14',4,'Second time Im there - had the classic Omakase. Really great - everything was very delicious. I wish they didnt use any mayo-based sauces - I felt that some of the sushi toppings were mayo-based. But an excellent experience nevertheless. Well deserved.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus366',136,'2017-01-03',5,'One of the best dining experiences Ive had. Â  The chefs tasting menu was 10 courses of deliciousness. Â I dont know how they get such fresh fish in Chicago, but every bite was magnificent. Â Much better than Katzu or other similar experiences. Â Very reasonably priced wine list and attentive service. Â My wife has Celiac disease and they really took great care of her to make sure there was no gluten present. Only complaint is that the parking can be a bit tough on a cold February night. Â A must try in Chicago.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1346,'2021-12-05',5,'If I could, I would dine here every day for breakfast, lunch and dinner!The best sushi experience Ive ever had... period.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',1653,'2017-03-28',5,'I have been going here since they opened and the address was a 1/2 address. Â The knowledge the staff has from the hostess, to the server and those incredible chefs is a great gift to your palate!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',1593,'2017-05-17',5,'I came here with my boyfriend and another couple on Valentines day and there was no disappointment whatsoever. We made reservations about 3-4 days before because they apparently become booked really quickly. When we came in they have really cute, tiny rooms that had candles lit up in the middle along with rose petals. That had to be the most adorable table setting ever. During Valentines day they had a 10 course meal all prepped out for $95. Â Literally every single item on that menu was outstanding. My favorite were their oyster shooters. You can tell that their fish is very well prepared and really fresh. Every bite I took from each course was literally mind blowing. The texture of everything is so soft and smooth yet the flavor was so powerful. I would definitely come back to this place if I ever return to Chicago! Very pleased with the whole experience and service. They also gave the ladies roses on the way out ;) Very generous!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',578,'2019-12-11',5,'Had dinner last night, absolutely fabulous. Â Food and service in this small quaint jewel is worth going to. Â They dont have their liquor license so they have a BYOBThe food is prepared with such finesse and creativity, this place has nowhere to go but to the top of the charts. Â We were served by the sister of the two brother chef team, this is a real family affair, and they know what they are doing.I wont go into detail about the food, you just gave to experience it yourself, and it is an experience. Â Listen to their suggestions they will steer you in the right direction based on your likes and dislikes',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',420,'2021-10-18',5,'I came here last week with a friend without a reservation. The receptionist ended up seating us down after a 10 minute wait after a table didnt show up. Im giving the place a 4 star instead of 5 because while she sat us down she informed us that we only had about an hr to eat because of another reservation coming in so we werent able to try out the chefs special. And also our server wasnt the best server. It took him a while to check up in us to see if we wanted to order anything else and it was our first time there so we didnt know the menu like that and while he was explaining the food on the menu he spoke too fast so i couldnt really understand what he was talking about and we ended up having to figure out what each items was by looking up pictures on yelp. The food was absolutely delicious. Everything was so fresh and marinated well. And our bill actually wasnt that much either. I would most likely try this place again hoping to get a different server.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',984,'2017-08-08',4,'I came to Kai Zan to celebrate my husbands birthday with another couple and had an amazing time. Granted, we are all sushi snobs and we usually stick to what we love which is Coast and Toro in Chicago but after all the hype and great reviews of this place, I decided to check it out. I made reservations like a few weeks in advance which apparently wasnt enough to land us the golden table. By golden table I mean those private four to six people booths. Now, those look freaking fantastic. When we came in around 8pm on a Saturday night, I kindly asked how long would the wait be for one of those fancy little private areas and the hostess up front told me about an hour. We didnt want to wait that long and just settled for our table. It wasnt too bad, by the window overlooking the bar, so we got to see all the action. I absolutely loved the decor and atmosphere here, perhaps more than Coast and Toro combined, it was sheek, but not overly done, not too loud and the wooden tables gave it that rustic feel which you dont usually get at these sushi places, it had that upscale feel without overwhelming prices. Okay, so now onto the important stuff, the goodies. We started with the dynamite mussels and Oh em gee were those amazing. You definitely need to try those, they are a tad spicy and comes six for $12. Definitely a great start to your meal. What I didnt like is that your sushi doesnt come out all at once, it comes out as its ready. Having said that, they mixed up a few of our rolls adding avocado instead of cucumber and forgot to bring the green monster roll for my friend. But the server made up for it later on by giving us all dessert on the house since we had to wait a little longer than most people and some of the rolls were wrong. Anyways, we got the angry crab, made with fresh tuna, spicy crab with chefs togarashi. It was delicious and also comes in a hand roll version for $9. We seriously got three of those by the end of the night. Then my husband got what I believe is the fiesta roll with plenty of fresh fish which he seemed to enjoy, dont quote me on the name though and its not on the website. We also got a bunch of simple spicy salmon, avocado with eel rolls just to get a feel of the fish. And the fish was super fresh and tasty and the prices overall were very decent for what you get. Like I said, although the service was a little shaky, she made up for it by the end and we got chocolate lava cake, mango pudding and green tea ice cream for the table. They were all yummy but not memorable. Sushi is where its at in this place and next time I will definitely call way in advance to try to get that private room. Kai Zan, youre a new sushi favorite of mine.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',866,'2018-04-27',5,'Best sushi spot in town. Period.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra37167',817,'2020-08-03',5,'I plan to write a longer, more thorough review but I had to at least give the 5 stars it deserves. Â Melvin and Carlo are awesome and have done something wonderful with the small space the restaurant lives in. Â They even said welcome back! when I came in last Thursday. Â Its always nice when owners appreciate your business.Food is delicious, escolar and maguro pearls melt in your mouth. Â If youre lucky enough to try the uni and uni/otoro tartar special, DO IT. This is a must go place and although I want Melvin and Carlo to get the business they deserve, I hope it doesnt get so busy that I cant squeeze in a reservation )',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien4153',1505,'2016-09-19',4,'Best place Ive been to ever for sushi and experience!!! Recommend the chef special, gives a great variety and experience of multiple tastes!! Will return again!',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed7891',360,'2016-07-27',5,'Hoe lee fuck that was good. The wait staff was amazing. Everyone works together, and I would definitely be back here.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a22154',75,'2018-10-11',5,'Hands down the best sushi spot in the city. Its honestly more of an experience. You get what you pay for and its not cheap. Albeit the neighborhood in it is a little rough, I was offered cocaine outside and was met with a nasty response when I replied with a no thank you. But the food is incredible, wish theyd open a location in Lakeview/Lincoln Park.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',525,'2016-08-31',4,'Best sushi in Chicago. PERIOD. Im a food snob, especially when it comes to sushi, this is one sushi restaurant that I go back to time and again.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dis16196',257,'2022-01-14',5,'Kai Zan is pretty much my new favorite sushi place - EVER. I would do downright dirty and evil things for their veggie rolls.Heres my top faves about Kai Zan- Unbelievable, intimate ambiance. If at all possible, reserve a booth on the left hand side of the restaurant. - Enoki bacon. Get 5. Hell, get 10. Enoki mushrooms wrapped tightly with a piece of grilled bacon with a side of ginger dressing...whats not to love?- Totally veggie friendly. I dont eat much seafood. In fact, I really dont eat any. The chefs at Kai Zan are more than willing to make just about any of their rolls vegetarian. Be warned though - you will still pay menu price.- Rice free rolls. Yep - thats right. Rice free. See below.- The Karaage (aka - fried chicken) Every dude at the table raved how it was the best fried chicken theyve ever eaten. I didnt necessarily agree, but I didnt disagree either.- The Green Monster - Even though I prefer this vegetarian, nothing is better than veggies wrapped in avocado.- Reservations accepted! Make sure you make them - the place is tiny and gets packed Â fast.Love sushi. Love veggie rolls. Love Kai Zan.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',1246,'2016-09-14',5,'We had a fantastic meal at Kai Zan last night! Â We ordered the Omakase tasting menu, and added the 2 specials of the night a wagyu beef and a tuna chip. Everything was so delicious, thoughtfully prepared, and interesting. Â The flavors were impeccably fresh, complex and simple at the same time. This is Japanese food at its best in chicago! Our party of 4 got to sit in a practically a private room - it was so intimate and lovely. Plus- the hostess and waitstaff were extremely friendly, even letting us try a couple roses and sakes from the menu before ordering. We have a new favorite spot in chicago!!!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',887,'2022-01-28',5,'Carlo and Melvin are both have a extraordinary ability to craft artful japanese dishes that are out of this world. Â I highly recommend the chefs omakase tasting with a mix of both sushi/sashimi and hot dishes.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',1613,'2021-07-26',5,'Hands down my #1 favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago. Nothing beats Kai Zan on taste, ambiance, quality, and value. First came here in 2012 and havent stopped since. Everything on the menu is amazing, and the creativity of the dishes and rolls really work. I would eat here every day if I could. Service is great, place is hip but not too hip where its pretentious, cozy (not good for large parties over 8 max), and menu is just large enough. Priced right. Ive told all my friends about this place and it has become their fave sushi place too. They have daily specials that change which is always nice, and an 11-course chefs tasting menu (totally worth it!).Some standouts Green Monster, Angry Crab, Danielle, Orange Rush and Flaming Tuna.Basically order everything, you cannot go wrong here!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',1036,'2021-07-07',5,'My girlfriend recently took me to Kai Zan for a special birthday dinner and we were nothing less than impressed! I would recommend the chefs tasting if you are open minded or adventurous as it gives you a great variety of what Kai Zan offers. Everything we tried was spectacular and so fresh. We were able to sit at the bar so we could see the chefs at work which I would recommend. It is on the more expensive end but very worth the quality and portion size.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',353,'2020-07-15',4,'Kai Zan!!!! Out of this world sushi. The uni is the freshest uni youll come across in Chicago. Everything on the menu is a slam dunk. We love sushi and have gone to some of the best places this city has to offer. Kai Zan is hands down number one.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('velit13144',1459,'2021-09-12',4,'While there are a few incredibly delicious bites to be enjoyed at Kai Zan, the bad outweighs the good.We chose to celebrate my brothers birthday here last night (Sat 6/21) and were seated in a cozy private booth. Â Kai Zan is BYOB so we brought a few bottles of wine. Our server Chris was nice, and did his best to provide a good experience, but the philosophy of the management here is get in, get the hell out fast.Three of us ordered the Omakase. Â The pacing of the coursing is absurd! Â We had three or four courses brought out within minutes, both hot and cold items. Â Theres no point in doing a tasting and exploring a restaurants menu when the chefs insist on sending everything out in chaos without any direction or order. Â We asked Chris what the deal was and he said hed try to slow it down. Â Sometimes three items at once would come out, then nothing for 20 to 30 minutes or so. Â I realize this may sound a bit whiny, but again, how simple of a concept is it to allow guests to savor and reflect on each course, rather than just shove food at us like were at a buffet?In addition to the ridiculous pacing, almost every dish had mayo on it. Â In some instances it worked well, but often I felt it just distracted from what should be clean, thoughtful flavors. Â The moment the last piece of sushi was eaten from our plates, they were cleared and a check was dropped. Â Literally minutes after we paid, the receipts were collected, and the manager (Im assuming, as she never introduced herself) Â asked us to leave since she had other tables. Â Theres a tough balance for restaurants in providing a good experience to its guests while also turning tables, but there was no tact or intelligence in this one. Â The right thing to do would have been to politely give us a heads up that in a few minutes theyd need the table, and offer a remedy, such as, such and such bar down the street is fun, this place is good for coffee, etc.. Â Kai Zan lacks tact, execution, and elegance, but not mayonaise.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',1560,'2017-01-15',5,'My absolute favorite sushi place in Chicago. Food is outstanding!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',1376,'2021-06-29',3,'Kaizan has weird hours and if you try to make a reservation for a large group, they treat you poorly. The woman on the phone was less than courteous, informing me that it was a hardship to accommodate 8 people for dinner, and that for such a party, they require you to order the $60 chefs tasting menu. To make it easier for the chef. These cats need a lesson in customer service.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',1439,'2019-10-12',5,'Im going to keep it simple and sweet as possible if you dont want to read all of this Kai Zan is geared towards a *very* specific sort of demographic. Not to say that this is a bad thing, but then from what I have experienced from this first time visit today, Kai Zan has definitely pulled the beginners club card upon my boyfriend and I as we were in the restaurant for about nearly two hours, oogling over the 10-course wonder that is the premium Omakase dinner. I feel that Kai Zan tries to live up to its expectations and the ever-tenacious repertoire of tuna-loving sushi freaks based in the West who have not even gone outside the realms of the gang of four salmon, tuna, yellowtail (hamachi), and ebi (shrimp), with their names in acronym form read out as stye, which is probably enough clues to why I think that my visit to Kai Zan has made me feel like someone who is completely clueless and new to sushi.Back to what I ordered the 10-course Premium Omakase Dinner. It is advertised as having non-traditional ingredients, which looked very intriguing, as Kai Zan seems to pride itself over as having a Fusion element with their food as well. At the time my boyfriend and I ordered this, it was $130 per person. Under the assumption that Kai Zan interprets Omakase as up to the chef[s mood and choice], we were cool with everything until we realized that were still in a sushi establishment based in the West. Our server, who I forgot the name of (Im sorry in advance!) answered a few questions that we had as much as she could, mainly with concerns of being served rolls, wraps, and gimmicks to please the individuals who aim to eat foreign cuisines to appear more cultured or exotic. Bad news was the Omakase here is very much a predetermined menu, which really made me a bit wary about what was about to come. Good news was she ensured that we wouldnt receive any of that bad stuff, which we are THANKFUL for, but then we stumbled upon the next level of how sushi culture became a realm for buzzwords and people trekking to Japans Tsukiji Market in Tokyo just to take pictures of tuna, boasting about the price and name of the meat rather than the quality, and then leaving promptly without getting a taste.Buzzwords. Ootoro, Chuutoro, Akami, and Wagyu are the main triggers when it comes to thinking about Japanese food. We received all of these, if not more in our dinner tonight. Im not sad about it. Im not mad about it either. Its just that I felt a bit underwhelmed for paying $130 to receive stuff that is of excellent quality, taste, and presentation, but not that interesting nor memorable. So much for the innovation that seemed to burst out of this place. Out of the 10 dishes we had, at least 4 of them had some sort of tuna in it. Having one sort of thing once is great. Having one sort of thing in different variables but then are tangent to each other (i.e. ootoro nigiri with pickled wasabi, then shoyu glazed chuutoro)?? No, thank you!!! Also, there was no uni in our selection. Im a bit shocked there myself, having paid that amount and not receiving the therapeutic treatment of sea urchin, but instead having a load of fatty-cut fish served to me with no innovative palate cleanser in sight or mind to balance the elements out. It was extremely heavy on the mouth, and by extension, the soul and the stomach; contrary to the nature of enjoying sushi, sashimi and nigiri. Sure, this would be an excellent sensory and pleasure overload to those who arent that acquainted with the taste and art of raw fish, but then I was looking for something to remember, something unique. And thats why I decided on getting the Premium Omakase, let alone an Omakase meal. I left disappointed. I was expecting to be served stuff that will give me the chills, something that I wouldnt be able to recover from, leaving me wanting for more. I didnt feel like I got the Omakase treatment that usually entails a spur of the moment choice to go with whatever has been served to my table already, plus the requirement of ingenuity that comes with being called an Asian Fusion place that would make my head, heart, and stomach race with excitement. After the honeymoon period of my meal, I just felt completely empty and couldnt even recall what I have ate less than an hour ago. I would want to give Kai Zan another shot at redeeming themselves whenever I have the cash to spare, or if someone is willing to treat me there (*wink wink, nudge nudge*).If you want a good sushi experience here, get the Omakase. If you want an even better sushi experience here, research a bit before you visit, and write down what you want to try since Kai Zan can make stuff to order, as long as its a standard sushi, sashimi, or nigiri item of course. You played it too safe, Kai Zan. Until next time.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',683,'2016-02-14',5,'We are so happy to find the former Kyoto based twins who know how to prepare sushi. I wish I could remember their names! The menu has some Kyoto favorites, and then a number of other tasty preparations. Make sure to try the Escolar Pearls and the Green Monster. No longer BYO, but the food is amazing. We will be back!!',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',1257,'2016-03-22',4,'My boyfriend and I made reservations to this place based on the reviews on yelp for our anniversary. Initially we almost didnt even walk inside the place because the area it was in was definitely not what we were expecting; the area looked a little bit run down. However after some decision making we decided to give it a go, and ended up being pleasantly surprised. We ordered the omakase (tasting menu) and were blown away! We sat right in front of the chefs while they prepared and made all their dishes, and they also made us feel welcome by asking us how we were and making small conversation. The food was amazing and our bill was priced right for what you got. Unlike others, our service was fine and we were seated as soon as we walked in. Overall a great place for a date or going out in general.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',425,'2019-05-18',5,'Would definitely recommend to each of my friends. Food ingredients are super fresh and the combination of them are perfectly infused with each other. Considering its quality, Kai Zan is worthy to visit every time you want fresh Japanese sushi.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',1073,'2020-05-10',5,'After coming here about seven times, I just had to drop a quick note to say that every single thing Ive eaten here has been amazing. Â I highly, highly recommend it!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut42159',1335,'2017-10-06',4,'Amazing staff!!! Amazing food!!!The hostesses were beyond wonderful. Â Our server made the most spot on recommendations. Â Everything was just perfect.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',786,'2017-09-23',5,'This is the most exquisite sushi you will ever have in the states. Each taste will take you on a voyage to Japan. Omakase is the way to go. Enjoy!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in3395',477,'2020-05-18',5,'Always excellent - we ended up getting the Chefs choice omakase AND the more expensive Chefs tasting (off-menu items). Â Highly recommend making the extra investment. Â  Everything was fantastic, and service was super friendly.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',505,'2019-09-17',4,'This was our second time at Kai Zan celebrating a birthday with the New Omakase tasting menu, and as always left ecstatic. Best sushi experience in Chicao.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',1320,'2018-07-11',5,'Food was excellent as usual however they make you eat in 90 minutes , and believe me they keep reminding you every 20 minutes how much time is left. Â Extremely rude and very very rushed. Â They rushed us for our order and never let us finish each course before the next would come out. Â Terrible dining experience. Â Cheapens the experience.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',1010,'2021-09-20',5,'Great quality upscale Japanese restaurant. Everything is fresh and carefully made. The uni shooter is a gem! Sashimi is wonderful and worth the price. Would definately come again!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi5344',60,'2020-12-04',5,'This place is an experience. Every single thing we had was delightful - visually and taste wise. I think we spent almost double what we planned to spend because if something was amazing we would ask for another order of it. That seemed to happen a lot. The uni shooters were great. The escolar pearls might have been my favorite - I know we had two orders of them. The orange rush and salmon sashimi were other favorites. Food came out fast and we could not stop ordering different things. I will go with the Chefs menu next time just to see what we will end up with. I think we ended up doing 10-11 courses as it was. I forget a lot of what we had because I was having so much fun and pretty much everything was equally good. I cant speak about any of the hot dishes. We stuck to raw and could not go wrong.I highly recommend.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('Ettu14',1655,'2020-01-27',5,'Had an amazing experience at Kai Zan. Get the Omakase (chef special). It was $65 a person and totally worth it. You get more than enough food and we had a great time trying every item that was brought out. Our server did a great job explaining what was in each dish. Also, is BYOB and there is a $15 uncorking fee.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',552,'2020-08-05',4,'Excellent sushi. Happens to be 2 blocks from home, nonetheless Id highly recommend Kai Zan. Just make sure to make a reservation. Even on a Wednesday night in the dead of winter I had to wait 2 hours to get a seat for one at the sushi bar. Be prepared.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vulputate64142',743,'2020-09-20',5,'I took a friend for a birthday dinner. Tuesday and Wednesday nights they have an early bird special for $35 each between 5-530. Â Must make a reservation. Â It was DELICIOUS and more food than we could finish. Â The quality was the best I have eaten, the flavors and freshness were amazing. Â The decor and service above reproach. Highly recommended!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',594,'2021-07-29',5,'We had the premium omakase. We enjoyed every bite of every course. As foodies and sushi lovers we give the food 5 stars. The service was excellent UNTIL our waitress informed us as we were enjoying our last course that we needed to hurry up and pay and leave because they had people waiting for our table. Â Granted we had overstayed our two hour slot, but we had JUST been served the last course of our expensive meal. No asking if we wanted tea and no time to finish our wine. Felt a bit rude. They need to either require pre-order of the premium omakase to properly space out the reservations or quit offering it to their 2 hour seatings.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',1311,'2016-03-22',4,'Wow. Â Impeccable service for amazing sushi with beautiful presentation along with being quiet & cozy. Â Best restaurant in Chicago.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra2114',1698,'2016-06-06',5,'Outstanding experience. We had the chefs choice omikase, no idea what all I ate but everything was delicious. The grilled scallop was unlike any seafood Ive ever had, I will be fantasizing about that until I learn to recreate the dish.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',38,'2017-02-08',5,'Nice place, good experience with seafoods, recommend to taste chefs menu! We really enjoyed!!!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',872,'2021-08-04',4,'We had the Omakase course menu. Its a good experience if you have the money to blow. P Pro- byobCon- pricey',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',1680,'2018-05-07',5,'Food here was pretty good. Â It is also more pricey than most other sushi restaurants but I wanted to stray from norm and it was worth it. Â Also your dining time is limited but they let you know that upfront. Â The crowd reflects this as well as you will not find loud obnoxious BYOB Riff raff here. Â Big plus in my book. Â We had the omakase and many other dishes but cant remember them all. Â I like the fact that they keep the spicy mayo, wasabi mayo, unagi sauce and shrimp tempura to a minimum if not none! Â High five!!! Â  Dynamite, escolar pearls, scallop/oyster shooter and lobster nigiri were all standouts. Â Nigiri and sashimi were both very fresh, kudos!!!If you know sushi, if you like sushi, if youre sick of makis(despite what many Chicagoans think, makimonos w bunch cooked stuff and heavy sauce is NOT sushi) come here ready to spend and you will have great evening. Â My hats off and respect to the sushi twins!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',328,'2020-09-18',5,'I would give them 10 stars if I could.After hearing raving reviews from our friends husband and I decided to go there to celebrate something.. I forget if it was an anniversary or a birthday.Anyways, we went there early because we heard it gets extremely packed. Well, we mustve gone too early because the restaurant was near empty.We chose to do Omakase and good lord we were already full halfway through.The server seemed aloof but seemed to warm up to us towards the end. Â I think we got half of a smirk from him at the end. Â Back to the Omakase. It. Was. AMAZING.Every dish was melt in your mouth delicious. Â I cant remember how much we paid for the Omakase.. $60 0r $70? Â Something along that range and we lost count of how many courses we were served. Â Didnt matter since we were so full at the end.The chef/owner also came out at the end of our meal for a small chit-chat.Overall, great dining experience and I cant wait to go back,',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('platea7440',746,'2020-06-07',5,'I tried this place for the first time today....well I tried to. I came in alone at 530 and the place was empty with the exception of a few tables. They would not seat me because reportedly all tables were booked starting at 6 and they dont do dinner under an hour. I explained I would be quick as Im just trying to eat and run. So unaccommodating. Will never be back.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed91175',120,'2017-06-11',4,'Had a incredible dinner here with friends.In fact I was so impressed, made another reservation.We sat in a private booth ,sits 6 made the evening even better.I love Sushi, this is another level Â of sushi.Highly recommend.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hina115',1670,'2021-05-29',5,'The tasting menu was honestly one of the best meals Ive ever had. I cant stop thinking about it. Every course was incredible. Very reasonably priced; great service and ambiance. We will definitely be back!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',963,'2021-01-21',5,'Kai Zan is a great place to stop by for sushi in the city. Â Street parking is easy to find. Â Id make a reservation in advance, since this place fills up fast. Â The expansion to the restaurant was done beautifully down to the smallest detail. Â All the dishes I have had here were carefully composed. Â The ingredients are always fresh. Â My favorite dishes here are Orange Rush, Hamachi Collar, and Escolar Pearls. Â A few items on their new menu Id order again. Â 1. Calamari Fry it was crispy, tender, and came with a creamy dipping sauce. Â It has all the qualities I look for in an appetizer. Â I could eat a whole plate of this, if calories didnt matter. Â 2. Mushroom Medley a combination of 8 types of mushrooms in a light sake butter broth.3. Kai Zan Salad Kind of like a low carb chirashi. Â I would definitely order this dish again. I am not one who likes to spend 3 hours at a course meal, so the friendly quick service was perfect. I got places to go, things to see (had plans to visit the Sky Deck in Willis Tower). Will come back again soon!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',1598,'2018-10-03',4,'5 stars for food, (romantic) atmosphere, and service. Â Ive never had fresher tasting ingredients in sushi than I have at Kai Zan. Â You can really taste it in every bite. Â Despite the past reviews regarding their poor service, we had a completely different experience. Â (They were recently featured on Check Please which might have something to do with the improved quality of service.)Everything was amazing. Â We decided NOT to do the omakase menu as we werent feeling very adventurous that night. Â We just wanted sushi and Im pretty confident we made the right choice. Â Maybe next time though..',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',200,'2016-07-14',5,'Is this place a gem? Â Perhaps. Â The omakase menu is affordable and always a great way to appreciate the chefs flexing their culinary muscle. Â Having that said, Im not a big fan of sushi being overpowered with lots of sauce that mask the freshness of the seafood. Â Maybe this is why my favorite parts were the japanese smelt which was simply grilled and served with daikon radish and lemon and the soup at the beginning of the meal with a skewer of tuna that cooked itself in the broth. Â We sat at the chefs table which Im also not a big fan of because when eating out, I want to enjoy the company of the person Im with - through great conversations and not by watching the chefs prepare our meal. Â However, this experience allowed me to really observe the chef and if nothing else, it was evident that they were committed and passionate about their craft. Â And this is why its sad that their efforts to share their talents with their diners have to be ruined by an inept hostess who lack tact in basic customer service. Â It was a rainy day in Chicago yesterday and after having just experienced lots of flooding, many roads were still difficult to navigate and rainy weather just has a way of slowing everyone down. Â So we were a little late with our reservation but it was 545 p.m. on a Tuesday for crying out loud; were not talking about 730 p.m. on a Saturday night. Â The hostess took my name and immediately said Â We need your table back by 645 which should not be a problem if you order all your food at once? Â Are you serious?! Â This is your welcome greeting? Â Well she caught me on a really bad day and the last thing I wanted was to be told that I had a time limit to experience a restaurant that was just crowned as one of Chicagos best new restaurants! Â Everything else tasted bad after that; the place was cramped and it was evident that they were rushing us from one course to the next so the tasting menu --- which is always supposed to be a relaxing experience, became a devouring menu that you had to force feed yourself to finish all your food at once because each course came right after one another. Â And wouldnt you know it? Â They finished by serving us by 645 p.m.? Â Never again- omakase menu may be cheap but so was the entire experience!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc61133',1131,'2016-06-07',5,'We found Kai Zan on accident. Â We went in at 530pm on a Friday and theyre reservation Â only. Â We said fine and walked out. Â Pulled out the Yelp app and noticed all these 5-star reviews. Â Went back in and told them we would be in-n-out. Â Mission accomplished.Ill cut to the chase, Kai Zan is a culinary experience. Â We did the omakase, which translates to Ill leave it to you. Â Cool. Â I cant wait to go back. Â I guess the owners are right in the middle of the action in the kitchen. Â Talk about passion for food. Â High praise.To put things in perspective, we did not even know this place was BYOB and still had a great time. Â Thats a first. Â I liked the service. Â I saw a few negative reviews, but this dining experience was as close to eating at someones home as you can get.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',1298,'2021-08-21',5,'Some of the best sushi Ive had! I would highly recommend the Omakase for the value and variety. You get 10 courses, some of which are 4-5 bites of food. You wont leave hungry. If youre not a picky eater and like surprises, this place is awesome. You dont know what youre going to get until its sitting in front of you. Everything was good, but I do have some favorites - the escolar pearls, uni and oyster shooters, angry crab, and fiesta maki roll. For dessert we had the seasonal mochi (sweet potato and brown butter) and the cashew panna cotta, which are good if youre not into really sweet desserts. Overall, an awesome meal and a really fun experience. Cant wait to go back!',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('volutpat2346',398,'2016-05-19',5,'Really enjoyed the experience. Sushi was fresh and creative. The Pearls on the appetizer menu are fabulous. We enjoyed every roll, although the spicy tuna needed more spice. The ambiance is great. Parking is incredibly difficult, but that was really the only negative aspect. Really great and creative, and wonderful service!We also had no trouble getting a reservation on a Thursday night. They were flexible and courteous, so we did not have the same negative feelings about the get in get out philosophy.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('enim3417',464,'2022-01-01',4,'Everything we tried was spectacular, service was incredible. My second time here and will definitely be back for more!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a22154',219,'2016-08-07',5,'Everything was amazing. We tried the Escolar pearls, Dynamite bites, Fried chicken, Green monster (my favorite; wrapped in avocado) and Angry crab. You cant go wrong with anything in the menu here. Great service and overall amazing experience!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',366,'2019-03-04',5,'I want to personally thank the chefs and staff at Kai Zan for making our experience last night a singular, exalted journey. We ordered the premium omekase dinner. It was gastronomic poetry... Romantic, decadent, intrepid, refined. The bar has been set very high. Thank you, Carlo and Melvin, for the delightful second act. What culinary dreams are made of.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede50164',1584,'2022-01-16',4,'I have been to most of the omakase restaurants around Chicago and find this to be one of the best. It is priced very fair and has been consistent every time I go. I am giving it a 4 star as they tend to be a little bit heavy on the salt for the cooked dishes but everything has has been great. Sushi is always fresh and the service is quick and attentive.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',1653,'2019-03-05',5,'Never heard of Kai Zan? Youre not alone. But this low key, charming Japanese restaurant is quickly on its way to becoming my new favorite sushi joint. The decor very homey, other than the funky/cool electronic koi pond that greets you when you walk in the door.Dont miss the Escolar Pearls (rice spheres topped w/ scallion, super white tuna, truffle oil, spicy mayo, and chili oil), Orange Rush sushi (salmon, scallop w/ citrus glaze) or Angry Crab (fresh tuna, spicy crab). All three were incredible. From the April Specials Menu we tried the Fiesta Maki (tuna, salmon, jalapeno, avocado, cilantro) and Dynamite Mussel (grilled in a half shell, the most beautiful presentation of mussels Ive seen) - both were fantastic as well. For dessert we ordered the green tea ice cream with red bean, which was good, but I didnt need more than a taste of it as its more of a savory dessert. Everything that came out was absolutely beautiful and delicious, it was a perfect night.Note Kai Zan is BYOB ONLY, so plan your wine or sake choice in advance. They have a very reasonable $5 corkage fee per table.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('integer6474',64,'2016-04-10',5,'I chose this restaurant off of the past reviews seen on Yelp. Very cozy and warm setting having both the course menu and chef special I have to say the food was great and I left full. If youre looking for a fun and refreshing experience to sushi try this place out!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus366',1208,'2018-07-28',4,'Omakase is a great experience. Â I would definitely recommend this place. Â Only reason I took away a star is the beer list was a bit low on actual Japanese beers Â and I am not a Hipster so I dont need FLYING DRAGON ON TURTLE BACK 400 MINUTE IPA.Very cool date place and I will be back to try the entrees.EDITAny restaurant where the Owner cares enough to respond like they did is worthy of 5 stars! Â Thanks and Congratulations, I will be telling this story everywhere I go!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',1174,'2019-07-14',5,'Wow. Â Ive dined here several times, and these guys never disappoint. Let me just say that this place not only serves some of the best sushi in the city, but Â I felt the Kai Zan crew has dished out some of the best culinary experiences of my life. All for a fraction of the cost of some of the more higher-end spots in town. Word of advice to get the most of your meal, go with the Omikase.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',679,'2016-11-11',5,'Stopped in on a Friday night and did the premium Omakase. It was amazing. Great chefs, great ambiance, great waitstaff. Great everything. Definitely a place I want to explore again at some point in the future.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4430',1128,'2017-03-12',4,'Tried the omakase tasting menu experience and it was truly expertly crafted from beginning to finish. Â My girlfriend and I shared the tasting menu together and ordered another maki (the Flaming Tuna roll) in addition, and altogether it was the perfect amount of food for both of us. Â We did order an extra portion of the Orange Rush dish, since we both wanted to try it (some of the items on the omakase menu were only one bites worth).Until tonight I actually never tried an omakase tasting menu before, and I was really blown away by the variety and intensity of the flavors and textures, with perfect balances of saltiness, sweetness, and umami. Â The service was excellent, and I never waited more than a couple minutes after finishing one dish before the next one was brought out. Â Some of the really stand-out items on the tasting menu the oyster shooter was one of the most unique items Ive ever had, and the combination of oyster, quail egg, ponzu sauce, scallion melted together in my mouth in a delicious union of richness. Â The Orange Rush was also quite excellent - you cant go wrong with salmon wrapped around scallop.All in all, the flavors were exciting in a way that doesnt hit you over the head, which is something that other lesser sushi places do badly when they provide a side of sriracha mayo with their rolls that completely overpowers any of the original flavors. Â Every flavor here at Kai Zan is really marked by balance that makes this one of the best meals Ive had in a very long time.Would definitely recommend coming here to try the tasting menu, and I definitely plan on coming back in the future.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',864,'2021-06-03',5,'Dined here last night -- was my life changed? Â No. Â Did I cry? Â No. Â  Did I make some this sh*t right here is amazing faces while pointing at my mouth? Â absolutely. Â  Â Make no mistake, this is a hipster establishment in a hipster hood. Â  If youre not a total d-bag or clueless suburban soccer mom you should have no problem getting with the vibe Kai Zan sets forth. Â  The staff was friendly, albeit a bit awkward, but it played into what felt like an artsy and creative atmosphere which matched the cuisine. Â When it comes to Sushi, freshness trumps any sort of creative fusion that a chef can offer. Â  The fish here was very, very fresh... so beyond that the creativity and innovation are just a great bonus. Â  The only other place in town that offers fish this fresh is the very traditional Katsu on Peterson.A very nice, focused beer selection was great. Â Some of the best beers Chicago has to offer are in the cooler (Krankshaft and Apex Predator) and nothing else. Â  Again, it adds to the ethos of offering quality and no BS.They make a hard sell on the Omakase, but we went ala carte and were not disappointed. Â Not a cheap meal, expect to spend at least $60-75 per person with drinks. Â  Â I will be back!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sodales69101',58,'2020-05-19',5,'My group of girlfriends and I split several courses, and I have to say WOW. The Uni taco plate was surprisingly great, especially since none of us had ever had uni before. The Maguro Pearls were delicious. The Polenta Bites were by far the best thing we tried. And the Angry Crab dish was pretty spectacular. I would highly recommend this restaurant, and would go back in a heartbeat.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',890,'2019-06-21',4,'My #1 spot in Chicago for sushi! Omakase is incredible. I appreciate their high standards for uni.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean2690',373,'2020-06-27',5,'Always delicious and fun. Amazing sushi, we generally do one of the two tastings and I highly recommend going this way. It gives the diner a chance to sample the breadth of the restaurants abilities. Go now, go often',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',1350,'2018-03-08',5,'Omakase at Kai Zan never disappoints. From the taste and creativity of the food to the freshness of the fish and plentiful servings, its always something we look forward to.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',89,'2016-09-12',5,'SO DISAPPOINTED. I have read so many good things about Kai Zan and couldnt wait to come here to check it out. The hubs and I had reservations last night. In short- our pompous server tainted our experience and we felt like we got ripped off. The deets Â After being seated for 15 minutes, our waiter finally came by to offer to open our wine. Side note- the place is so small there are 5 tables and a sushi bar. We were seated at the sushi bar and he had to walk by us at least a dozen times before acknowledging us. Anyways, 10 MINUTES LATER he still hasnt delivered our opened bottle of wine. We wanted to walk out, and would have had he not been holding captive the wine we brought. In retrospect we should have walked out and just said sayonara to the vino. We started with the escolar pearls. They were really tasty but small for $8. Ok fine. Still feeling optimistic. We ordered the 3 of their featured sushi items. Eel wrapped in tuna, angry crab, and scallop wrapped in salmon. Each were $8. We expected them to be rolls. Instead, we discovered that they were 2 bites per order, equating to 1 bite per person. Where we felt the most taken advantage of though was on the sashimi we ordered. They had 2 sashimi specials of fresh fish they were featuring. One was a steelhead trout, the other was toro. The other sashimi items we were going to order were $3 a piece. Of course having been tempted by the sound of the specials, we ordered 2 pieces of each. When the bill came we found out they were 3 times the price of all other sashimi- $9 a piece!! Lovely surprise when the bill came to discover that 2 bites per person cost $36. Our server was MIA for the most part but when he was present to deliver our next dish, he couldnt be bothered. The whole experience just left a bad taste in my mouth. Â I get that the fish quality was really good, and honestly we liked everything we got. That is the only thing keeping this from being a 1 star review. But we left starving after spending $80. There are so many great, super fresh sushi joints in the city and Im just sorry I wasted a dime at this one.',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',1718,'2018-10-23',4,'O.M.F.G. Wow, wow, wow, wow, wow. I had been here before, but my friend and I had been on a bar hop, so having a full evaluation of the sushi just wasnt happening. This time, however, I was sent into nirvana. Ill fully admit, I havent had sushi from tokyo and whatever other great sushi cities one can come up with. I have had what I believe to be very good sushi, and Kai Zan is heads and shoulders above anything else Ive had. I went here with 3 other friends. Were all very into wine, so yes, many bottles were brought. I do love that they are completely BYO, and yea, we kinda abused that. Thankfully the staff was cool with it and we made sure to reward them for that. Anyway, its near impossible to get into all of the food. Mostly because we just let our waitress pick for us. So, food would just appear and she would tell us what we were having. I was only paying so much attention and more just focused on the killer fish in front of me. We started off with the oyster shooters and the escolar pearls. The oyster shooters are a complete trip with them being so wrong that they are insanely right. The escolar pearls were absolutely awesome and should be ordered by everyone. Here is where things got hazy as it was one order after the other. I do remember there being some steelhead trout sashimi that was amazing and a fiery crab (or was it angry crab?) that we had to order twice. The major point being though, everything put in front of us was both gorgeous in its presentation and just as delicious as it looked. Kai Zan is a very small spot. We were there for a little over an hour and we could see a line forming out the door, so we did have to leave a bit sooner than we probably wouldve liked. But, it was also a friday night and I fully understand that they have to turn over tables since there is so much demand. I cant wait to come back and Im already plotting yet another return.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1416,'2021-12-24',5,'Wow... seriously wow. Â Came here on a double date because my wifes cousin got us a gift card to Kai Zan. Â And let me tell you, it was awesome.The four of us made reservations for Sunday (Sat was already booked five days in advance). Â Online reservations, easy to manage, shame they dont have their online menu/website up and working yet.We ordered the omakase ($50) and received a lot of food... Im going to list all that I can remember, in case you choose not to go omakase, and instead order piece by piece. Â Heres what I can remember.Escolar Pearls - Yes, these are amazing. Â We each received four full bites of escolar pearls using super white tuna and lean tuna (maguro). Â Best dish of the night.Angry Crab - A full 12 pieces for the table, so three pieces a person. Â Another clear winner.Oyster shooters - Beautiful presentation, and one of the few ways my wife enjoyed raw oysters. Â (Actually, the first time shes ever said she enjoyed raw oysters).Dynamite mussels Â Very flavorful and a great combination. Â Mussels were slightly overcooked, but only in the barest of ways.Agedashi tofu Â Soul satisfying broth, but the tofu wasnt crisp/crunchy on the outside... I think weve just had better agedashi tofu elsewhere.Jalapeno poppers Â Perfectly fried, nice combination.Bacon wrapped enoki Â Not a huge fan... I think I was expecting the bacon to be more crisp and more texture to the enoki.Marinated shitake Â These were awesome... so packed with flavor, I saved these as my last bite for this particular dish.Yakitori smelt Â Tasty, good flavor, nice and smokey. Â Reminded us of some filipino fish dishes in terms of preparation/smell.Steelhead trout Â Really, this tasted like salmon. Â I would have never guessed that this was trout... but then again, they are both very closely related, so I guess it makes sense. Â A phenomenal sashimi.Mango pudding Â Refreshingly light and simple, perfect way to end the meal. Â Best shared with two people, though we did share with four as we had additional dessert plans afterwards.Verdict Â Get reservations early, as this place literally will only fit 22 people or so. Â Great service, phenomenal food, and you have got to make your way here to enjoy it. Â The Omakase is a steal, in all our opinions, and I hope they keep it that way because it will keep us coming back for more and more. Â Only disappointment for the night was Agedashi tofu... but considering the amount of courses we had, one off course is nothing in light of everything we enjoyed. Â Cant wait to come back again.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',1209,'2016-11-15',5,'Excellent. I have been limiting my out-to-dinner situations lately - trying to eat clean. I made an exception for a holiday dinner based on a recommendation. We ordered the chefs special ($60/person) - 10 courses. I was thoroughly impressed with the authenticity of the dish. No, I do not eat a lot of sushi but I could tell that they used excellent ingredients and didnt over season their dishes. This is very important to me as a food lover. I walked away feeling great - this is how you know food is done right, with great top-shelf ingredients. The environment was excellent, homie. The service was impeccable and natural - they were very helpful in recommending favorites and moving the process along. Thumbs up!',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',1680,'2020-03-15',4,'Kai Zan is a special place that makes me happy I live in Chicago. Â I am not super adventurous but I really loved everything on their Omakase menu. Â Except maybe the raw quail egg shooter. Â That was a little too syrupy for me. Â I am looking forward to our next special occasion to come back.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',1649,'2019-10-17',5,'Ive got a new favorite sushi spot!!! We winged it on a Sat night with no reservatin at 615 and snagged a spot at sushi bar. We were watching them make all these amazing dishes that I didnt see on the menu only to find they were part of the omakase menu. We had already ordered but next time for sure. Green Monster and Orange Rush were amazing. And we did some tuna, salmon, hamachi, and escolar that were all super fresh and great cuts. And how could I forget the escolar pearls? And we had a few skewers of scallops and shrimp as well.All-in-all fantastic.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean2690',747,'2017-02-12',5,'Hands down my favorite sushi restaurant in the city. Im in trouble as this place is less than a mile from my apt. When we first discovered it my boyfriend and I kept switching off as Yelp Duke/Duchess because we just couldnt get enough. Sadly we have lost our reign as this restaurant has gained more of a following thanks to their Michelin star. Not to mention they have doubled in size. The food is all amazing, everything. Nothing Ive ever ordered has been a disappointment. Although my boyfriend and were not the biggest fans of the tasting menu, probably because we know what we like. Our favs are the Unagi Poppers, Oyster Shooters, Orange Rush, and Escolar/Maguro Pearls. We always go for the specials. Despite their super cute two person booths, I prefer to sit at the bar here. We discovered another one of our favorite dishes- the Dynamite Mussels this way; watching the chefs sear them on the grill right in front of us. We have joked about stopping in just for the Oyster/Uni Shooters and walking out because they are just that good. Overall fantastic, and I will be back!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',447,'2017-12-13',5,'Rarely do I give out five star reviews. Its not because Im an elitist or speaking out of ignorance - like some reviewers like to do. Rather, its because Im a simple gal who has always been taught the value of quality service (thanks, mama!), and Ive been fortunate enough to know what fresh ingredients taste like. Since Ive also traveled all over, studying and absorbing different cultures, Id say that my palate is also fairly astute and diverse.That said, Kai Zan is phenomenal. It delivers on all fronts with its friendly, knowledgable, and courteous wait staff to Japanese inspired dishes that are innovative and simply put, damn good. With its uber intimate interior, make sure you make reservations because it caps off close to 27 seats - though Ive heard they are expanding its dining area. With its cozy setting, Kai Zan is better suited as a date spot instead of a large group of folks ready to rage. Take that business elsewhere in Chicago, like Sunda or Roka.Once you settle in, youll be in for a culinary treat as your appetite is taken on a culinary euphoria that balances textures with delightful flavor profiles. A few favorites include the Orange Rush, Gomae, Zuke, Escolar Pearls, of course my personal fave and also something thats flown in thrice weekly is the uni. Melt in your mouth delicious. So, go. Eat, drink and be merry. Give a big Kampai to Melvin and Carlo. Just make sure you come hungry because youll want to order everything on the menu. Youve been forewarned )',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',921,'2016-02-01',5,'The food was amazing! We ordered the chefs choice and each dish that came out was presented beautifully and tasted delicious. We were stuffed when tenth course came out.The atmosphere was very cute, great for a date or small group. My only complaint was the courses came out so quickly, sometimes before we had finished the present one on the table. I know this place is popular and reservations are difficult but the two hour time limit on each table made us feel rushed. We would have finished in under two hours easily but I was very aware of the time. Outside of that I will check this place out again. Also, the sake selection was superb!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1300,'2020-07-29',4,'Listen just do the $60 tasting menu, you will regret it if you dont. It has very unique and delicious creations that you will enjoy even if you are someone like me, who isnt very adventurous when it comes to sushi and sticks to a lot of basic rolls.Not only do you get 12 courses of food which are promptly delivered dish after dish, but its also an incredible value. Â You are probably getting over $100 worth of items by my guess.The service and decor are wonderful, the only reason I gave it 4 stars is because I also ordered some basic maki rolls, but I thought were maybe above-average at best, which isnt in line with the rest of the items I tried, which were exceptional.I think they focused all of their creative energy and quality on the tasting menu and let the quality of some of their basic rolls suffer. Â Even though they are still quite good. Â I will definitely be returning.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',538,'2017-08-14',5,'I would love to rate this place but unfortunately no one at Kai Zan answer the phones and that presuaded me not to go. Â Tried to make a reservation for 3ppl but was directed by Yelp to call the restaurant to give a credit card to reserve. Â Ok..I called before 5 so I tried again at 5, 6 and then 7pm. I left a message. Â U have great reviews because of great food, but its kinda frustrating to call ur establishment and NO ONE can answer the phone. Â Maybe u dont take reserves being that its small in there, then I suggest u take off the link to make a reservation from Yelp or just answer the phone.UPDATE Â I would like to say...Im impressed with the quick response Â and acknowledgement of my review. Â I rated them at 1 star due to my frustrations to dine in there but now with an understanding of technically difficulties on their end I have given them a total of 4 stars. Â (Sound so lame). Â Anyways...I will attempt to reserve my next dinner plan at Kai Zan.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',559,'2017-08-19',5,'Best sushi Ive ever had! Try & get a seat next to where they prepare the food. Its great to watch them cook! Highly recommend getting the Chefs choice! Its worth it & youll try some things you probably wouldnt order otherwise!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',569,'2016-07-18',4,'Absolutely best sushi in Chicago! Every time weve gone the food has been phenomenal. Ive done both the omakase and ordered a la carte and never been disappointed. Wish they offered delivery.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean2690',604,'2019-09-12',5,'This is hands down our favorite restaurant in Chicago. Easily the best sushi we have had, and the service is excellent. Melvin and Carlo are masters of their art and really know how to accommodate their guests. Not enough stars to adequately rate Kai Zan!',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',1052,'2021-07-25',5,'Possibly the most delicious japanese restaurant in Chicago. They are not a sushi only place. Especially good are the collar and the sliders. Love Kai Zan!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',132,'2017-08-09',4,'This is my favorite sushi spot in the city. Highly recommend any of the omakase options. The ingredients are fresh, the service is top notch, and the presentation is fantastic overall. Ive been here several times and have yet to be disappointed. Street parking is pretty reasonable in the area. Five stars!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',391,'2016-03-24',5,'Having moved from Hawaii recently and hearing all the good things about this place and their omakase menu made me super excited since its literally 3 blocks from my house. Â This place has really good items on the menu, but *do not* order the $60 per person omakase menu. Â Based on my experience of omakase style in Hawaii, you get chef special sushi style courses. Â Here, its 10 courses, but only 4 of the courses were actually sushi. Â One of the courses was an octopus soup in a tiny cup, that was a slight upgrade over powdered miso soup only because there was octopus in it. Â Im actually not kidding. Â I would say that at least 3 of the courses were actually cooked fish, and most of the courses were very heavy on the tuna. Â I love tuna, but Im looking for different types of flavors if Im doing omakase - uni, unagi, etc. Â Towards course 7, I actually told the waiter that we would really like sushi / sashimi, and he said good news, the last course is all sashimi. Â Maybe Im spoiled having the opportunity to experience omakase style in Hawaii, but I really dont think that for $60 a person that this is good value. Â Id rather order what I want and spend the equivalent of $120 (for two) on exactly the fish that I would like to eat. Â We did a menu calculation, and for $120, you can basically sample everything on their specialty menu. Â Do this if you plan to spend $120! Â Omakase should never include octopus soup in a shot glass and a seaweed salad with squid. Â I would say 4 of 10 of the courses were up to par and delicious.Also, the $15 corking fee is a bit high I think. Â They said this is new because now they have a liquor license for wine and beer. Â I think when you are paying $120, its a bit high to pay $15 to uncork your own bottle of wine just because they now have a liquor license. Â Feels greedy.Even though Im giving this place 3 stars, I think if you stick to the menu and order what you want, you will be happy. Â Just stay away from omakase style if you know what you are doing.I took a friend out for their birthday, and they overheard this and did bring us two deserts on the house. Â They also Â threw in an uni roll on the house because they could tell we werent exactly thrilled with the omakase choice. Â These were both very nice gestures that made everything more worthwhile, but I wont ever be doing chefs choice again.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',360,'2016-02-21',5,'Omakase was amazing. Kai Zan was the perfect date spot. Each bite was delicious and the service was terrific. Its always fun to sit at the chefs table! We will definitely be back.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat89150',247,'2021-02-01',5,'The Chefs Omakase is a fantastic value considering how many varied dishes you receive. Ive got to check out the premium version and see their greater offerings.',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',884,'2018-04-05',5,'Kai Zan.Man.Its one classy restaurant.I love the private booths. Â I love the regular tables, too. Â The staff is nothing short of exceptional. Â Accommodating, enthusiastic and wanting to make your experience amazing.And the experience is serious. Â When I have brought people to Kai Zan Ive preempted our visit by explaining that this is not your typical sushi experience. Â Yeah, they have a few rolls, but youre not getting a spicy tuna roll. Â Youre getting shooters with oysters and raw quail egg. Â Youre getting interesting sashimi selections. Â Not for the sushi virgin, probably, but definitely for those with adventurous palettes looking for something... different. Â And exciting. Â And most of all, really yummy.Best bet is to go for the chefs special, which will be a tour of whats freshest, best and most exciting that evening. Â Be sure to tell them what you like and what you dont like. Â Theyll accommodate. Â And youll be glad you ordered it because you pay $60 and just get a bunch of awesome plates. Â Definitely the way to go.Despite having a less than stellar reaction to uni last weekend (apparently it happens), I still rank Kai Zan with 5 sexy sushi stars. Â Theyre awesome.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit42135',105,'2018-05-23',5,'Cool take on escolar. Rare. And very tasty. Well, as they say sake happens.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',952,'2017-11-05',4,'WOW. This is the best sushi/ fresh fish fusion I have ever eaten. It is pricey, but you absolutely get your moneys worth.The servers are lovely, and one of the chefs (Sam, perhaps?) is very friendly. My only complaint is that the booths (which are very private, if you are looking for that) feel a bit like a prison with their completely enclosed concrete structure. Its a little sterile for such awesome, ornate food.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat1120',1316,'2017-10-12',5,'One of the best dining experiences Ive had so far. Very intimate and personal. Each dish comes with a bursts of unique flavors with nothing that tastes similar to one another. Great place for a date. Its reasonably priced for the treatment and great quality food you get. I would definitely come back when I get the chance again and try everything else. The hand roll uni and toro topped with quail egg was my favorite there. The char siu was out of this world.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean67124',1079,'2016-11-16',5,'Very good. Â My husband and I went here and ordered one regular omakase and one premium omakase. Â This was a good way to go for us, since we were able to taste many different dishes.I ate most of the regular omakase, so I will concentrate my review on that. Â Overall, I liked all of the dishes. Â Least favorite were the entree and the shooter (the flavor of the shooter was good but I generally dont like having my mouth THAT full! Â haha). Â All of the dishes before the entree were great - I especially like the escolar pearls and the carpaccio. Â The entree itself was 4 different bites - I just didnt think the shrimp/mushroom dish or the fried item fit well with the rest of the menu. Â The last 2 dishes were a full maki roll (6 large pieces) and a sashimi platter. Â Wow...this was a lot of food to end with! Â I wish I was able to eat more, because the few bites I took of the sashimi were very good. Â I think there were 9 pieces on that last plate? Â I think if the sashimi course was served earlier, or actually had a few less pieces, it would have been perfect. Â And maybe serve a half maki roll.The couple sitting next to us actually shared 1 omakase, and I can see how that could work out very well for the amount of food served! Â But for a single person, I think the pacing needs to be worked out a little. Â But, the food was great and definitely deserves 4 stars.As for the premium omakase, my husband like it alot, and the few bites I had (mmmmmmm wagyu!) were delicious. Â He had the same comment that the pacing was a bit off, as he also had a sashimi platter at the end that was a bit too much.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',1270,'2019-04-28',4,'Get the Omakase!! My husband & I came to Kai Zan after hearing rave reviews from friends and it definitely lived up to the hype! The food was excellent & at 60/each for the Omakase tasting menu -- you cant go wrong! Our favorites were the orange Rush, Angry Crab & esscolar/maguro pearls. We will definitely be back!!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',700,'2016-07-22',5,'By far the best sushi outside of Tokyo. Ive never been to Japan, but if the sushi is as good as Kai Zan, I would take the 20 hour flight just to eat it. Order the chefs special and keep an open mind. Everything they serve you will be amazing.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',1687,'2017-12-11',5,'Great BYOB sushi spot in quiet west neighborhood that is becoming more well known everyday. Â They recently expanded to allow for increased capacity and larger groups. Inventive menu, dont be shy! Orange Crush and the Pearls are my favorite. Never seen anything like these mussels before, you have to try!Great spot for groups, can bring own booze and keep the price much lower than in wicker park or river north.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',1391,'2021-01-21',4,'In summary One of the best sushi options in Chicago, but the reservation process is a bit of a disasterThings weve tried Maguro and Escolar pearls. Orange rush. Flaming tuna. Green Monster. Fresh, unique and made with attention to detail. Everything was delicious.Reservation system Its been a bit of a logistical nightmare; twice now. First time we were told that they had a table for us, but to our surprise we had to wait an extra hour for it. The second time, we were promptly provided with our table but were given a time limit of how long we can keep it (about 60 minutes). Not a fan of that policy. Perhaps adding a delivery service would be a way to make up for the lack of seating.In conclusion Completely worth the visit despite the limited seating and reservation quirks. The quality of the food is top notch.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',809,'2021-06-23',5,'Absolutely amazing. Without a doubt five stars. Intimate tables, great service and amazing food!! I read some people thought the food was rush when doing the coursed meal we didnt however. We got the omakase which was 14 courses our night. It was perfectly time. We didnt want to sit there all night!!! And for 60 bucks nonetheless, its the best choice ever!!! Cant wait Togo back!!!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',920,'2020-11-01',5,'There are very few things in the world I love more than seafood.(I am allowed to say that; I dont have children. My pets dont count, I cannot eat them. Yet. OK The husband has a place up there as well.)Hearing glowing review after glowing review of Kai Zan left me filled with envy, anticipation and the very distinctive mouth tingling accompanied by the slightest surge of saliva that occurs when you think of something you really, really, really want to eat.I am sure you know what I mean.Well, ladies and gents, Kai Zan didnt disappoint on any account.I knew it was BYOB; I brought a lovely bottle of Pouilly FuissÃ© (one of my French faves; a Burgundy Chardonnay in translation) that pairs perfectly well with fish and holds up to the stong-profiled flavors of soy sauce.I knew it was small; my friend made a reservation for 6 pm. We were sitting at the counter; it was roomy, comfortable and manned by the very efficient Michelle who did an excellent job all throughout.But yes, it is SMALL. Think of it, and divide the size by two. That small.I knew it was delicious. And my, oh my....Specials are always a safe bet in a restaurant; they highlight the best of whats available that day. Kai Zan is no exception. So be attentive when the waiting staff explains them to you at the beginning of your meal, cause you dont want to miss, for example, a plump kumamoto oyster served as a shot with a raw quail egg, scallions and ponzu sauce. Or the uni and toro tartar concoction that you spread yourself on nori if you can resist eating the whole thing with a spoon (provided. You dont have to bring your own.)These two dishes blew up my mind, as well as my taste buds. Rich, flavorful, complex but also subdued in a way that let each ingredient shine while combining superbly with each other.A rare experience.Another great surprise was the bite-size kushi skewers; the shitake-ponzu one should illustrate umami in a dictionary. The best $3 spent on food in your life. It totally beat the crap of the scallop-onion one, and God knows I love scallops. Fact Mushroom are definitely magic, with or without hallucinatory proprieties.You will also find more traditional sushi and sashimi, a few rolls and a couple of cooked dishes such as yaki, noodles and cooked protein for the non-raw eaters. But if you come here, you should really stick to the creatures of the sea because its what they do.And they do it pretty damn fucking well.And yes, it totally requires the emphatic swearing.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',790,'2021-01-08',5,'Went in for a quick bite without reservation, lucky me they have a spot open at the sushi bar. Ordered couple pieces of salmon nigiri which were amazing (have to order couple more pieces to take home for snack later) . Shitake Maki was amazing as well.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',735,'2020-02-15',5,'What happened to Kai Zan?My wife and I came here two years ago when they were trying and the place blew us away. Â The menu was interesting and the food was enough to keep us talking about it, telling everyone we know to go, since.And then we show up yesterday and from the moment we walk in the door we could tell things have changed.The sushi was well, boring, bland, and less exciting than prepackaged sushi that you can get from 7/11.The hosts first words to us didnt mention our reservation notes at all, celebrating our first date after the birth of our child, but we were instead told that we have 90 minutes to eat and then they have to give the table to someone else.Our server was strange but knew what he was doing. Â The menu was converted into a lame plastic laminate with the descriptions of the food being dead on. Â Tune and cucumber - that literally all thats in there.This place sucks now',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',809,'2016-06-16',5,'Amazing, amazing, amazing. Â I can not rave enough about our experience at Kai Zan last night. Â A friend had recommended the place to us as her favorite sushi place in the city. Â Contrary to a lot of the complaints Ive read in other reviews, I had no trouble making a reservation through the online  site that Kai Zan directs you to from their Facebook page. Â We went on a Monday with a party of 3, and booked an 8pm res.Also, contrary to other reviewers comments, we had no problems with the service and had no feeling of being rushed. Â My fiance and I arrived 5 minutes early and they prepared the table, seated us, and opened our wine for us to enjoy while we waited for our friend. Â They may act differently on a busy weekend night, but with a space this small, it is understandable that they want to keep their tables used efficiently.Once our whole party was seated, our server Chris explained the menu and asked how wed like to proceed. Â Based on the overwhelming recommendations on yelp, we each decided to do the $50 omakase (Chefs Choice) tasting. Â In a word...perfection. Â Did we enjoy every single item completely? Â No, of course not. Â With the kind of variety Kai Zan offers, theres bound to be some items that dont agree with your personal tastes. Â But every single item was prepared to perfection, presented beautifully, and only the utmost top quality ingredients were used. Â We were completely and pleasantly full after the meal, no room left for anything additional. Â Its the perfect amount of variety and quantity, and a tasting like this would easily be $85 at any of the other top sushi places in the city. Â Trust me, if you appreciate sushi, this is the best $50 you will ever spend. Â And the restaurant is BYOB so our bill was literally $50 each, plus a $5 corkage fee. Â Not bad for one of the best meals Ive ever had.You wont need any soy sauce or siracha sauce with this meal. Â Just sit back, order the tasting, and let the chefs dazzle you with their brilliance and creativity. Favorites- Uni shooters and oyster shooters Both were delicious, but I was surprised to find that I liked the uni significantly better than the oyster (and I usually love all things oyster). - Escolar and maguro pearls These were both equally delicious and just as everyone else has mentioned, easily a favorite of the night.- Angry Crab A bite of heaven and the wasabi perfectly hits you at the end. Â Its like it was created in layers so you can taste each individual layer as youre chewing and each has a distinct flavor.- Steelhead Trout Sashimi Â Imagine the best salmon sashimi youve ever had...and then imagine having something similar but twice as delicious.- Tako The octopus salad was served at the perfect time, the vinegar was light and refreshing to cleanse our mouths and the touch of wasabi was nice.- Unagi Poppers The jalapeno poppers were also very tasty, but I was a little confused. Â They were said to have had unagi inside the jalapeno, but there was none, so I think somebody messed up there. Â Either way, the panko covered jalapeno with cream cheese and eel sauce was not their most original creation of the night, but still tasty and enjoyable.- Shrimp with Shitaki Mushrooms The shrimp was good but the moist and barely cooked shitaki mushroom cap with delicious ginger dressing and other sauces was fantastic.- Mussel My memory escapes me, but we had a mussel on a shell dressed in deliciousness. Â I had hoped wed get to try the Orange Crush, but the mussel was a wonderful substitute.- Sushi Roll The sushi roll came out towards the end, as we were all discussing how there was no way we could eat any more food, so my fiance ended up eating most of this for the team. Â Im not sure what the roll was called but it was a simple roll of tuna and cucumber, salmon and a bit of spicy sauce. Â It was delicious, but I could only eat one bite.Not Our Favorites- Agedashi Tofu The broth that the tofu was served in was downright drinkable, but the tofu itself was bland and unseasoned and a little bit boring.- Enoki Bacon I didnt try this one, but the other two said it was just ok.- Grilled Yellowtail A little bit bland and boring as well.- Charred Smelt I believe this dish was prepared to perfection and Chris seemed disappointed that we didnt enjoy it, as its one of his favorites. Â But the smelt was just a little bit too fishy for our tastes. Â If youre okay with strong fish (and okay with eating whole fish, head to tail), youll love this.Service was prompt and friendly. Â They were great about clearing dishes quickly, always explained what each dish was and recommended the best way to eat it, and did not make us feel rushed at any time. Â The place is very cozy and casual and welcoming. Â I cant wait to go back again.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',530,'2022-01-22',4,'I really wanted to like this place but the waitstaff was so unpleasant, I just cant give it a higher rating. I brought my children and the was told on two separate occasions that I should have told them ahead of time when I made my reservation. (They were in the number count for the reservation- I have no idea where I would enter the age of each member of my party). The entire time the host and the waiter made us feel super uncomfortable. It was too bad because we were celebrating a birthday.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',89,'2018-06-16',4,'The 10 course meal was phenomenal, they give you the choice of sharing the 10 courses and adding a couple extra dishes for 75 instead of 60 bucks. This was perfect for my girlfriend and I. The sushi is really unlike any sushi; the fish tastes fresh caught. Everything on the 10 course menu has so much flavor but our favorites were the orange rush, the mussels, and the escolar pearls. On top of the crazy good food the service here was great. The chef made us a special starter because we had to wait just a few minutes for reservation. Nothing but good things to say about this place. If you want life changing sushi, go here.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',1280,'2021-08-28',5,'The best sushi place in Chicago! Always fresh and delicious. First timers must try the Omakase. Â It is always delicious and perfect for a special occasion. Â  Unfortunately it has gone up in price since they first opened, but it is still perfect.Favorite dishes are the Flaming Tuna roll and Escolar Pearls, but everything is good. Â BYOB with a $5 corkage fee so make sure to bring a bottle of wine. Â Reservations are usually necessary as it is a small restaurant. Â They typically post any last minute openings they have on Facebook so make sure to check if you did not make a reservation in advanced.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',1707,'2020-05-30',3,'Reservations recommended, very limited seating!Well, well, well. Lookie here at little Kai Zan making some big waves in Humboldt Park. Fresh and inventive sushi has arrived, my dears. And, you should go get you some. Rawwwwwwwsome. We arrived around 630pm with a group of 4 on a Tuesday, and it would be good to note that they only have two tables that seat more than a 2-top, so as mentioned...make a reservation. This isnt a great spot for a big group. Even as is, the space is fairly tight. Better for a date spot. We were allowed to snag one of those bigger tables, but it was reserved starting at 8pm, so we had to hustle just a bit. Luckily all the food came out expediently! We started with a round of specials, some oyster shooters, seabass carpacio, among others. Everything was delicious. We ordered some special rolls (take care here, some only come with 2 pieces) as well as some standards rainbow, california, spicy tuna, et al. Again, all exceeded expectations. Our service was wonderful from start to finish. Never felt rushed despite the timeline. All dishes and specialities explained with just the right amount of excitement. Wine opened, glasses distributed, smiles given. *BYOB with $5 corkage fee per bottle. *Some of the best sushi Ive had in a very long time! *Street parking fairly easy (and non-permit) Fantastic, off the beaten path date spot that will impress your miss or mister with the quality, location and uniqueness. Its super indie, but just posh enough to be special. The food will knock your socks off, you can bring your own bottle of wine to impress...whats not to love?*Also, if you are waiting for a table...pop into Komodo or Squasht for some local shopping! Total bill for 4 was just over $115 (without tip), and we were stuffed and sated. A better value than anticipated. Now, take that someone special. Youll thank me, I promise!',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu1673',229,'2016-05-16',5,'This really was a great place to go and eat. I went with two of my friends and ordered the omakase (chefs choice). And the chefs didnt disappoint. Â Everything was put in great presentation. The fish was very good and fresh (considering that this is the midwest, this is super awesome) and the UNI. Oh the UNI, just was delight to eat. I had to order more. The experience was just so pleasant and it started with great service from the hosts and chefs which came by all the tables. They love making sushi and it shows. I highly recommend this place to anyone. Its worth the price. Its a bit small, but I like that. Please take the time and enjoy Kai Zan. Â I will be going again soon.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',212,'2018-03-14',5,'I had a wonderful experience. We opted for food off the menu rather than the pre fix. All of the dishes we tried were so different. The chef was so skilled in the technique of how he cut fish, this raw fish like melted/evaporated in my mouth, leaving beautiful flavors that lingered. I really loved the red snapper, and the fiesta roll was great. Our server was helpful and not pushy to rack up a big bill. Thanks! Â I look forward to go back.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut97174',192,'2019-10-29',4,'This place is amazing and unique in the sushi elements. I had a reservation and saw a picture of an avocado specialty roll which was not on the menu. Upon asking about it, the waitress kindly took my phone and asked the chef if he could make it, he said yes! I HIGHLY recommend the Escolar, its incredible.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',1105,'2020-06-26',5,'My husband and I went there last night and had a wonderful experience. Â The chef went out of his way to accommodate a food allergy (he made a couple one of a kind sushi just for me). Â We had the omakase and it was just an experience we will not forget. Â This was sushi taken to the next level. Â The service was also wonderful.We highly recommend it to anyone, but plan early as reservations are hard to come by!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sem33132',863,'2022-02-06',5,'Ive been here a couple times and love 99% of Melvins and Carlos creations!I highly recommend the omakase menu for those with hearty appetites (10 or so small courses for $50/pp). Â You will be really full but not uncomfortably stuffed, and if you are, you are no fun! Â My recommendations (a la carte, or if you can ask them to incorporate these into the omakase - not sure if they will allow it?)- Escolar pearls (nigiri - super white tuna with truffle!)- Orange crush (seared salmon and scallop)- Creamy roll (unagi & shrimp tempura wrapped in avocado instead of nori seaweed)- Hamachi collar (seared fish with lemon juice)- Unagi popper (jalapeno, unagi, and cream cheese - deep fried!)I do NOT recommend ahi tuna flatbread, chawanmushi, or the katsu rollsSuggestion #1 Come here if you enjoy sushi at other restaurants already but are willing to try slightly more refined Japanese cuisine - both traditional and creative.Suggestion #2 Do not sit down and pour soy sauce right away because you will not need it. Â Use the appropriate sauces that come with the dish because the food here is already so flavorful.Suggestion #3 Make reservations to be on the safe side because this restaurant only seats around 20 people. Â Also, large parties would not fair well here. Â Come here as a couple or in a group of 4 max.Suggestion #4 BYOB!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',234,'2018-09-19',4,'Hands down my favorite sushi place in Chicago. Fresh sushi, unique dishes, street parking and great staff-- what more could you want? Ive done the Omakase three times now, the regular and premium and both were delicious. The last course, salmon is literally like butter, yum! The amount of food you get is worth the cost. The premium has unique things off the menu that the chef determines that week based off fish quality but the regular is a great way to try dishes and not have to chooae. Theyre great about food allergies and confirm several times. The brothers are delightful to talk to and you can see their passion for what theyre creating. They do have a 2 hour limit so they time the courses well but at times it felt a bit rushed. Cant wait to go back and order off the menu.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dolor4397',1099,'2021-06-19',5,'My kind of place!charming, intimate, and (my favorite) unpretentious. Most importantly, exquisite! By far, best sushi experience weve had in a while! not only for their one of a kind menu options, but the service is also worth mentioning. they truly enhanced our experience. Brandon even suggested a few options which ended up being our favorite bites of the night. We will definitely be returning. This time, with friends and family. Not all at the same time, the place is very small. oh, and dont forget, its byob.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',1441,'2020-03-24',5,'Best of the best! I cant stop talking about this place. From the swimming goldfish projected on the entrance floors, to the cute smiling waitstaff.. and the chefs testing menu... we were impressed from start to finish! The Angry Crab and BOTH perl apps were INCREDIBLE... melt in your mouth sushi that made you close your eyes and really savor it.. I was so satisfied when we left but wanted to keep eating because it was THAT good... A little hidden GEM off Chicago Ave.. I cant wait to go back. The seating is quaint and we were able to enjoy a romantic evening of it.. the staff were so knowledgable and kind. This is my new favorite in Chicago for SURE! Thanks Kai Zan!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',557,'2017-01-28',4,'First time? Omakase tasting menu is the way to go. And If your worried about reservations, go during the week so you can skip a long wait or crampy crowd.As I walked in our server immediately addressed the beer we brought and put the six pack on ice and cracked our bomber of barley wine. I appreciate that kind of attentiveness, sometimes your beverages get ignored at BYOB spots. So THANK YOU!The Omakase menu is the chefs creation, which is a solid way to explore the menu and even some off menu items. Some highlights were the Escolar and Maguro Pearls, Oyster and Uni Shooters (raw quail egg in oyster shooter, OH YEAH!), Dynamite Mussels, Smoked Oyster wrapped in salmon, Octopus Salad, and countless and flawless pieces beautiful sushi with more components than I can ever remember. There vanilla ice cream and mango pudding were delicious as well. Kai Zan provides incredibly fresh, clean, and beautifully crafted food. The portions, progression, and value of the Omakase menu are perfect. This is perhaps one of the best sushi restaurants Ive ever had the pleasure of visiting. Some final quick tips Nevadas across the street has a great beer selection for your last minute BYOB needs, plenty of FREE parking can be found on Chicago, and biggest tip is to GET YOUR BOOTY IN HERE IMMEDIATELY!!!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',484,'2021-01-22',5,'Yelp did not lead us astray on this one. Â Kai Zan was a totally awesome, unique experience. Â They basically mash up sushi with a pre-fix dining experience and the result is perfect. Â We did the 10 course tasting menu which is a total steal at $65/person. Â It is a BYOB with a reasonable corkage fee, so overall I felt like it was a great deal. Â My only caveat to people is that you do have to really love raw fish. Â Because that is pretty much every course. Â Suited me just fine, but if youre expecting a hibachi steak type entree, nope, courses 9 and 10 are just more raw fish. Â But the fish was excellent quality and variety, super flavorful and prepared in all sorts of ways with different garnishes and presentations. Â Service was on point, with the spacing of dishes absolutely perfect. Â We went with a group of 4 and had a great little private-feeling booth. Â All in all, the meal took 2 hours, which I thought was ideal. Â By the end we were full without being miserably stuffed, and delightfully tipsy from the bottle of sake and bottle of champagne that we brought. Â Highly recommend this spot!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',197,'2017-08-04',5,'I hesitate to give 5 stars because Ive only been there once. Â Knowledgable and professional staff. Â We sat at the bar, which I think I actually preferred over a booth, something about sitting side by side. Â Everything we ordered-sushi, oyster shooters, appetizers, etc-was amazing. Â I have to go back soon so I can raise it to a 5!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',56,'2019-02-01',5,'Want to know the next hot sushi spot in Chicago that you wont be able to get into? Kai Zan - out in Humbolt Park on Chicago ave. Simply put, it has all the right ingredients (pun intended) to go viral and cultish. Its small (like 20 seats), awesome decor, BYO, off the beaten path, and happens to serve delicious food thats not your typical maki roll from Dominicks. And its crazy affordable. Not much else you need to score big.The meal started off with a bang by ordering the Escolar Pearls Â (rice spheres topped with scallions and super white tuna soaked in soy sauce, truffle oil, spicy mayo, and chili oil, then lightly seared), and sides of edamame and gomae. The pearls of little rice with amazing flavors on top were so good and had four pieces for the three of us that we need another order. Easy call. Delicious. We all said we could come back for a meal entirely of Pearls (theres Maguro too, for variety).We followed the pearls with some sushi/sashimi. I believe we ordered some hamachi sashimi (not 100% on that), the flaming tuna roll and the orange rush sushi. The sashimi was nice but a little fatty/tough for my preference. Light sauce was very nice. Loved the flaming tuna, had a lot of fun items and nice texture variety. Really nice. Finally, the orange rush gives the pearls a run for their money for favorite of the meal. Its served on a single shell, and is a one bite show. Theres scallop on some rice entirely wrapped in salmon with a nice citrus glaze. Big fan, would order again and multiple. We also tried some of the yakatori to get a little variety and try the menu. We had the chicken, shrimp and beef. Everything was nice and flavorful (though Id stick with the amazing fish), and the shrimp was the best and most interesting option (and really cool presentation). We werent hungry for more but also wasnt completely full and wanted to extend our experience. We asked for a chefs surprise and they brought us three huge pieces of fatty salmon belly (something only offered on the tasting menu). It was really nice, definitely fatty (in a good way) and super generous portion. A great way to end the meal.I very much look forward to getting back to try more items and some of my favorites. The BYO is just icing on the cake (liquor store across the street) and the bill was remarkable ($35/person). The space is cool, intimate and fun with great food and value. Its the next hot spot.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1413,'2019-05-03',5,'This place has great sushi but it was completely misleading.My boyfriend and I came in with no reservation (which I recommend making in advance since there are 5 booths and the sushi bar) we were told there was a reservation coming in so we had 45 min to eat which was completely fine with us.We had ordered miso soup which was great! the special, steal head trout which could of been better and we also ordered the shrimp and cucumber roll which had 8 pieces in it and another $8 roll (only had 2 pieces). We were very confused about the portion sizes since the server never specified. After our measly dinner, we were both completely unsatisfied, we had gone home and made more food. Â Overall this place is nicely decorated and the concepts are well thought out but I will not be returning to Kai Zan.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',1503,'2021-08-07',4,'What can I say about this place that hasnt already been covered by the countless other super fans below? For me, like the rest, it was a phenomenal dining experience--really, one of the best in Chicago. However, beyond the incredible flavors and presentation, it was the staff at Kai Zan made our visit truly memorable. Its worth recognizing. My husband and I were married at the courthouse the afternoon before our reservation, and although I made very brief mention of this during the reservation call, the staff took GREAT care to make us feel celebrated and special. The hostess and staff immediately, loudly congratulated us upon walking in, as did one of the head chefs. Half way through the Omakase, he enquired about the meal, gave us his best wishes table side and even threw in free dessert! Anyway, cynical readers may suspect that the aforementioned, borderline cloying sweetness of the staff may have colored my sensory experience. Fine. All you have to do is scroll down the page if you need further proof. Besides, this level of hospitality at other hip Chicago restaurants is nearly nonexistent (despite the fact that it costs the venue nothing and is so appreciated by clientele), so I dont mind gushing over it a bit. I love this place, its extraordinary. Ill be back again and again.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',1068,'2020-02-12',5,'Sushi + Service like whoa. How have I never been here before?! Hands down the best sushi place in Chicago, which I know 8,000 people have said before, but its still true. Our server, Alan, was super attentive and wonderful. And the runner (I dont know his name, sorry) was fantastic. Their attention to detail is impressive and they were super accommodating when I forgot to tell them I dont eat mushrooms (even though they asked about allergies/dietary restrictions) until they put mushrooms in front of me. We did the omakase and it was delicious. There were multiple uni courses and it was sweet and briny and amazing. Save room for the last course (sashimi) because I did not and I was so sad! Green tea ice cream + azuki bean paste was so-so, but theyre clearly not a dessert place. Probably makes more sense to skip dessert and go somewhere else. And theyll let you try a wine if youre torn between two bottles, which I thought was a nice touch.I made reservations through Yelp SeatMe (for the first time ever) and they called the day before to confirm, which I always appreciate.All in all, five stars. Go there. Go there now (but make a reservation first!)',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',157,'2018-05-10',5,'Bad costumer service !! , we made a reservation for 830pm party of two , got a confirmation by text . we also got a phone call around 500pm to make sure that we are coming and told us that we might have to wait 10 minutes .we got there at 830 sharp and was told that out table will be ready soon, at 845 we were offered to buy a drink from the bar(yes to pay for a drink while we wait to the table the was promised to us at 830). at 900 i was asking if we will get a table today so i was told that they are very sorry but there is a table the is about to order a dessert so we will have to wait ... this is a joke , totally amateurs and no professional management.after we left the place no one even bothered to call us and maybe offer some kind of compensation or any alternative option.will never go there again , dont waist your time or money ... Â  not everything in a good restaurant is food , when you pay good money you also want to be treated as human and not like a dog ...',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed91175',611,'2020-02-06',4,'Absolutely blew me away. Â My girlfriend is not a sushi person so it took some arm twisting to get her on board, but the folks at Kai Zan showed her the light. Â We ordered the omakase and each dish was both aethetically and palate pleasing. Â Completely raised my personal bar for sushi.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',559,'2018-12-29',5,'Great food! Very creative idea on sushi and uni shots.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',455,'2019-07-13',5,'Great Omakase! The chefs are not only great, but personable as well. They go out of their way to talk to their customers and get feedback. Food is wonderful. It truly beats the Michelin starred Japanese restaurants in SF!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vulputate545',683,'2016-06-20',4,'Kai Zan is the most innovative and decadent sushi restaurant I have been to in Chicago. Highly recommend the Omakase if youre in the mood to treat your taste buds to some exciting flavor profile. Â They have a great beer selection for those who love the enhanced ocean flavors brought on by beer. Â The decor and the seating areas are minimalist yet cozy and inviting and the service is impeccable. Try it, expect to drop some bucks but you definitely wont regret it.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',84,'2016-08-11',5,'Great date night spot. We did the Omakase Menu and I do not regret it. I am a big fan of sashimi and no rice style sushi and the Omakase menu delivered just that. The flavors were great and truly unique. The best part is, they are BYOB. The Omakase menu might be pricey at $65, but you can bring your own wine or sake.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4994',1198,'2016-06-06',5,'I wasnt totally impressed with the food we did the chefs tasting menu... meh... also service was so-so we had a 1015pm reservation which maybe contributed to that but still.... meh.... better options for a $200+ dinner for 2.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',362,'2016-03-26',5,'The digs get an A+The Sushi and Sashimi get somewhere between A- and B+ pending the dishes you order.The grill items get a D.... The only thing going on there was the presentation and the nice little cabbage and ginger dressing garnish on the side. Â I wasnt tasting any soul in these dishes at all!!!The service can range between an A and a C- depending on the night... Â Needs improvement to be more consistent to its potential. Â They also badly need a coat rack or coat check there!!!!! Â Unless you like sitting on your coat the whole meal.....The detailsThis is a really fun cozy place with cool atmosphere and a cool crowd. The sushi quality is really nice, but watch out for very pricy specials that are good but can really multiply the total in your bill.Regardless, most of the sushi is quite delicious. Â On the other hand, I have tried several of the small portion grill items, and I have yet to find any that have any real taste. Â  Also, watch out for the oyster shooters. Â It is not a fusion dish, but it was a totally confused over the top disaster that just had too much going on and could not pull together the flavors in any delicate or balanced way.Stick to the sushi there and you will fine. Â  The Gomae was also quite tasty and among the best in the city. Â Get that too....Service needs to be more consistent. Â I loved the restaurant, when the servers kept my drinks filled plentiful the first time and even helped pour our beers. Â That was great, but.... Â  The next time, drink refill requests were forgotten, the server never poured or refilled any of our BYO beer, servers did not appear for long extended time periods to continue the ordering process (costing the restaurant revenue loss as well), and somehow the whole great service experience I had the first time was totally lost in visit 2. Â I also tried to cancel a reservation for visit 3 recenty, and the phone was busy or nobody would answer all afternoon.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nascetur76125',999,'2017-01-27',4,'This place is awesome. We got like everything.. scallops, tuna, crab, octopus, etc.. Everything was great, really great. It would get 5 stars if I could afford to go there more. Â Food bill for the 2 of us was $60, so plan to spend some dough. I am totally willing to pay a pretty penny for food this good and will again.. but thats the only reason for 4 instead of 5. The private booths are really cool!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',1321,'2021-08-10',5,'The Kai Zan experience is one of the best restaurant experiences possible, easily the best sushi in Chicago, arguably the best sushi in the United States. Â I make it a point to come here as often as possible and bring as many out-of-towners as possible. Â The food is absurdly good, the very definition of the word umami. Â The food is as tasty (braised pork belly skewer) as it is unique (salmon-wrapped scallop). Â A fantastic balance is achieved between allowing the ingredients to shine, and pushing and tweaking them with the grill, various sauces, and original combinations.Must try dishes include Angry Crab, Orange Rush, Grilled Hamachi Nigiri, Grilled Scallop Nigiri, Flaming Tuna, Green Monster, Madai Carpaccio (basil misto?!?!?), Momo Skewer, Tako Skewer, Kamo Skewer, Hotate Skewer, Char Siu Skewer, King Oyster Mushroom Skewer. Â It is also quite important to listen to the specials as there are some fantastic gems in there as well. Â Recent specials have included Otoro tuna, the highest grade of tuna belly. Â (The Otoro was absurd)The vibe at Kai Zan is one of relaxation and serenity, dare I be clichÃ© and call it zen-like. Â Isolated booths are available for larger parties. Â The wait staff is kind and respectful, but also distant enough where one can feel privacy and intimacy. Â The one time we had to wait for a reserved table, the chefs were kind enough to give us a freebie snack (an absurd escolar lollipop). Â I dont actually have anything negative to say about Kai Zan. Â Go there.Grade A+',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('in54195',1712,'2021-07-12',5,'Really great food plus a good atmosphere. Definitely a spot I enjoy taking my friends.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',885,'2018-12-03',4,'I had an inauspicious start here - called on three separate days to make a reservation, but no one answered during business hours. Â Decided to risk it and showed up 5pm Sat, but of course they were completely booked (they said their phone was broken.....whatever). Â Ended up making a reservation for SundayTwo of us ordered the omakase and I chose to a la carte it. Â The most memorable Angry Crab ($8) - spicy tongarashi crab wrapped in tunaEscolar Pearls ($8), Uni and Otoro Special - uni, otoro, quail egg, watercress and other delicious seasonings over a bed of rice with nori on the side to make small handrolls.The snapper and steelhead trout were also quite good in both the nigiri and sashimi forms. Things to pass on - Kushi Lava Rock Charbroil - beef, scallop, enoki in bacon ($4 - all quite bland)I didnt try the teppan yaki part of the menu (e.g. yakisoba or teriyaki) but their hot foods were below average for me...sorry!BYOB $5 corkageThe mango pudding with whipped cream ($4) is made in house and was a wonderful end to the meal. Â For first timers, get the omakase! Â For this price (~$50 ea), this has got to be hands-down, one of the best places in the city.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',1151,'2016-12-20',5,'Im not sure my review will do justice. Please take an evening and visit Kai Zan for dinner. Truly phenomenal Japanese preparations. I hope this place is here for 10 years to come.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',428,'2019-05-01',5,'Do you really need any more convincing? Do the $60 Omakase and you will happy and full. Order the 21% alcohol sake and try the Japanese craft beers. Done.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',234,'2018-11-08',5,'I have been back here 4 times since my first Yelp review. Â We had previously gotten the chef tasting menu; however they now have a second more expensive chef tasting Â (which to me was just the original tasting we had before but twice as much). Â The 1st tier tasting menu is still very good - it just has been repetitive courses time after time. Â The final sashimi final course presentation has gotten smaller and smaller each time we have been. Â They are now full service bar not BYO which also drives the price up. Â Fish is still amazingly fresh and food is very very very good. Â Have not had anything bad yet! Â Would still go back - prices are just getting very harsh to justify!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',705,'2019-12-10',5,'Looked like great food but the server told us we had to be done with dinner in 1 hour. Â I was like, really? Â Is this a cafeteria? Â We got up and left. Â Very disappointing',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',376,'2017-01-20',4,'I loved every bite, but the fact that you have a time limit, stops me from coming back. This place is beautiful has friendly service and trendy decor, with the most deliciously unique menu items...yum!!! Seriously their small plates will blow your mind even if you have the most sophisticated taste buds, but they give you an hour and a half and that is not enough time for a meal in my book... that is how they lost one star and an opportunity for the encore of my company )',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1340,'2020-12-24',5,'This place is a foodies dream come true. The $60 omakase menu is quite possibly the best deal for food (not just sushi) in Chicago. The finale sashimi/sushi plate on that menu would be $60 alone at some other restaurants. Weve come here many times and Melvin & Carlo have served consistently better food every time, if thats somehow possible. On occasion, they will get a fresh batch of uni in from Santa Barbara and IT IS HEAVEN.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',741,'2021-04-08',5,'This is my new sushi spot for someone special or folks visiting Chicago. Why?Edibles- Oyster shooters- Seabass carpacio- Salmon wrapped scallops aka Orange Rush- Great sushi rollsNon-edibles- $5 bottle poppin fee - Easy street parkingDone and done. Make reservations. Get after it.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede20152',585,'2017-03-08',4,'I will start out by saying that the dishes we ordered were incredible...that said, the service was the complete opposite. I had called ahead to make a reservation for my birthday and also noted that we wanted uni if it was available. We were 15 minutes late (which I also called to notify them of) so they said we couldnt order the tasting menu because there wouldnt be enough time. When we got there, we were given the worst seats in the house (in the corner by the bathroom) in front of the sushi chefs who I thought might at least acknowledge our presence. Our waiter was very curt and didnt smile once- seemed like he just wanted to rush us out from the beginning (didnt talk about any of the dishes, only quickly took our order). We ordered a la cart as thats what we were told they could accommodate and- after ordering the special, which included uni- I made note again that we would want more uni. Our waiter said they were out except for the special (our reservation was at 530, by the way). When we ordered , the food was rushed out one thing on top of the next and we ended up being done with our entire meal 1/2 hour early. Also, not one acknowledgment was made about my birthday (usually one at least receives a free dessert or is offered a special nigiri of some kind during the meal). Ive lived in NYC and LA and eaten at the best sushi restaurants in the US and this was truly the worst service Ive ever experienced...to top it off, I have stage 4 cancer and this could be my last birthday altogether. Im not sure the quality of sushi was worth this disappointing experience.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',1158,'2021-04-22',5,'Best sushi in Chicago! Most creative chefs. Friendliest staff. I could go on and on (and I do...to everyone I know). Kai Zan is a gem and a refreshing take on Sushi. Nothing you order here will disappoint. I dream about the uni toro tartar special. I would tell everyone to sit at the sushi bar, but I dont want anyone taking our seats )!!!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',1293,'2018-07-20',5,'Hear ye, hear ye citizens of Chicago, this sushi place fan-diddly-astic. I fear that it could jump the shark if it gets any more good reviews. Â But, the Vizconde twins did not disappoint when I sat promptly at 5 p.m. in front of them at the sushi bar after not having eating a single thing all day in anticipation of my omakase experience. Â They completely toppled my previous favorite, Coast. Â Dear Coast, Ive already forgotten what you look like. Â Just to give you a little perspective, I worked as a fine-dining server for 15 years in the best American and French restaurants. Â I have a razor-tuned palate. When it comes to sushi, while I love it and have eaten at countless sushi bars, Im a bit out of my element. Ive Â I dont know any Japanese terminology. Â I only explain this to tell you that I do not lightly say this This was not only the best sushi Ive ever had. Â It was the best meal Ive ever experienced in Chicago in terms of the entire experience . Â . Â . and the value for the dollar. Â I know when restaurants are screwing you over for a tasting menu and this does not happen at Kai Zan. Â Now I know that their prices have risen slightly since their opening, but what I received for $60 last night was spot on. Â BTW, Dear General Public Do you know that whenever you eat out for brunch you are getting totally hosed on value for your dollar? Here the dollar sprouts little angel wings and flies further than you know it could in the overpriced universe known as Chicago.The food, everyone else on this forum has emphasized the food in great detail. Â My favorite was the Angry Crab and the Scallop pearls with truffle oil. Â The dashi broth course was also excellent. Â And ending with the sashimi plate instead of starting with it . Â . Â . absolutely genius. Â After already having had around 10 courses, you realize now matter how full you are you can slide down just one more perfectly cut piece of fish. Â The Dynamite Mussel was also excellent, much more flavorful than the standard French presentation of mussels & frites. Â I checked with the chef and, of course, even the mussels were sourced carefully, New Zealand Â green lipped as Id suspected. Â They are richer, slightly larger, fattier, and more flavorful than the standard PEI mussel that is generally served in restaurants. Â If you ever have your choice at the fishmonger, buy them when you see them. Â Prepare them as you normally would, but they will taste better. Sitting at the sushi bar was a great experience and the chefs made a couple extra items in addition to the standard menu that night and handed them directly to me. Â I always sit at the sushi bar so I can ask chefs to prepare me something off the menu, but these guys did it without me even having asked. Â That really sealed my imminent return. Â I began to wonder at one point if they suspected me of being a food writer, because I just kind of look like one and if youve read this far, you really can tell that Im a writer, just not a food writer. Â (Occasional psychology articles if youre interested.) One food critique that Im going to include, and only because I read many other reviews on here that mentioned it too, is the Tuna-tini. Â Now, I think American brains get a bit confused some of the time because we always want our taste buds to be knocked out of the park, and an important element of Japanese cuisine is subtlety and simplicity, as in the dashi broth. Â The Tuna-tini is a simple salad composed of Blue Fin toro, avocados, and heirloom tomatoes over a bed of seaweed. Â The server described a dressing that was in it, but I didnt taste it. Â There was nothing to highlight all of the flavors, Im really thinking this dish is calling out for a bit more acidity to cut the fatty tuna and avocado flavors and textures. Also, as much as I love the taste of Blue Fin toro, the entire world needs to stop eating it for a few years. Its clearly listed as a fish to be avoided by the Monterey Bay guide. Â I had no problems with the service. Â Many on this forum have complained of stoic or aloof service. Â Dear General Populace, you are not at TGI Fridays. Â The service needs to do their job not fulfill any inner-emotional vacuum that you might be having. Â As long as servers make a suggestion or two, are knowledgeable about the food, are quick efficient, thats all you need. Â Theyre not there to be your friend, they are doing their job. Â Get over yourself.Obviously, I highly recommend you patronize this establishment. Â It has a nice romantic atmosphere that is not trying to hard or overdone in anyway. Â They serve alcohol but I was informed on the phone I could bring a bottle of wine or sake for a corkage fee of $15/two people. Â A very reasonable corkage fee if Ive ever heard one. Â I seized on the idea and brought a nice white wine to enjoy. My next big meal out is definitely going to be the elevated omakase, with my beautiful wife and a bottle of demi-sec champagne. Â Wont that be a lovely evening?',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4994',312,'2021-12-02',4,'Definitely would go back again.Service GreatUnagi popper Mediocre; good as a jalapeno popper but couldnt taste any unagiGreen Monster very fresh and delicious; loved the texture, but it was supposed to have unagi in it and didnt taste anyEscolar pearls Probably the best thing we had; truly amazingKaki fry LOVE; and love the small salad it comes withAlthough not on the menu, we asked for a sashimi platter, and the waiter said the chef could prepare something for us - fantastic; only thing i didnt like was the saba, but ive also spent a lot of time in japan so perhaps im spoiled; all the fish was fresh and they gave 2 tempura shrimp heads as wellTip everything was great except things that we ordered unagi in; they either serve quantities of unagi that are undetectable or theirs isnt very good; would recommend everything but those pieces; having said that, those items were still delicious, just couldnt really taste the unagi! 1 of 2 really great sushi places in chicago',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',1711,'2018-02-05',5,'We have lived in Humboldt Park for 28 years and never dreamed a place like Kai Zan would show up within walking distance. Truly a tactile and sensual dining experience.The Omagashe is the way to go even for experienced sushi munchers like us, we were in protein heaven, a lot of food. Service was informative but respectful and we look forward to another visit',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',1064,'2018-05-28',5,'This is a wonderful place for couples dating! I went there with my fiancÃ© and he loved this place too. The service is very kind. The most important thing is the food!!! The Uni tar tar and king oyster mushroom are my favorite dishes!!! They are really tasty and fresh!',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt318',1708,'2019-07-30',4,'The tasting menu is the way to go! Best sushi in Chicago for sure, definitely make a reservation!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum5724',809,'2016-10-05',5,'I absolutely loved Kai Zan sushi. Â If you enjoy little dive type sushi bars, then you will love this place. Â It certainly is not a dive. Â Its clean, nice, and trendy. Â I referred to it as a dive more due to it being out of the heart of the city a bit and it pretty small. Â We sat at the sushi bar and whats great about that is that you get to watch the chefs all while eating. Â We decided not to do the amakazi but I must say everybody else was and it looked great. My favorite was the dynamite mussels. Â Though its not a real popular dish here or I mean it is not suggested by staff but we loved it is the spicy tuna and cucumber roll. Â The fish is fresh and very good.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',1254,'2018-02-15',5,'came here twice and got the omakase both times. do make reservations, as itll be nice to get a more intimate booth to add to the ambiance. the omakase price is a little steep $60. each time, though, the thoughtfulness of the flavors and presentations of each dish were not disappointing.my favorites from the chefs special were the pearls with truffle oil and the uni shooters. the pearls were incredibly delectable and truffle oil sauce added such a deep richness that i loved. we have a word for such a flavor in korean, but im not so sure how to translate it in english. perhaps savory is the best term for it. theres a subtle spice that helps to balance out the richness.the uni shooters were outstanding. at first gulp, you get the rich creaminess of the yolk and uni. add a little citrus tang from the ponzu. then, theres a hint of spice from the tabasco. the black roe atop most of the pieces is money. i love them. my friend wisely articulated them as balls of flavor. this is, perhaps, the best sushi experience ive ever had.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris70121',1664,'2016-11-01',4,'My initial review removed a star only because of the service issue, but that issue has been addressed and resolved. Â The owners quickly responded, acknowledged what happened, apologized, and offered to generously accommodate us on our next visit, which is all we could really ask for.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',1528,'2020-09-25',5,'Amazing place ! Â Superb food - and even better service. Â A splendid mix of Japanese and Latin culinary brilliance. Sit at bar and watch how focused and intense the talented chefs are.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',1266,'2021-09-04',5,'Oh man, I thought I wrote a review for this place. So so good. Im not even the biggest sushi fan but I loved going here. We for sure splurged, not a cheap meal, but worth it. I enjoyed everything that was brought out and ordered. The orange rush and angry crab were my two favorites. BYOB, great for date night or double date night. We were waiting a tad for a table and they brought out free food for us, which was so nice and not expected. The service was perfect and they gave great recs to me as a newbie. Cannot wait to go back and splurge again.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed7891',878,'2016-08-26',5,'very limited seating of 22 (if that!), definitely need reservations!loved the chef special rolls, but the maki rolls were so small and normal. the fish is very fresh and creatively presented with out the different kind of sauces that covers up all the fish! will come back for affordable fresh fish!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',515,'2017-09-25',4,'Spectacular fresh creative sushi. Value for omakase cannot be beat in the city. No longer BYOB, sadly (',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',445,'2018-04-08',5,'Wow this place lived up to the hype - had 2 friends highly recommend and we stopped by after the Bulls game tonight. Â Appetizers included the Escalar and Magura Pearls and the spiciness combined with seared fish and truffle was perfectly complimentary. Â The Madai Carpaccio was red snapper with basil, miso and olive oil and was light and delicious. Â The angry crab of tuna wrapped around crab was very fresh but simple. Â The Grilled Hamachi Nigiri was unreal and my favorite - the flamed grill flavor and minted jalapeÃ±o is just sushi perfection. Â We also had the chef bring out the spicy toro bite - tuna belly, chili oil, Massago rub and fried kale chips with truffle soaked scallions - wow what a combo. Â The steak skewer was just ok but the pork belly skewer was to die for and we ordered a second. Â Green tea and their donuts that were Spanish inspired with egg nog and rum infusion were so good that my wife couldnt stop talking about it and she generally hates donuts. Â This is going to become my go to sushi restaurant in the City of Chicago.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra2114',41,'2021-04-18',5,'This place is amazing. Â I had been wanting to try to for a long time, it was worth the wait. Â My boyfriend and I opted for the Chefs menu and it was outstanding. Â Definitely worth the price, some of the best quality fish Ive ever had. Â Each course offered something adventurous yet approachable. Â Our waiter was knowledgable and the presentation of every course came with a detailed explanation was what was being served. Â They now serve wine, beer and saki and BYOB is still an option but it comes with a $15 corkage fee.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',496,'2021-05-13',4,'This place is nice inside and the food is good and all, but boy are the prices inflated especially for the area!!! OMG Kai Zan get a grip, youre not better than the majority of the sushi places in and around Chicago. Ive had just as good sushi, if not better, at other restaurants and at fraction of the cost. For the price we paid, I would have expected alot more food than what we got! And whats up with the food showing up in less than 5 minutes from the time we ordered it? Boy thats the quickest Ive experienced, but I had to wonder if it was even fresh?Now onto the bigger reason I had to write this review, the waitress! Have you ever had a waitress who literally hovers over you as you are looking at the menu???? What the heck is that all about?!?! She did so twice, and the I think the only reason she didnt do it again after the second time is because my friend finally told her we need a few more minutes! Gosh, how obnoxious! I think she was eager to get us out of there prior to or by 7. We didnt have a reservation when we walked in, so they did seat us however, they made it pretty clear that we had to be out of there by 7 as they had that table reserved for a larger party at 7....so i suppose me and my friend were not large enough! Also, since it was our first Â time there, we asked what she recommends. We realized later that everything she recommended were all the priciest items on the menu! What a scam! We spent $70, walked out of there still hungry! The experience was NOT a good one whatsoever! I probably would not have even written this review if it wasnt for the obnoxious, scam waitress and for her eagerness to get us out of there by 7 and suggesting all the most expensive items on the menu which we got very little considering the price! I hope she got her fat tip from her large party for basically trying to push us out of there before 7! Huge disappointment!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',500,'2020-07-04',5,'I love sushi and Japanese cuisine. Â My meal here was one of my most memorable in the city. Â  Fantastic food, presentation, service and ambiance. Â I sat at the sushi bar and enjoyed the respect the chefs gave to the food preparation (and I got a few extra samples too!). Â I had the Chefs tasting menu - definitely worth doing! Â This place is BYOB too! Â  Reservations are a must, and if you are a party of 4, you will likely get a nice bungalow style table. Â Better than Momotaro, Juno, and priced better as well. Â A great dinner out on a date or with a small group of friends. Â  Not recommended for groups, and the neighborhood doesnt offer much in terms of pre or post dinner options. Â I cant wait to',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',358,'2019-07-21',5,'This place was fantastic - my wife an i celebrated our anniversary here and after reviewing the menu we decided to do the Chefs selection - i was totally blown away.We are sushi veterans but have never seen presentation and execution quite like this, i was actually a bit nervous when the sushi shooters came out but they were one of our favorite dishes. Â our server was very easy going and informative - the plates were cleared on time and we did not ever feel rushed despite the busy restaurant.we sat at the sushi bar which was nice, the kitchen staff is friendly and very detail oriented. Â i highly recommend this place.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisi29157',1592,'2022-02-08',5,'One of the best meals Ive ever had and I cannot wait to go back.My friend made reservations for a large party there, which is kind of hard to do due to the seating arrangements. We insisted on all of us sitting together quite cozily in the front. None of us seemed to mind or care - we wanted to be together and not divide up. Almost all of us ate the Omekase menu and each dish was more amazing than the previous. Service was great and the chefs are super kind. I appreciate them tolerating us rowdy folks.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis34168',934,'2020-11-12',5,'So this is one of my new favorites - Ive been here at least 5 times in the last 6 months. Â Its not because its the most authentic, because its truly not. Â The escolar balls, the orange rush, danielle (aforementioned three of our favorites) and their other sushi/sashimi bites and various grilled and raw options, all have an ingenious little twist from the standard sushi fare - but its awesome. Â I am the last person to endorse a sushi place that caters too much to sauces and pairings, but when the flavor combination is this good, you know that the sub-standard fish is not hiding behind the flavored mayo but it is taking that fresh fish to another level. On top of all of that, it is byob! Â Bring a quality white to go with the quality fish, and you wont regret it!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ami17',345,'2017-06-08',4,'Absolutely fresh food. Had my most favorite sea urchin and sweet shrimp here. Highly recommend uni shooter and sea urchin & sweet shrimp sashimi. Everything is just perfect here. My greatest experience ever!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rhoncus2633',206,'2017-06-14',5,'Food was good but we were rushed which took away from the experience. Husband and I ordered the Omakase and our kids ordered a la carted off the menu. Theyve been eating sushi for 10 years so they are old pros at ordering and behaving. However, we just werent given the time to savor our food - before Id finished one, another order came out. No offers to refill our drinks either so I can only assume they wanted us out to seat more people. Â As nice as the food I remember was, I can have a much more pleasant dining experience ce somewhere else. 5 arrived at 505 for our 515 reservation and with a 10 course Omakase we were in the car in the way home by 620. Way too rushed.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla91184',1649,'2021-09-19',5,'Service good! Food great! Best Japanese place in this area! Recommend its tasting menu!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',562,'2019-04-11',4,'Kai Zan is my absolute, hands down, favorite sushi spot in all of Chicago. I literally dream of this place. Went with a friend for dinner and after setting a reservation we were kindly but firmly made aware of their reservation policy and its a strict one so dont take them lightly and show up on time. Went with the Omakase and was not disappointed. Everything was so fresh and delicious, from the uni to the escarole. A true hidden gem in the city. Cannot wait to return',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',1272,'2021-10-06',5,'How have I not actually written a review for our absolute most favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago?! We have been coming here for... Forever and just when I attempt to try another sushi/Japanese places I am always so incredibly disappointed and sad we didnt just come here. I am always left wondering is it actually possible to EVER tire of this place?! Im thinking not... We have tried just about everything on the menu, and needless to say we always struggle in choosing which items to pick when we go because it is all SO AMAZING! We have also tried the omakase tasting menu. Holy OMG amazing! However, on our normal visits, the orange rush, angry crab, and dynamite mussels are our absolute go to. The Escolar Pearls or Maguro Pearls are spot on as well. To supplement our meal we will usually order the yaki soba with either beef or pork. I cant say enough wonderful things about this place. My only gripe is it can be somewhat difficult to get a reservation... Unless you want to eat at 530 or 930. Otherwise, by far our favorite restaurant ever!!!!',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat1120',435,'2021-07-04',5,'SO GREAT! Amazing small dishes with so much flavor. I recommend the green monster roll, but you really cant go wrong.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus0123',974,'2020-07-22',4,'Upon entering you are transported to a wonderful, curated world that feels decidedly modern and Japanese. Â Our lovely, small booth was perfect for two and elicited excited exclamations from my sister the patterns, the flowers, the coziness- as it was her birthday, I was delighted! Â The specials Â - all of them too intriguing to pass up...at once complex, intricate and deliciously simple. Â  Our dinner was unhurried, perfectly timed and of the highest quality. Â You know its going to be good when the Chefs and waitstaff check in on you excitedly - wondering what you thought. Each item selected was balanced and worthy of a repeat. Â Obviously, I was blown away. Reminiscent of Uchiko in Austin. Â These dishes were not experimental, rather very intentionally developed over time to leave you wanting more. BYOB. Â Small, tiny really. Â Plan ahead, make a reservation and prepare to be delighted.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',52,'2016-09-01',5,'We had a superb dinner at Kai Zan. Â What happened to be a lucky find on yelp, turned out to be a real gem. Â The sushi was fresh and we loved the oyster shooters, uni nigiri as well as the uni and tuna special. Â Service was attentive and food was outstanding! Â We will be back soon to try the omakase. Â Love the place!',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',642,'2017-11-04',5,'We ordered the Omakase--the food at Kai Zan is good. But 10 courses in one hour is a frantic pace for a meal. We tried to order another round of sake after having been there for exactly 1 hour and 5 minutes, and were told by our waitress that shed have to check, because there might be another reservation. I really wanted to like Kai Zan, because it is cute, and the food is good, but I wont go back. Its just not fun to be rushed through a meal at lightning speed--they say when you make a reservation that you have 90 minutes to dine, but thats only if they feel like giving it to you, apparently. I guess that sums it up--just not very fun.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc15',1252,'2021-02-18',5,'Ive been following Melvin around from restaurant to restaurant since 2002. It was at his last place I discovered he had a twin brother (Carlo) of equal culinary skill. Ive known about Kai Zan since they opened, but since I now live out of state, I havent been able to visit till now. Its been about 4 years since Ive had the pleasure to eat their food and Im very pleased to see their skill has improved greatly since my last visit. I highly recommend checking them out. They buy their fish daily. Staff was extremely attentive and friendly. We showed up late for our reservation and they tried to accommodate us with a bit more time at the end. Extremely appreciated. Well done guys. Ill be back.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et65112',1609,'2017-07-09',5,'Best Sushi Ive ever had. I am very picky so thats saying a lot. Do not leave without ordering the orange rush, pearl escolar, salmon belly.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien4153',853,'2019-11-02',5,'Great sushi, BYOB, and free street parking.All their signature sushi pieces and rolls are awesome. Â If you dont want to have to pick out stuff on your own, just get the omakase and let the talented chefs surprise you!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',56,'2016-09-15',4,'Oh hai!!!! Welcome to the neighborhood, Kai Zan. How I love you so very much!!!! I noticed that theres a new restaurant opened up next to Komoda but I wasnt very sure what type of restaurant it is. One day, after doing some work from Star Lounge, my boyfriend and i tried to come in for dinner. Sadly, it was about an hour of a wait and we cant wait that long ( so, the next day, i called in to make a reservations and 7pm right on time, when we walked in. we were seated at the booth, cool waters and hot towels were ready for us ) Our server.... Shame on me for not remembering his name was super nice and friendly. He introduced himself and asked if this is the first time we were there and showed us the yummiest items on the menu. And so, we had the Escolar Pearl, which is AMAZINGLY YUMMY!!!! Its a must try!!! The chicken karaage was also very delicious. We tried a few of the Omakase which also very very good and fresh. We had the green monster roll and the Angry Crab. Yum!!! Everything was very delicious. We tried the skewers but werent very impressed by it, but that didint ruined it at all. I am just happy to know that theres delicious sushi spot a block away from where I live. All the servers are very attentive and friendly. The place is too adorable. Its really small but very cozy and lovely. You cant come in a big group because on how small the place is and make sure you call in ahead of time for a reservation. I love everything about this place and definitely will be back sooner than later )',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',1023,'2017-08-19',5,'Theres not a lot to be added to the already huge list of glowing reviews for Kai Zan.The experience was fantastic, the price was very reasonable and the fish was amazing!Sign of a good restaurant...people making reservations to come back before they finish their dinner!If you havent already been, go there immediately but dont forget a reservation!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',710,'2016-04-18',5,'Fresh sashimi and nice nigiri, creative dishes are surprised! Not happy about the takoyaki tho',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus6748',674,'2018-12-11',4,'Having lived in the neighborhood for 3 years, I was really excited we were finally getting a sushi spot. Â It didnt live up to my expectations at all .....pros = its beautiful, really well done on the build outcons = 1. Â we waited for 10 mins @ 6pm on Saturday when it was 1/2 empty for our server to acknowledge us. Â This is likely to improve I hope as they get their stride.2. Â Even though they have a hood, the grill emits a very greasy smell, not pleasant for a healthy adventure into a clean sushi dinner3. Â The rolls were good, but not amazing4. Â The grilled items were OK, but not anything particularly special.5. Â The flat bread seemed like something concocted with ingredients from Dominicks down the road (aside from the quality sushi of course.Overall, I felt like they are just trying too hard, the menu is trying to do too much. Â If they focused on doing some simple, but fresh sushi rolls, I think they would do much better. Â Id only go back if they revamped their menu....',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',457,'2017-08-02',5,'Fantastic!Think of it as a very up scale BYOB neighborhood Japanese joint. Complete Â with young too hip staff..',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',1548,'2021-08-16',5,'Amazing. amazing. Amazing!!!! Â Everything we had from the chefs tasting menu was wonderful and super fresh. Â Weve already been back several times since our first visit. Â Love this place!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',1229,'2016-05-19',4,'The food is awesome cause they are all special and creative. However, it has a limited time for each party. For example, you need to return the table at 630 pm if you arrive at 500 pm. So I think if you want to chat with your friends for a long time, maybe thats not a good place. Anyway, the food there are really amazing, I like it.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',437,'2018-05-23',5,'The food was $$$ but amazing. Â Flavor profiles and infusions Ive never had before and just amazing treats for my mouth (could have done without the seared tuna on a stick in Dashi during the omakase). But....the service was douchey. Â We came to celebrate 3 out of 5 people in our party bc it was our birthdays so we were in it to win it and try everything. Â Our server, while Im sure a nice enough fellow was very snooty and kept interrupting us during our birthday celebration in a snotty way. Â When 3 out of 5 of us decided to order the omakase chefs special, his demeanor changed and he was more polite. Â Part of his attitude probably had to do with the alcohol we brought bc of their byob policy. Â We admittedly brought in a lot of different sakis and Japanese beers to try with our meal bc of byob policy. Â But its very unclear what their policy is. Â Is it even posted anywhere officially? Â I couldnt find it after all of this occurred just found bloggers and reviewers posts. Â We were under the impression that there was a 2 bottle min and for every 2 bottles theres a $15 corking fee. Â But after already opening 2 bottles of single bottle beers, we were told we were done, it was only a 2 bottle policy. Â First of all...there really should be better rules for single beer bottles vs a bottle of wine. Â You get 4-5 servings out of a wine bottle vs a single bottle of beer. Â The server was wishy washy about it, upset, then fine that we had already opened the bottles....we were celebrating so we didnt really take that into account and didnt want to let it ruin our evening, so we opened some very small sake bottles to try and then all of a sudden the manager trips over to lecture us on respecting their policy. Â Im sitting there dumbfounded bc Im still unclear on what their policy is and how they now serve alcohol, etc. Â Honestly I think half our table still didnt understand either and we had to talk it over long after the principle, I mean the manager left our table. Â Long story short, we respectfully put our alcohol away (they wanted to take it from us to ensure we didnt open any more unauthorized bottles and we assured them we wouldnt) and were forced to order from their alcohol menu. Â Really Kai Zan, eliminate byob if you are pushing your liquor now. Â People who come to eat your amazing food WILL pay for your liquor too. Â Not even sad to say I will not go back for a while, possibly ever. Â Not worth the douchey service, and kind of ruined our night.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',1311,'2021-03-01',5,'Carlo and Melvin the brothers who own this have an amazing gift of creating interesting and delicious taste combinations. We had the Chefs Choice tonight and it was amazing!! The team they have built are top notch and first class!! Love.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',1603,'2020-01-26',5,'So I finally tried this place for the first time and wanted to see if it lived up to the reviews. Â I had the regular omakase and I would say half of the courses were good, while the other half wasnt anything too special - items that you can find in other restaurants that taste exactly the same (for example, the torched salmon and tuna roll and the mushroom & clam soup really wasnt anything that unique). Â But for the amount of food that youre getting, $65 for 10 courses is quite a good deal. Â The service here is also quite outstanding...our waiter took the time to explain each and every course that came out. Â Its just a very friendly and hospitable atmosphere. Â Overall though, I just wasnt wowed away and had expected to be. Â Again, this likely due to the inconsistency I felt in the omakase.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',309,'2016-05-28',5,'This place is amazing and the food is so good! Go for the Chefs choice! Its really worth it! One of my favorites Japanese restaurants in Chicago for sure',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',1412,'2020-08-29',5,'People love this place and I always wonder why. We went up eating here when we are starving after work and the portions are not enough and the prices are sky high. Sure its cute, but there are other places that you can go to get some great sushi. The staff is really friendly and help you make some smart choices. If you do do I recommend the calamari strings and whatever the chefs special role is. I didnt like the limited dessert menu. As someone with a big sweet tooth that is a must!!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',1699,'2018-07-28',4,'Great atmosphere and food. We did the chefs menu and it was out of this world. Service was swift and informative.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',305,'2022-01-01',4,'As fantastic as always. Â Carlos and Melvin continue to impress with their variety and creations. Hope to be back soon',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',1351,'2018-09-08',5,'This is the best sushi spot in Chicago and Ive been to many! Its up there with the real fancy shit in loop too, chefs menu is EXCELLENT! And the price is too good to be true ! Im so impressed and so is my BF and hes been to Shiros in Seattle! Everyone is nice and smiley and our waitress was so adorable and well trained. Its tough to get in so I almost dont want to encourage people to come LOL, but I tell like everyone I know about them anyway. I hope they expand or something ... I love this place to pieces !',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',203,'2017-03-27',3,'Short review Go here. Ask for Arlene. Let her take care of you. Seriously, just do what she tells you.Longer review Omakase is worth double what they charge. The uni was so good we couldnt stop eating it the day we were there. Just dont be afraid and eat anything they bring. The red snapper sashimi was superb. Cant rave enough.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',1567,'2018-06-21',5,'This is some of the freshest sushi Ive had in Chicago. Â Kai Zan is really small, so its nearly impossible to get a last minute reservation (or make a reservation change) and the location is a little off the beaten path, but its definitely worth the trouble! I went with a friend on a Monday night and the place was completely full at 10pm (which admittedly might not be saying a ton because of how small it is). Kai Zan had been recommended to each of us recently, so we figured it was a must try...and we were definitely glad we did!We didnt order the Chefs tasting menu, but it came highly recommended by my friend and our server, so Id definitely like to order it next time Im there. We ordered a ton of items off the menu instead and some of our favorites were the escolar pearls appetizer and the angry crab sushi. The seasonal hamachi was also delicious. You cant go wrong with any of the nigiri, but the steelhead trout special was some of the most buttery, tender nigiri Ive ever had. I love that Kai Zans menu has really inventive flavor combinations that dont overpower the fish. If you like your rolls huge, deep fried, and with a lot of spicy mayo - this is not the place to go!This place only serves water and green tea, so the BYOB policy applies to just about every type of beverage, which means you get to spend all your hard earned money on some excellent sushi instead of booze )While I had a great experience, Â I can see why some Yelpers mention a pretentious wait staff. I got a little bit of that vibe when we asked for our servers recommendations, but nothing so over the top that it spoiled our meal.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',1705,'2016-12-23',5,'Hands down the best sushi Ive ever had. Every single thing Ive tasted has been delicious - escolar pearls, angry crab, orange rush, and green monster being some of my favorites.My only gripe is the location - it is pretty far from where I live, wish it was closer to Lakeview!',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',273,'2017-07-23',4,'2nd time here and everything is so amazing! Service is great, the chef came out and checked on things- how wonderful!They were very accommodating as well! Will continue to come back!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',256,'2017-04-03',5,'I came here for dinner with my daughter this past Tuesday, she had heard of the place but it was a first time visit for both of us. Â The first thing that strikes you is its small, intimate size and setting (making reservations a must). Â For its size (and the fact that it was packed during our visit) it is remarkably conversation friendly. Â We were seated right on time and never felt rushed.Kai Zan is BYOB with limited non-alcoholic drink options so be prepared. We used it as an opportunity to choose a few extra items from the menu in lieu of cocktails. My choice was the unagi poppers that, although he waiter tried to persuade me against as not unique, I thoroughly enjoyed.A few general words about the menu. Â Small and well chosen. Â It is the size of an single sheet of paper offering a broad, but still select group of options. Â It was nice to not have to wade through page after page of house specialties.What we both found unusual was the preparation of the rolls. Â There seems to be a trend to over sauce to the point of losing the flavor of the fish in current soy/wasabi blends. Â Not so here. Â It has been a long time since I enjoyed such a great balance between the ingredients. Â Very refreshing....and yes, the Escolar Pearls and Angry Crab are must tries. Â All of our choices were both flavorful and delicate simultaneously though sometimes the construction required a light touch on the chopsticks lest your bite disassembles on its way to your mouth. Â I had the mango pudding for dessert, also a winner.Prices are very reasonable though portions are just a bit on the small side. Â It did allow for a nice sampling experience and now that I think back I would describe the meal as sushi meets tapas. Â The two of us left fully satisfied for $75 (not including tip).The service was good with an exception of a miscalculation on our servers part at one point overwhelming our small table. Â In a small sushi restaurant with a lot to sample, timing is everything. Â I will go back to sample the great food Â in one of the four cozy, enclosed dining booths on the left side of the restaurant. They looked like a great date/anniversary setting.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',1715,'2019-02-15',5,'This place is just about as amazing as people say it is. I highly recommend you go with the Omakase, just like I recommended you do the degustation menus in Paris. When there is an option to let the chef feed you, do it.Hard to remember all the dishes, but the uni shooters were lovely- a teensy bit acidic for my taste, the bacon wrapped mushrooms were great, and the little mushroom soups were so aromatic and full of flavor. Just the broth was amazing. Obviously all the fish was perfect- they are a little heavy with the spices instead of leaving the fish in its natural state, but it worked, so I was okay with that.The space is so tiny, you have to make reservations or youll probably never get in. But its BYOB, which is really nice. Im a big fan of the BYOBs. I would definitely go back, and I think I would order off the menu this time, just kuz Ive already done the Omakase, and Id like to try more of the sushi. Overall a definite must in the Chicago Japanese food scene.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',223,'2021-09-09',4,'The best sushi in Chicago, hands down. Â No need to run to overrated downtown, when you have an absolute 5-star restaurant with phenomenal service. Â I took my boyfriend there for a celebratory dinner and he was stunned as much as I was. Â And, Im hard to please, especially when it comes to sushi in Chicago, LA, or New York. Â We both had the 5 courses, every one was deliciously prepared, the first time I was happy enough to try sea urchin as well. Â I need to go back; now that Im in LA, I know Ill be hitting it up if Im anywhere close to flying back to cold Chitown weather.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis2682',653,'2021-06-01',5,'If you are a sushi lover this place is a must. Try spending the $65 on the Omakase 10 course pleasure train and youll be screaming Oh My Kase as your mouth explodes with flavor. Bring a towel. If you are ordering a la carte then my fav apps were the Tako Yaki (somehow they pack a perfect punch of juicy delicious not weird-textured octopus into this fried ball), the Escolar pearls(maguro pearls too, prob my fav thing on the menu so delicate and the truffle is the perfect settling touch) followed by the angry crab, orange rush, andy any of the Nigiri. To provide some balance we chose to dabble in a few skewers and went with the beef tataki and Hotate. I do highly suggest sitting at the bar as opposed to the booths because you are front row to a cooking clinic and watch your food get made in front of you and served in under 5 minutes of ordering. No clue how they do it but maybe its those surgeon-like hands magic jazz hands that serve up fantasies on a plate all night long. All in all this place is a mouthgasm waiting to happen.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula91137',492,'2018-09-30',5,'Wonderful restaurant! It one of the best Japanese restaurant in the Chicago area I think. The sashimi is very fresh. You need to try everything.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum23143',554,'2021-10-06',4,'New age/fusion sushi rarely works for me, but I cant help but admit that I was very impressed by the innovation flavors. The chefs here are very, very talented.First things first, make a reservation before coming here. This place is SMALL (ironic how Im using large caps to say its small). There were about 8 seats at the sushi bar, then there were 6 or 7 other small tables. We got lucky when they seated us without a reservation on a Monday night. With that said, I think small works for this place. The intimate setting, the friendliness of the staff & chefs, and being able to watch the chefs cook in front of you reminds me of Japanese izakayas.A very cool thing this place offers is the option of having the chef design a menu just for you by giving them a price range of how much you are willing to spend. I didnt try it this time because others wanted very specific things off the menu, but I am planning to try that next time based on the wonderful flavor we experienced here. There are many, many other places that charge much more for sushi that just taste really crappy...dont waste your money at those places. Though Yelp has this @ $$$, the pricing is really $$ and a half...very, very affordable. (plan on spending $50 - $75 a person here).',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',1111,'2019-05-17',5,'I do not want to review this place...because it is my favorite spot in Chicago and I dont want you to go!!! Please dont go. More pearls for me.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis14141',1465,'2017-06-16',5,'Wonderful place for authentic Japanese food! Started with a hot miso and nice salad before the fish started to roll off the bar. Sushi was true to form and delicious. Â Staff was excellent and even mailed my credit card to me as I had already left town. Will definitely come back when in chicago again.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed7891',104,'2021-01-06',5,'Absolutely wonderful. The chefs menu (Omakase) is a tremendous value and a great way to try a broad swath of the menu. Weve been there several times and have always enjoyed outstanding tastes and very attentive service. Highly recommended.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',1191,'2017-12-21',5,'Definitely 4.5 stars, rounding up.RIght up there with one of the best sushi/japanese spots in chicago - not your run-of-the-mill, japanese and then some thai dishes on the side (blah).Finally swung by to experience this sleeper of a japanese concept on the border of ukranian village and humboldt park. Â DESERVES ALL THE HYPE.Usually would not want to advertise it, but I feel this spot needs a push because on a Sunday evening, the restaurant was quiet and half-full (and its quite a small space as it is). Â  The space was very cozy and zen. Â We tried the omakase, which IMO is quite a good value for the quality and variety of food. Â We went for two more rounds beyond the standard $50 which was enough to fill me up.Omakase starts with a best-of appetizer line-up and various raw sushi components following. Â Wish there was more of a true progression, but it was all very tasty, so I guess I dont really care.What we lovedMaguro pearls - perfect small bite of sushi and flavorAngry crab sushi - soft texture of sushi wrapping flavor packed spicy craball the Uni dishes - uni with king crab, uni on seared yellow tail and straight up uni on rice AMAZING!Salmon belly & hamachi belly Â the salmon lightly dressed and succulent, the hamachi served straight up and perfectly buttery and fresh.Salmon wrapping scallop Â cant go wrong with this comboThe fish quality here is really great, not a step wrongI would say the cuisine is taking fresh sushi and putting a special twist on the sauces and flavoring. Â the combinations of proteins where just decadent and much appreciated (salmon + scallop, tuna + crab, hamachi + uni, king crab + uni, YUM).Definitely coming back and bringing friends!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',1578,'2017-08-01',4,'Two of our party had the tasting menu and the other two ordered a la carte. Â The food, presentation and service was uniformly wonderful, The hostess on duty was a treasure.The only problem I have with Kai Zan are their policies requiring a $75 credit card deposit which is collected if you dont show up, or if you have a reservation for four and reduce the number of guests to two. Â Equally troublesome is imposing a time limit on the duration of your meal. Â Neither of these turned out to be a problem for us, But why start things off like this? Â Its unnecessarily arrogant and off putting. Â There are many outstanding sushi restaurants in Chicago. Â No shows and table turnover are unfortunately problems for all restaurants, but most establishments dont approach these problems by rapping their guests on the knuckles during the reservation process.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',713,'2016-02-12',5,'You dont come to Kai Zan just to fill your belly, you come to Kai Zan for an experience! This is by far the best Japanese restaurant in the city. Every item on the menu is carefully thought out and then crafted to perfection. Kai Zan is not your ordinary sushi restaurant. Menu items are innovative, unique and with a twist. The quality of the fish is nothing short than perfection and if you sit at the sushi bar you can get a first hand glimpse of magic in the making. The restaurant itself is quaint and cozy perfect for a romantic evening or to celebrate with friends. My husband and I really enjoy sitting at the bar just as much as anywhere else in the restaurant. I really cant say enough good things about Kai Zan. If you are thinking about trying it I would definitely recommend it. Make reservations in advance though, this place fills up quick and once you dine here you will see why.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',829,'2018-10-10',5,'I love everything about the place. The location is cool too since its kind of on the border of where everything ends on Chicago avenue. You wouldnt expect such a great sushi spot in Humboldt park.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',1394,'2018-12-17',4,'The best sushi in Chicago.Hard to locate this spot as its tucked Â away but very cute when you go in.Almost always a line so make sure you have a reservation or go early!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',475,'2021-11-29',5,'Do yourself a favor and reserve a table at the best sushi joint in Chicago. Our favorites Danielle. Orange Rush, Green Monster, Flaming Tuna, & Angry Crab.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',345,'2021-06-17',5,'Third times a charm. After I left a negative, but accurate review for Kai Zans reservation process, someone messaged me from the restaurant and said to come in for a free meal with a friend. I felt slightly odd cashing in on the offer, but took my best friend to see what the hype at Kai Zan was all about. My strongest recommendation is for you, dear reader, to find a way to go. I thought the food was absolutely amazing. My friend and I both decided to go for the Omakase and we were beyond delighted. We were filled to the brim on $50 worth of food (not including tax or tip). Â Highlights were the - Gyu Tongue Kushi- Fiesta Maki- Dynamite Mussels- Oyster shooters- Tofu in brothI cant wait to go back. Making reservation now.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ipsum9843',1461,'2020-08-05',4,'amazing first time experience!i went for my wedding anniversary and our server was justin.quite frankly this was a michelin star like experience. Â we had the omakase!like a prie fix tasting menu for 60. it was awesome. 10 course dinner!red snapper with oil and tobiko carpacciooyster and scallop shooters with quail eggescolar and tuna makia spicy tuna bitedashi soup w tuna and mushrooma salad with garlic polenta and seared tunagrilled shrimp salad with tako yaki and pork belly and peanut sauce and octo w wasabifinished off with dynamite musclesand salmon spicy roll then sashimi were some of the coursesmy only critique is save one of the courses and change it to a desert if the chefs had made a desert finale we would be in heaven!its a lot of food even at 9 coursesamazing tastes and we had such a good time the ambience, service and food was better than i have had at high michelin star placesget the calamari as well!thanks for a great dining experience!',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',1015,'2018-03-18',5,'Absolutely the best sushi in ChicagoCreative, balanced flavors accompany the best quality fish. Â Omakase is a fantastic way to sample best of menu.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu25190',771,'2016-11-13',5,'Love, LOVE, the sushi here... Everything I have tried, I enjoyed immensely. The Green Monster roll and the Orange Rush are absolutely delicious... I do miss the days when it was BYOB... But options for booze, are never a bad thing!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('Ettu14',1723,'2020-05-13',5,'George and I have been eagerly awaiting the opening of Melvin and Carlos Ukraine Village 600 sq feet of their own creation Kai Zan (Its fun figuring out who is the Kai and who is the Zan!) The space is cozy and full of energy! Not only are they talented Chefs but equally talented with carpentry! Ive posted a few of their mouthwatering creations that shows their creativity and their Kai Zan sauce is amazing. Fish is fresh. Homemade Tofu was a delight. Uni was soft and fresh. We usually just let the chefs choice for us (omakase); try their homemade cheese cake! Reservations should be made as it is a small space, BYOB as well! Looking forward to the next visit!',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc61133',744,'2016-04-01',4,'Love the uni here. Always fresh. The uni toro taretare is a must. Escolar pearls are also awesome here. My only complaint is that they recently added a corkage charge without giving notice. I would have opted out the $15 corkage and ordered their providing alcohol instead if i knew.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rhoncus2633',701,'2021-07-22',5,'4.5 starsI have long awaited my visit to Kai Zan! Attempt #1 was foiled by lack of reservations. Lesson learned! Tiny restaurant good for sizes of 2. Also BYOB as well with small corkage fee. Seriously, amazing sushi and BYOB are my two favorite combinations.The tasting menu was legit. This place is the fancy sushi dressed up with creative truffled fireworks. But the simpler seared sashimis were buttery and phenomenal themselves. Beautiful presentation, but slightly rushed service.The tasting menu was so much fun since you get to try SO many different pieces of sushi and they include a lot of the specials. My favorites from the tasting menu were the salmon wrapped tuna and escolar with truffle oil, seared salmon sashimi, and the fatty yellowtail. The sashimi was so buttery and creamy--- it just melted in your mouth in a sushi explosion.My least favorite was the wasabi tako (octopus)-- To be fair, I do despise tako because its often a filler on sashimi platters, but I gave it a chance. Way too much wasabi! Itll clear your sinuses unpleasantly. I also wasnt a fan of the shooter in the beginning-- very vinegary. Overall, a new sushi favorite in Chicago!',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean67124',239,'2017-07-13',5,'I only came once and we did the tasting menu which was such a great deal for the amount of food you got for the price point. Id say only one of the dishes failed (soup was way to fishy) but great presentation, variety and quantity to be well worth another trip.Next time Id try some items not on the tasting menu but if its your first time, its a great way to explore their menu.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit9598',1258,'2017-11-29',4,'Kai Zan lives up to the hype! Â Very fresh sushi, excellent staff and awesome West Town location! Â Omakase Menu is a must',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacinia30117',1009,'2021-02-19',5,'This was great. We came in, sat down, ordered the tasting menu, and was done in about 30 minutes. The food was well prepared, had great presentation, and tasted as good as it was fresh. Only downside (surprisingly) was the speed of the service - it was too fast! I want to enjoy my dining experience, and sometimes time in between courses is actually a good thing. Otherwise, conversations keep getting interrupted by the food, and the experience just isnt the same. At one point, a dish was brought out even before my companion was done with the first dish!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum7621',64,'2018-01-02',5,'Impressive! Â Went specifically for the Omakase and was not disappointed! Â There are 12 generous courses and the fish was fresh and delicious. Â Left the restaurant stuffed, but quite content that I didnt feel gypped of my $60 dinner!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cc110',1684,'2020-08-22',5,'Solid food, great environment and the chefs choice was the way to go. Â I thoroughly enjoyed this spot and with the reasonable pricing, I look forward to going back.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ac67183',1235,'2016-07-01',5,'BEST sushi ever totally legit food definitely going back soon 5 stars',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',1050,'2021-03-17',4,'Amazing. Go with the chefs tasting and sit back and enjoy the most amazing flavors through the various courses.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',209,'2016-12-20',5,'LOVE this place! Â Its small and so make reservations ahead of time, not great for large groups but a perfect date spot!DEF recommend the Omisake chefs multi-course option, everything was amazing! Â My favorites Â Escolar Pearls (I could eat five dishes of these!), Zuke & Creamy Roll! Â Id pass on the fried stuff, just meh. Â Was so full after the meal, a great deal!Try to get a seat at the sushi bar, its so fun talking to Melvin and Carlos, theyre great!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt58127',1533,'2020-08-13',5,'Get the omakase for one and double up on a few key plates for a nominal surcharge. Its a great breadth of superbly done Japanese dishes. Great date place. It took weeks to get a reservation and I had no luck with the pop-in but it turned out to be worth the wait.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',1527,'2021-03-24',4,'This really is as good as sushi gets. Â Every item we received had us wanting our incredibly knowledgeable server to just funnel down our throat. Â I think I even heard someone ask if it would be acceptable to butt funnel oyster shooters if he ran out of room in his stomach. Â Really. Â I think I heard someone say that.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec5093',1694,'2021-01-18',5,'Excellent, everything is very good and fresh. We will go back again, best Japanese restaurant in Chicago. This is a fusion of European method cooking but maintaining the Japanese tradition freshness.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1180,'2016-08-17',5,'This is my favorite sushi place in the city hands down. Â Ive been there about 4 times now and each time has been amazing. Â Ive ordered off the menu as well as tried the Chefs Tasting. Â Id highly recommned the Chefs Tasting. Â You get a lot of food for your money and its all delicious. Â They now serve beer and wine but you can still byob for a corking fee. Â Parking is also very simple and free.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id4362',1361,'2020-05-08',4,'Food is amazing. The presentation is gorgeous, everything is supremely fresh and the staff is very friendly and knowledgeable. Seriously probably some of the best sushi if not the best in the city.Now what lost them one star was the cost of the beer. Granted they do have a $15 BYOB option but we figured we would just have one drink each so it wasnt worth it. Â The beer is not on the drink menu so we were simply told the options and picked from what was told. We did order 2 craft beers and one was a large bottle (the size of a large Saporo if you ever got that) and I expected it to be a bit more than a typical restaurant. When the bill came I was honestly shocked to see that the larger beer came out to $22 and the smaller was $18. Now I realize that this is an upscale place but $40 for 2 beers (no tax or tip) is insane and should at least be listed in the menu to prepare people! Overall conclusion, I will definitely be back for the food but I will not be ordering any alcohol there.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',1419,'2021-07-21',5,'So yummy! Â The escolar pearls are so amazing. Â We loved everything that we had.Im so happy this place opened. Â The hood needed a good sushi restaurant.Its BYOB with a one time $5 corkage fee for the table. Â I think it seats maybe 15 people, so make a reservation. Â Great service, great food. Â Check it out!',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra76180',1154,'2019-02-04',5,'If you have had the Twins food before, You know what you need to know, and are already eating at Kai Zan.If you havent had Carlo and Melvins food yet, you really, really need to go - and soon.The food is always very fresh, and very tasty - and pretty too! Â Everything from the perfectly marinated Zuke Salmon, to the variety of rolls and noodle etc. has been a taste treat that I, and my friends, want to come back and get more of.As others have said, they built the interior out by hand, with some really interesting tricks that you might not notice unless shown... The decor is very neat as well - my favorite thing being the bait bucket lamps. Any way, get to Kai Zan before the seats are too hard to get! Pure awesomeness.Also, they are BYOB, but if you forget your beverages there is a store right across the corner from them - so very easy to get some.*Edit*I dont know why this review was filtered, everything in it is my opinion of the restaurant. Anyway, if you see this, go eat! Youll like it.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',30,'2018-06-26',4,'Everything from the Chefs choice to the Kai zan favorites were fantastic! The angry crab and flaming tuna were my favorite. We ordered the Hotate, Angry Crab, Orange Rush, Beef Tataki, and the Char Siu. The only slightly disappointing thing was the beef....the chunks were big and chewy. They wouldve been better had they been a little more thinly sliced. Overall, we will definitely come back!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',464,'2017-08-07',5,'To begin, our server Justin was amazing. My husband and I are huge sushi feigns so we have basically tried every sushi restaurant in this city, from the totally mediocre to the absolute amazing ones. I have to say, Kai Zan is one of the amazing ones. The place is small, only has about 12 tables so a reservations is definitely recommended unless you want to wait. We arrived for our 545 reservation (I swear were not 95 years old, this is just all that was available) and were promptly seated. They had some very reasonably prices wines, which is definitely not something that you come across often at a good restaurant. We got the DMK rose and it was about $30 if I am not mistaken. The menu was a tad overwhelming so we had Justin do a run-through with us. We ended up doing one of the chefs omakase and then putting in a few additional dishes that we wanted to try -Tako Yaki (4 stars) this is basically fried octopus, and its amazing. A tad spicy, not for the faint of hear, but really delicious. Im not a huge fan of fried dishes, which is the only reason this is not getting 5 stars from me. But if you are, this is a must. -Escolar/Maguro Peals (5 stars) The fish was amazing. And the additional of the truffle oil really only made it better. These are small, like really small. But what it lacks in size, it makes up for in flavor. -Dynamite Mussels (4 stars) These were really great as well. I believe we were only served 2 mussels, so another small portion for the price, but amazing. --Uni/Oyster Shooters (5 stars) These were one of my favorite dishes of the night. If youre a fan of shooters, these are some of the best Ive ever had. The flavors were incredible, and they top them off with a bit of Tabasco, which, being from the South, really sealed the deal for me. -Madai Carpaccio (4 stars) As far as flavor goes, 5 stars, but a tiny tiny portion, so I left feeling a little disappointed in that area. But if my only complaint is that there wasnt enough of it, then were doing okay.-Angry Crab (5 stars) absolutely my favorite dish of the night. Although it was a very small portion, it was incredible. A must order.-Orange Rush (3 stars) this was similar to the angry crab, only this was made with salmon as opposed to tuna. The salmon had a pretty strong fish taste, so this was not my favorite dish, however my husband loved it. Â -Fiesta Maki (4.5 stars) This was one of the two rolls we were served (6 large pieces). It was part of the omakase. To start, I dont even like cilantro in my sushi, but I loved this roll. The combination of the chili oil with the jalapeno was just great and I would definitely order again. If youre looking for a simple, fresh roll, give this a shot. -Flaming Tuna (5 stars) This was SO GOOD (8 smaller pieces). One of my favorite parts of the night. I only wish I had been hungrier, as this was the last dish brought to us. It was on the richer side, so different from the Fiesta, but it was delicious. A must order for me. I think our total bill was about $160, without tip, if Im correct. Possibly a little more than that, but we had a bottle of wine so its a bit fuzzy. All in all, I think this is a good price for the quality of food we received. I would say they could increase their portion size, but other than that I have zero complaints. A great, cozy date night spot that I highly recommend!',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8636',494,'2019-06-16',5,'Theeeee BEST sushi you will eat in Chicago. You see the reviews, it speaks for itself. Staff is super friendly, knowledgable and the sushi is to die for.If i could eat here every week, i would. Now im just trying to find another reason/occasion to go back!!!If youre still reading this.. StopGO. GO RIGHT NOW!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam2176',939,'2018-06-02',4,'A confident team, fun, professional with excellent service and of course the food is exceptional.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',851,'2020-03-21',5,'Went for my parents anniversary dinner and had a wonderful time! The food was excellent as usual. We had the 10 course omokase menu for $60 per person which is packed with great courses full of bold flavors and impeccable presentation. Portion size was just right. Also, they are serving wine, beer, and sake now. We had a nice bottle of champagne. (You can still BYO for a corkage charge of $15 per 2 people.) I love the ambience and environment here - the booths feel like you are in your own private dining room. Service was very good - everyone was friendly and knowledgable. The chef even came out to wish my parents a happy anniversary! I love coming here and feel it is really a neighborhood gem!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',1478,'2020-01-28',5,'This is literally the best place ever. The quality of the food and the attention to detail is insane! Do not pass up the chefs omakase, its a must, and dont forget about dessert!! Everything we ate was absolutely amazing and I cant wait to come back for round 3 ;)',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pharetra2114',288,'2020-12-27',5,'First experience at Kai Zan and its 100% worth the hype!! Get the Omakase... you will not be disappointed.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',46,'2021-08-11',4,'Kai Zan is a magnificent in terms of the quality of their food. However, this past trip, I was very disappointed in the service. We are treated poorly by all the staff -- after asking 3 times, we received a tea cup that we could drink tea out of without burning our hands. We asked for certain dishes with some of the sauces on the side but these requests were ignored. It was a shame since I have had an amazing experience in the past and had raved about it to my guest.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae9127',1343,'2018-06-02',5,'For the food = 5 stars. For the service = 4 starsOne of the regular menu items, the Angry Crab, was fantastic.Also a special item, a just barely grilled hamachi, nigiri style was also great.Apparently they have only recently started bar service, but a nice selection of sake.The waitress said they had beer but really didnt know one from the other, and made no effort to find out, which was one of the few flaws in a really remarkable meal.Most creative sushi I have found. I am not an expert, and we normally ask for soy and wasabi; Â half way through this meal I stopped using it, the food is so well crafted it doesnt need embellishment.We will return soon.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus31129',1453,'2018-09-12',5,'Best sushi in the city! BYOB, cordial staff. Chef Sampler is enough for 2 with the appetizer and is between 60 - 80. Great deal!!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',877,'2020-06-18',4,'Wow!!! The atmosphere is nice and cozy . We ordered the Chefs Choice and it was amazing. My favorite course was oyster / uni shooters . Excellent service ! Cant wait to go back !!!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hendrerit9264',1645,'2018-08-02',5,'Simply put, this is one of the best (if not the best) sushi places in Chicago. Its pricey but worth it. I recommend the chefs choice pre fixe.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',1457,'2019-04-07',5,'The best sushi we have ever had! They are a wonderful family run restaurant. The atmosphere is relaxed and fun. The sushi is simply the best.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ultrices32193',39,'2019-05-02',5,'Amazing fresh food, good service and place! We tried Chefs choice omasake $65. Well be back soon for sure!',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cc110',688,'2017-07-08',5,'This place was amazing. We did the Chefs Choice Omakase ($65) and not even a single dish in the 10-course tasting disappointed. The tasting menu included some new inventive options like seared salmon with scallops or red snapper with truffle oil, as well as the favorite a la carte items like the oyster shooters. Completely 100% worth the money. And the BYOB option is fantastic too! Would love to go back.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes11130',1516,'2021-08-02',4,'Felt fortunate enough to get a prime time Friday reservation and after recommendations was very excited to go. The recommendations were right on. We took the Omakase and was a great selection off the menu. It was also great to sit on the kitchen bar and watch these guys work. The food was awesome, from the escolar to the scallop shooters, to this pepper popper and the sashimi at the end. The only down sides, the place is cramped. Im a big boy but I dont sit on multiple chairs. I was bumped into constantly which got pretty annoying about half way thru the meal. Also, the price... eh... It was good, but was it $60 good? Im not so sure. So its a great experience, go if you can, and if you do, request a booth...Cheers',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu25190',382,'2016-06-19',5,'This place is amazing!! Very creative and so fresh! Â If you are looking for a place to have your typical dragon type rolls, this isnt the place. Â The mussels, angry crab, and orange rush are a few of my favorite things. Â It can get pricey since you want to try everything so I wish they were still BYO. Service is great though and worth the $$ spent.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4430',233,'2018-10-09',5,'We loved Kai Zan. We came in for the early bird special which was a great value for the quality of food served. Service was very warm and friendly, and the meal was perfectly paced. Would absolutely recommend and were looking forward to returning for the full omakase in the future.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',757,'2017-02-11',4,'Love, Love, Love this place!!! Service and food are great. Â If I could eat sushi everyday, I would eat here. But alas, this place is now quite a hike. Â But will definitely be back for special occasions! Def recommend!',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue8191',1582,'2017-11-12',5,'Brilliant food. Really creative bent to sushi. Just the most amazing taste sensations. Dont be put off by front desks attitude on the phone or when you arrive.',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',283,'2020-09-21',5,'Loved my meal here. A friend and I had reservations so we didnt have to wait at all. The servers take care of you as far as taking your order, checking in on you, refilling your water, etc. but if youre sitting at the bar, the cooks just hand the food directly to you. They dont wait until youre finished with your bite or theres a pause in your conversation and you have to grab it with your hands, so it was just a really odd/undesirable part of the experience. But it was minor.I loved everything I ate. Very fresh, simple flavors done right. Order what sounds good to you, but do try at least one sashimi dish. In general everything is priced very fairly/reasonably, and if youre running on a budget, the rolls are a great option.Im sure it will earn 5 stars from me in no time -- Ill definitely be back!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat89150',831,'2020-05-04',4,'So good. Had the chefs choice menu last night and enjoyed everything I ate. Â Definitely should be on everyones list and worth making a reservation in advance. Staff was nice and not pretentious at all for someone who had little japanese/sushi ordering experience. Fried oysters, some type of mussel/quail egg shooter (i think), angry crab were just some of the items on the chefs choice menu that stood out. if you go the chefs choice route, definitely do not snack beforehand. was left feeling very full but was worth it.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',1001,'2016-05-20',5,'We picked this place based on a high review online. But I honestly dont know what the hypes are about. First of all, they dont have any high chairs or booster seats, that means kids are not welcome. I understand that if they are an high end restaurant. But they are not. In fact, the way they design this place never considered having kids to dine in. Â None of the table can really accommodate high chairs or booster seats. Food is really mediocre. Â Theres nothing special about any of the sushi or maki. Actually one of the maki we ordered had no flavor. Same goes with the charbroiled skewers. Menu has very limited selections. We dont know what else to order so we stopped after we had some maki rolls and few pieces of fish. The waitress gave us a dirty look after I told her we are not going to order more. I normally dont like to write review on restaurants. I think that if the place is bad then Ill just never go back again. But this place annoyed me so much that I just had to write a review. Our experience was just awful, from the first minute we walked in until we walked out. We will never go back.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',168,'2016-12-12',5,'I will always come back here. It was my second time at Kai Zan. As usual, the service was impeccable. Every staff was incredibly friendly and knowledgable in their foods. The dishes were incredible and I was very happy. My stomach was happy. What more is there to ask for? )',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit9598',531,'2021-09-08',5,'Excellent meal. Order the omakase tasting menu and promptly received a steady stream of well prepared sushi/fusion courses. By the 4th course we were sort of dizzy with excitement and anticipation. We were seated at the bar and in true Japanese tradition, it was cozy and occasionally kitchen-like in atmosphere. Thankfully, the service and food was similarly focused on quality. The fish was fresh for being in the midwest. There was a nice selection of shellfish too, so the omakase menu really took us through a variety of flavors and textures.Where to begin? The pork belly with rapini was delectable. I wanted more. A lot more. The grilled smelt (nicely paired with a mushroom dashi) was that hit of fishiness that I love. You gotta eat the whole thing thing, head to tail. The red snapper with basil and olive oil was a great shout out to italian raw preparation. The truffle tuna nigiri was a subtle use of a luxury (and overpowering) ingredient. Lastly, uni shooter. Yeah, oyster shooter too but uni is my sushi kryptonite. The only time I used the soy sauce was with the maki and sashimi courses, which tells you something about how well seasoned each plate was. In fact, I could go on and describe every course mouth-watering detail but Id like to end this review sometime in 2013. Maybe I couldve loved this more if we had unagi and mackerel (aka my other sushi kryptonites) but thats just me reaching for something negative to say. On the whole I was deeply impressed and satisfied with my meal. And so was my date.At one point, the tea kettle they were serving from broke and tea spilled all over the place. The staff couldnt have been nicer. Several members came up to see if we were okay. Everything landed on the table. No big whoop. They even offered to replace a possibly ruined plate. It wasnt. It was delicious. But it was very indicative of how they dealt with an emergency situation, which was with total professionalism. It made what was our holiday night out, special in an unexpected way. There are a lot of great sushi restaurants on Chicago Av. Kai Zan doesnt have to worry about them. Highly recommended.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',523,'2020-12-19',5,'Not only a amazing Japanese spot, Id argue as one of the top 3 restaurants in Chicagoland. This intimate spot on west chicago is very meticulous about every dish that leaves the kitchen. Im actually proud to bring guests and friends here. Its one of those places that you can let the server just order for you, and I dont usually do this at all. People are catching on to how special this place is, which makes same day reservations nearly impossible. My advice is to order as much as you can sample, so that you know what to order more of. Id recommend the orange rush, dynamite mussels, and the oyster shooter, just to name a few. If youre a fan of saki, theyd be happy to let you sample whatever ones youd like. Id also recommend the Demon Slayer for a higher quality saki at a reasonable price. Enjoy )',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede63105',1637,'2018-07-09',5,'Great food, but upsell from waiter was way too long. Tried to push tasting menu ($65 per person), and only gave a la carte sushi menus when we asked.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',556,'2019-10-19',4,'Sushi was really good but the other menu items were average. We tried the edamame, potatoes, mussels, pork, shrimp, chicken and steak as well. Â Of those, I would only go back for the pork.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc22',1207,'2018-12-28',5,'The chefs playground omakase was a great selection. The service was attentive and food fresh, inspired and absolutely delicious.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis14141',262,'2018-06-27',5,'I refrained from reviewing Kai Zan for two years because I already have to wait long enough for reservations. Sadly Check Please and Zagat have done much more to add to that wait than my lowly review ever could. First let me say that this has to be the most friendly, unpretentious and approchable sushi/Japaneese restaurant in the city. Every time I eat here the staff is so friendly and helpful. You can genuinely tell that they all love to work there and want to share their restaurant with you. If you have never eaten here or are unfamiliar with what to order, I reccomend splurging and going for the omokase tasting menu. Try sitting at the bar so you can watch chef brothers Melvin and Carlo prepare the plates. It is truly an experience to watch and converse with these two artesians as they craft some of the best seafood plates available in the city. If you wish to order from the menu instead, I would say its hard to go wrong with any of the fresh seafood choices, although I would implore you not to miss the escolar pearls. Enjoy Kai Zan, but try not to tell too many people, or you will be waiting outside on Chicago Avenue with me.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('augue90110',1261,'2016-02-12',4,'Excellent in every way. The sushi was very fresh, service was impeccable, and the space has a great vibe.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum5887',1256,'2021-01-11',5,'The sushi was great but the service was not. Â  They were pushing us out as soon as we got there. Â They kept telling us that we had to leave by 815pm and we had a reservation at 630pm. So basically they dont give you an option to take more than 1 hour and 45 min. Â  We asked to do the chefs tasting but the waiter advised us that there wasnt enough time. Â On top of rushing us the waiter spoke very slowly and as if we had never eaten sushi before. Â If they were in such a hurry to rush us out then the waiter should have been more prompt and not talk so slow. Â When going out with friends an hour and 45 min is not enough time and would likely not return here.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',1546,'2019-03-31',5,'I too am reluctant to write this review, but this is the restaurant that made me finally write a review. My wife and I went here for my Birthday. We sat at the bar and ordered the Omikase. Everything was fantastic. Each course was better than the last and Im usually wary of inventive sushi as it brings to mind the kitchen sink rolls served all over, but everything was so balanced and delicious. The fish was fresh and took a front seat. The chefs/owners and the staff were very attentive and seemed to really enjoy being there and watching us swoon with every bite. I would love to eat here every week if I could afford it (Im back in school). Although it is very reasonably priced considering the quality, and the byob makes affordable for those increasingly rarer nights out.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum5887',24,'2016-08-01',4,'Kai Zan has amazing food and service. Â Make your reservation early and come ready to enjoy the experience!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',539,'2017-02-08',5,'its in a very strange neighborhood for the kinda pricey place that it is. Â however, the omakase menu was so much fun (AND SO FILLING). Â we went for the omakase with all their greatest hits and enjoyed almost all of the dishes. Â *favorites Â uni and oyster shooters! Â *make reservations!',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',34,'2016-08-06',5,'Exquisite. Im not sure there are many other words that describe my experience here. We had the chefs special which we were so happy to do. Not only is it a ton of food, it gives such a variety of sushi and sushimi that I would have never tried any other way. The ambiance is beautiful and the staff is super friendly and helpful. Pretty much the most amazing sushi experience Ive had in Chicago. Must try people!',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',1720,'2021-01-04',5,'You can be a purist, or you can embrace change. Â Theres a lot of places that take traditional sushi and other Japanese cuisine and put a modern spin on it, but theres few that pull it off as well as Kai Zan, a nice spot in West Town that flies a bit under the radar because of its location. Places like Japonais and Roka Akor get more buzz because of the chic decor and the River North location, but Kai Zan offers up similar food at similar quality, but at a slightly lower price point. Â Add in that its BYOB and you can see why it gets the Yelp cred that it gets. Â We were able to score a same night reservation around 7pm. Â It sounds like they keep to a pretty tight schedule as we were informed we had a little over an hour to eat when we sat down. Â That put us off a little right off the bat, but ultimately after that, they never really pushed the issue and we ate without feeling rushed or pressed.The menu is split into cold and hot appetizers, sushi and rolls, and a few choice robata style entrees, along with a nice selection of seasonal specials. Â We got a pretty wide mix of everything, although we were tempted to just go with one of the omakase choices (next time!)We started with the angry crab roll and medium-thin sliced piece of maguro wrapped around a ball of fresh lump crab meat mixed with a spicy mayo and topped with pankos. Â A solid mix and a good way to start the meal. Â The tuna was more meaty and tender than fatty and melded nicely with the crab.As someone whos always on the lookout for good fried chicken, karaage is tough to pass up. Â While good, the karaage was one of the more forgettable dishes of the meal. Â A bit salty on the batter and a bit overcooked.The hamachi kama, taken from the neck/collar of the yellowtail, was the highlight of the meal. Â The grilled char gave the cooked fish a nice smokey flavor and the fish itself had a nice meaty texture. Â Cooked yellowtail is quite different from the raw hamachi most of us are used to and has a very fishy flavor, almost like mackerel. Â The portion size was very generous for the price. Â These apparently are in somewhat limited supply so if its in stock, I highly recommend grabbing one.Next up is the takoyaki - the skewer comes topped with just a touch of wasabi mayo, bonito flakes. Â These little fried octopus balls were solid and the bonito flakes, the wasabi mayo, and the touch of teriyaki gave it a nice mix of sweet, salty, and spicy.Feeling like we had to sample a few things from every portion of the menu, we next ordered a few pieces from the grill. First, Â the slightly fatty cut of pork belly, served with a small side of kimchi, and the second, a large prawn,which was just a bit undercooked but massive in size.To finish the meal off, we moved on to the raw fish portion of the meal. Â The salmon was superbly fresh and well cut to a nice thickness, and the escolar simlarly so, although it lacked a bit of the usual crisp, moist bite that bursts when you bite into it. Â We ended with a pair of raw ama ebi shrimps - fresh and sweet and followed by the meatiest, most flavorful shrimp heads Ive ever had. Â These almost made the meal in itself.Thankfully, the meal didnt necessarily need the extra support from the shrimp heads. Â Even before that, there was a number of dishes that put this meal into the upper echelon of Japanese meals Ive had in Chicago. Â Id put the sushi just a step down from Katsu, but still better than 95% of the joints in Chicago. Â And we cant wait to go back.Pics and more up at',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',640,'2019-02-15',5,'The restaurant itself is very beautiful inside. They seated us 15 minutes early. We got the omakase and a couple of drinks. Despite being a tasting menu the portions were generous. Its expensive, but not inappropriately so. You pay a good amount, but get some excellent stuff.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum23143',1163,'2020-08-19',5,'I have been to Kai Zan twice now and I am a big fan. The service is excellent, the ambiance is quaint and cozy. For our second visit we opted for the chefs tasting menu, it was wonderful. Each dish was inventive and aesthetically pleasing. It also didnt taste half bad! Their sashimi is so fresh and tasty, the smokey mussels are amazing and angry crab roll is to die for. There were a few misses, which included a little tuna salad cup that was just okay but overall it was a great meal. Also the value for 11 courses cant be beat, $60 bucks for a ton of seafood. Ill go back soon and probably stick to the dishes that shined during the chefs tasting.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat89150',782,'2018-07-14',4,'What can I say.... My girlfriend and I were looking to get sushi yesterday and the usual place was closed. I remembered driving past Kai Zan on my way home a few times (We are right up the street) and I always wanted to check it out. I called at about 330 to make a reservation Â and showed up later that evening with a bottle of wine in tow. First and foremost... I would suggest making a reservation as this place only seats a handful of guests. Once that hurdle is passed, prepare yourself for some of the best sushi in Chicago. We were greeted by a very friendly wait staff who knew the menu (small) very well. Our waitress had a few suggestions that we tried as well as other things that looked appealing to us. The chef gave us a complimentary appetizer that was to die for. Fatty tuna with truffle oil. Can you go wrong??? The food was OUTSTANDING, the chefs are great, the waitstaff is stellar, and the prices are unbeatable. Our bill was $63 with a corking fee and we left stuffed. We have found our new sushi staple. Thanks Kai Zan!!!',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',368,'2019-04-19',4,'We showed up a little before 8pm on a Monday night and were told we couldnt be seated until 830 - 845. We ended getting sat around 820 in a nice booth by the window.Our server was lovely and all the specials sounded amazing. We couldnt decide between everything and ended up doing the Omakase menu. 12 courses, but it really felt like 20 with all the different little bites. AMAZING!! Everything was delicious and well portioned so at the end we still had room for dessert. I had the chocolate lava cake and it was super soft and moist with great chocolatey flavor. Hands down fantastic service, food, and atmosphere.When we left, I texted all my sushi enthusiast friends and told them they MUST try it.The tasting menu was great because we tried many different things at a great price. Considering how much sushi I like to eat, I definitely would have spent that much, or more a la carte, and gotten less food for it.DELICIOUS! Great job, Kai Zan.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('hina115',491,'2019-01-22',5,'Both of our birthday dinners were had here. It is that phenomenal. There is no where with the quality fish that Kai Zan has in all of Chicago. And Ive been everywhere. The agedashi tofu, the pearls, the uni shooters. Anything you get, I believe, will be superb. Even the less exciting items salmon avocado roll - still leaves you never wanting to go anywhere else. No longer BYOB, but we wont complain too much. Your sushi dreams come true.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',1131,'2020-02-06',3,'Im afraid to say how much I like this place bc then more people will go and I wont be able to get a table! Haha. First things first- its byob so dont forget to bring yo own booze. In fact there is a really great liquor store right across the street we go there every time we go. The consistency is what I appreciate most about this place. Weve gone and had the omekase every time and every time I have to unbutton my pants bc Im full but a satisfied full with a big smile on my face! Â  Cant wait to go back!!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',1098,'2021-03-09',5,'Full disclosure that I know someone on the staff here and this might have made service extra special, but everything at Kai Zan was great. Our party of three had the omakase menu which was just fantastic. It started us off with a few small bites that made our appetite beg for more. The scallop and uni shooters were great. The rolls were fantastic. Each cut of tuna, otoro or lean cut were fantastic. We were also treated to the seared waygu beef over rice, which was unreal. It was my first time having it and it just melts in your mouth. The omakase finished with a few choice cuts of sashimi which were wonderful and a great end to the meal. We were stuffed at the end but able to walk it off and head home. The service was really spectacular and everyone was so nice and accommodating to us. The staff was also very knowledgeable about the ingredients and preparations and answered all our questions. This place is a gem in Chicago!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo41119',330,'2017-12-12',5,'Yummy! Â Came here for a girls night and we all left very happy! Â Everything we ordered was very good. We had 5 ppl in our group and they were able to adjust some orders that had 4 pieces to 5 pieces. Â The only downside was that their drink list only consisted of sake and wine. Â Will def come again to check out their omakase chefs choice! Â Street parking was also easy on a Friday night.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id3571',889,'2019-07-22',4,'Second time there. We ordered the premium omakase. It costs more than the regular one. But every bite is worthy it. Try that one for sure.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisi29157',1541,'2021-01-09',5,'Kai Zan never disappoints. Best quality fish in Chicago by far!',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut1923',822,'2018-07-23',5,'A lovely, if tiny, BYOB sushi place. Â  The sushi is fresh, unique, and creative. Â  The staff is very attentive. Â And the prices are reasonable.Nice decor too - the bar is fun (as it should be at sushi places). Â  And the booths that line the opposite wall looked cozy and cute - could be a great date place!We went with a group and sat at the bar. Â  Everything we ordered from the menu (regular and specials) were lovely. Â  From their non-sushi menu, I recommend the bacon-wrapped mushrooms. Â We ended the night with a couple of chefs choice rolls, and they were some of the best we had that night. Â So definitely cozy up to the chefs if you can!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',141,'2016-12-16',4,'We have been trying to dine here for a while and finally got in on a Friday early evening. Place is small, but super cozy. We grabbed a bottle of wine just down the street and brought it in for a $5 corking fee. As recommended by our server, first timers, we went with their tasting menu. This created a very unique experience that we both enjoyed. We tried things we wouldve never thought of ordering. Â Surprisingly, I liked the uni shooter, although I had to talk myself into trying it for the first time. The sashimi was out of this world, especially the white tuna and the portions were just right. Service was excellent, though we did feel a little rushed to finish some dishes so the next one can come out, but I guess it makes sense since they need to keep a certain pace. We walked out of there very satisfied and looking forward to going back.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',1650,'2021-08-27',5,'Mother of Pearl!!! Â This is worth every bit of time it takes to get a reservation and get in. Â These are very very bad men. Â Like bad in the MJ (both Jackson & Jordan) sense of the phrase.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',1490,'2019-03-27',5,'I really like this place and am glad its come to my corner of the UKV! Ive been about 4-5 times already. Escolar Pearls were delicious, I always order the jalapeno poppers, and have not been disappointed with any of the rolls. You can clearly tell that the ingredients are fresh and of the highest quality. Â The only food items I werent so jazzed about were the okra & tofu (but Im not a huge fan of okra) and the green tea ice cream. The $5 corkage fee isnt my favorite, but it still saves some $ to BYOB. The service is really warm and quick. Ill be back here and hope I can get a table- once people find out how good the place is, it is going to be consistently mobbed!',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc8538',1239,'2019-04-04',4,'This place is like a magical dream. Â The plush, darkened wood, the womb-like intimacy, the cloudy haze of the first sip of hot sake. Everything is top-notch, from the solicitous staff to the tasty takoyaki. Â We both got the Omakase, me n the special lady, as per the recommendation of previous yelp reviewers. Â Neither she nor I consume land animals, so the waiter enthusiastically offered to replace the one beef dish in the ten-dish omakase with scallops. Â The food was cartoonishly perfect, so fresh it practically melted away in my mouth. Â I had a vision of myself as a grazing shark-- this must be what its like, I thought, not to have to use a jaw. Â People, you need not the heavy artillery of psychedelic mushrooms or huffing paint to get this high, when the potent drugs of fresh fish and hot sake await you down the low-lit halls of Kai Zan. Â This is the kind of place that makes you think, damn, weve made it as a human species. Â Were at the top. Â All evolution beyond this point must be downhill.',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu25190',655,'2016-07-14',5,'Best sushi experience I have had in Chicago. Amazing service. Melvin and Carlo are sushi gods. Melvin heard I liked uni and hooked me up on one of the rolls too! Went for my birthday and I will be back without a doubt. One of my first Yelp reviews - it was that good.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo41119',1520,'2021-11-12',5,'Had the Omakase...it was incredible, and an amazing deal to boot. Dont forget its BYOB!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',906,'2020-07-17',5,'Best Sushi ever. This place is amazing. Try both the pearls, angry crab and orange rush. Make a reservation. Enough said!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl43160',2,'2017-04-29',5,'This is hands down the best sushi I have had in Chicago. Whether going out with friends or on a nice dinner this is a great experience. The service was amazing and couldnt think for anything that they would be able to improve on. Also get the chefs choice, its everything and more.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis2682',1040,'2021-09-21',4,'This place is amazing! Sat at the sushi bar which I highly recommend. One of the Chef owners was giving us lots of special dishes and recommendations. Everything was fast, fresh and delicious. There is such a unique and delicious blend of flavors that you never need soy sauce or any other condiment other than what they present to you. So amazingly good.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mone116',55,'2021-07-18',5,'Absolutely outstanding experience. The servings were creative and extremely tasteful. The courses were also paced extremely well and the service was great. Highly recommend Kai Zan and planning a return visit',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',1274,'2018-02-05',5,'Omakase - Omygoshe. Â We sat at the bar and this place was great, staff was helpful. Â Cant wait to head back.',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',1714,'2017-02-05',4,'Everything was delicious. I wont go through all the choices because thats been done as nauseam; just get the omakase and absolutely everything will be fantastic. It cost $65 but was more food than I could eat, and my fiancÃ© and I both felt like the value was good for what we got. Weve been to Katsu, Momotaro, Juno, and a really terrific Michelin starred sushi place in Tokyo, and Kai Zan was a different sort of experience (more creative, unusual dishes than we are used to) but no less wonderful. We just went tonight and Im already excited to go back soon.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',1238,'2018-10-12',5,'Unique and unbelievable sushi! Everything made with elegance and care with flavors and textures that pop in your mouth! The escolar pearls and scallop nigiri were my favorite! Excellent service and once you have a first round if you tell the waiter what you like they will suggest things that are off the menu and lushish as well! Very small and intimate space. While reservations are not required, unless you want to eat at 430 or 10pm on the weekend, they are highly recommended!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',412,'2018-11-19',5,'Amazing little restaurant that transports you out of the city into a private top notch dining experience. Â Friendly, knowledgeable staff and unreal Omakase. Â We were celebrating our sons 23 birthday and opted for the Premium Omakase experience, a 12 course tasting that blew our minds. Â  Delicate layers of flavor, umami , stunning presentations, not one disappointing dish. Â  Â The omakase menus are pricier, but the regular dishes are quite reasonable. Â  Worth every penny and well worth the trip!',20);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',1159,'2021-09-14',4,'Super fresh and delicious! Some tasty morsels the Unagi Poppers, Maguro Pearls, and the Mango Pudding dessert. BYOB and $5 corkage fee. Will be back.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',938,'2019-04-22',5,'Excellent sushi! Â Super fast and attentive wait staff. Â Ran into heavy traffic and were late by 45 minutes which they had no problem accommodating. Â Had to rush to make a concert and they pushed the food out quickly and we made the showtime with no problem.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',1158,'2017-06-13',5,'I just have to write this review . Its one of the best dining experience weve had in Chicago. We like this better than L20 and that was when they initially got the three Michelin stars. The fish was so fresh and the preparation was so innovative and amazing.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',279,'2017-11-17',5,'I feel bad about this review because we met one of the young owner/chefs at the end of our meal and he seemed like a great guy who probably really knows what he is doing as a chef but it seems clear that what Kai Zan is lacking is a business manager. Â Our visit was for a birthday and thank God it was not the actual day of birthday meal but just part of the birthday weekend. Â To start, they need to get much better organized with reservation confirmation. Â I was contacted three times by seemingly three different systems to confirm my reservation Â by phone (by a rather surly woman) the day before, by email the morning of, and by text about two hours before the meal (so, not a fan of seatme.com which I assume is a cheaper alternative to OpenTable). Â Asking me to confirm my reservation three times is completely ridiculous.The surly problem continued upon our arrival. Â We were unfortunately stuck with a young, brooding fellow who was just about the most uncommunicative and seemingly unhappy person to be waiting tables that we have ever encountered (and we eat out a LOT). Â We could barely understand what he was saying because he spoke so quietly (when he spoke at all) and we felt like we were putting him out with our every request...like keeping our water glasses full. Â He really set the tone for the entire meal and may have single-handedly helped to color our experience to be as bad as it seemed. Â He was either really having a bad day or should consider some other occupation...for sure the restaurants management should help him with this revelation either way.This problem of keeping our water glasses full leads me to our next problem. Â Why is it in this great food city of ours that so many new restaurants these days think that it is cool to be BYOB. Â It is not cool...it may be trendy...but what it really is Â cheap! Â OK the fact that we showed up without the sake bottles that we had in the hotel room was my fault. Â I missed that it was BYOB. Â So, this is truly mea culpa. Â However, I really do not want to have to remember whether I need to bring my own sake or not...and sushi simply is not the same without sake. Â But, beware, because it is worse than that. Â They have almost nothing to drink! Â We were told after we were seated that we could walk across the street and buy soft drinks if we wanted (because the store still looking like it was open). Â It is pretty much either green tea (apparently only hot, not cold) or water...and getting our waiter to keep either in our cups was difficult. Â I am sorry but if you are not going to do me the favor of having a liquor license, at least have more than water and hot tea to drink!We moved ahead with the hot tea and water and tried to be open minded about the food. Â We decided to try some of the fish (as sashimi) and still do the omakase (yes, we are pigs). Â While we do enjoy rolls, we gauge sushi restaurants by the fish in sashimi form Â every fish has a unique flavor and you should be able to taste them. Â For what our opinion is worth, the fish was reasonably good. Â However, the selection was not impressive and they were out of some of those!The omakase experience that followed again demonstrated how much Kai Zan lacks, more than anything, an experienced restaurant manager. Â We were absolutely inundated with a rapid fire arrival of course after course. Â We were not alone in this complaint Â we heard at least a dozen complaints about the service coming way too fast from numerous other tables being relayed to the kitchen by the staff. Â In short, everybody was being buried under courses and nobody was enjoying it. Â And then the service stopped...all service. Â For about 10 minutes we sat there with no food, no drink, no attention. Â Eventually the service did restart but, still, with no attention to our pace. Â Later, I was told that this was on purpose.Overall, the food was almost as good and creative as Chicago Magazine ranted when they placed Kai Zan number five on the list of new restaurants for this year. Â  However, some dishes did not work Â one was somehow transformed into having a bologna-like taste!All in all, there is hope for Kai Zan because I think the chef(s) is (are) actually talented and knowledgeable. Â However, to have rated this place number five on the best new list either colors the new restaurants in our city as really bad this year or leads us to think that maybe we should seek other sources than Chicago Magazine for our recommendations! Â As much as I attempt to try everything at least twice, it will be hard to go back to Kai Zan. Â The one real positive, I guess, is that the price is pretty reasonable so we could still afford to have a more satisfying sushi experience the next night.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mollis81165',1654,'2021-09-30',4,'Great sushi. Fresh fish. Unbelievable service. Our servers name was Erin and she was such a delight to have serving us. I recommend this restaurant to anyone that loves a delicious sushi meal. The chefs menu was the best! Thanks!',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tristique8035',277,'2021-01-23',5,'I am still impressed with the quality of the food they serve here. I am in love with the Green Monster roll, Uni, angry crab, and anything they serve. The thought of this place still makes my mouth water.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1259,'2018-12-18',5,'The food is good but I highly doubt the wait is worth it. Especially the 45 minutes wait even with a reservation is definitely a turn down. I like Sunda better compare to this place.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',1056,'2016-08-02',4,'The best sushi in Chicago is here. I havent been obsessed with sushi since ever. These brothers are doing mind boggling combinations that are not normally found in sushi spots around the city or even nation. The wine list here is killer. Everything about this place is insane. From the wood work, to the pickled horse radish, to the expertly paired bottles of soy sauce.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ullamcorper075',1656,'2020-03-26',5,'We went back for the omakase for our anniversary and it was mind-blowing! Â We have been to Alinea, and this was actually more enjoyable! Â You will be stuffed, so dont go crazy on the beginning courses, because they just keep coming and coming. Â Delicious, fresh, innovative sushi. Â Our favorite sushi restaurant in the city!',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',1501,'2018-04-29',5,'Wow. This is the type of restaurant that will ruin other restaurants for you. Â It was seriously life-changing.Its true, the escolar pearls and orange rush were really good.. however for both myself and my boyfriend, the ultimate star was their mussels appetizer. Im not sure if its on their menu year-round but if you see it, try it!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a83185',296,'2019-11-28',5,'Did the chefs choice-absolutely amazing. Every single dish was spot on. Â Incredibly tiny spot, which isnt a negative, just an FYI. The courses came too fast, as they want you out in an hour and a half. At one point we had 3 in front of us. Totally worth it though. Best sushi in the city.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',493,'2018-10-18',5,'Service=2 starsFood=5 starsI had no trouble making the reservation. However, the girl that works up front is very inexperienced and somewhat rude. We were originally seated Â at the sushi bar, towards the back of the restaurant. When I realized how uncomfortable that seat was, because everyone that walked pass me, bumps into me; so I asked for a table instead. Because a table was not available, she got flustered. She then proceed to tell me that there is a 1.5hr Â limit per table and that Â we will need to give up the table according to our 630 reservation. Umm, okay? So, basically they are limiting to how much I want to order? I understand that this a small establishment and they want to turn tables around faster than usual, but I didnt feel like there is a need to announce that their customers. Â As we were standing, waiting for a table to be free; she asked if we wanted to order appetizers. Um...excuse me, would you like for us to stand here and eat? Â When we were finished with everything, they asked if they can bring the check. Ummm..can I order dessert please? By this time, we were WAY over our 1.5hr limit. So I know they wanted us out. Â When we were waiting for our dessert, the girl up front came by and asked if were ready for the check. Â I was slightly annoyed by now. Over all, Â The food at Kai Zan is a must! Our waiter was super helpful, and recommended a lot of good dishes. The Chef also came by twice to see how everything is. Â I would absolutely return to to Kai Zan! I wish they would train their staff better. We hadEscolar pearlMaguro pearlZuki ( It was a little fishy)Green monster roll( rolled in avocado instead of seaweed)Toro Tartar- A MUST try! The concept and presentation is unique, and mouth watering. Orange Rush( Must try)Uni nigri-(very fresh)Salmon nigriAngry crab handroll. Fried Oysters',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit3622',1487,'2017-12-11',4,'Superb restaurant. Reserved a booth for the family. Unique atmosphere. My family commented on the unique lights overhead. I recommend the calamari and any of the sushi. Had complimentary appetizers due to our multiple orders of sushi. Amazing experience. If I had time, Id try the omakase menu. Come early to search for street parking.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a22154',251,'2020-08-12',5,'My wife and I have been to all the sushi places in the city and Kai Zan is hands down amazing! Hip area, beautiful space and an outstanding dinner! Will be back many more times and this us a must try!',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',639,'2021-05-17',5,'Well the secret is out so I might as well write my review. Â Hands down my favorite sushi place ever which I would give 6 stars (sorry Nobu and Toro, but 5 stars is not bad). Â Some places just stand out above the rest and Yelp does not have enough stars to properly differentiate the top of the pack from the rest of the pack. Â I did remove some additional hype from this first paragraph so I dont have to make reservations months ahead some day.I dont know where to begin, so Ill will start with the Omakase. Â Got that the first time, $60 a person, and it was a great deal with great quality food. Â I wont go into details, but if youre a first timer, Just Do It. Â Second time I went, I ordered more basic nigiri and maki + a few specialty items and everything was fresh and tasty as I expected. Â Next time I go, I am going to order on the warmer side of the menu. Â The truth is, you cannot make a mistake ordering at this place because everything is excellent.The waiter service has been top notch both times. Â When you do make reservations, you do need to confirm them I believe. Â You will usually get a call for confirmation the day before, and if not confirmed, a text message the day of your reservation to confirm.Luckily, it is in Humboldt Park rather than Lincoln Park, Lakeview, or Downtown, so making reservations in advance is not too ridiculous since it is a part of the city a lot of people (especially tourists) either dont know about or avoid.Lastly, its places like Kai Zan that make me feel spoiled to live in Chicago and have access to this caliber of cuisine.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis14141',870,'2016-06-20',4,'Probably one of the better places to get fresh uni. Â The other sushi/sashimi is also pretty good. Â Byob which is nice. Â Only drawback is that it is very expensive. Â $7 for one piece of uni makes it difficult to frequent. Â But, money aside, its a great place.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',1403,'2020-05-30',5,'Amazing sushi! I have to say the best Ive ever had! My husband took me here for my birthday. They were very accommodating with the fact that I had just broke my ankle the day before, so they put us in a booth too keep my foot out of the way. Everyone one was super friendly, sushi was so fresh. Amazing different combinations that Ive never had. Would highly recommend the Pearls...amazing and the eel poppers but everything was wonderful! For dessert I had lava cake with sesame seed ice cream with was sooo good! Definitely will be back soon! With my comment on Good for Kids I put that Im not sure even thou my 8 year was with us. My daughter is so use to going out for sushi and tapas. She use to it taking awhile and there is always the ipad...lol. So if they cant sit still I wouldnt recommend it.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit96122',538,'2016-11-04',5,'Smart girlfriend suggested Kai Zan for dinner. Â As a restaurant manager and former oyster shucker, I have high sensitivity to how a restaurant smells and how the flow of the room translates into vibrations Â Kai Zan was the most impressive restaurant Ive been to all year for these attributes. Â Stepping off far West Chicago Ave, the open kitchen, four person partitioned wooden booths, two person grey banqueted booths, exposed wood, concrete and sunlight. Â It smelled incredibly clean and inviting. Â The server was polite and deferential and greeted us with warm hand towels. Â The omikase started with shooters of briny, rich oyster, raw scallop and quail egg we were instructed to break the tiny yolk to make it easy to swallow. Â We had a steaming soup of mushroom and sesame with skewered tuna, the only miss. Â This was followed by smelts, grilled to perfection and wholly edible. Â Smelts are one of the best lake fish the rule of thumb is what grows big faster is better because it has less time to absorb pollution. Â We had raw crab, octopus, tuna, fried freshwater eel from China, superfresh yellowtail sashimi, grilled mussels, and resounding salmon belly. Â Girlfriend said it was the best fish shes eaten in Chicago, and the best Japanese restaurant in the city. Â I listen to her because shes good. Â Kai Zan with good energy, delicious smells, amazing mouth-watering chefs tasting, and sparkling clean washroom called the Necessary Room is good too.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('platea7440',1011,'2021-07-10',4,'This is one of my favorite japanese restaurants in chicago. Â Ive been wanting to go here for a year and we decided to go last weekend. Â It did not disappoint. Â The food here is inventive and delicious. Â They have the regular rolls but their specials/signature are what is to die for. Â I would suggest skipping your usual rolls that you can get in any Sushi place, get their signature dishes. Â The menu online is not representative of what is in the restaurant its missing some items Some of my favorites areOrange Rush we had some hamachi/salmon saladrolls without rice fish and cucumber, sashimi, the fish melts in your mouth, i would skip this next time as I can get this anywhere. I cant remember the rest, everything was really good.They expanded their space so they can hold up to 50 or 60 now. Â I like the intimate setting and the fact that its not so loud that you can talk normally. Â  The only complaint I have is that the AC was dripping due to condensation, they need to get this fixed. Â This didnt affect my experience in this place. Â Our server was also great with his ecclectic hair style. Â Parking is also easy in this neighborhood. Â Make a reservation in advance, they are always packed',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut35181',1169,'2021-09-15',5,'This is our second time at KaiZan and I have to say that they exceeded our expectations again. Great service, very fresh fish, perfect mixture of flavor. Defiantly a must visit place. Presentation is out of this world as well Â .',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit9598',995,'2017-10-10',5,'Amazing! Â Celebrated our 22nd anniversary here and it couldnt have been better. We had the new omakase-yum! Â We also had the best seats in the house-at the bar where we could see the chefs in action. Cant wait to go back!',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nibh7765',916,'2021-07-07',4,'Oh Kai Zan, hands down you are the BEST SUSHI/Sashimi restaurant in ALL of Chicago! Â I would recommend ordering the OMAKaSA and Im certain that your taste buds will thank you afterwards.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempor6567',857,'2020-01-16',5,'I have thoroughly enjoyed Kai Zan every visit, but my last experience really pushed the envelope. Heading into dinner tonight, I already knew Chef Melvin would not disappoint on savory cuisine (I consider the staff flavor engineers, and just thinking about dining here elicits a Pavlovian response...I think I could live on Maguro Pearls alone!). What really made the experience memorable tonight was the staffs more-than-accommodating service.I originally had a reservation for 4 for a birthday dinner. Last minute, 2 additional guests wanted to join. I called, spoke to the hostess, and she offered to attempt to move other groups around to accommodate my request, but I declined, feeling it was too much trouble. Not 10 minutes later, the hostess called back to let me know she found a way to make it work. The thoughtfulness, service, and consideration of reaching back out to me is a welcome rarity.Our group fanatically devoured a vast array of delicious samplings, and we were not rushed out the door, even though we had a late dinner time (we in fact closed the place down). Thank you, Kai Zan for making my birthday not only scrumptious, but granting a birthday girl and her friends the freedom to thoroughly enjoy!',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',840,'2021-10-01',5,'I am a huge fan of sushi and so when my foodie friend told me about Kai Zan and showed me the delectable pictures of uni nigiri I immediately made room in my schedule and prepared myself for lots of uni.But then we got there and could NOT find parking for the longest time. It was terrible---we ended up being 15 minutes late and they told us that we only had an hour and 15 minutes left to eat and so we better hurry. We had known about the hour and a half policy and tried our hardest to be on time but traffic and parking had worked against us that day. So we started out our meal totally frazzled and squeezed ourselves into the bar where my friend proceeded to order the omakase (because it looked delicious and didnt require making more decisions based on our time restraints). It was a lot of food and she really enjoyed it. Her favorites were definitely the amazing mussels that were broiled with some kind of sauce and the angry crab and orange rush sushi. I agreed with all of these assessments since the angry crab and orange rush were basically perfect little bites of food (their special nigiri) that were packed with flavor! I also loved the maguro pearls and escolar pearls. We were both disappointed to hear that they were out of uni that night but we still ended up having a delicious meal. The sushi was very fresh and cut well but a lot of the flavors seemed to keep repeating themselves (seemed to be a reliance on truffle oil and spicy mayo (though in moderation). Also we definitely kept checking our watches to see when we would get kicked out. What made this more frustrating was the fact that our server disappeared for a long time near the later part of our meal and we were trying to order dessert while we still had time. But then when she returned she told us not to worry about going over our time and brought out our desserts with only 5 minutes of our hour and 15 remaining. So that was nice but we definitely would have preferred them to reassure us that there would be enough time since we felt rushed the whole meal...',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ucc26',932,'2020-07-22',4,'Sushi at its finest!! Not your everyday run of the mill sushi, expertly crafted, to balance flavors & unusual ingredients. The chefs are a treat to watch. Beautiful atmosphere for a date night or fun night out. Im up for another visit soon ).',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('platea7440',1051,'2021-06-06',5,'LOVE cozy little - off the beaten path places with great food, attentive staff and interesting decor.Stopped by Kai Zan on a Sunday evening, without a reservation, and waited about 10 minutes for a table. Â Next time Ill either make a res., or for the spur of the moment cravings, pick up the phone and pray - because Im guessing, as word gets out, short 10 minute waits may be a thing of the past.There were two of us, and for less than $40 we sampledEscolar Pearls Angry Crab Orange CrushSpecialty Roll of the night - name escaping me - three different types of tuna and a kickSpicy OctopusHamachi / JalapenoFlavors were wonderful and soy sauce was only needed for the hamachi. Â If I was forced to pick a favorite ... it would have to be the Orange Crush (which was a surprise from one of the chefs towards the end of our meal) or the Angry Crab.Thank you Kai Zan for a superb end of the weekend meal. Â I will be seeing you again soon!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede20152',34,'2019-01-04',5,'This place was sweet. Â Its in a very nondescript area.. you wouldnt know its there just walking by. Â Its BYOB, and theres a minimart right across the street. Â So we bought 2 bottles of cold sake and brought it over. Â Once you walk inside, you know its going to be good. Â Pretty hostess, hipster servers, clean/modern decor, personal asianstyle booth-rooms. Â We sat in one and its nice. Â Immediately a server brought over warm towels to wash our hands and a bucket of ice for our cold sake and sake glasses. Â Most of us got the Omakase, and it was Omakawesome. Â Basically its the $60 tasting menu. Â It was probably 12+ dishes, and it was soooo much food and very good. Â I cant remember it all, but that wasnt the point. Â The point is theyre bringing out a lot of yummy food fast and furious you just eat it. Â I love that way of eating. Â It was a lot of sushi favs like sashimi and rolls and carpaccio, and other raw items like oyster shooters, uni shooters w/ raw quail egg, and also yakitori type things like grilled mackerel, octopus salad, grilled mussel, fried jalapeno, bacon wrapped enoki mushrooms, and then other random stuff like a crab dish, mushroom dashi, etc. Â There were several other dishes as well. Â Its a lot of food. Â They dont try and overcomplicate the dishes w/ a ton of ingredients and flavors, but they do make some of the more unique dishes interesting. Â Service was great and the dishes came out quick and plates cleared and dishes were described and they checked up on the one person in our party who didnt order the omakase. Â Id recommend this place to anyone!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',1287,'2021-04-09',5,'The other reviews are all spot on (1) omakase is the way to go; (2) make sure you have the escolar pearls; (3) unagi poppers are as ridiculously amazing as they sound; (4) the service is questionable and they definitely want you to eat and GTFO.That sums it up.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aenean2690',1658,'2021-01-19',4,'Took my mom here for her bday. For a Tuesday early dinner we still need a reservation. The place is teeny tiny but feels airy and light. Our server was awesome and the food was killer. Took other yelpers advice and got the Escolar Pearls. I cant wait to get them again. The oyster shooters with quail egg and fly fish roe was also great. Theres a ton on the menu I cant wait to go back for. I am treating my boyfriend to this place next week, mostly cuz I want more for myself!',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',483,'2017-07-01',5,'First visit to Kai Zan and definetly not the last. My boyfriend was recommended by one of his fellow firefighters. He knew that I love sushi and in our three years together we had never gone for sushi as a couple, he never has had sushi. First of all, the staff was friendly, gracious and very helpful when it came to ordering and questions on what we were about to eat. We ordered the Omakase for $60, worth every penny. Â My boyfriend and I did not have much conversation relating to anything other than the food that was put in front of us and into our mouths. Â We will be back, soon!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non8128',226,'2020-08-12',5,'Best sushi in Chicago. Â The fish is so fresh and delicious. Â Seriously, the quality of the fish is amazing and the place is clean. Â So happy to have found this place!',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('convallis3283',1098,'2020-01-22',4,'Came here for the first time this evening with some friends who rave about Kai Zan. It was delicious! And the atmosphere was delightful. Prices were a little steep, with a corking fee of $15 to boot.. Our waitress (arlene) showed up late, apologizing and seeming stressed. Broke our cork in the bottle, while rushing though the specials. Didnt catch any of the specials because she had to get help opening the bottle. Still charged the full corking fee. Our runners/bussers were on it, but wasnt impressed with the service otherwise. Will try again on another night possibly.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra37167',1731,'2021-02-19',5,'Air condition did no seem work well last night when we first ate there. We were sitting in a small room and everyone was sweating. Food and service were pretty good.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dictumst76178',1062,'2021-10-30',5,'Ive been meaning to try this restaurant for a while. Â I am always on the lookout for good sushi places of all types.The decor was interesting, without being flashy, stuffy or kitsch. Â I thought the place has a nice, homey feel from the second I walked in. Â Strangely shaped, small and a bit cramped, but interesting, with some nice semi-private areas and not too loud.We tried a huge variety of sushi rolls and a few other dishes. Â The kaki fry was an awesome version. Â 3 massive, juicy oysters with a nice, thin and crisp coating. We also tried a special of mixed mushrooms and tofu steamed in sake that was really delicious. Â We enjoyed the rolls quite a bit. Â The fish was fresh, presentation beautiful, and the special combinations were not heavy handed.We enjoyed the service as well. Â Our server was knowledgable and accessible, and our water was filled and empty plates removed in a timely fashion.As for value, the place is not cheap, but not overpriced either. Â We spent just over $90 for two including tip, but we really pigged out. Â You could do it for $50-60 most of the time, which is about what Id spend at Coast or similar places. Â Portion size was decent in most cases, although a few of the specialty rolls were only 2 pieces, which for $8 is pretty small.Overall, a great experience and Ill be returning very soon.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('turpis45182',1458,'2019-03-30',5,'Insanely good. Â Tonight we had the $90 Tasting Menu. Â There is a $60 tasting menu but tonight there was a special offering and it was worth it. Â I have had Uni a lot and heard it described as the foie gras of the sea. Â I have never thought of Uni as foie gras ish but tonight was the first time I have had it so fresh that is melted on my tongue and it was amazing and did have a foie grasness about it. Â Maybe two courses were good, the rest were great or insanely good. Â The service was fast and knew their food. Â I have been to Koi in L.A., Blue Ribbon in NYC and Pod in Philly and this place smokes them all (better then Koi is not saying much, L.A. hype b.s.). Â This is an absolute must. Â Good luck on the reservations though!',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ligula35188',305,'2019-09-24',5,'I agree with some of the other reviews. Â The bad outweighs the good.We felt rushed, omakase was poorly timed (i.e. 2-3 dishes at a time, server trying to take my plate away while Im still eating). Â Plus, I dont think the food is that creative or tasty. Â Spicy mayo on everything. The flavor profile is pretty one-tone and the condiments (i.e. mayo, chili oil, tabasco, etc etc) take away from the freshness and the flavor of the seafood itself. Â A good example of this would be the uni that was drowning in ponzu. Â I did really appreciate that the seafood was fresh. Â And I thought the decor of the place was awesome with its private booths!',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',1707,'2018-11-09',4,'Sensational sushi - fresh, wonderful flavors and very interesting options. Â Not the overwhelming menu or over the top flavors. which often means no real flavor, of so many other places. Â Our favorites are the Maguro pearls, Danielle and Angry Crab, and the Fiesta roll. Â Also the different skewers are wonderful, particularly the different veggie options such as Shitake or asparagus.The restaurant is quite small but a very nice atmosphere. Â Hard to get a reservation but worth it.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',1719,'2021-09-29',5,'Not a big raw fish fan but there are plenty of other dishes to choose from. Excellent Excellent Excellent. Atmosphere is intimate, casual, and cozy. Service was just right. We shared a few rolls and skewers. My fav was the fiesta roll. Everything is fresh with the right amount of spice. Had green tea ice cream for desert. Prices were reasonable. A very pleasant suprise for living 2 blocks away. Make reservations ahead of time!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('adipiscing8461',459,'2019-03-23',5,'Dined at Kai 7/24/14.Despite the fact that I had heard amazing things about this restaurant, I was apprehensive after making my reservation, which I made online day of. Â Over the course of my day, I was reminded multiple times, either in writing or verbally from restaurant staff (when calling to confirm) that my table was mine from 7-9pm. Â I am comfortable giving my credit card number to book a reservation, but, as an industry worker, this is something I have never heard before. Â Would I be rushed? Â Might my Omakase be cut short? Â What if I want dessert? Â They did a very good job of instilling a sense of urgency and time into my mind (as Im sure was intended) before even arriving at the restaurant.However, my fears were unfounded. Â We arrived about 15 minutes early and were seated instantly in what I believe to be the newer area. Â We sat in a luxuriously large and private booth meant to accommodate up to 6 I assume. Â There were five of us and we had a TON of space to spread out. Â Still feeling a little bit like we might need to hurry, we wasted no time in a ordering. Â We actually ordered all of our food BEFORE discussing beverage, just to be safe.Between the five of us, four had Omakase and one ordered from the menu. Â Someone (the kitchen or our server Abby) did Â a wonderful job making sure that our lone ranger was fed in a way that timed very well with the rest of us eating Omakase. Â So I dont have to say it over and over, we found all of our fish to be of the highest quality.I cant remember everything that I ate from the Omakase, but most of it has been previously mentioned here on yelp. Â I can, however, say that we tried all but one of the daily specials. Â We skipped the Lamb Pops (although Im sure they were delicious) and started with the Scallop Sashimi, which we were told was freshly shucked, to order, from live scallops. Â So clean tasting. Also we enjoyed Otoro tartare over rice with a quail egg, wasabi, some truffle and three MONSTROUS Uni lobes. Â Finally the fried Aji, a mild mackerel. Â So cool. Â They served about 6-8 slices of Sashimi from the Aji, inside of the Aji. Â The fish itself was fried, but because it has soft bones (like a softshell crab?) you can eat the whole fish. Â Ive had whole fish before, and I what they plate usually looks like in the end. Â This was not that. Â We were served a whole fish, and returned plates with no debris. Â Awesome.We followed this with Omakase. Â All I will say is that it feels to me like a steal. Â At $60, you cant afford NOT to have it! Â I would happily pay another 40-60 if Carlo and Melvin maybe added a Wagyu course, maybe used some fresh truffle instead of oil, I dont know. Â I thought it was wonderful.After Omakase, we wanted to try some of the grilled skewers. Â We were pretty filled up, but we had some time left on our table! Good thing we ordered quickly. Â We tried the beef tongue, duck, pork belly shishito peppers. Â The pepper were wonderful as well with ponzu (?) and bonito flakes. Â We commented to our server that we felt the Uni was of an especially high quality and the kitchen sent for us the Escolar Pearls (oysters wrapped in escolar) each topped with another HUGE Uni lobe over a tobasco and ponzu foam as our final bite. THANKS CARLO AND MELVIN. A rich end to a rich meal. Â All in all, we never felt rushed during the meal, loved everything we ate and look forward to bringing the rest of our friends back. Â Everyone should hurry up and go before they get their Michelin star and Carlo and Melvin realize they are shortchanging themselves on price, because they are.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vulputate545',642,'2019-12-23',4,'Had the omakase. Â It was well worth it. Â Service was great. Â Great value at $50, lots of food, a great variety of flavors. Â One of the beat Japanese-style restaurants ive been to in a long time. Â Will definitely be back!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tempus72169',551,'2019-08-02',5,'Came here to celebrate with some friends. The server recommended the tasting menu, which was $60/person, telling us it was a great value for the money. The skeptic in me thought it was a great up sell, but we all opted for the tasting menu anyway. We were not disappointed. 10 courses, everything ranged from good to amazing. They were also very conscientious about all the various dietary restrictions for our party. Wonderful sushi, byob, and the private booths (if you can get them) are great!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien16194',674,'2016-03-26',5,'The Green Monster maki was amazing as was the Eskimo Clouds. Â The Tako Yaki was ok - I wished I had ordered the Maguro Pearls instead. Â The place is small so I wouldnt recommend it for a large group. Â For a first time visit, I walked away wanting to come back and thats always a good sign. Â I look forward to trying the Chefs Choice omakase.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lectus27103',1180,'2017-03-28',4,'Omakasi. Get it. Â And bring some good wine along; this is a BYOB. Dont forget a robust appetite. You are in for a real gourmet treat. And the last course? Its to die for......',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',1655,'2021-03-09',5,'This a cozy and beautifully decorated restaurant. But I did not come here for just the decor! Â I was really looking forward to trying Kai Zan but unfortunately it fell short of my expectations. The best part was the escolar pearls. They are truly little bursts of deliciousness! Â But they are LITTLE! Â The sashimi pieces were just alright, nothing to write home about. The husband said the tuna and octopus were fresh...but in general this place is mediocre in my book, considering the price and lack of super fresh sushi. Â I would rather go to Lawrence fish market and get fresher sushi for much cheaper, and eat it in the comfort and mediocre ambience of my own home.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('venenatis75118',1164,'2016-10-14',5,'I love what these guys are doing. They have been passionate & hardworking for years. Now on their own the twins are truly shining. The omakase is so good it truly blew me away. The quality of both food & skill will make you smile. Being able to walk here makes it even better for me. I didnt want to keep spreading the word because I never dont want to be able to get in, but this whole place is amazing so I had to keep word spreading of the succulent splendor they create. All the best see you soon.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',1410,'2016-03-06',5,'I use Yelp regularly for recommendations, but only write reviews if I am blown away (good or bad). Â This place BLEW ME AWAY! Â I have never tasted anything quite like the dishes they prepared and presented. Â My husband and I ordered the chefs tasting menu (omakase) and I am so glad we did. Â We got to sample so many amazing creations such as oyster and quail egg shooters, a caramelized scallop skewer, and chocolate lava cake with black sesame seed ice cream (I think!). Â These are just a few of the creative and perfectly executed tastings that were placed before us. Â This is a must for everyone to try - sushi lover or not. Â In fact, the sushi is a mere filler on a menu like this!GO!!!!!',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('morbi7160',987,'2019-01-18',5,'Ive had both omakase menus here and they are both excellent. Â The entry one is one of the best restaurant experiences for the money that I have ever had. Â The chefs special one is worth doing, but I plan to do the entry one for future visits. Â Pearl Escolars are one of my favorite dishes at any restaurant.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',1578,'2016-02-12',5,'Phenomenal food and service. It is super small and you have to make a reservation at least a week in advance if not further. Well worth. I believe they are expanding into the space next door which should help.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',272,'2016-08-30',4,'this place is awesome i dont think i can go back to low quality sushi. this is a palates dream. Â i cant wait to come back',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('fusce2549',1685,'2018-04-28',5,'Ive been here twice and cant wait to come back again! Great food, best value. The chef special omasake is so worth it!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3652',525,'2020-09-09',5,'Look, all I can tell you is that I rarely give 5 stars. Â This place is as good as it gets in Chicago. Â Its that damn good. Â Go, NOW, before you die... your soul will wander the spirit world forever if you dont go, haunting your family, wondering WHY DIDNT I GO TO KAI ZAN FOR THE BEST DAMN SUSHI IN CHICAGO? Â WHY? WHYYYY???? Â It aint cheap, but great fresh seafood never is.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',691,'2016-06-03',4,'This place is really great, one of my favorite sushi places in the city and Im a snob about sushi. Considering the quality of the fish-which was excellent-the menu is very fairly priced. My friends and I were sat in a cabana, the service was great, the ambiance comfortable and its BYOB. Check it out!',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('velit8725',1247,'2017-06-06',5,'Fresh food...fast service...knowledgable & friendly staff...great place!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet7277',425,'2018-11-05',5,'I found Kai Zan on Yelp and was intrigued by the great reviews. However, I was not thrilled by their sushi. It wasnt bad, just average. I would give another place a shot before going back to Kai Zan. On the other hand, the dÃ©cor and atmosphere are great, very clean and modern. Also, the BYOB feature is awesome!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum7621',843,'2017-03-16',4,'A couple people have told me about Kai Zan and after going I can see why. It is amazing! Â The sushi is so fresh you can really taste the fish. It specializes in little bites more along the lines of nigiri and sashimi rather than huge rolls with lots of spicy mayo. So if that is what you like do NOT come here. We ordered so much it is hard to remember everything, but my favorites were the escolar pearls and the angry crab sushi! Beyond amazing! One thing to know is that it is BYOB for everything. I wanted a coke but they informed me that they only have water and green tea, but if you forget he mentioned a store across the street where you can get your libation of choice. It is also a bit hard to find. The sign is very small, blink and you miss it. But it is so worth it once you find it! Enjoy!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',1614,'2021-06-08',5,'Best affordable modern Japanese restaurant Ive been to in Chicago. Â We got the Omakase and it was delightful. Â My favorites were the escolar pearls and the salmon belly sashimi. Â But when you get the Omakase, you just get the best of everything. Â So there is no need to order by taking peoples recommendations on Yelp.The ambiance is beautiful. Â We sat in the sunny little patio up front but the wood interior is gorgeous. Â I hope to sit in a booth next time. Â One of the twin brother owner chefs walked around to ask us if we enjoyed our meal. Â The wait stuff was attentive and you can tell they love their food as well. Â As they should. Â Its so good. Â Make a reservation now.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam10149',715,'2016-11-08',5,'Kai Zan is one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago! The food is fantastic and the ambiance is perfect for a tiny BYOB. Â Ive had the chefs tasting menu and Ive ordered off the menu a la carte. I even grab food to go when Im feeling lazy. Â The staff has only gotten better with time. Â This is great place for a foodie who doesnt want to break the bank! This restaurant is making my neighborhood a better place to live and visit! Thanks so much Kai Zan- you guys are killing it!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pellentesque33136',1533,'2021-06-21',5,'Sushi was delicious and the staff was attentive and helpful. Â Will definitely be back.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1142,'2021-02-14',5,'We went last night for the omakase. was not planned, just happened to think omakase would be a great idea for $50. and it was a LOT of food.service is sketchy. our server spoke to low and i could barely hear what was on the plate. shooters, uni in broth, steamed scallop, sashimi, escolar pearls, eel tempura, and a huge range of other things that i can no longer remember.for the size of restaurant, cleanliness, quality of food it is excellent. none of the fish had an aftertaste.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',927,'2016-01-10',5,'Best sushi restaurant in Chicago in my opinion. Â Love that its BYO, love the new addition for more seating and to accommodate larger groups, and I love the specials and creativity of the chefs. Â The fish is fresh and the rolls are inventive, I could eat the Maguro Pearl appetizer every day!',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',1346,'2016-09-04',4,'Omakase all the way. Â My brother lives by here and Â told me about the omakase, but unfortunately for him his wife is not as adventurous with food so they ordered off the menu. Â The only downfall which is minor is that we were sat right next to the window so any time the door opened it was cold, but a small price to pay for the phenomenal culinary experience. Â The ambiance of the restaurant is ideal--I kind of felt like I was at a spa. Â Great for date night and you cant beat the quality, creativity and presentation of the food. Â Will definitely be going back!',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',173,'2016-01-04',4,'(psst i have a 745 pm reservation tonight, 12/19 for 4 that i cant use. friend/message me if you can use the table)___________________________________incredible sushi. truly. not what you expect for sure, not from the neighborhood, maybe not from the exterior, just go with an open mind. and dont order a california roll--this is the place to be adventurous because its all insanely good. at some point in the meal you will gasp and look around and try and figure out if what youre experiencing is real. its *that* good, people.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',906,'2016-08-19',5,'Excellent fresh sushi, oyster shooters to die for. Ambiance A+. Plenty of parking. Priced well.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',1238,'2019-05-17',3,'4 visits and enjoyed all of them. Â  This place is great! Â I would suggest something to try specifically, but everything is well made so you really cant go wrong. Â Just make a reservation early as the place is tiny and there arent enough tables to go around if you are a walk in.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',1323,'2020-05-13',5,'Great hidden gem and BYOB sushi spot. Â A little off the beaten path but food was excellent. Â Make a reservation because its very small and you will have to wait. Â The green monster was an awesome sushi roll and I would definitely get it again. Â Escolar pearls were also good but I wouldnt have to get them again. Â Overall great date spot and great sushi.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',45,'2018-10-27',5,'Unfortunately the recent expansion has taken its toll. Â I dont think that the small kitchen is dealing well with three times the diners. Â Omakase rounds are ill timed...temperatures are mostly all now room.temperature.... service is less personal and consistent. Â The raise in the omakase price would be justified if the food hadnt taken such a hit in quality. Â Lastly, and most alarming... sashimi is a bit warm, texture is off, and pieces are cut peculiarly small. Â The angry crab is still spot on...amazing...so good...as if a seperate chef is responsible for that one dish. Â Sorry guys. Gotta be honest. Â You were one of my faves... lots has changed.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1493,'2019-04-21',4,'I almost dont want to tell people about this place its so good. Â There are only like 18 tables so make a reservation. Â Its really tight in there but totally worth it. Â The sushi is really tasty and unique! Â Its expensive, but makes up for the cost of the food b/c its BYOB! Â Theres a liquor store on the corner that sells sake too!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra9531',737,'2019-11-21',5,'Although the food was delicious there were a few things I found wrong with this place. Before I review I must state once again that the food is Very Very good. This place is just way to cramped. The minute you walk in you feel like there is no room to move. If u weigh over 140lbs dont even think of sitting towards the front. I know because my big behind was knocking stuff over left and right / Also, its BYOB which is totally cool but as far as anything to drink all they offer is warm water. This is definitely more of a date night place. Not bad but I dont think I will be back..',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',524,'2021-02-13',5,'Our favorite sushi place in Chicago, by far. Been here 15-20 times. The Omakase is legit. Great combination of flavors and textures. Very happy they expanded and can seat more... More opportunities to enjoy now. Also love leaving a restaurant with only a $100 tab for two.. Doesnt happen often in Chicago.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl36148',50,'2017-08-27',4,'Angry crab made us so happy. Â Everything else was equally as great! Â The only thing that made me sad was that my stomach wasnt larger. Â They do it right! Â Welcome to the neighborhood! Â I just hope I can still get a table once the rest of the city catches on to this tiny space full of amazing!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam9757',554,'2021-02-20',5,'The food here is delicious. Â Any of their special sushi items are highly recommended. This is what we ateAppetizers- Maguro Pearls Â These were so good, reminiscent of the 8-ball at Kyoto, where the chefs used to be.- Tonkatsu with shiso very good, although just a touch dry.Kushi- Momo Â Perfectly cooked and juicy, although unseasoned. Â The sauce was good, but the chicken needed salt.- Shrimp negi mayo Â Again perfectly cooked and fresh, although not mind-blowing. - Shitake Â These are meaty and have a great sauce. Â I dont like mushrooms, but these were given to us by the itamae so I went for it. Â Not bad, but nothing to write home about.Nigiri- Mackerel Â Although the fish was tough, the fresh grated wasabi on this really stood out. Â It was bright and citrusy, with a touch of heat but not the overly-artificial flavor of wasabi paste. Â Makimono- Yellowtail Scallion Â At too many places a roll like this is bland and boring. Â Not here. Â The rice doesnt overpower, but complements the fish very well. Â You can taste each ingredient independently, which is much more than 99% of the sushi places in Chicago can say, where a makimono tastes almost completely of bland rice.Kai Zan Sushi (this is where Kai Zan really shines)- Danielle Sushi Â A perfect little bite. Â A bit spicy, a bit sweet, and very fresh tuna. Â Id also order this each and every time I visit Kai Zan.- Orange Rush Sushi Â A seared piece of salmon with a great citrus glaze, wrapped around a very delicate scallop. Â Im not typically a salmon fan, but Id also order this each and every time I visit Kai Zan.- Angry Crab Sushi Â Another great piece of tuna with a great sauce. Â I couldnt necessarily distinguish the crab, but with tuna so good, its hard to fault this one. Â Likely another order every timer- Flaming Tuna Roll Â As much as we love fresh fish, every once in a while we like to splurge on an Americanized fried with lots of sauce roll. Â This was it, and was a great representation of one. Â Shrimp tempura was crunch inside, with Dessert- Green tea ice cream with red bean Â The red bean was interesting - my only experience with red bean is with red bean mochi, and the red bean here was much more savory than sweet. Â The green tea ice cream was very good, and complemented the red bean well, but Id likely pass on this in the future as it wasnt all that impressive.- Mango mousse Â Not on the menu, but was a special. Â This was more like a custard than a mousse, but was light, not overly sweet, and a good way to finish a meal. Â I likely wouldnt order it again, but for those who like light custardy desserts (not sure how that works, but thats the best way I can describe it), you could do worse.ObservationsService was good and friendly. Â We sat at the sushi bar, where the itamae would check to make sure everything was satisfactory. Â Our server was not intrusive, even in a tight space such as it is. Â They absolutely need to do something about the fryer on the line...we sat at the bar and all we could smell was the oil, which was a bit unappetizing. Â I also love sitting at the sushi bar and watching the itamae work. Â You cant do that here, as their hands are hidden from view by the fish cooler. Â Id suggest moving the fryer to the back (I dont think they have room...) and rearranging the bar so that people can feel a connection with the itamae, especially if you opt for the omakase.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',1693,'2018-09-08',5,'Although I was looking for a pure Omakase experience (aka, fish only), however, I probably found one of the best Kaiseki places in Chicago. The food, the creativity and the flavor here is great. At a price of 50 bucks, Kai Zan is a steal for the kind of food you get.Although Id go back and just order the fish and nothing else, just to have a pure omakase experience.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede2192',1472,'2019-10-13',4,'Best tasting and most creative sushi Ive had in Chicago. Unagi shooters and black sesame ice cream lava cake are a must, but you cant go wrong with anything on the menu.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',404,'2016-08-29',5,'Great sushi. Â Now serving wine. Cant wait to go back favorite neighborhood sushi in Chicago.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',963,'2017-03-16',5,'This to me is the best sushi in town. Â Ive been here several times. Â The restaurant is full of the family that owns the restaurant and they seem to take a lot of pride in what they do. Â I recommend the pearls (I like escolar a little better than the tuna), orange crush and angry crab. Â Everything else is really good too, but those are my favorites.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',1555,'2016-11-22',5,'My favorite Japanese place in the city. The omakase never disappoints. Great food, great service and great value in an intimate yet casual space. Plus you can choose from their great liquor selection or BYOB. Its the bomb.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',192,'2020-02-16',5,'I cant say anything bad about this place. Â Its truly a hidden gem.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cycy23',565,'2016-01-26',4,'Sushi restaurants in Chicago are a dime a dozen. This is the best sushi I have had the pleasure of eating in Chicago. Â Fresh, melt in your mouth good with an amazing balance of flavors. (No soy sauce needed!) To top it off the staff was friendly, the decor is adorable, the prices are great and byob...Kai Zan, Im in love!',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',1671,'2016-04-08',5,'The sushi was amazing - some of the best Ive had. Only a few selections for Maki rolls but they were delicious. MUST get the two Pearls apps. My only regret was not getting more Pearls.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra74104',507,'2019-11-28',5,'So glad to have the Twins back! Ive always said I love Sushi, but really its what the Twins do with sushi. Â Their preparation is unique, fresh, and amazing. Â There is no place that compares. Â My friends and I always let the chefs decide what to serve us and have never been disappointed. Â I highly recommend going this route. Cant wait to try some more of their new items. Â The space is fantastic and shows off the heart and soul they put into creating it.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nisl1470',194,'2017-07-08',4,'If I told you that you could get a 10 course meal that would both include some of the best sushi Ive had in Chicago AND it would be filling, how much would you expect to pay? $100? $150? So you can expect my surprise when I realized that their 10 course omakase was only $60 a head. Heres how the meal wentWhen we were first seated, I was a little disappointed by how long it took a server to come by and help us out. But other than this hiccup, everything else went perfectly smoothly. We put our orders in and were soon served with... (some of these names are real. Some of these names are names I made up based on what I remember)- Madai Carpaccio - A great start to the meal. A soft but flavorful fish with hints of cilantro.- Tuna and Escolar - Just some great pieces of sushi that have a little more fat than the previous fish.- Oyster and Scallop + Uni shooters - One of my favorite dishes of the night. Both were rather slimy as they were topped with an egg but the flavor was unbelievable. Some of the best oysters and uni Ive had.- Angry Crab - This is basically a crab roll wrapped in some delicious tuna. Just imagine the best crab roll youve had and know its better than that.- Tunatini - This was a rather disappointing dish. It was basically a sashimi salad but the ingredients didnt really work well together. But all the ingredients were all very fresh.- Tuna Dashi - Favorite dish #2. A small piece of tuna on a skewer is placed inside a mushroom dashi (soup) and while the tuna is still on par with all the other fish Ive been eating, the dashi was the star. The dashi was packed with flavor but it wasnt heavy. It was refreshing and clean and was one of the best soups Ive ever had.- Shrimp, Crab Cake, Pork Belly, Octopus - I thought these were the last 4 dishes of the night but instead, they ended up being one dish. My favorite part was the pork belly. Soft, perfectly spiced but with a crispy exterior. The worst part was the greens the pork belly was placed on. Way too salty. Also the octopus was slightly too tart for my liking.- Mussel - Honestly, I dont even remember it because it came with the previous dish. But Im pretty sure it was good.- Tuna/Salmon Roll - Another roll with tender, full-flavored fish.- Assorted Sashimi - A crazy way to end the night. I was barely able to finish this because I was so full but because the quality was so good, I got through it.TLDR Go get the omakase. You wont be disappointed.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',577,'2019-05-08',5,'Omakase! I got to say...Kai Zan has leaped into my top 10 restaurants in Chicago and Ill definitely be coming back.Fresh fish, creative preparation, and great service.',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',1326,'2021-04-16',5,'Great sushi experience, felt like going to someones home (when you visit, you will know what I mean; it looks and feels like a house) and being served with such care and importance. We did the $50 tasting menu. Each dish was a new Â and fun experience. We marveled at the artistry of the presentation and dove into the delights. Each dish was paced almost perfectly. Â Just as we finished one dish, enjoyed some saki and conversed, the next one arrived. A cycle repeated that at one point it seemed it would never end. The only thing stopping us was our full bellies. We had a reservation (recommended) but sat at the sushi bar, which happened to be directly in front of the both chefs. I noticed they were so interested and attentive to how we reacted to their creations, watching carefully out of the corner of their eyes. The moans, oohs and aahs brought a slight smile of great satisfaction and pride to their faces, knowing that they had succeeded in delighting us. Cant wait to return. Â ã©ã†ã‚‚ã‚ã‚ŠãŒã¨ã†ã”ã–ã„ã¾ã™ Doumo arigatou gozaimasu. Thank you very much!!!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dolor4397',1213,'2020-04-13',4,'Flaming tuna app was one of the best things ive ever had. Â  Good Maki, not great but everything else made up for it. Â The duck skewer was awesome. Â when I go back Ill try more skewers',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',1025,'2020-10-17',5,'Went last night with another couple. I wish I had thought to track how many times we said wow. We all did the 10 course Omakase menu and were so glad we did. Â We felt like you got a lot of sushi for $60 and everything was awesome. Â We were seated in one of the private booths and were very happy with it. Â I am not a food geek who wants to try every new and fancy and expensive restaurant but I am dying to go back and get the other chefs choice Omakase. Last night it was $120 and my experience with the $60 one just made me curious as to what else the chef will come up with. Â Bravo!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',703,'2018-12-22',5,'A bit over priced. Got the fried calamari appetizer assuming that a high end sushi restaurant would cook it properly. It was horribly chewy and tiny thin pieces of calamari, so it was like eating mostly breading. The green monster roll and fiesta roll were very good, but much more expensive than you can get elsewhere. The restaurant set-up and decor look very nice though.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin9892',938,'2018-06-28',5,'Got takeout from this place and it was Oh so delicious!!! I usually stick to the California rolls at other Sushi places, but I felt comfortable trying new bites here and I was not disappointed.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',125,'2019-08-03',4,'We went to Kai Zan last night on a date. It was a rather serious date, needed to do lots of important and rather private talking. This was a tiny bit of an issue, because we ordered the chefs choice; this means they clear the used plates and bring the next course about 10 times. so our privacy was a bit invaded. the food was surreal. everything tasted better than i could have ever imagined. the fiesta roll to die for. the regular makes, were just regular, and very fresh. the specialty rolls are so fresh and so expertly made, the tastes are superb. The price was not outrageous and we felt so pleased with our meal and the portions. it was worth it. I cannot wait for the next special occasion that will take us back. stellar menu, nice ambience, and overall amazing dining experience.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus366',1385,'2022-01-25',5,'My wife and I went o Kai Zan tonight and had to write a review ASAP. Â We have been to just about every sushi restaurant in Chicago and have a new favorite. Â Kai Zan is terrific. Â The sushi is flown in fresh daily and is evident from the very first bite. Â The manager grew up in Japan on the waterfront and was charming and knowledgeable. Â The twin owners/chefs came by our table to say hello and are clearly proud of their work. Â Go to Kai Zan and you will not be dissapointed. Â This was an easy 5 star review.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('potenti62109',734,'2018-11-08',5,'Hands down the best sushi that Ive had the pleasure of eating in Chicago. Â Superb service by our server Michelle. Â Angry Crab was great, as were the little Escolar Pearls. Â I felt that prices were creeping toward the high side, but the quality was extremely high, so therein lies the trade-off. Â I feel like Id like to have a standing reservation once a week here, its that good. Â Nom, nom!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',338,'2019-05-23',4,'We went here for the first time last weekend thanks to all the wonderful yelp reviews. The cozy atmosphere welcomes you as you walk in, and it would be perfect for a romantic date night (like my husband and I) or if you wanted to kick back with a couple of friends. We had a reservation but still had to wait around 15 minutes which we were fine with. The renovations seem to be nearly done as there were big booths on the new side and there were people in the 1st one. We sat a a very cozy 2 person booth across from the bar. Our waiter was very attentive and gave us lots of recommendations. Â The food... Incredible! Insane! Spectacular! We couldnt believe the freshness of this fish was like none weve EVER tasted in our lives. We enjoyed many of the creative dishes. Â Our favorites were the Unagi poppers, Escolar Pearls, Orange Rush and Angry Crab.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',986,'2020-09-12',5,'Brilliant, succulent sushi in a Midwestern city. Â Impossibly great. Â A triumph.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('velit13144',333,'2017-01-14',5,'Fantastic, unique menu. Â Come on an empty stomach and get the omakase for a glimpse at what this restaurant does best. Â BYOB.Service was great. Â They gave us time to eat and enjoy.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dapibus9796',478,'2017-09-19',5,'Our premium omakase dinner at Kai Zan was wonderfully memorable. None of the reviews prepared us for the perfect scale, color, textures, and flavors of the 10 dishes. Â Although the ingredients in the dishes originate from traditional Japanese cuisine, the dishes require active engagement by the diner, which leads you to appreciate the composition of each dish more fully than a traditional Asian meal. I can barely remember what we had on 6/17/17, but I seem to recall (1) very finely diced poke (that you place on taro chips), (2) a potato-seafood puree, (3) horse mackerel rolled around pickled daikon; (4) black truffle slices served with lobster (that you place on the truffle); (5) wagyu beef interleaved with kumquats (?); (6) king crab on thin cucumber slices (that you roll up); (7) four varieties of nigiri (wagyu beef, yellowtail, horse mackerl and toro); (8) Scottish salmon encrusted in nori; (9) sashimi platter; and (10) fresh sorbet dessert. The ingredients are such high quality that you feel that youve never eaten them before. We told chef that we most enjoyed the Scottish salmon. I am sure this meal will stand out even if we go to more omakase in the San Francisco Bay Area.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('rutrum7621',1533,'2019-10-02',5,'This place was mind blowing and was sex in my mouth! Â It was so good that I made another reservation while there for my first time for dinner. Â Their menu is creative and not ordinary at all. Â I highly recommend the Escolar Pearls rice spheres topped with scallions and super white tuna soaked in soy sauce, truffle oil, spicy mayo, and chili oil, then lightly seared = OMG!!! Â Flaming Tuna Roll shrimp tempura, spicy tuna & avocado with seared tuna = OMG! Â The entire menu sounds amazing and I cant wait to revisit and bring my sister here when shes visiting from Florida.',22);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('amet65139',553,'2018-06-13',4,'Amazing sushi taken to the next level. Not just your standard rolls. Do the uni shooter. Regardless of your past experiences with uni, youll become an immediate fan.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('semper2147',472,'2017-05-02',5,'Kai Zan is such a relief for this neighborhood. Delicious, original, fresh Japanese food. Friendly service. BYOB. I found a spot at the sushi bar and ordered Omakase. Unbeatable. Small tastes from the deep menu, plus dishes not listed, but even better. Tasty sushi and sashimi. Inventive little bites of raw fish. Rich grilled skewers. Get in here!',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede23147',486,'2020-11-24',5,'I went for the tasting menu and I didnt regret it at all. Loved this place. The experience itself wasnt perfect but the food came pretty damn close. Heres my full review',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',169,'2018-04-18',4,'The sushi was great and the $50/person omakase was excellent value for money. Â Both my date and I really enjoyed the food. Â Service was good (not great, but more than adequate). Â I did notice that our first few dishes seemed rushed like they were trying to turn our table quickly (as others have mentioned), but the pace relaxed a bit for the rest of the meal and we didnt feel like they were trying to push us out. Â  Â  Some of the dishes in the omakase are fairly spicy. Â They ask in advance if you have any preferences for the food, so speak up if you dont like heat. DRINKS ARE BYOB. Â Theres a Dominicks on Chicago, just west of Damen, if youre in a rush and need to pick up a last minute beverage. Â I had my cab stop there on the way and I was in and out with a chilled bottle of white in ~5 minutes.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',20,'2018-12-09',5,'I cant believe I have yet to write a review as I have now been here several times all the way from Arizona. I met the chefs when they were working at Kyoto and followed them to their own restaurant Kai Zan - I tell everyone I can about this great restaurant! The sushi is one of a kind - I highly recommend going and just letting the chefs feed you. Its BYOB so dont forget your wine - absolutely have the green monster roll and go now! You wont be disappointed!!',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('montes9279',1072,'2021-10-15',5,'We both ordered the 10 course Omakase market price. It was fantastic. Im too tired and full of awesome food to remember all the dishes perfectly but will focus on the highlights. All of the fish was superb. Stated. Second course was bar none my favorite- an oaky smoked mackerel served in a cold liquid nitrogen smoking granite bowl thing. K. Other things of note a cappuccino style broth dish- foamed top that you sip with shaved truffle- Â with 3 small neck clams in the bottom- yay! The wagyu beef was buttery melty (Im not a big beef person and it was nice). Fatty tuna surfaced a few times in the courses (nigiri and sashimi) cant go wrong there. The sea urchin came out served between tempura sesame leaves which I had never had before- like a little labia it tasted weirdly like the ocean as it should. Edible flowers throughout. Oh! and they ferment their wasabi and serve coarsely chopped in a saucy consistency rather than as a paste- lovely. Many complicated broths and sauces. We loved it.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lorem8131',364,'2020-12-12',4,'Lovely atmosphere; very pleasant and intimate. The three 2-person booths are great for dates. Service was cheerful and friendly!FYI, while it is BYOB, Â there is a $5 corkage fee for the table. Each dish we ordered was spot-on-- unique, fresh, tasty. We greatly enjoyed the spicy tuna roll w/crispy shrimp tempura, and the escolar pearls-- bits of truffle- and soy- marinated escolar over small rice balls, with a tasty aioli and a little kick. There was a superb, refreshing, sea bass and cucumber roll special; I had never seen sea bass on a sushi menu, and the dish was delightful. The dessert options were not the most exciting (green tea ice cream, cheesecake, coffee gelatin). We tried the coffee gelatin with bean curd and whipped cream-- the bean curd and cream combo was delicious and novel, but the gelatin was a bit odd and didnt really blend with the cream. (You know what would be awesome? Green tea ice cream affogato with the bean curd topping!)A really nice spot, I look forward to going again!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magnis7699',1082,'2018-04-26',5,'Absolutely beautiful. Â Lovely little cozy restaurant. Â I am not even a huge sushi fan, so I just let my three girlfriends order, and absolutely loved everything I tasted. Â Orange rush was my personal favorite. Â Really is a must.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('qqqq18',1697,'2016-05-10',5,'Small and cramped. That being said, this was one of the best meals I had all year. The omakase, which I had on several different occasions, was unbelievable. This is by far the best sushi spot I have ever been to.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('id8072',1564,'2021-02-09',4,'Best sushi ive had in the city! Â Absolutely phenomenal. Â Went with 3 girlfriends and we all did the chefs choice menu, which left us all very full. Â Service was great. Â The place is very small and quaint, but cute.Cant wait to go back!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',950,'2016-11-28',5,'My wife and I had a fantastic date at Kai Zan. Â We ended doing both of the omakase (both the Chefs Choice ($60) and the premium ($100, cost varies each night)). Both were amazing. The only downside of ordering both was occasionally there were one-bite plates. Not a big deal though. The food was incredible. The service was also great. Both meals were 10 courses. Highlights were the cold smoked fish served in a small stone bowl, scallop wrapped with wagyu beef, perfectly cooked pork that somehow tasted like foie gras, and a huge plate of sashimi. The classic omakase was incredible and I would highly recommend. If youre thinking about going for the premium, its well worth it. Â There was a discrete bump in quality and presentation, although both were great. I would certainly recommend and will come back again someday.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ut97174',1278,'2016-11-07',5,'Im in love with this place. Â Best sushi in Chicago. Â I used to say this about Ora in Andersonville and this place beats Ora. Â We sat at the sushi bar and wanted everything we saw. Â From the oyster shooter, pearls to the yummy goodness on the skewers, we enjoyed every bite. Â Our server was laid back, friendly and real. Â He wasnt the fake server that you see often. Â Make sure you make a reservation. Â  The servings are small which is great because you can try so much of the menu. Â Must try if you love sushi.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('a83185',1561,'2021-07-29',4,'First, thanks for opening a sushi spot near my house. Its just what this area needed. Second, thanks for serving amazing food at fair prices. I was in with my wife and 2 friends the other day. I must have tried 8 different rolls/dishes and wasnt let down by one of them. The Danielle roll is amazing! The only negative is that I didnt bring enough booze with me as its BYOB. No worries though, there is a great liquor store across the street!',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nulla23161',550,'2017-12-07',5,'Very delicious food. Â The portion sizes were a bit misleading. Â For example, in the same section of the menu were dishes that provided 2 rolls for $8 and the other 8 rolls for $8. You have to be careful when ordering. Â The pearls in the appetizers were delicious. Â However, there were 4 small bites for $8. Â The food here tastes very delicious. Â The chef gives recommendations on whether to eat with or without soy sauce. Â The standard maki rolls were especially affordable (about $5-6 for 8 rolls). Â I did wish that they had more specialty rolls.The ambiance and decorations were great. Â It is absolutely tiny in there (about 20 seats), but it was very nice in there. The service was great. Â The girls constantly refilled the drinks. Â Also, the servers memorized the daily specials.Make sure you call ahead, even on a weekday!',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('habitasse99106',449,'2017-04-25',5,'The best sushi I ever had! Everything is fresh and amazing! Nice presentation! Foods are out of my expectation! Absolutely I will go back again!! Sooooo good! The price is totally worth it!',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sapien72146',1162,'2017-07-03',5,'Three weeks ago this was the best sushi in Chicago. We were excited to come back, sit at the Chefs table and get the omakase. Unfortunately, they have just performed a cheap expansion and cant keep up with all of the business. The 10 courses were mostly mediocre, the service was inattentive, our dietary restrictions were repeatedly forgotten and the chef never swung by for even a passing hello. Why would I trek out to Humboldt park for something slightly better than supermarket sushi?? This once adorable spot with meticulously delicious food is now only worth the visit if you live in the neighborhood.',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',174,'2017-05-27',4,'hands down, best sushi ive had in chicago. like others have said, almost didnt want to share this news so that I can just enjoy it all to myself. we shared a bunch of different things. some of the favs were the escolar pearls, orange crush, danielle, and the uni. those were just the standouts - we absolutely loved everything. go there. now. before all of chicago does.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',464,'2020-12-21',5,'In terms of quality, its probably my second favorite Japanese restaurant in Chicago (Katsu still reigns supreme). As for bang for your buck? This is tops and not only when it comes to Japanese food. Reservations should be done far in advance and driving is sort of necessary to reach the location. Definitely recommend booking for a party of 6 people as you will get your own booth. You receive a lot of privacy but not at the cost of service; this place is remarkable at looking after your every need. Everyone in my party got the omakase meal which I highly recommend. At $60 per person, everyone in my group was full after their meal. By comparison, pricier places downtown (cough cough Roka Akor) can barely get you an entree for that price. The omakase set menu includes skewers, soup, appetizers, sushi rolls (3 full rolls between the 5 of us!), and sashimi. Everything was very fresh and tasty and I liked how it wasnt too modern of a take on traditional fare. I was so happy I finally had the chance to visit and look forward to returning',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus44156',1618,'2019-05-03',5,'Some of the best sushi Ive had in Chicago. Â We got the Chefs Special, which was excellent. Â But now we want to go back for some straight up nigiri. Â And, BYOB!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suscipit47120',847,'2018-11-18',4,'Super cute concept that I wish had a bit more to it.When we went, luckily there was only a small line and we didnt need to wait very long. They dont have a very large menu, but I ordered the Taro Dream and was pretty happy with it. You need to pay a bit of a premium for the raccoon hand to come out, which is the novelty of this place. It was cute when the drink came out but I almost wish they could have played up the concept a bit more. Maybe with more decorations so the place could be more aesthetic because that was its greatest selling point (the raccoon theme). In terms of flavor and quality, it was a solid drink. I could not adjust the sugar or ice on my beverage though, but it was not too sweet.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('enim3417',1302,'2016-03-29',5,'Pretty solid place for a modern take on Chinese food.When my friends and I came on a Thursday evening at about 7:30, there were not many tables available anymore. You order at the front and bring a number to a table, where they bring you your food. It was fast and we appreciated that.We ordered the family style meal for 4-5 to share among 4 people. It came with a pretty decent spread of variety, with 3-4 bowls of rice. We were impressed with the flavors and the modern twists to traditional Chinese dishes. My favorite was the cucumber and cauliflower dishes. The duck fat rice was interesting too but not as flavorful as we expected.It would be great if the portions were just a bit larger, maybe 10-20%. The four of us finished the meal within 20 minutes and still had room. I dont think 5 people could eat this meal and feel filled up, but maybe we were just hungry.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',438,'2017-07-14',5,'We came here for a dinner on a Friday night. Make sure you snag a reservation online to get a table indoors. Its a pretty small place, but very cozy. I definitely appreciate how casual the vibe was.We ordered the tarine and the orecchiette. Both were stunning! My favorite of the two was the orecchiette - super flavorful and a very decent portion of pasta. Im used to places skimping on the pasta and pesto quantity, so I was happy with how generous they were. The little bits of "sausage" added some great flavor and texture. For the tarine, we were actually surprised by the appearance of the spaghetti squash. It was made wonderfully and we enjoyed the whole vegetables and rice that the dish came with. Definitely cleaned the plate on this one, too!This has become one of my favorite vegan spots in nyc. Its one you cant miss out on, and the reasonable prices, cute storefront, and delicious food should be more than enough reason to come.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',710,'2018-04-27',5,'We came here for a business dinner because of the recommendation of one of my colleagues. We were promptly seated at our rsvp time, and got to ordering. There was a decent amount of variety and some decent prices, so I was excited.Overall, the place is great. Its very cozy and homey, and service is fast. The food is delicious and I got to try a bit of everything my table ordered. My favorite was definitely the cod croquettas-- very unique and well made. Im only taking off stars because some of the items were very small in portion (empanada were not 2 pieces, but one cut in half) and after speaking with two different servers, I still did not receive the drink I ordered. Pretty solid place, just had some bumps on the road.',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nunc5158',1190,'2021-09-20',5,'I cannot even begin to explain my excitement for this place. Chinese pickled cabbage and fish soup is such a winter comfort food that Ive never seen done in Chicago, so when they opened up Yao Yao, I was so thrilled. My friend and I walked in at about 2PM on a Saturday. There were some empty tables left so we were seated immediately. I really like the ordering system on our phones -- it was super efficient when we figured out what we wanted, and we could spend time flipping through the options. We ordered the fish soup for 2 and added tofu. Were lame so we did no spice.This bowl was massive. We were so surprised when it came, and pleased that the server provided us with bowls of rice as well. Even without spice, this was delicious. The pickled cabbage was just right -- not too sour and not too salty. Im really picky about pickled Chinese vegetables so this was a welcome sight. The fish pieces were tender and bountiful, already soaking up the broth. The soup was filled with flavor from the broth. Im really craving it all again and its only been a week.Please give this place some love. Its now become my go-to comfort food spot. Love it so much!',16);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('potenti62109',308,'2020-01-21',4,'Etta Bucktown is officially one of my favorite brunch spots now. SO many reasons why!1. Food was hands down amazing for the price. Like everything else in the Wicker Park area, expect to spend at least $20 per person if you want to be filled. I usually dont order French toast at brunch spots because of how not filling they are, but WHOA, this French toast was on another level!! It was the thickest piece of brioche Ive ever seen and delicious all the way through. The crispy chicken sandwich was savory and well spiced. Definitely more than filling for two.2. Ambiance was crazy. We were seated in the upper greenhouse area, and while we were able to watch the snow outside, we were incredibly toasty. I dont find that in many Chicago restaurants -- not only was the heat up, but also were there heaters spread among the tables to keep us all warm. I could have forgotten it was winter.3. Service wasnt the best Ive experienced, but they were prompt and attentive. Food came out quickly and we did not feel like we were left waiting at any point.',2);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('wcc113',1211,'2021-01-14',5,'My friends and I walked in on a Saturday morning and it was decently busy. We were seated quickly at a smaller table, but we did not need to wait long for service. The real showstoppers were the buttermilkPancakes and the omelet. Everything was surprisingly filling for what I expected if a brunch joint, so I was happy with the food. I wish service could have been a bit faster as it took a while for orders to be taken after we were seated with menus.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum76177',530,'2019-01-07',5,'My friends and I were a party of 5 on a Friday evening for prime dinner time (~7:30PM). We called in advance to see what availability was looking like (about 7PM), and they were nice enough to add us to the waitlist. By the time we arrived, we only needed to wait about 5 minutes. I havent seen this kind of service at other AYCE sushi joints in chicago!I dont eat raw fish and was pleased with the selection of cooked rolls. My friends and I ordered a bit of everything - nigiri, rolls, apps, etc. The apps came out quickly; probably about 5 mins after we ordered, the first began to show up. That was great for our hungry selves! The sushi pizza was surprising but was delicious and we ended up ordered a second one later.The sushi, however, was the showstopper. Unlike other AYCE locations, they put our sushi on a whole BOAT. I usually only see boats for special orders, so this was extremely great for us and we were super excited. We ordered a decent variety and everything came out much faster than other AYCE locations. For the cheaper price, faster and better service, and AYCE deal, Koi Sushi is my go to place now.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam9757',1063,'2017-02-28',4,'We came in 30 minutes early for a weekday brunch reservation and were seated immediately, despite our mistake of getting there too soon. We were escorted upstairs and it felt like you would be completely transported into a different time! Fresh fruits and vegetables were the decor of choice and it felt like a cute getaway from the usual busy NYC.We were in a bit of a rush to catch a flight, so the server (Adrian) was very helpful in getting our orders in quickly. My friend and I were both stuffed by the time we completed our meals! We didnt even need any appetizers or sides.My friend ordered the Southwestern omelet, and I had the Chicken Pot Pie. I like to say I judge places for their chicken pot pies, and this was a winner for me. The Rosemary sprig was a cute touch and the rest of the pie was equally aromatic. The crust was fresh, and unlike other puff pastries Ive had with pot pies, this was more dense and was great to dip. The filling was brimming to the max. It was enough to keep me full till nearly dinner!Everything was delicious, I just wish there was more crust for me to accompany the filling. By the end of the meal, I was definitely just scooping up the insides with nothing to pair with.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('volutpat2346',1073,'2018-05-10',5,'Shine is now one of my favorite casual eateries. The restaurant is well kept and clean, the servers are some of the most upbeat Ive seen. I had a lovely time with my friend and am looking forward to coming back.We shared two rolls, taro fries, and the Singapore noodles. Im always a sucker for Singapore noodles and had not seen it in chicago often, so I was very excited when I saw it on the menu. Similarly, Ive never seen taro fries here, so I knew we needed to order them. My favorite of the meal had to be those fries -- they were light and not heavy on seasoning, allowing for pure taro root flavor. The curry aioli was a perfect sauce.For our rolls, we shared the Akuma and Kadamao rolls. We chose them because they were pretty interesting and not ones weve seen in other restaurants, so why not give them a go? The Akuma roll was sweet with pecans and was a great roll to finish off the meal, while the Kadamao was filling. Im not sure if Ill order these rolls again but I was definitely making sure every piece was finished.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',1655,'2021-03-24',5,'As if you needed another 5-star review to want to come to 3 Arts Club Cafe!We showed up about 30 minutes early to our Saturday brunch reservation, and we were told our table would not be ready until the reservation time. No problem at all -- we decided to kill time by walking through the floors above to stare at furniture we cant afford. It was relatively empty in the above floors, and you could definitely tell how mindfully chosen each of the room arrangements were. It was a lovely way to kill 30 minutes. We returned at the time and were seated promptly. First of all, the environment of the cafe is stunning. Breathtaking. Its like a greenhouse with the most beautiful furniture, plants, and arrangement of space. Like the other floors, the layout of the cafe was artfully done. That alone was enough for the five stars.Our food was delicious. I had a matcha latte and was pleased at how strong the matcha flavor was without being overly bitter. My friend and I shared an artichoke starter, and it was the first time we had artichokes prepared in such a way. They were lightly fried till crisp without being heavy on the oil. Id still advise to eat them on the side of your entree as our munching on them made us a bit full before the main courses, but still lovely. The aioli was a perfect side. When I see restaurants like this, I usually anticipate smaller portion sizes. This was not the case at all. My friend and I were stuffed after each sharing an appetizer, a side of bacon, and 2 entrees. Everything was lovely and we didnt need to wait long for the food.3 Arts Club Cafe has shot itself to the top of my list of places to bring friends, parties...just anyone!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4430',1552,'2019-12-14',4,'We came in on a Tuesday at 8PM for our reservation and were quickly seated. The host was polite and attentive, and we appreciate his fast work. We were pretty excited for Meadowsweet because of what we had heard from others. The food was amazing. My friend and I each ordered an entree and shared the maitake and ricotta toast appetizer. The appetizer was delicious and a very hearty portion -- it was enough to be someones entire brunch. The entrees were lovely, too. I was pleasantly surprised by the portion sizes because Im used to smaller plates at star restaurants. I had the salmon while my friend had the duck, and both were very filling.The reason Im dropping stars for this review is because of the service. Our server, after taking our first order, never checked up on us again for the whole meal -- she wasnt even the one who gave us our checks. Our wait times were unreasonable: after we finished the appetizers, it took at least 45 minutes for us to receive our entrees. The table next to us has recused/finished their appetizers after us so we assumed that something had gotten wrong with one of the dishes. However, the customer should be notified of any changes like that. When the food came out, our server didnt set down the food properly and set it down at an angle so that the sauce under my salmon had hiked an inch up the side of the plate -- as a server myself, I was shocked to see such carelessness in handling. Multiple times we tried to flag down a server for our check and water but none seemed to be paying attention to the floor and were more interested in standing and chatting with each other. Im also a trained server in Michelin restaurants, and the service here was disappointing.',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna6451',416,'2017-08-15',5,'I was invited to come try out the X Pots Chefs Tasting Menu, and I was not disappointed!Such a gem of a spot in South Loop. Youre definitely receiving the service that you pay for -- the restaurant felt polished from head to toe, with beautiful and exquisite furnishings. Its so easy to forget that youre dining in South Loop by this experience.The staff here are also some of the most positive and cheerful that Ive met. Everyone was friendly with us, from the very sweet hosts up front to the runners bringing us the food. I am also a server myself and I felt bad at times because of how polite they were! When I came to dine, it was a bit obvious that they had just opened up. For example, some of the staff were serving the menu for the first time, and there was a bit of miscommunication between them. However, these are simply small areas that can be fixed easily with time. Everyones positive attitude makes me confident that they will be more than able to address this. When it comes to the food -- wow! Presentation is 10/10, but even the quality was amazing. I chose the Golden Chicken soup base and my friend opted for the Lobster choice. Both were very hearty and filling, and you can tell that they were simmered for quite a few hours. Vegetables were clean and fresh as well. I would have like a bit more variety in the produce, but it was still a solid, typical selection. Our favorites were the Dumplings, but our least favorites were the Meatballs -- the meat felt a bit crumbly and dry from what we expected. The appetizers are what stole the spotlight for us! We loved the X Swan. From its presentation to the duck within the pastry, it was a lovely experience and way to kick off the meal.We ordered mocktails for beverages, and my cherry/peach mocktail was a bit too sweet. Im already someone who loves to drink sweet beverages, but this one felt too, too much (to the point that it was slightly tart). My friends mango beverage was a bit better in the sweetness. Overall, I would recommend this place for a high-end hot pot experience. Youll be treated like royalty here and feel it, too!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('platea7440',1477,'2020-07-14',5,'One of my favorite bars, hands down.We came on a Wednesday evening around 9PM, and we were greeted by a very polite host. He checked our vaccination and when we asked if the outdoor tables were available, he helped us to seats and grabbed a server immediately. However, another server came out and let us know she could get us a table inside! We were a party of 3 so we wouldnt be able to have the smallest table be enough -- it was an absolute miracle that they cleared a decent table for us in the heart of everything.The decorations! Ive never been to anywhere, much less a bar, that had such lively flair. I loved how there was something to look at everywhere and it really kept the atmosphere fun. Our server was prompt and helped us quickly. We ordered our drinks, which my friends enjoyed as well. I got a mock tail and it was probably one of the better ones Ive had.Overall, this is a gem of a place. Its now one of my go to bars to bring anyone to!',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('porttitor2919',410,'2020-11-30',5,'While the food was lovely, Im dropping stars for the service. My friend and I shared the Mushroom Carbonara side as a starter, and it really was some of the best mushrooms Ive had. The sauce really carried the flavor instead of the mushrooms, but we cleaned it to the last drop.For mains, I ordered the Beef Cheek Pot Pie. It was lovely and more than filling -- I was feeling stuffed. It was some of the better pastry Ive had on a pot pie, and I like how filled to the top and juicy it all was. Unfortunately, the spoon they gave for the bone in the middle was too small to scoop even anything out, so that was frustrating. Im dropping 2 stars for the service because of how lacking it was throughout the evening. We arrived right on time for our 8:30P reservation on a Monday night. It was a packed place and the host was attentive to us, being very polite despite the fact that Im sure she was stressed by the table situation. We were told that the table we had booked was not available yet and after standing for 10 minutes, we were escorted to a different cocktail table to wait until it was ready. We were not brought over to our table until 9:00. It shouldnt need to take 30 minutes for a table to be ready at that time in the evening. This is simply evidence of an overbooked restaurant thats sacrificed customer experience for profit. The host was doing her best, but thats really too much. When it comes to the service, I was disappointed. It took nearly 10 minutes after we ordered for the server to come to us and let me know that the entree was possibly out of stock and that they were waiting to check. I work in the industry as well, and before serving a customer, we need to absolutely know what is out of stock. While they ultimately "found" more of my entree, it creates unnecessary confusion to the customer and shows a lack of professionalism. We switched servers in the middle of service, and I watched our new server sit down at various times with different customers and chat as we were trying to flag her down. If this is how they train servers, I cant help but be disappointed in their service expectations. If anything, it was the overbooked host who was most attentive to us.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mi8963',1042,'2017-06-15',5,'Its been difficult finding traditional Japanese food around Chicago that doesnt break the bank, so I was so happy to see Umais menu. There are classics like sushi and rolls, but they also include favorites like ramen, soba, and udon. Theres really something for everyone!Our table ordered a few rolls to share, then entrees for each person. Personally, it was more than enough food and I brought some home at the end of the meal, but the rest of my table was very satisfied with the portions. I ordered the Zaru Soba with tempura because I havent been able to find it anywhere else in Chicago. I was pleased with how large the portion size was and that it was very traditional -- the dipping sauce for the soba was not too salty and was rich, and the soba itself was well-prepared so it was neither undercooked nor overcooked. The tempura featured a healthy variety of vegetables without much repetition. I was so pleased!Service was a bit lacking but it was understandable given that we came in on a Friday afternoon of a holiday week. It felt like we were being rushed when 3 different servers came to ask for our orders within 5 minutes, and we were unable to find a server to help us in the middle of the meal.',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('penatibus7389',1398,'2020-06-03',5,'Ive eaten here a few times now and came in on a Thursday evening with a group of friends. The place was packed and it was nice to see the restaurant doing well!Everything was delicious and simple at the same time. Nothing was complicated or hard to understand, which I appreciate. The ingredients on the page are the ingredients you expect and get. My personal favorite is, and always has been, the Ebi Katsu rice bowl. When it comes to ambiance, I really liked the aesthetic and environment. The restaurant makes you feel like you came into a small eatery in Japan with its wooden decor and traditional decor.In terms of service, there are places to improve on. We had to flag down the servers instead of them checking in on us. It was a busy night but it felt like the staff were more interested in all supporting the new walk-in customers than the advanced support of current customer.',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam2176',49,'2021-05-08',4,'We came for a decently early reservation in the evening of a Wednesday and by the time we headed out, the restaurant was packed. Ive walked by countless times but never had the chance to try it out so Im glad I was able to pay them a visit!The food wasnt anything special to me. Much of the food was fried and on the greasier side as most Chinese food with Western adaptations is. Everything was swimming in chili or hot sauce-- it was a bit difficult for someone like me, with a low spice tolerance, to be able to find menu items I could enjoy. However, this is more of a personal preference. For the few items I could eat without feeling like I was on fire, it wasnt bad.This review is really dedicated for the server who helped us. He was a taller, light skinned gentleman with curlier hair, and he was so patient and helpful. My party happens to have some of the most annoying dietary restrictions to navigate and be was able to help us find ways to enjoy the menu. Even until the end, he was friendly and bubbly. Id definitely come back just to be served by him again -- as a server myself, I was amazed and impressed with his dedication to us.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',71,'2018-05-24',5,'Finally somewhere for the mango lovers in this city! Mango Mango is hidden in the top level of the Chinatown Plaza and is definitely one of those places that you only go to if you know it exists.I appreciate how clean this little cafe is. You can tell that everything is polished and sparkled regularly, and the bright lights help. All the furniture and decor are mango themed with aqua accents, and it feels lively and bubbly.I always get the #1 or #3 Mango smoothies. #3 has strawberry while #1 has cream. The strawberry makes the drink a bit more tart and less sweet, while the first is more creamy and closer to a milkshake taste. Both are lovely with generous scoops of jelly. Whenever I have the chance, I like to bring friends to Mango Mango. Dont skip over this place!',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et65112',909,'2019-03-03',5,'Came by without a reservation on a Sunday afternoon at about 1. It wasnt very busy so we were promptly seated. We must have come at a good time because by the time we left, it was packed!!I was really happy to see their Express Lunch set. For $16, its an amazing deal to get a small bowl of ramen, rice with protein, salad, and marinated cucumbers. Everything tasted great and I would especially recommend the miso salmon rice bowl. My friend and I both commented on how well done the salmon was!Our server was very proactive in refilling our water and checking in on us. The ambiance of the restaurant was casual but exciting, with the stickers plastered everywhere as decor. I was really happy to have stopped by and discovered this lunch spot -- will definitely bring some more friends back next time.',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam2176',1080,'2021-04-10',4,'I had come on a weekend afternoon with a friend and there seemed to be enough seating for the customers there. It didnt feel overly packed, but there was a decent crowd.I got the Gogi Bowl with kimchi fried rice. I was really looking forward to it, but the flavors were a bit lacking. I didnt feel like I was eating Korean Mexican fusion. It tasted like a typical Korean bibimbap except for the addition of some lettuce. The meat was a bit tough and at some point early on, it felt more like eating for the sake of just finishing what I paid for than enjoying it.This place deserves some applause for the staff though. The individuals who helped us were very outgoing and friendly, and this surprised me for a casual place like this. They were helpful with every customer and my friend and I definitely noticed, even as we were eating and overheard them helping first-time customers.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eu1673',1,'2019-10-09',5,'We had a 7:30 PM reservation on a Tuesday evening and didnt see many other tables, which made sense since they were definitely a new restaurant. The staff were friendly in guiding us to the table and we enjoyed the quiet and peaceful environment.We had ordered a spread, a hummus, the octopus, and the broccoli for appetizers. We didnt order bread with the spread but still received a basket, which surprised us and it surprised us even more when we were told that the extra basket of bread was a part of the order with the spread, meaning we had to pay for it even though we werent explained that the bread was a required piece of ordering the spread we already had on the tab. We asked for the basket to be taken away -- a restaurant shouldnt charge customers for an item unless letting them know first that it would be a part that they would be charged for and agree to ordering it. In terms of everything else, it didnt feel like anything special. Nothing was bad, but nothing was standout either. I found myself wondering at some points if everything tasted similar, and I realized it was because it tasted as if everything was seasoned similarly. Dessert was lovely though -- the basque cheesecake with apple butter was a new one for me, and it was a delightful way to end the evening.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tristique8035',444,'2017-05-01',5,'Im writing this as Im on the train home after stopping by here for some dessert. I had the Strawberries and cookies flavor, which was so refreshing and smooth. I dont know why more places dont do strawberry and chocolate combinations! Most of the reason Im writing this, though, is because of the incredibly sweet and friendly employee who helped us. I never got her name, but its been a while since Ive had someone help me who was this patient. She could tell how indecisive I was over the many delicious flavors, so she kept giving me samples to try. When I asked for her advice, she was bubbly and smiled and helped me find a good choice. I got toppings on my ice cream, and was floored with how much she kept adding onto my single scoop of ice cream. It was practically buried in all that she had stacked on!! When I was done checking out, I thanked her and she was friendly up until the last second.She made my night better. Id come back just for her. She deserves a high five and nice customers! Come give them some love!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('tincidunt318',1625,'2020-11-01',4,'This was one of the best croissants Ive had -- I had the pistachio croissant and was surprised by the cream filling. I wasnt expecting it, but inside the flaky croissant, there was an abundance of sweet, nutty cream that was really great at breaking up the mouthfuls of pastry. I also had a tropical smoothie on the side. It felt very fresh, and it wasnt too sweet like I had expected so it was a good sign to me that they were using fruits instead of syrups. I would have given 5 stars, but the staff had forgotten my order and it wasnt until my friend and I noticed that everyone who ordered after us was already eating that we asked them. They were really busy and I could tell the staff were stressed/not as patient with customers, but forgetting an order isnt gr',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('eget5868',569,'2021-04-27',5,'Came here last night with a friend and we were running late by 15 minutes. Called the restaurant and let them know, and they were very understanding. When I checked in with the host, she remembered my voice and thanked me for calling in. No way, thank you for being accommodating!!Our server was a bit difficult because when we asked for his recommendation between choices, he wouldnt exactly give a definitive answer and felt more indecisive than we were.I settled on the vegan mushroom teriyaki bowl and its now my favorite from the restaurant. It was packed full with juicy mushrooms and a strong taste of spices/herbs. It was so aromatic and I could have kept eating it because it didnt feel too heavy, either. I was amazed!For dessert, the chocolate cake was a bit too rich for my preferences. However, Beatrix has my favorite cookies so those will always be delicious!',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed6042',1490,'2018-11-22',5,'We came for Mid-Autumn festival and there was a long, long line. The fact that so many people were willing to wait 2 hours for a table speaks highly to the food!Straight off the bat, we were excited by the decor of the restaurant. There were very beautiful Chinese style walls, railings, furniture, etc. You could have come here for the interior design itself! Its a massive place and you can tell there was attention and care put into every part. If you were just looking from the outside it would have been impossible to tell that there was such a grand place inside. Dont be deceived by outside appearances!Their plating comes next. They really dont take shortcuts with the presentation! Youll feel like a king eating here, with fresh flowers and carefully laid ingredients on every plate.It would be too difficult to talk about everything we ordered, but my favorite was the herbal chicken broth. It was both light and not too oily, but also incredibly cozy. Its been a while since I found a restaurant in Chinatown that had the broth done so well, with strong (but not overpowering) medicinal qualities. Id come back every time for this broth!!My friends and I were blown away. The service was stellar -- every employee was very considerate and attentive to us despite having such a busy time evening. Im also a server who has worked in Chinatown before, and I have to give them a double thumbs up for how sweet they were. Some of the best service and food in the area, so make sure you dont miss it.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo40189',190,'2018-12-05',5,'Ive been to CafÃ© Babareeba a few times now with different friends, and we never walk away disappointed. If you ask me what my favorite restaurant in Chicago is, this is usually up there on the list!Unlike other tapas places Ive been to in the city, CafÃ© Babareeba is decently priced for its portion sizes. I usually feel that tapas can rack up quite a bill as youre sharing the small plates with friends, but CafÃ© Babareeba is always well-priced and delicious.My go-to favorites here are the potatoes and the wrapped dates. Theres always enough on the small plate for everyone, and you can probably feel decently full from these two alone. The bacon wrapped dates have a very sweet date in the middle wrapped by strong, smoky bacon, all drenched in a juicy sauce. You can never have just one bite! However, if you need a bit of vegetables or something more refreshing, I would also recommended the brussels sprout salad.I also really enjoy the environment at CafÃ© Babareeba. It can both be a casual place to catch up with friends, or a beautiful date night evening. The dÃ©cor is well thought out and it almost feels like youre in different worlds based of which part of the restaurant you sit in. Sometimes you can even catch customers seated and dining on cushions on the window panes as you walk into the entrance!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',1074,'2020-06-14',5,'My friend and I decided to come here for late night Chinese food near midnight on a weekday. It seemed to be the only place open in Chinatown, so we decided to go in.It looked like everyone else craving late night Chinese food had the same idea because the place was packed! We felt lucky to have gotten a seat, because when we were ordering, we noticed how some customers walked out after being told a wait time.My friend ordered a curry lamb bowl, and I had the rice noodle rolls. He really enjoyed his bowl and said that while it wasnt the greatest hes ever had, it was definitely a steal for the price. I said that mine was about the same - my rice noodle rolls lacked seasoning of anything but soy sauce. We agreed that this would likely be a great place to hit late night Chinese food cravings, but maybe not the best if you wanted to enjoy a nice meal.I had a mango sago to finish off the night, and I was happy with their traditional preparation of the dessert. To be honest, I had gotten used to seeing it as a beverage everytime I came to Chinatown, so I was surprised when it came out to me in a bowl with a spoon. It was sweet, flavorful, and quite big. Definitely hit the spot for me!',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',554,'2018-03-05',5,'CafÃ© Babareeba is one of my all-time favorite restaurants in Chicago, but Ive never had the occasion to go to Lil Babareeba. When I finally had the chance to go, I was very excited to!My friend and I checked in on our reservation for a Sunday brunch here. We noticed that the restaurant was not very packed and seemed to be at 30-40% capacity when we were seated. We decided to go for 5 tapas between the two of us, and were able to order quickly with our server.Because my friend had never been to any of the Babareebas before, we got a few items from the brunch menu and a few from the main menu. I always go for the wrapped dates as those are my favorites. I was happy to see that Lil Babareeba prepared them just as deliciously as CafÃ© Babareeba does!From the brunch menu, we tried the avocado toast and the French toast. I was not expecting it, but this was some of the best avocado toast Ive ever had. It was so savory and filled with flavor, and each bite was a lovely medly of avocado, spices, and bacon. My friend and I had to make sure we split it in half because if we didnt, one of us would have eaten the others! The French toast, on the other hand, was a nice way to finish out the meal, but I could not think of anything particularly standout about it.Unfortunately, it was a bit difficult to check out at the end of the meal. We were unable to catch a servers attention at all, much less our own server, when we had already cleaned our plates and were raising our hand to check out. It seemed that no one was looking at us and had forgotten we were there; by the time another server came around and asked if we wanted the check, I was already a bit annoyed it had taken so long for them to even look at us.While I will always love CafÃ© Babareeba as the original, Lil Babareeba has also won a piece of my heart. The service was not as attentive as I hope it would have been, but Ill happily come back another time with friends to enjoy another meal.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae3832',1651,'2019-08-26',4,'Keens is famous for their mutton chops, but because I cannot eat lamb, I am unable to comment on their prized dish. The rest of my party ordered the Taste of Mutton and the Mutton Chop, and they all said it was amazing. I had the chicken instead, and while the chicken was cooked well and I had enjoyed it, I couldnt help but wonder how this was different than eating any other rotisserie chicken. A gravy was given to me to pour over the meat, but the lack of vegetables on my plate of literally just chicken was rather disappointing when I looked at everyone else with a side of vegetables.I did, however, enjoy the free starters of bread and vegetables. Ive never had a restaurant give vegetable sticks and ranch as a starter, but I cant complain. I love a good celery stalk with ranch, and it definitely felt like necessary breaks in between the mouthfuls of meat. I was happy that they were generous in how large each vegetable stick was, too.I would recommend Keens to those who have never been here before and want to enjoy the famous mutton, but if youre like me and will be unable to, then you might be better off at another restaurant.',26);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',1622,'2016-12-03',4,'Make sure you come here with a reservation! The place opens at 5:30PM, and I had shown up early because I was able to get out of work that evening. By the time they opened doors at 5:30, there was already a decent small crowd gathering outside. This is definitely a good sign of a restaurant.Throughout the meal, I really appreciate how sweet every employee was. There definitely was a touch of "home" to the restaurant, as each employee who helped us was very cheerful and kind and patient. In NYC, this was something I was surprised by but very much happy to see. The cuisine itself is elevated Korean food, but the restaurant, service, and ambiance is still so nostalgic of my favorite hole-in-the-wall Korean restaurants run by families. I was very, very pleased and appreciative of the service we got even though they seemed to have a full house from opening.When it comes to the food, my favorite of what we ordered was the black sesame tofu. It was not too light and not too heavy, perfectly refreshing as a bite in between my bibimbap. The black sesame sauce was interesting, as Im used to sweetness when it comes to anything with black sesame. However, this one was very nutty and very strong in the sesame flavor. It was great as an appetizer and worked well as we made our way through our mains.The bibimbap itself felt a bit lacking as the flavors were not very standout. I remember feeling like it was on the bland side, but couldnt exactly pin down what flavors were missing. It wasnt the greatest that Ive had, but my friend really enjoyed his fried rice, so maybe I should order something different next time.I do recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a hearty Korean meal. Id come back for the service alone! It was such a nice breath of air from the usual intensity of NYC.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curabitur44172',1059,'2020-07-30',5,'I came to Nonnina with two other friends for a reservation at prime dinnertime, and we were seated at a nice table that was still indoors, but near the patio enough so that we could enjoy the outside air. Our server was very prompt with us and we did not feel rushed throughout the meal and did not feel like we had to wait very long, either.We enjoyed each course that we had gotten, some more than others. We made an effort to each order different items so that we could have a little taste of as many dishes as possible. I would say that by the end, we felt decently filled up without feeling like any courses were too heavy or too light.While the meal was delightful, it is hard for me to say if there was anything standout about the restaurant. Chicago is a city with more Italian restaurants than you could ever want, and I understand that its difficult to discern one from the other when you have so many options. Unfortunately to me, Nonnina did not feel like there was anything special about the meal - it was nice and it was delicious, but I have difficulty coming up with how it might be better than the next Italian restaurant.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',1118,'2017-04-23',3,'Quartino had always been one of my favorite Italian restaurants in Chicago, and I have been coming here for a few years now. However, I have mixed feelings about the restaurant since I came a few times ago.Last year, I had come with my dad as a birthday celebration when he was visiting Chicago. We had included in our reservation that there was a birthday, and the host had very cheerfully wished us a happy birthday when we were seated. The food was the same delicious quality I remember and my dad was very pleased as well. At the end of the meal, our server came out with a tiramisu dessert with a candle and said that it was for the birthday. We were very excited and surprised, as tiramisu is one of my dads favorite desserts, and we enjoyed it happily. However, when the bill came, we noticed that the tiramisu was charged for. When we asked our server about it because we had not ordered it ourselves, he said that it was how they did birthdays - they choose a dessert for you and add a candle to it. That seemed rather strange to me. On birthdays, the restaurant doesnt ask if you want dessert, chooses a dessert for you, and then tells you to pay for it? What if a customer did not want a dessert or was allergic to one of the dessert options? This felt frustrating to us and we had voiced this to the server, but he said that it was just how things were done and we had accepted the tiramisu. Had we known that this was what was going to happen, we would not have accepted it - we were quite full already and werent planning on dessert, anyways. In order to not ruin a birthday dinner, I gave up my card and stopped trying to fight the bill. When our bill came back, it was a host who told us that they had removed the dessert but "wouldnt be able to next time". I knew then that next time, if I were to come, I wouldnt mention there was a birthday.I enjoy the food at Quartino and think they are very well priced for the authenticity and for the quantity. However, this experience was quite hard to forget as Ive never been treated like this at a restaurant, especially for a birthday celebration. If this is the restaurant policy, then all I can say is that if you come for a birthday, be prepared for a dessert to be forced upon you.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elementum51171',1722,'2016-03-08',5,'I had a reservation for 6 on a Friday evening, and my party had arrived on time to be seated. We had a lovely server, but it was apparent that they were understaffed. I do appreciate that everyone seemed to be trying their best, though. It wasnt the best service I had ever received but I do believe it was the best that the team could have done, so hats off to their efforts.We had ordered courses for our meal and were actually slightly confused when our second course came out before the first. We shrugged it off, assuming that the kitchen was busy or something had just not been fired in order. Our server came back a few minutes later to apologize for the mistake, but we were flexible and didnt mind.I ordered the fish for my main entrÃ©e and was actually very pleased with its cooking. The fish was on the thinner side, but I prefer that because I was able to feel the cook on each side. My friends all tried my fish as well and said they had wished they had gotten my fish, too.Avli is a great option for Greek food if you are out in the city and not in Greektown. I liked the ambiance of the restaurant and the efforts of the service. They are still on the newer side of restaurants here in Chicago and deserve lots of support and love.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vestibulum0126',60,'2016-04-07',5,'I had a reservation on a Monday evening at roughly 7:30PM with a friend. We were seated quickly by the friendly host, but we instantly felt that service was lacking. We could tell how busy the restaurant was and how understaffed they were, but it felt like no one was even looking at us as we tried numerous times to get anyones attention to place our order. It took about 10 minutes after we were done looking at the menu for our server to come ask for what we wanted. When he came, we felt that he was impatient and slightly curt with us, as my friend (who was rather annoyed at this point that it took so long to order), said "Were actually ready to order now" and was responded with "Okay great, but how are you doing?" when it was obvious that he just wanted to place our order. That comment itself took us aback after the server left because it was not necessary at all, and instead of taking our order, the server seemed to ignore my friends statement. Im a server in Chicago for a few years now and I could sense that while our server was frustrated and was balancing many tables, he was giving my friend attitude like he was trying to match my friends tone. While it is a busy and packed restaurant, we would have appreciated if the server could have just taken our order without giving us additional attitude so it would have been easier for all of us.When our food came out, we were actually very pleased with the ricotta pillows. We had never had anything like it and very much enjoyed the pesto it came with. From the way service had started, the food almost made up for it.When the main courses came out, however, my friends pasta reached the table about 5 minutes before mine did. Its understandable that at a busy restaurant, they cant time that all the entrees come together, but we were rather confused because the runner who gave us the food did not mention whether my course would be coming out anytime soon. It felt rushed as it was dropped on our table without a mention, and my friend was very confused if he should start eating because he didnt want his food to grow cold but also did not want to start too early if mine was close by. He ended up starting his own meal, and was nearly finished by the time our server came around again and told me that mine was on the way. By the time I got mine, he was done.At the end of the meal when we checked out, our server stopped by and said he appreciated our patience. We responded similarly, but the start of service left a bad taste in my mouth. I understand how stressful and difficult it could be to be handling many tables at the same time on an understaffed evening, but there are small things here and there that can be done to ensure that a customers experience is not negative. It was okay if we did not receive their top service, but this felt like service that was below average. We talked about it at the end of the meal and mentioned that we knew our server tried to handle things professionally, but it was obvious that the stress was getting to him and he had then displayed it to customers.Im a server as well in this industry, and I sympathize with our servers situation. While it was not a great experience, I think this reflects more on the shape of the industry as a whole. Management needs to take steps to make sure staff do not feel overworked and that they minimize the risk of this kind of dining experience, while also training staff to handle pressure well. If they cant handle a full house, then they shouldnt offer a full house.Overall, the food was delicious and I quite enjoyed the cooking. However, until service improves, it would be difficult for me to want to return.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suspendisse22163',991,'2022-01-23',4,'This has now become my go-to order for a quick, healthy lunch. I like how healthy and transparent the ingredients are, and how on each bag, they include a note about their charity work. Unlike other salad places, I like how every bowl is on the simpler side so their price can reflect it, but its still delicious. It goes to prove that yummy meals dont need to come at complicated ingredients.My current favorite is the buffalo cauliflower bowl. I dont need to add anything extra to the bowl to enjoy it, and sometimes order an additional bit of pineapple to add some sweetness. I like how their buffalo cauliflower does not imitate meat; instead, you can tell that you are eating cauliflower and are enjoying the taste of cauliflower that has been prepared in a batter similar to that of meat. Furthermore, I usually feel full for lunch with a small bowl; for dinner (or when I have a bigger appetite), I might opt for the large bowl.Another favorite of mine is surprisingly the sesame sauce in their Asian sesame bowl. I feel like most of these kinds of sauces taste similar, but I remember that the first time I tried their dressing, I was instantly blown away and loved the taste of it. There were strong notes of sesame that worked well with the sharpness of the sauce. Sometimes I get this bowl just for the sauce!',23);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',1532,'2016-03-11',5,'I came with a part of 4 and we each got the 3 course tasting menu. It was a nice day outside, so we opted to sit on the street. By the end of the meal we had all commented that we were the only ones sitting outdoors, and so I really appreciated the attentiveness of the servers, runners, and sommelier to giving us service when everyone else was indoors.Our server was lovely with recommendations and definitely knew how to help us choose from the menu. I was very pleased with each dish I had ordered. My second favorite was the duck - I usually do not enjoy duck cooked medium, but this was one very well cooked. Instead of the usual gamey taste that makes me stay away from duck, I did not taste it at all in this dish. I enjoy the various preparations of the duck that I had on one plate, and each had a unique taste and flavor. For the first time, I might say that I would order the duck again.My favorite, as usual, was the dessert. I had gotten the candy bar dessert as recommended by the server, and I was very happy that I did. Cutting into the bar, you can notice distinct layers with a caramel filling slowly oozing out. I enjoyed the soft chocolate crumble, the mousse-like texture, and the thin chocolate shell. The sprinkle of salt at the top really brought it all together.My biggest compliment to the restaurant, however, would be the plating. Everyone at my table was very pleased with each courses presentation, especially given how quickly we were able to enjoy each course after the other. No dish felt like another, and so I want to give kudos to the team for their inventive and creative dining experience.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4755',1118,'2022-02-01',5,'My friend and I had come on a Monday evening without reservations at about 8:30 PM. We were told by the host that the wait would be about 7-8 mins, no more than 10 mins. We stood outside and chatted for a while because it was nice weather, but after 15 minutes, we still had not heard about our table and considered leaving. At that moment, the host came out to fetch us. Although we were slightly frustrated, we knew they were busy and were appreciative that they had seated us at a larger table for two near the back at a nice booth.We shared the fresh burrata to start as an appetizer. My friend was very pleased with the cut, and how fresh the burrata had tasted. I remember being more surprised at how quickly it came out - I swear we had only ordered 3 minutes earlier, and suddenly, the burrata came out. We were happy that they had recognized it was a dish that was easier to plate so they had quickly fired it out.We each ordered one of the two risotto dishes that the restaurant had, and we both enjoyed our own plates. I had the risotto with truffle, and while I could taste the truffle in each bite, I was happy that it was not overpowering as it would have made the risotto too rich. I also liked that my risotto did not feel too soupy or too solid/chunky. It was wonderfully made, and I enjoyed each bite. We each cleaned our plates by the end of the meal.I would recommend that if you want to come to Serafina, make sure you make a reservation in advance. It was a lovely Italian experience and I would recommend it again.',17);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra74104',440,'2019-12-13',4,'Every time I come here I try to get something different, and each one has been a refreshing treat. La Michoacana has become the late night go-to spot for me and my friends. It never disappoints, because how can you go wrong with ice cream, popsicles, milkshakes, hot Cheetos, and more?My top two favorites will always be the Mangoneada and the Fresa con crema. They prepare the mangoneada with generous toppings, filled to the top with mango sorbet and sauce. Even the small size is decently filling. For the Fresa con crema, I like how there is such an abundance of strawberries in the yogurt beverage, and they add toppings of your choice. I like MnMs and almonds, while my friend likes almonds and granola. It only comes in one size and thats already a pretty big 16oz cup.I cant believe it took my three years in Chicago to discover La Michoacana, but Im never turning back. They get pretty packed at around 9-10PM so sometimes the drive thru can be a better idea.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',676,'2017-09-13',5,'We had come here at about 8PM to pick up a to go order and it was my first time at Salt and Smoke. I had heard from so many people about how I just needed to try them, so I was pretty excited. We got a Bestie combo to share with three types of meats. Right off the bat, my friend made a confused face when he looked at the sauces and he mentioned that these were not the ones we ordered. We shrugged that they were probably close to closing and this was all they had left, but we would still have appreciated if they had let us known what they had actually given us.The sides were delicious, so I have no complains about the Mac and cheese and the coleslaw. The meats, however, were a bit disappointing. We shrugged again that it was likely because they were close to closing, but it made us feel like we were eating the leftovers. The brisket was delicious, and there was a hearty portion. The wings and the ribs, however, were lacking. The wings felt like there was barely any meat on the bones and the same would be said about the ribs. It even tasted too charred where there were bits that were straight black. We could barely get anything off of them before having to toss the whole bone.I could tell that despite the quality of our order, the seasoning was what everyone was so excited about. Had we had more filling pieces, I could see myself also raving about this place. Ill definitely look forward to coming back and trying more but perhaps when its not an hour before closing.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',144,'2020-12-08',5,'My friend and I walked into here on a weekday lunchtime looking for a fast bite. We were seated quickly by a server, and it looked like there were only two servers supporting the whole restaurant (including both indoors and outdoors). While it took a bit of time for us to receive service when we were ready to order, it was understandable and we appreciate our servers cheerful demeanor despite a stressful full house.I ordered the yellow curry with chicken and was very pleased with the portion size when my plate came. Usually have the issue of too much curry or too much rice, causing an imbalance and a sadness when I finish one and dont have the other anymore. However, the large chunks of vegetable and protein in the plate helps to make sure that there was enough of everything throughout the entire lunch. By the time the server came back to clear our table, my plate was cleaned. Its a lovely little cafe near the campuses that I definitely recommend. Please be patient with the staff -- theyre doing their best, and their best should be commended. :)',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('luctus0123',890,'2018-05-26',4,'What a hidden gem! The restaurant front is rather unassuming, but when you enter, you can tell theres so much more. We were brought upstairs to the rooftop for our dinner, and it was such a surprise. Their patio is decked with lights and plants so that it almost feels like youre eating at the rooftop of someones apartment. It felt very cozy and tables were rather close to each other, which did make me feel a bit uncomfortable, but we were seated at a table towards the side and away from the main seating. Our server was very visibly busy but still did a wonderful job helping us with recommendations.Our favorites were the pork belly with apples and the wrapped shrimps. I couldnt tell what it was about the shrimps, but they had the most delicious oils and sauces. Even near the end of our meal, we were using bread pieces to sop it up. Even the shishito pepper it came with was delicious -- it had soaked up the flavors of the shrimp and the oils amazingly. For the pork belly, it didnt look like any special at first, but when we had a bite, the combination of a slightly tart and sweet apple with fatty pork belly was mindblowing. Even though these were just the starters, they were the stars of our meal.Definitely recommend you come to Taxim as a date night dinner -- ambiance is romantic and casual, and the food cannot be complained about. Take a stroll around afterwards for some dessert!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('posuere8385',332,'2018-05-01',5,'We got lost finding Lazy Bird, but a friendly chef from Cira saw us from the window and pointed us where to go. Theres no outside entrance, so you need to enter from the Hoxton Hotel. Its a bit of a maze to find how to get there even when youre indoors, but hopefully itll get easier over time.I love how illustrious the cocktail menu is. Theres a little drawing for each cocktail, which I havent seen in many bars. The place isnt even exactly a bar, but more so a real classy lounge that makes you forget youre in the heart of West Loop. We got seated in velvet seats and a booth with cushions. It was quite luxurious, and a pity that they dont take reservations. Walking in at 8PM on a Thursday didnt seem so bad though.I had the mock tail from the menu, and my friends had beverages that they seemed to enjoy. I really liked the cookie and ice cream dessert with a touch of orange. Ive never had this combination before, but if you come with a craving for dessert, Lazy Bird doesnt disappoint.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',1466,'2016-03-28',5,'My friend and I made a very last minute reservation into the restaurant, and they were very accommodating. We were able to enjoy five dishes between the two of us for ~$85 each, not including the bread course.Our server was very informative and patient with us, which I appreciate because I know we may have taken a bit to order. Unlike other star restaurants, I also felt like each dish was a decent size for the price. It was one of the only times I walked out of a restaurant feeling full. The real stars of the show for my friend and I were the cauliflower small dish and the Satsuma ice cream dessert. While I usually order cauliflower at every option I can get, they did a great job with the seasoning and the portion size. The dessert was one of the best Ive ever had -- dont miss out!',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('accumsan84173',1328,'2020-02-15',5,'Picole was absolutely lovely. First off, hats off to the two lovely ladies who were behind the counter. Im writing this review an hour after visiting because I just needed to give them compliments for their friendly and upbeat service. It was the first time I had felt staff at a small shop like this be so cheerful and please keep up whatever is keeping them so motivated.I got the Mango Crazy smoothie. It was a relief from the blazing Austin Sun. The drink was made so quickly and the girl who hated it to me so so sweet. The drink was a bit sweeter than I would prefer but when youve been sweating outside all day, anything is good. Please come check them out!! There seemed to be a ton of happy customers but this place deserves so many reviews. Stay happy here!!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('viverra74104',1162,'2022-01-12',5,'My friend recommended that we visit here and he warned that lines would be long so we better get in early. Im glad we listened to his recommendation -- by the time we were done eating, the line was nearly to the door!!I got the GoodNight/GoodCause burger and had them take off the jalapeÃ±os. I really enjoyed the flavor of the burger and the bun was one of the better ones Ive had -- Im used to the bun being too much of a mouthful, but this one almost felt thin. The caramelized onions were a good touch even though they kept falling out. There was a healthy portion of sauce, and the Parmesan truffle fries we shared were deliciously seasoned and had a very savory sauce with them.My only complaint is that everything kept falling out of the burger, especially the onions. I felt like I was eating most of the onions on my plate and not in my sandwich. Otherwise, I felt really filled up after a single burger!',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('interdum2176',571,'2017-12-10',4,'Ive come here a handful of times now with different friends, and I enjoy the thin Italian pizza each time. If youve only had Dominos, Pizza Hut, or other instant delivery pizza, then you dont know what youre missing out on with traditional Italian pizza.My personal favorite is the Veneto -- Its very flavorful, and I find that the caramelized onions go so well with the sausage. My friend loves the Margherita, but he has complained to me a few times now that the mozzarella is different from how he remembered it -- rather than the discs, they now use shredded pieces. Ive only had dessert here once, but it was absolutely amazing. We got the Neapolitan ice cream, expecting just a typical scoop of ice cream. This has now become one of my favorite desserts in Chicago -- just take a look at the picture below. We were so amazed by the presentation, the chocolate shell, and the overall innovative serving of the ice cream. Beautiful!',13);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('at81162',1621,'2021-03-02',5,'Theres a lot of hype around Nobu, but I couldnt help but feel like there are better places to eat Japanese in Chicago. Especially for the price.I came here for a friends birthday dinner with a reservation for 6. The host and the staff were attentive and did well to take care of us. The food just had a difficult time living up to the price point. My personal favorite was the eggplant -- but 8 cuts? It just wasnt enough. Out of most of the places Ive eaten in Chicago, it just did not feel like the price was worth the food. It was difficult for us to find options that were suitable for everyone. Their sushi selection is limited for individuals who do not eat raw fish, and there did not seem much room to have family style meals just given the size of each dish. Im pretty sure my drinking glass also had a crack in it as I kept having water drip all over me throughout the meal, and it was much more than the usual condensation from a cup of iced water. One of the runners/bussers noticed me being uncomfortable as water was pooling around my cup and came over to wipe, but only once as I continued to watch the puddle grow.',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('non93107',1119,'2020-08-02',5,'Came in with a large group on a Friday night, and they were really accommodating of the fact that we underestimated the group size and would need two tables. Some staff even helped us pick up and move tables in the middle of a very busy patio to make sure we had space. I had the melon and feta salad, the cinnamon knot, and the blondie with ice cream. The melon and feta salad was a mix of diced watermelon, cantaloupe, cucumber, sunflower seeds, cilantro, and feta. It was the first time I had anything like that and it was decently refreshing. The cinnamon knot was my favorite of them all -- it was delightfully gooey, with strong twists of cinnamon in every bite. Crystallized sugar on the top made it a lovely dessert to have. I shared a blondie with the Mexican vanilla ice cream with two friends. It was pretty good, but we expected more from the ice cream. I would not have been able to tell if the ice cream were bought from a store and the blondie felt like it had been on the counter for a while -- they could have toasted it up a bit, at least.Overall, I could tell the servers were doing their best to accommodate us and I really appreciate it. Our server was sweet even though she had a handful of big parties. The food was not bad either, especially given a beer garden. The ambiance in the patio is a great social setting for large groups.',10);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede4256',1589,'2022-02-20',4,'Came here with a friend with a lunch reservation, and the place wasnt too busy. We were seated quickly next to a pillar near the center of the restaurant. Our server was rather helpful in explaining the menu to us, but it felt slightly awkward at points. It felt like there were moments when he was waiting for us to say something while we were waiting for him to say something, so we all kind of looked at each other for a few seconds. Otherwise, the rest of the meal was decent for what you would expect at a steakhouse at lunch. Nothing was extremely standout, but it was all quite good. Im a huge dessert person so I absolutely enjoyed the creme brulee I had at the end! It was well broiled and not too sweet.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('erat1120',622,'2018-12-26',5,'Came here at about 8:30PM on a Thursday, and the place was decently busy. It took about 10 minutes before we got seated but everyone was polite and it was a busy evening for them, so we were happy to get seats without a reservation. Our server was attentive and filled our water glasses many times. I really appreciated that, and she gave us ample time to look at the menu before coming back. She had a lot of tables but I think she did a good job.I personally had the $14 fried chicken burger, and it was on the better side of fried chicken burgers that Ive had. I like how big the piece of chicken was, but would have preferred a greater amount of sauce. I did not think there was enough sauce at all, and that I even had to take off the buns at one point to make sure there was sauce. I would have liked something to dip my chips in, too. Otherwise though, the chicken was done well and I still enjoyed it.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('maecenas6140',857,'2017-03-10',5,'Ive been to Bombobar a few times now just because of the craving for a dessert in the West Loop. Its always exciting to get a dessert here, but I wouldnt say Ive been blown away by anything.The Bombolini is their version of a jelly filled donut, with the novelty of filling in the jelly yourself. Neither the filling nor the donut tasted like anything special, and I think the bigger selling point is the fun of squeezing the bottle. Unfortunately, most of the times Ive gone, the jelly is difficult to squeeze out because of how hard/thick the plastic bottle is. My friends have learned to soak the bottle in hot water for a bit first, but otherwise, its difficult. The ice cream sandwich was also nothing that was super exciting. The cookie got hard very quickly, but I expected that with ice cream...just not that fast. It made me wonder if the cookie had been sitting for a while already, and I was hoping at the least, that the cookie could be kept warm when it wasnt ready to be eaten. My favorite from Bombobar is their hot chocolate, loaded with cookies and goodies. Ive only had it once, but Im looking forward to seeing it again sometime in the winter if it comes back. I really enjoy how decadent it all was and how I was able to share it with a friend. Its mostly because of this hot cocoa that I come back to Bombobar every now and then.',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vulputate64142',932,'2019-08-06',4,'When I moved to Chicago, I was so pleased to see that there was somewhere in Chinatown that I could relive my childhood nostalgia of walking into an Asian bakery, wafting in all the smells, and loving the hustle and bustle. Chiu Quon is the place, no doubt. They have regular varieties of baked goods that you can reliably grab and go, but then they also introduce new snacks every now and then. The women working the counter are super efficient and have come to recognize regulars, making this bakery feel like a home if you make it. My go-to items here are the Portuguese egg tarts, the pineapple buns, the black sesame buns, the lemon swiss roll, and the many, many cakes that they have. I love how everything here is neither too sweet nor too bland, and it hits what youre looking for without giving you a sugar overload. You can see them constantly churning out fresh bread and goodies in the kitchen near the back, with racks constantly coming in and out. They have so much demand and turnover that you know youve got fresh buns everytime you go. Support small AAPI businesses. Come to Chiu Quon!!',7);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nonummy2158',254,'2016-03-09',5,'Support small businesses! This has now become my go-to place for late night donuts when I just really need to hit that craving. I love how every time I go, theres still a great selection of sweets that I can have. They have your classic donuts, but they also have their own fun spins that really take you back to childhood times fueled by decadence. I love how they have nostalgic flavors of fruity pebbles or cereals, or peanut butter and jelly, or chocolate overdose, or... honestly, too many for me to remember! They all look so good, and I like how helpful the staff were when I was indecisive. Come out and support them. Its always a good night when Im heading to Manna at the end of the evening. :)))))',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ullamcorper075',1124,'2016-03-11',5,'Ive been to 7 Leaves each time Ive come to Southern California and have tried a handful of their locations. Im happy to report that they stay consistently delicious as each one!I visited during the pandemic, so I was able to enjoy a shorter wait time. I usually default to their taro or mung bean options. Both are delightfully sweet but not too sweet, even without adjusting the sugar levels. You can taste how fresh the ingredients are and you know they use real ingredients because of the drinks textures. I dont find mung bean often in foods here, but am glad that 7 Leaves has it on their menu!However, SoCal is the home of every boba option you could ever want. While 7 Leaves is lovely and will always be a staple, I have a feeling that competition is growing fierce and that they may need to find means to step up their advantages. Ill always enjoy 7 Leaves because Ive been coming here for a while and I hope that they can stay.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elit9486',1662,'2020-06-30',5,'Ive come to Ema twice now -- once before and once after the pandemic -- and I was pleased to see that the menu was still rather consistent in quality and flavors. A favorite is definitely the brussels sprouts! While its hard to mess up brussels sprouts, these were absolutely delicious. Roasted but also slightly sweet, it would be a mistake to pass these up. I also love any of the spreads that they offer. I still havent found a favorite, but its because they are all so flavorful in their own ways. We enjoyed being able to have more pita bread to scoop up all the spread. The bread itself is so aromatic and its a steal that you can get refills for free. We had the honey pie for dessert, which came with roasted grapes. Weve never seen a pairing like this before, but it was delicious with a slightly yogurt cream. It was neither too sweet nor too bland and was the perfect way to finish the meal.Between two people, we shared 3 small plates, 2 big plates, and 1 dessert. Its definitely more than enough! The servers were a bit inattentive with my party and we usually needed to find another server or runner to help us. When they did come to help us, they didnt look very cheerful or happy. Maybe they were tired and busy, but it felt a bit off-putting.',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cubilia59166',411,'2018-11-06',4,'Ive always come to MingHin for late night dim sum, and Im always walking away satisfied. Ive enjoyed all of my favorites here, and unlike other dim sum restaurants, it feels like their quality has been consistent over years and over various locations in Chicago. For example, Im happy to see that their BBQ pork buns have roughly the same amount of dough and filling at each location, and they havent tried to cut corners with more dough and less filling. :) Minghin is great for both dim sum and entree ordering. I always enjoy family style meals with friends everytime I come. Ive brought my parents here before, and they were impressed at how authentic everything tasted. We didnt need to wait long for the food, either! They have a huge selection and will have options for everyone.In terms of the service here, theyre always busy so they dont have the best service. You need to flag for servers and ask for help, but its understandable because theyre trying to attend to so many tables. Ordering on the paper dim sum menu or on the ipad makes it much easier for the customers and the servers!',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('mauris12138',484,'2019-11-28',5,'I came here with a large group on a beautiful Saturday afternoon, and the owner + employees were super accommodating of us. They recommended a handful of their favorite items to us and we brought them out to the parking lot around the corner so we didnt take up space inside the small bakery.I had their chocolate hazelnut pasty. Ive had so many chocolate croissants in my life, but this was something different! The chocolate was gooey and creamy, and the pastry was flaky, crisp, and melt-in-your-mouth. There was a slight glaze and sheen on the top, as well as a few baked hazelnuts (or roasted). The nutty flavor came through and blended well with the chocolate -- neither was too overpowering over the other. It was hard not to love it!This pastry was rather decadent and is definitely more of a dessert than a brunch bite. We also had the Earl Gray croissant and the sticky cinnamon buns. Everything was delicious down to the last bite and we were licking our fingers!',6);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('quam39115',443,'2021-03-01',5,'This place is so underrated!! Its in the most unassuming location in town, but dont underestimate its quality.I always get the #1 Bambu Special. For 260 calories, you will feel much more filled than a boba. Its full of fresh fruits and flavor, and I always feel so refreshed afterwards. Coconut, Pandan Jelly, Longan, Basil Seed, Coconut water.Some people complain that its a bit more pricey than your average $5 boba, but it makes complete sense. The drinks are made fresh and the ingredients are prepared fresh everyday -- not canned! The owner was so friendly and explained to my group how they made the drinks and ingredients.A perfect afternoon? A #1 Bamby Special from Bambu and a Banh Mi next door. They complement each other perfectly for barely over $10. Can you ask for anything more out of Argyle?',15);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',996,'2020-04-18',4,'Ive only ever been to Au Cheval at 11PM in the evening because Ive found it to be impossible to come in at any other time. I can see why!They are more than generous with their portion sizes. I mean, do you see that cut? You eat half a burger and you already want to knock out in a blissful food coma. Strangely enough though, the salad was one of my favorites. The burger is quite heavy (without being too greasy), so it was refreshing to have some fresh vegetables...albeit, the fresh vegetables are accompanied by huge slices of bacon. I wasnt as impressed by the fries, but then again, Ive never been a fries kind of person. They werent anything special compared to the standout burger and salad and bacon, and was more there so I could keep munching when I finished the meal.I wish the desserts had a bigger selection, though. When Im done with the massive meal, I still want something sweet to finish everything off! Overall, I would describe Au Cheval in a few words: Juicy, satisfying, and coma-worthy.',19);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vel1641',116,'2018-06-08',5,'Service isnt the greatest, but I dont blame them because its a demanding job to serve AYCE to a full house. Sushi Taku is the only AYCE sushi place I would go to in Chicago. They have the greatest selection of rolls and nigiri, so everyone in your party has something to enjoy. I like how they also included selections of desserts and appetizers.Their AYCE menu doesnt skimp, either. They arent small rolls -- they include their larger roll options too, including baked rolls, fried rolls, etc. Thats not something you see often at AYCE but is a huge plus. I cant eat raw fish so I usually dont like to go out for sushi because Im tired of just having Dragon rolls, but Sushi Taku always makes me excited.Im used to AYCE sushi places also skipping out on plating efforts because most of the customers are there for the quantity, not the quality. The chefs here still take the time to make every presentation beautiful, and I know theyre always so busy! Its a popular place for a reason. The price per person has increased over time and they dont take reservations, yet its understandable because youll leave there feeling stuffed. Make sure to skip out on lunch and show up early to get a table!',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('proin7639',1235,'2018-02-22',5,'Ive been to Gaijin twice now, once when they opened and another time more recently. Im happy to see that theyre still serving the same delicious quality of okonomiyaki!For anyone whos never tried, okonomiyaki is quite tedious to make at home. Its a very classic Japanese street food and is always a mountain of toppings, but to prepare it at home, you need to have the right ingredients, tools, griddle...you get the deal. So I was so happy to hear that Gaijin was in West Loop!Each okonomiyaki is HUGE. Its more than enough for one person. We got 2 for 3 people, and it felt like the perfect amount. At a certain point though, the flavors all start merging together and it feels like a rather consistent taste throughout the pancake. Regardless, its rather delicious!Weve gotten the donut dessert here before, too. I remember it being a bit more dense than I would have preferred, but the frosting was not too sweet, so I enjoyed it. Trust me though, after a whole okonomiyaki by yourself, its absolutely difficult to finish another bite of donut (no matter how delicious)!!',28);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede20152',74,'2021-11-09',5,'Its still delicious, even in a to-go box. Dessert Dealer is my favorite dessert in Chicago because of just how good the deal is for their DIY ice cream tacos. Hidden inside Pizza Parlor, if we have a bit of luck, we can be seated at a table and enjoy our dessert there. It just happens that we werent so lucky this time and had to take our sweets to-go, but it was still the same yummy ice cream I love. Theyre incredibly generous with the toppings, and theres something for everyone to love. The customization options are not too overwhelming but enough for everyone -- from the chocolate lover to the fruit fanatic, theres an ice cream, topping, cone taco shell, and drizzle flavor for all. This ice cram taco is big enough for two people to comfortably share, and will not leave you wishing you had more. Whenever I have someone visiting Chicago, I make it a huge point that we need to go to Dessert Dealer and enjoy the night there! Love the noise and crowd at Pizza Parlor, too. It just takes a while for them to get our order at times.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('duis68199',992,'2016-04-27',5,'I usually dislike Asian fusion because it tends to feel like a misrepresentation or misuse of Asian flavors, but Sunda? Hands down, one of my favorite restaurants in Chicago.My friends and I come here for birthdays regularly, and the service has never been short of stellar. From the hosts to the servers to the runners, weve never had a problem. Everyone has always felt friendly and lively, even when we phone in for a reservation!My favorites are the Brussels sprout salad and the Sweet potato caterpillar roll. I was impressed by the vegetarian options and how much variety there was, but also, how delicious they could be! Other classic favorites that my table enjoys regularly are any of their noodle options. The restaurant is rather large, and offers private dining rooms, too. I would definitely want to book a bigger party here when given the chance, as their food and service make me feel satisfied each and every time.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',1319,'2019-11-16',4,'When I go out, I like to get an entree for each person at the table and an appetizer for every two people. My friend and I came to Cira together and each got an entree and shared a spread. Honestly, compared to other Mediterranean restaurants in the city, we were a bit more satisfied than what I was used to, but it still felt lacking. The spread was the star of our table. The flavors were delicious, but the plating was what took it to another level. I appreciate all the colors and fresh vegetables/flowers used to garnish, and they tasted wonderfully with the pita. There just wasnt enough pita and spread! :)We got a pasta and a fish entree to share. They each felt lacking on their own, but were better together. It just felt like neither could be filling on their own as they were each lacking a certain amount of complementary flavor that was fulfilled by the other. I enjoy that nothing was seasoned too strongly but the flavors still shown through.Overall, I would come again, but maybe not on a hungry stomach. I had seen other present parties enjoy more dishes slowly one by one, so that just might be the way to go.',11);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('lacus3581',145,'2020-09-03',5,'I had always wanted to stop by here for the longest time, but the line has always been out the door so I never bothered. When my friend wanted to give it a go one day for lunch out of the office, I decided to tag along.The ambiance inside is very quaint and open. I enjoyed how cute and classic diner the decor was, but I did not feel like there was no breathing room between customers or seated guests. It felt like the space was open and airy. The line to order was a bit confusing, as some guests were standing around waiting for orders so it may have been difficult to figure out where we were supposed to go. At certain points, we couldnt tell if we were in line or if we were just standing around, too. I wish there would have been more organized means of keeping people in where they needed to be rather than all hovering near the front. I ordered the summer bowl. It was pretty fresh and I appreciated the whole pieces of fruit, but I wish there was more variety in the bowl. At one point, I felt like I was just eating straight mouthfuls of acai with no difference between them because it was nothing but acai and fruits. Overall, I might come back but may stay away from an acai bowl. My friend got a salad and it looked pretty filling!',24);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cc110',202,'2016-05-03',5,'Came here with a party of 6 for a birthday, and because everyone was absolutely starving, we decided it would be a better deal for us to go for the cheapest AYCE option (~$40). Given everyones appetite...it was definitely the better option. Im someone who usually does not eat much meat, so I tend to not eat as much at these kinds of AYCE meat places. Therefore, I was a bit turned off knowing that I would be paying the same as everyone else for AYCE meat. However, I was pleased to see that the AYCE option had abundant veggie and appetizer options for a bbq house. Its not going to be the most variety youll see in a veggie buffet, but youll be able to still get decently full without having a mouthful of veggie. Our table really liked the potstickers, but I wish there were other carb options than just rice. My personal favorite was the cucumber salad or the seaweed salad. The service was a bit lacking. I understand they were understaffed, but we had gone on a Monday evening and our server didnt smile with us at all and seemed annoyed with us on the get-go. Im a server myself and didnt think we were doing anything wrong to make him cross, and it felt like he was rolling his eyes whenever we ordered another round.',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('brk11',1514,'2021-12-13',4,'I had come by on a weekend brunch with a friend on reservation. I had seen the photos of this exquisite place in Logan Square, and I wanted to give it a try!I was instantly interested by the indoor design when I walked in. I dont think Ive been to another restaurant that has been so ornate and made me feel like I was transported to another decade. It was like you could have forgotten you were in Logan Square. They also had some of the most beautiful tables and comfortable chairs Ive sat in at a restaurant. Couldnt wait to bring friends here just for the ambiance!Music was rather loud and it was a bit difficult to hear my friend, but we moved so that we were sitting next to each other instead of across. I ordered the Shrimp & Grits, which is my classic brunch choice already. We were a bit confused because the server who introduced herself to us as our server wasnt the one who took our order, but as long as we got to order, that was what mattered.When my food came, I was please by how much grits I had. I really enjoy a hearty portion, and it did not look like it would disappoint. But what REALLY pleased me was how many shrimps there were! They werent the largest shrimps Ive had, but they were each seasoned and cooked so perfectly, and could easily be eaten in a delectable bite. I was so pleased that I could keep on digging in the grits and there would be more shrimp. Ive never had this many in my shrimp & grits!! Blown away.Id literally come back just for the shrimp & grits.',27);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('consequat2734',1193,'2017-12-29',5,'Easy and convenient Korean food, served street style. What isnt there to love? We came when it was close to closing time, and felt sheepish for eating within an hour of when the employees might be trying to get customers out. However, the service was friendly and efficient, and I didnt feel rushed to get my order in. I came with a small party of 4, and we each ordered something different. Unlike a Taco Bell, everything tasted different from each other and had distinctive fusions of Korean flavor. I got the Bulgogi Banh Mi. I was pleased with the tall mountain of fresh vegetables and picked vegetables on my sandwich, but the bulgogi felt a bit tough. I was expecting the meat to be a bit more juicy and filled with sauce, but it was on the dryer end (probably because it was closer to the end of the day). I wish they had added some sauce of some sort because it was all rather dry in my mouth, but everyone elses orders had no problem.',1);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yycc11',1369,'2021-08-22',5,'Some of the best (and only!) Taiwanese restaurants here in the Inland Empire. I felt that the bento meal I had gotten was more than filling -- alongside of a bowl of white rice with minced meat, there was a beautiful mountain of fried popcorn chicken to accompany. The classic Taiwanese side dishes of pickled vegetables were present and tasted fresh. I was pleased to see such a satisfying meal for ~$10. When we entered the restaurant, it was relatively empty. I believe there was only one other party that was present. As a result, our food came pretty quickly. Its such a pity because I would have hoped that there would be more business to this restaurant. While the cleanliness of the place could have been improved, its still a place that I would come frequently when I need my Taiwanese food.',4);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('justo788',368,'2021-04-06',4,'So simple, yet so delicious. Thats what I love about Korean bingsu. Top it off with juicy, fresh mangos, and you have the only dessert you need for a hot LA summer. Unlike other types of Asian shaved ice, bingsu uses milk/cream-based "snow" that is flaky in layers, much like layers of snow would be if it just came out of the clouds. The snow is not course at all and instead feels fluffy, melting when it comes into contact with anything. It feels delicate and dainty, not heavy at all. We got the mango bingsu, which tasted fresh and made to order. Unlike American shaved ice, there was no use of syrups but just cream and mango juice, simple ingredients that are a match made in heaven. The combination isnt complicated, but because its used with the best ingredients, its so hard to resist.We love that our bingsu came with a mountain of mango chunks. Even until the last bite, there was enough mango to go with every spoonful. We felt refreshed by the end and didnt feel heavy! Definitely take a visit here and enjoy your time. :)',3);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('massa9626',849,'2018-12-04',5,'When I go out with friends, we usually each order an entree and share between ourselves. When we ordered two entrees from this place, it felt enough to feed a small family. The location and ambiance of this place was completely unexpected. You walk through unsuspecting doors in a stone alley to feel like youve been transported back in time, where the furnishing, decor, and walls are all making you feel like youre in a classic, old-American tavern. We ordered the pot pie and the roasted chicken, to our servers recommendation. The pot pie itself was delicious, brimming is sweet broth and juices and stuffed with tender chicken meat and vegetables. The bone marrow it came with was the cherry on the top. The real star of our table was the coal-roasted chicken. They werent kidding when they told us it would be a lot of chicken. This is a plate definitely meant for sharing, and each bite was as delicious as the last. The skin and outside was roasted to a beautiful char without being burnt, and the flavors were throughout the meat all the way to the bone. Trivoli Tavern feels like such a hidden gem. You would have never guessed that such a restaurant could exist at the end of the alleyway, but we are so glad we discovered it!!',0);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et8078',363,'2017-05-09',5,'Legend has it that Im still trying to finish this...Talk about GENEROUS! Everything in SoCal (especially in this area) tends to be extremely overpriced, so this is such a hidden gem. I had trouble finishing this myself, and Im usually someone who has an endless stomach. They were absolutely loading my fries with, chicken, and everything delicious. The checking was fried to a perfection, feeling neither too greasy nor too dry. It was friend chicken exactly as I would dream of it to be, and then top it off with heaps of sauce and cheese? You cant get any better.But they did. With fries. A bed of fries on the bottom. Youve got me passing out. This isnt something you should be eating if youve got on a pair of pants with only a zipper and no elastic. Youll walk out of there feeling stuffed to your brim with enough leftovers to feel the same ecstasy all over again the next day. This place shouldnt be called Hangrys -- you literally cannot leave this place feeling anything but stuffed, content, and ready for the best food coma ever.',5);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('cursus11108',909,'2020-05-02',4,'This was the first time I had Tiger Sugar in America -- Im a bit more used to having it in Taiwan. When we arrived to the location, we noticed that it was rather small inside. In the midst of the pandemic, it felt like you could only comfortably fit one party inside at a time. Therefore, most people were waiting outside for their orders. I chose to get fresh milk without tea for my beverage, and I kind of regret it. It was much too sweet without the tea, but it was still the classic Tiger Sugar aesthetic that has gone viral recently. The boba was warm and you could tell they had just pulled it out from cooking, which I did appreciate knowing. However, like a few other reviews wrote, the boba was a bit more firm than I would have expected. It felt like it wasnt cooked long enough but it was a bit inconsistent, too. Overall, I think its a good place to try if youve never had Tiger Sugar before. Otherwise I would have recommended going to a different boba place -- the name carries the hype at this location more than the taste and price.',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('elit9486',1534,'2019-06-28',5,'This was the first time I finally tried the viral mochi donuts, and you cant ever go back to normal donuts afterwards.Mochinut was everything I loved about Asian desserts. The frosting flavors (ube, mango, and green tea) were not too strong but not too subtle either, and were sweet enough that we could enjoy them without feeling like we were getting cavities (as I normally do with donuts). I loved that we were able to watch the employees dip each donut by hand into the frosting as we were waiting for our order!The dough is something else. I love how chewy it was, and you could definitely tell the mochi flour adds an extra bounce. I like the shape of the donut that made it easy to pull apart and enjoy bite by bite without getting the hands too messy. It took less than a few minutes for our order to be ready since we ordered it, and so we were in and out in no time. Everything still tasted fresh, so it was obvious that the donuts hadnt just been sitting in cases for the whole day. We really appreciated how fast the service was for such an amazing treat here in SoCal!',9);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dui8069',577,'2020-02-13',5,'If youre ever in West Loop and looking for dessert, then youve found the place. I stumbled upon Sugargoat looking for a quick treat to grab for some coworkers before heading to work, and knowing that ice cream wasnt the best idea, baked goods seemed like the solution.Since then, I come to Sugargoat regularly if I ever need to pick up treats! The shop is cozy and small, exactly from a childs storybook of what a color bakery could look like. It felt like you were walking into a fun, vibrant world contained within a small space, but there was so much to see with the eyes.In front, there were racks of baked goods. While the rainbow cupcakes were absolutely the spotlight, everything else couldnt be ignored. The cakes, cookies, coffee, and beautifully frosted desserts were so difficult to choose from. On the right, an ice cream freezer was stocked full of goodies, too. It felt like I could have stared at every flavor there was and not been tired!I ended up getting a Cheez-it cupcake for my coworker, which sounded like the classic Goat spin of whacky and whimsical into delicious bites. I was helped by very helpful and cheerful employees who were patient in explaining each item to me, and what the flavors were. By the time I left, there was a small line growing outside. Hard to stay away from this place!Definitely make sure to grab a quick treat here if you have the chance. For the size and flavors of the cupcakes, there isnt a $5 better spent anywhere else in the city.',29);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('leo58100',1273,'2016-12-27',4,'As much as I love Acai bowls, they tend to feel like overpriced smoothie bowls that I can just make at home for a fraction of the cost (and at the cost of presentation). When I came to the Haven City Market with a friend, we decided to split a bowl. Why not?I was in shock when they were stacking the Acai bowl. The poor little bowl couldnt fit everything that the employee was stacking! There was just mountains on mountains of delicious, healthy nutrients in our bowl, it would be impossible to say it wasnt worth the price. I would definitely recommend getting the DIY option. There was not as much variety as other places might have, but this was decent for its location in a food court. Our employee did not shy away from placing absolute mountains of each topping on our bowl. When we walked away, we had to keep on licking the sides because it was overflowing!Everything felt very fresh, and we enjoyed how the flavors were distinct from each other. Definitely my go-to acai place if Im in the area again!',25);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et4994',122,'2016-08-19',5,'I visited Little Goat Diner for the first time with a friend so that we could enjoy something more casual from an acclaimed chef. When we went on a weekday brunchtime, there were still available tables and nothing felt rushed. The server was pleasant with us, and we got ourselves a nice booth next to the window. Unlike other Goat restaurants, this one felt much more "casual". Of course, its a diner! I enjoy that they served classic diner favorites with the Izard spin to them, making it a comfortable familiarity to many of us. Los Drowned -- I normally wouldnt get a sandwich at a diner, but I decided to go for this by the recommendation of the server. The sandwich was massive and I have no idea how anyone could fit it in their mouth, so I took it apart and ate it piece by piece (as assembled as I could manage). Every flavor was delicious, but I felt that it lacked the signature combinations of wacky and wonderful Ive come to love about Goat. This Little Piggy Went to China -- Ive always appreciated how Goat restaurants try to work in unique ingredients that bring strong kicks of flavor, and this did not disappoint. On the menu, the list of ingredients would raise some eyebrows, but I was pleasantly surprised with how well everything went together. It felt a bit on the heavier side as well, but thats diner food for you, right?At the end of our meal, we went to the photo booth near the doorway. We received two photo strips from our few minutes inside and loved that the Little Goat Diner logo was there at the bottom of each. :)',12);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus16134',658,'2019-04-02',5,'I felt conflicted about the $55 tasting menu. I know that at other tapas places in Chicago I could have walked away feeling more stuffed on the same price, but I know the pricing behind tasting menus is that they bring you their best dishes that when combined, comes to a price slightly higher than the packaged deal. That only made me wonder if the plates were just smaller and thats why I didnt feel so satisfied. Everything tasted amazing. It was the first time I had done a tapas tasting menu and I appreciated the variety that we had, including the dessert. For $55, we were able to get a healthy mix of proteins and mains, as well as appetizers. It was a bit disappointing that the largest, most filling plate was the potatoes. They were delicious, but noticeably a larger portion than everything else. Most everything else was finished within 2-3 bites, leaving much to be wanted. Our server was helpful to explain everything that we were eating. We were surprised at how quickly the food came out, one after the other. We didnt feel rushed and felt like we were able to enjoy everything that we were given but maybe would have preferred a bit more breathing room between each of them. Our server felt a bit awkward at times when there were silences as he hung over my friend and I before realizing we were doing okay and did not currently need help.Otherwise, we were seated at a lovely table next to a window overlooking Michigan Avenue. The location is in a nice hotel and is elevated on the second floor, meaning that we were able to enjoy some people watching. Overall, I would bring a friend here again if they were visiting Chicago but might choose a different tapas restaurant if I were going out with locals.',8);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('curae84116',102,'2017-11-27',5,'Everytime Ive gone to this place, Ive never needed to wait for a table. Its the exact same menu at the Chinatown and Streeterville locations, but this one always gets me seated immediately. Such a hidden gem down in South Loop!! It deserves so much more attention compared to its Chinatown branch -- its literally 1 CTA stop away, too. Dim sum in Chicago has never been cheap, but Ive found MingHin to be the most reasonable. Its great that I can get dim sum during any time of the day, even late in to the evening. The flavors are authentic, and theres an amazing selection of sweet, savory, traditional classics, and new favorites.You order on tablets that the restaurant gives, which in my opinion, is super smart for customers. You can take all the time you need to decide with your party what you want to eat without feeling like a server is hovering over you, annoyed that you and your party havent been able to decide if youd have enough stomach space for one more dish. Its also super convenient that they have pricing "tiers" so that depending on the "tier/size" of your dimsum plate, its a fixed price. Makes it so much easier to plan what to eat on whatever budget!Aside from the dim sum, the rest of the food here is authentic as well. I was pleasantly surprised, expecting that this location would not be as authentic because of where it is. Im glad to see that the same quality and tastes from Chinatown could be found in South Loop!Make sure to leave stomach for dessert. The complimentary almond cookies and fortune cookie goes well when washed down with hot tea.',18);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus16134',184,'2017-12-12',4,'I used to love IHOPs unlimited pancakes deal, but Wildberrys takes pancakes to the next level. Im always so stuffed that Im bewildered how I used to go to IHOPs. Theres no reservations and the line can be seen snaking around the corner on weekends. I like to go on weekdays instead to keep my fingers crossed that I can get in within 30 minutes. Its a fairly large restaurant, but its always packed! The location is prime in Chicago, so even if you have to wait a while, you can take a nice stroll at the park next door. I like to always order the egg menu items that come with a side of pancakes, and then upgrade the pancakes to specialty pancakes. Trust me, this is more than enough food for one individual already and the value is out-of-this-world, but my hungry mouth always waters when I read what they offer so I can never order without the pancakes side. Theres usually more than enough food to bring home and heat up another day. As most restaurant are though, the pancakes dont heat up so well at home, so I would try to finish it at the restaurant. Service was a bit slow, and it felt like our server was trying to get rid of us as soon as possible. I get that it was a busy day but there wasnt even much of a smile from our server.',21);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('et65112',1208,'2021-10-15',5,'For $25, you can have all the rice cakes, cheese, spicy sauce, fishcakes, and food coma you could want...for three meals. Everytime I come to eat here, there are leftovers galore. And Im not someone who has a small stomach. There are serious tupperware leftovers that are still gloriously delicious each and every reheating. Fair warning to everyone, they take the spice levels seriously. Im not someone who hates spice, but even the mild is the maximum I can do. Between how fresh and piping hot your MASSIVE bowl is, the spice feels so elevated. Please listen to the reviews. My friend and I usually like to come here about 15 minutes before they open so we can get a table without waiting. Theres usually already a small group forming near the door at lunchtime, so it seemed that many others had the same ideas. Ive never needed to wait past an hour for a table, but when your stomach is hungry, carbs cant come any faster. The rice cakes tend to be a bit sweeter than Ive found other places to be, and while I usually do enjoy a bit of sugar in my meal, its a bit more than I like. It doesnt ruin the flavors but might be something youll notice. If youre in the area and are looking for something to completely, and I mean COMPLETELY, fill you up to the brim until you cant walk anymore, then youve found your rice cake heaven.',14);
INSERT INTO restaurants_comments (user_id, restaurant_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('ac67183',638,'2016-07-02',5,'Sodam is located in a very unassuming location right behind a busy gas station. If you arent looking for it, you could very easily miss it. However, this is a hidden gem that you cannot miss out!My friends and I always come here, since I was in high school, for a very delicious and very filling kimbap roll. We usually can split one roll between two people, and its all for ~$6. Our favorites are the beef and fishcake rolls! The pickled daikon is always so flavorful but not too sour as you might find in store-bought varieties.Other favorites Ive had from this restaurant are the multicolored Korean rice desserts that they have on the center island of the store. One single pack can nearly feed a whole familys dessert cravings for an evening, and my family already has difficulty eating the whole pack. When you buy them, make sure you have a crowd hungry! These go bad within a day or two of being left in the fridge but is so great fresh.The fridges are stocked with Korean side dishes that my family likes to buy to accompany a dinner at home. Kimchi can be bought in small jars, or in massive bags. You can really tell that everything is homemade because of its packaging, and you wont ever need to worry about how fresh it all is. This small, hole-in-the-wall grocery store and restaurant has become a go-to everytime I need a quick, easy, filling, and delicious meal.',3);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('vitae1580',4329,'2019-02-20',5,'If you are needing to go to Chicago and find adequate lodging at an affordable rate this is the apartment for you. Everything was as stated in the description and pictures. The host is very responsive. This neighborhood is ok if you are just here to sleep and go about your day. Overall a really great experience at a great price. The unit is warm and accommodating. I would definitely rent this spot again.',2);
