INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('faucibus366',2795,'2017-03-01',5,'You get what you pay for in this case. The apartment wasn t terrible by any means. However, it was missing some key essentials hair dryer, oven mitt, toaster. The trash can was extremely tiny. Beds are smaller then expected, single and double sized rather then double and Queen. One couch is long enough for an adult to sleep on the other is not. Amenities were falling apart during our stay. Both tables were broken, screws were loose in the light bulb. The space was live-ably clean, however it would not meet expectations of someone whom is a Germaphob. The place desperately needed to be dusted and there were spiderwebs in corners, and crumbs in the microwave.  There is also no washer and dryer in the apartment. A laundry service is offered, however you have to hang a small bag of clothes on the front door. They cannot gaurentee nothing will be lost or stolen either. The area is not safe, we did not have any personal issues. However we were warned by every uber driver that there were at least two shootings a week, and we were in a very bad area. There were sirens throughout every night. There was also a lady who would sit in her car on the street blasting music in the middle of the night, while she smoked something and screamed to herself.',1);
