INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('orci41111',15,'2021-09-20',5,'I stayed at Luiz s place October 19-21. The apartment is conveniently located to Penn Station, Bolt Bus drop off, and Port Authority. There are two rooms in the apartment so you will take one of them. During my trip, there was another person in the other room. The shower and sink portion of the bathroom is located in the apartment. It is very small. Thus, as someone who is over 6 feet tall and that has a decent wingspan, it was very cramped. So I just want to head warning to anyone that is tall that is thinking about booking Luiz s place. Another unique thing about the apartment is unlocking the front door. I found it to be particularly difficult as I struggled to unlock every time I came back from being out. Anyway, this is a nice place for a solo traveler that allows the ease of coming and going as you please.',4);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede82145',1418,'2021-10-22',5,'Luiz is a wonderful host. Very responsive, very friendly.  My only issue is that the setup of the bedroom can prove stressful to other solo female travelers like me. You are locked into   an apartment with a - in my case - male visitor in the other room with whom you will be sharing the kitchen and shower. I would have fared better had I met the guy, but I never did. It made me very nervous.',8);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('commodo87170',1551,'2017-07-22',5,'Luiz s place is perfectly located - near Penn station, near the Theater district, near the subway stops, lots of food choices around.  His description of the location was spot on and even better than originally shown in the photos.  No more loft bed.  Very comfortable bed and just the right amenities for my Theater getaway.',7);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('magna4984',323,'2018-12-24',5,'Luiz s place is exactly as described. Very close to Times Square. Safe gated community. Although the washroom is outside, it s only used by Luiz s other airbnb guest, so not a problem at all. The place is very quiet despite the busy location. He recently renovated it, so that s a plus.',2);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('nec37198',4390,'2017-02-08',4,'It is indeed a top location! Even better than I expected! Luiz is a great host, easy to communicate with and super friendly. He made sure that I had everything I need. The place is compact, comfortable and really cosy. I would totally recommend this!',8);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sit9598',2029,'2021-01-08',5,'Luiz is a really good guy and he makes a hell of a cup of coffee if you re fortunate enough to have him there while you are. This place is quite small, a bit smaller than the photos show, but it is certainly what affordable NYC looks like. Especially the toilet room (outside the apartment) is no larger than an airplane lavatory, and it is very tricky to stand square at the sink in the shower room without one foot in the shower. Most everything was very clean, but I did find a bug on the wall one night. I had the privilege of sleeping in both rooms of the apartment. The room with the loft is larger, but be wary of the loft temperature - it was a hot summer week when I was there and the loft area was around 20 degrees warmer than the floor with AC on full, which for me was extremely uncomfortable, especially because memory foam absorbs heat. I had to convert the couch into a bed and sleep on that the first night. The loft is also pretty unforgiving - rough wood and visible screws at the corners - so make sure you can always see where you re going. The other room had a larger bed, but as a 6 1   man, I couldn t lay all the way flat even diagonally without my feet up against the wall. Both mattresses are very comfortable and the sheets were very clean. Luiz s friend Tony was a gem when helping with check-in. Overall, this is a pretty darn good way for a young solo traveler to learn what living in Midtown would really look like for them, and I m glad to have had the experience, especially because it was less than half the expense of nearby hotels.',5);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('sed91175',4179,'2017-05-19',5,'Ideal for a solo traveler if you re in the city for a few days. Luiz was very easy to communicate with, responsive and a super easy check-in and check-out. The apartment is located in Hell s Kitchen, a few blocks from Times Sq and close to bars and restaurants.',0);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('suscipit47120',2932,'2019-03-01',4,'Great location! Exactly what I was looking for',6);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('yccc14',3143,'2016-03-12',5,'Really enjoyed my stay here! The location was perfect. It was only a 10-15 minute walk away from all the places I wanted to go. There are plenty of food options and things to do nearby. The apartment is small, but cozy and surprisingly quiet. I felt very safe there. Luiz and Tony were very responsive when I contacted them beforehand. They were even nice enough to let me check in early on the day of my arrival. I would definitely stay here again.',4);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('pede23147',2805,'2018-07-05',5,'This place is an awesome value in a great location, but make sure to read the description! The layout is a little odd, with the toilet not in the actual apartment, and the room with the shower and sink is really small. I had some issues with the wifi being a little in-and-out - not sure if this is typical. The window unit A/C was greatly appreciated, and the lofted bed results in a really nice sitting area. Luiz is great and really flexible with check-in and check-out. Everything was nice and clean. If you re looking for an inexpensive place to stay really close to Times Square, this is a wonderful option.',4);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('www112',3992,'2019-06-22',4,'Great location in heart of the kitchen',2);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('dis16196',4270,'2018-01-02',5,'I can t believe the morons who have made negative posts. Luiz has been very clear in his description of what the apartment is like.  READ CAREFULLY. I needed a shower, a bed, Wi-Fi and a room to safely spread out my stuff.  That s what he described and that is EXACTLY what I found when I got there.  If you assumed certain services would be available, but failed to verify ahead of time, that is YOUR failure, not the hosts. Luiz exemplifies the best qualities in a host and I highly recommend contacting him if you are going to visit Times Square and Hell s Kitchen.',3);
INSERT INTO accommodations_comments (user_id, accommodation_id, comment_date, rating, comment, comment_likes) VALUES ('aliquam8037',4569,'2018-08-30',5,'Luiz s place is fantastic! Great location, terrific hospitality and most important for me, a really comfortable, quiet place in the middle of everything in NYC.  I m a fussy sleeper and was really impressed with how comfortable the bedding in the sleep loft is.  I ll definitely stay here again!',3);
